    '{"id":"01KC4WAEM4ZKWGT7D0Q1FYZAM8","title":"Powerhouse Gym & Ideometry: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Generation and Marketing Communications**\n\nThe team decided to make the marketing communication opt-in checkbox mandatory to ensure leads can be reached effectively.\n\n- **Marketing communication consent will be mandatory** on waiver forms to maximize outreach potential to prospects (07:18)  \n    - Nina Belina confirmed this is legal if unsubscribe options are clear and accessible.  \n    - Milan Wagner emphasized that leads who don''t opt in cannot be marketed to, which defeats the volume-driven business model.  \n    - HubSpot automatically tracks unsubscribes and opt-outs, helping monitor communication health.  \n    - Colin Costigan advised monitoring unsubscribe rates to avoid HubSpot flagging the domain for spam.  \n\n- **Milan Wagner will create segmented lists** to track unsubscribes and opt-outs for ongoing monitoring (10:38)  \n    - This will complement HubSpot’s automatic tracking to keep unsubscribe rates manageable.  \n    - The team agreed to watch the \"email health\" metric in HubSpot, which uses green, yellow, and red zones to signal risk levels.  \n    - Current unsubscribe rate from a recent 6,500-email blast was **0.99%**, considered acceptable (13:18).  \n    - Milan and Colin will ensure that unsubscribed contacts are excluded from future campaigns.  \n\n- **Email marketing contacts are managed manually by toggling status monthly** to free up marketing contact slots for new leads (18:00)  \n    - Milan explained that former members are removed from marketing contacts at month-end to prioritize active prospects.  \n    - This manual process aligns marketing capacity with campaign timing and monthly promotions.  \n\n## **Integrations, Syncing, and System Costs**\n\nThe team reviewed current integration usage and explored opportunities to reduce monthly operational costs.\n\n- **Current Make integration operations are underused compared to plan, allowing cost reduction** (20:40)  \n    - The plan allows **500,000 operations per month**, but only about **55,000 operations** are used with 22 days left in the cycle.  \n    - Colin Costigan expects they can reduce to a **150,000 operation plan costing $116/month** after developers verify usage.  \n    - Yefei Jin requested tracking usage for October and November to set a cost-effective limit with a buffer.  \n    - Colin will provide a recommendation for a lower tier plan based on verified data.  \n\n- **The team has a rollover balance of 42 consulting hours monthly with Colin’s firm** (22:28)  \n    - These hours can be prioritized for website development, HubSpot integrations, or marketing automation.  \n    - Yefei Jin emphasized focusing on HubSpot automation first, as internal developers are handling Framer website work.  \n    - Colin confirmed asynchronous communication works well to accelerate project completion within available hours.  \n\n## **Website Strategy and Analytics**\n\nThe group agreed to rebuild the website with emphasis on HubSpot integration and SEO improvements, while preserving positive user engagement elements.\n\n- **A new website will be developed using Framer with Shopify integration and HubSpot connectivity** (22:49)  \n    - Colin Costigan’s team can handle design, development, and integration without requiring weekly meetings.  \n    - Milan and Yefei emphasized using existing templates to reduce build time and then customizing for smooth animations and functionality.  \n    - Nina Belina highlighted the need for SEO audits and content creation focused on keywords, meta descriptions, and blog posts to drive organic traffic.  \n\n- **Current website analytics show strong engagement but low lead conversion** (48:07)  \n    - Yefei Jin noted visitors spend over a minute and a half on the site, which is unusually high and positive.  \n    - Colin and Nina suggested this might reflect current members seeking info, affecting engagement metrics.  \n    - They recommended a holistic rebuild to cater to both prospects and members, maintaining positive site elements while improving conversion.  \n    - SEO and user experience improvements will target increasing organic traffic and capturing more lead info faster.  \n\n## **Marketing Automation and SMS Implementation**\n\nThe team committed to implementing automated SMS workflows with strict opt-out tracking to improve lead follow-up and compliance.\n\n- **A $600/month SMS automation service will be activated immediately** to trigger messages based on user actions like form fills or club visits (25:32)  \n    - Milan Wagner will lead project management with Colin Costigan and Nina Belina to implement SMS workflows in HubSpot.  \n    - Automation will include triggers for visits, sign-ups, and non-joining prospects to increase engagement.  \n    - The team stressed the importance of logging opt-outs manually in HubSpot when users text “stop” through Air Call, since full sync is limited (27:38).  \n    - Colin proposed adding a checkbox in HubSpot to mark contacts as opted out of texts to prevent further messaging.  \n\n- **Legal risk from improper SMS opt-outs is recognized, driving compliance focus** (28:22)  \n    - Yefei Jin recalled prior legal issues and requested strict controls to avoid lawsuits.  \n    - The team agreed to prioritize these automations and dedicate consulting hours to finish setup before the busy January-February period.  \n\n## **Paid Advertising and Lead Generation Goals**\n\nThe team plans to conduct a paid ads audit and increase ad spend to triple daily lead volume, aiming for aggressive membership growth.\n\n- **A paid ads audit will be conducted next week to optimize campaigns and reduce cost per lead** (36:30)  \n    - Colin Costigan’s team will review Meta campaigns, comparing 2024 data to prior years.  \n    - Milan Wagner expressed a need to understand ad changes’ impact and improve efficiency, since current lead generation is inconsistent.  \n    - Yefei Jin set a target to increase leads from about **12 per day to 30+ per day** through higher budgets and different ad types.  \n    - They noted past Google Ads efforts were too expensive (up to $70 per lead), and currently no LinkedIn ads are running.  \n\n- **Membership growth targets require aggressive lead volume and quality improvements** (43:36)  \n    - Milan shared goals of **4,000 members per club**, requiring approximately **800–1,400 net new members** in key markets annually.  \n    - Yefei explained the churn of roughly **150 members leaving per month** in Miami means gross sign-ups must exceed churn by about 3,500 annually.  \n    - Colin stressed the importance of balancing lead quantity with lead quality to maximize conversion rates.  \n    - The team recognized social media leads convert at about 10–15%, so volume increases are crucial to growth.  \n\n- **Website lead generation is underperforming, prompting plans for SEO and conversion improvements** (47:26)  \n    - Milan noted that other gyms generate many leads from websites, but their current site delivers low numbers.  \n    - Colin and Nina pointed out that current Facebook lead gen forms bypass the website, and the site lacks content for organic Google traffic.  \n    - SEO improvements including blogs and technical audits will support better organic search visibility alongside paid efforts.  \n\n## **Process and Reporting Improvements**\n\nThe team refined lead source tracking, list management, and reporting workflows to improve data accuracy and operational efficiency.\n\n- **Manual enrollment is required for leads missed by automated syncs due to timing gaps** (16:00)  \n    - Nina explained that late form submissions can miss sync windows, causing outdated lead source data.  \n    - Milan clarified this requires refreshing workflows and manually enrolling contacts to update segments properly.  \n    - Screenshots and guides were provided to Milan for managing manual enrollments and hot list segments.  \n\n- **Milan is managing lists independently and will seek help as needed for reports** (14:22)  \n    - He confirmed list creation is working well, while report building depends on available dashboard slots.  \n    - Nina sent tutorials and screenshots supporting manual enrollment and dashboard updates.  \n\n- **Collin and Milan agreed to monitor HubSpot sync and email list health continuously** (10:13)  \n    - This ensures communication metrics stay within acceptable limits and protects domain reputation.  \n    - Milan will track unsubscribe trends and coordinate with Colin if issues arise.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","SMS automation","Paid Ads Audit","Lead Generation","Website Redevelopment","Marketing Communication Opt-Out"],"overview":"- **Mandatory Marketing Consent:** Opt-in checkbox on waiver forms is required to improve lead outreach and ensure legal compliance.  \n- **Email Unsubscribe Monitoring:** Milan will create segmented lists to track unsubscribes; current rate is 0.99%, acceptable for campaigns.  \n- **Integration Cost Reduction:** Underused integration plan allows for a switch to a lower tier, reducing costs significantly to $116/month.  \n- **Website Rebuild Focus:** New site will enhance HubSpot integration and SEO while maintaining user engagement to boost lead conversion.  \n- **SMS Automation Implementation:** $600/month service for automated SMS workflows to enhance follow-ups, compliance is critical to avoid legal issues.  \n- **Aggressive Lead Generation Target:** Aim to increase daily leads from 12 to 30+, focusing on both volume and quality for membership growth.","action_items":"\n**Milan Wagner**\nMake marketing communications checkbox mandatory in waiver forms and monitor opt-outs/unsubscribes using segmented lists in HubSpot (06:00)\nReach out to HubSpot rep to set up SMS automation contract and manage its onboarding process (30:40)\nLead project management of SMS automation collaboration with Colin and Nina to ensure timely setup before January peak (28:30)\nManage manual enrollments in HubSpot workflows to correct lead source data and lists (15:00)\nShare 2026 aggressive membership goals with Colin to inform paid ads audit and campaign strategy (43:31)\nCoordinate with Colin and Nina on HubSpot lists and workflows to optimize lead management and marketing contact limits (14:22)\n\n**Yefei Jin**\nProvide Facebook Business Manager business ID for paid ads audit access and confirm admin approval (38:39)\nOversee approval of the SMS automation budget (~$600/month) and prioritize initial contract signing (25:32)\nFacilitate prioritization of hourly support resources toward HubSpot SMS automation rather than website build (22:45)\nCoordinate and approve paid ads audit scope and support audit development (36:30)\nMonitor audit output next week and decide further marketing initiatives based on results (42:10)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nVerify Make (Integromat) operations usage with developers for potential subscription cost reduction (20:10)\nAssist with HubSpot SMS automation setup, including workflow triggers and content, and create opted-out checkbox for text messaging compliance (26:00)\nLead paid ads audit for Meta platforms, deliver recommendations following December (36:30)\nSupport integration and access approvals for Facebook Business Manager (38:39)\nConsult on website rebuild including HubSpot integration requirements and overall marketing strategy (47:30)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nProvide tutorials and screenshot guides for workflows, lead gen forms, and manual enrollment in HubSpot (14:54)\nAdvise on email health metrics and HubSpot compliance monitoring (11:58)\nCollaborate on the auditing and strategy implementation for SEO and website conversion improvement (48:00)\nSupport SMS automation setup and opt-out process alongside Colin and Milan (26:00)\n"},"duration":54.15999984741211,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Milan Wagner"},{"id":1,"name":"Yefei Jin"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Nina Belina"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Reports?","index":0,"end_time":92.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.35,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"No, but you got the same size Mac as me.","index":1,"end_time":99.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.71,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I think I''m gonna get a bigger one.","index":2,"end_time":101.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.83,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"We want that space over there.","index":3,"end_time":105.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.88,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yes.","index":4,"end_time":106.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.28,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Oh, really?","index":5,"end_time":107.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.16,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":108.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.8,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Oh, all right.","index":7,"end_time":109.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":108.24,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Let''s try to make it happen.","index":8,"end_time":110.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.44,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"That''s really kind of.","index":9,"end_time":111.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.36,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Oh, thank God.","index":10,"end_time":113.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.2,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Positive thinking.","index":11,"end_time":118.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":117.56,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Positive thinking.","index":12,"end_time":120.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.92,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Stuff on anybody.","index":13,"end_time":128.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.82,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"It sucks because I''m, like, really heavy.","index":14,"end_time":131.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.9,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"On my feet, too.","index":15,"end_time":132.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":131.58,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So you can, like, really hear me, like, coming.","index":16,"end_time":134.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.46,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Nail.","index":17,"end_time":137.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.7,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, right.","index":18,"end_time":139.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.3,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"They''re not.","index":19,"end_time":140.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.82,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"They''re not on this meeting right now.","index":20,"end_time":141.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.42,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Ideometry.","index":21,"end_time":143.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.46,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":22,"end_time":144.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.5,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I''m going to talk to them a little bit about our goals for next year and.","index":23,"end_time":149.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.9,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And kind of the information we need.","index":24,"end_time":151.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.58,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I found out some of those questions that you were asking.","index":25,"end_time":156.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.82,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I built a report, but it looks like zero of this month''s web leads have come in.","index":26,"end_time":162.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":156.86,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Wow.","index":27,"end_time":164.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.58,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"See?","index":28,"end_time":165.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.1,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"But we''ve closed three.","index":29,"end_time":167.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.58,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Well, they''re not from this month, though.","index":30,"end_time":170.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.06,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"But I mean, it''s.","index":31,"end_time":172.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.38,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"It''s one thing that people marketing can drive lead, but they don''t think it is.","index":32,"end_time":177.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.26,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s one.","index":33,"end_time":178.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.58,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"They''re being contacted, though, every single day, right?","index":34,"end_time":183.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.11,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I mean, They''re being contacted.","index":35,"end_time":193.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.23,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"They''re on email drip campaigns.","index":36,"end_time":195.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.63,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I don''t like that.","index":37,"end_time":209.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.62,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"It.","index":38,"end_time":230.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.71,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"He was just on here, wasn''t he?","index":39,"end_time":280.399,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":279.119,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I was just like.","index":40,"end_time":281.919,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":280.399,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"What happened?","index":41,"end_time":282.799,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":281.919,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I don''t want to say.","index":42,"end_time":283.719,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":282.799,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Ah.","index":43,"end_time":283.999,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":283.719,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Terry didn''t.","index":44,"end_time":284.769,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":283.999,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Can you hear us?","index":45,"end_time":291.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":290.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Milan?","index":46,"end_time":291.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.12,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Hello?","index":47,"end_time":299.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.08,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Hello?","index":48,"end_time":299.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":299.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you hear me?","index":49,"end_time":300.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.88,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Hey.","index":50,"end_time":300.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.48,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Yeah, we can hear you.","index":51,"end_time":301.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can hear you.","index":52,"end_time":302.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":301.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Oh, my God.","index":53,"end_time":303.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.44,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Tech issues.","index":54,"end_time":305.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":305.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My.","index":55,"end_time":307.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.68,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m always having tech issues, guys.","index":56,"end_time":311.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.16,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"No.","index":57,"end_time":312.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.5,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"We haven''t noticed.","index":58,"end_time":316.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":315.14,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I like that.","index":59,"end_time":319.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.9,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"How we doing?","index":60,"end_time":321.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.66,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"You guys good?","index":61,"end_time":321.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.3,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, man.","index":62,"end_time":323.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":322.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":63,"end_time":324.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":323.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Trying to stay warm.","index":64,"end_time":325.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":65,"end_time":327.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.34,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Cold up there.","index":66,"end_time":328.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.38,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Where are you?","index":67,"end_time":328.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.3,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Up in Maryland.","index":68,"end_time":330.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":329.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maryland.","index":69,"end_time":331.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.74,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay.","index":70,"end_time":331.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.38,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"We were actually just looking at a club up in Maryland to buy.","index":71,"end_time":335.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.74,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Were you?","index":72,"end_time":337.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.5,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":73,"end_time":338.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.3,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"What was the name?","index":74,"end_time":339.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.5,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Robert.","index":75,"end_time":339.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.3,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"It didn''t have a name.","index":76,"end_time":341.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.22,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"That''s a good one.","index":77,"end_time":342.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Confidential stuff.","index":78,"end_time":344.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.1,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that''s a good one.","index":79,"end_time":345.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":344.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I go there.","index":80,"end_time":346.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.62,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"We can''t disclose that.","index":81,"end_time":347.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.54,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Got a no name, Jim.","index":82,"end_time":352.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":351.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":353.659,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353.1,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay.","index":84,"end_time":356.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.06,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Do you guys have any updates, things like that, that you want to share.","index":85,"end_time":361.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.5,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"For the waiver form to checkbox?","index":86,"end_time":364.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":362.3,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"One checkbox is for other communication.","index":87,"end_time":369.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":365.37,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So anything that''s, you know, in regards to, like, newsletters, you know, additional communication, they would have to sign up for.","index":88,"end_time":376.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":369.29,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But usually that checkbook is not mandatory.","index":89,"end_time":379.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":376.97,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So is it, like, can we have it mandatory?","index":90,"end_time":384.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":380.17,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mean, like, I feel like people usually want to sign up if they don''t have to make, you know, newsletters mandatory.","index":91,"end_time":393.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":386.73,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So.","index":92,"end_time":397.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.26,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay, if we check that.","index":93,"end_time":398.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.38,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"If people don''t check that off, are we still automatically putting them into our Newsletters or the system.","index":94,"end_time":406.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.86,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"There''s a workflow built out so that it doesn''t happen.","index":95,"end_time":409.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.62,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":96,"end_time":413.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":413.34,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It shouldn''t happen because, like, they signed up only to receive, like, normal communication.","index":97,"end_time":419.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":414.54,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So anything in regards to their account to maybe, like, invoices that need to be paid or, you know, anything that''s in regards to what they signed up for at the gym, but anything additional, so, you know, like Christmas specials, stuff like that, like, that''s something that they can choose or not choose.","index":98,"end_time":437.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":419.3,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We.","index":99,"end_time":439.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.68,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"They.","index":100,"end_time":439.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.04,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"We have to have that mandatory because our.","index":101,"end_time":442.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.36,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Our whole business is, like, volume, and we.","index":102,"end_time":444.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.28,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"We have to be able to reach out to them.","index":103,"end_time":446.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.64,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So there.","index":104,"end_time":447.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"There''s zero point of us getting a lead and then not being able to reach out to them.","index":105,"end_time":451.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.56,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":106,"end_time":452.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.13,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Are we able.","index":107,"end_time":455.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.53,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Is it legal to make it mandatory?","index":108,"end_time":457.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.33,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"You can make it mandatory, but people, you know, tend to, like, not want to check anything that they see.","index":109,"end_time":463.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":457.89,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like, oh, I have to check to, you know, also to receive a newsletter.","index":110,"end_time":467.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":463.89,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But you can, you know, if you make it clear enough that they can unsubscribe and you know, where they can find the unsubscribe button, then it''s fine.","index":111,"end_time":475.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":468.69,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Well, all of our email drip campaigns and any email that we send has that unsubscribe button at the bottom.","index":112,"end_time":481.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.69,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And our text messages also has the ability for them to just say stop to.","index":113,"end_time":486.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481.65,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":114,"end_time":489.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.32,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"So we can make that mandatory.","index":115,"end_time":490.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Milan.","index":116,"end_time":491.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What?","index":117,"end_time":491.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":491.52,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"I''ll just ask if you is just have a pulse on new people signing up and if they have any issues with it and if we should have a further conversation about maybe not requiring it.","index":118,"end_time":500.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that''s not just for people signing up.","index":119,"end_time":503.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.56,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"That''s just for people like that.","index":120,"end_time":504.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.32,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"That waiver that I showed you was just the, like, schedule visit.","index":121,"end_time":508.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.6,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Mm.","index":122,"end_time":509.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":508.77,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So how are we going to schedule a visit if they don''t click that and we''re not?","index":123,"end_time":515.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.69,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Because it''s not other communication.","index":124,"end_time":517.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":515.65,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like, schedule.","index":125,"end_time":518.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":517.41,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s like, different categories of communication, if that makes sense.","index":126,"end_time":521.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s like, marketing communication.","index":127,"end_time":524.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":522.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Go ahead.","index":128,"end_time":526.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":525.65,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, so it''s like marketing communication.","index":129,"end_time":528.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would be like, here''s our monthly newsletter.","index":130,"end_time":531.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Things like that versus we.","index":131,"end_time":534.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re already required to say that you can communicate with them, just not from a marketing standpoint, if that makes sense.","index":132,"end_time":540.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so a text message to them, pushing them a promo.","index":133,"end_time":545.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.46,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"That''s a marketing text message, right?","index":134,"end_time":550.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.22,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":135,"end_time":551.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.7,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Unless it''s, like, connected to some, like, special points on their account that they have.","index":136,"end_time":556.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":551.9,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But these are prospects.","index":137,"end_time":559.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.62,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Most of them are prospects.","index":138,"end_time":561.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.98,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"They''re not going to be, like, members.","index":139,"end_time":562.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.14,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, members.","index":140,"end_time":563.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.03,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"We don''t really reach out for members.","index":141,"end_time":566.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.63,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"We don''t reach out to them for.","index":142,"end_time":568.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.83,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"With any kind of like deals or anything like that.","index":143,"end_time":571.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.47,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Any marketing based material.","index":144,"end_time":574.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.47,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"It''s, it''s more like prospects and a huge chunk of like our text messages and SMS to them is marketing based stuff.","index":145,"end_time":581.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.07,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So I think we just need to do it mandatory.","index":146,"end_time":585.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.75,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And what do you mean by that, Colin?","index":147,"end_time":587.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.75,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"That I have to keep a part false on it.","index":148,"end_time":589.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.63,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I was just like if, if people express any frustration with having to subscribe to marketing communications.","index":149,"end_time":595.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":589.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, okay.","index":150,"end_time":597.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.95,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"It''s just like if you think about.","index":151,"end_time":598.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":597.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":152,"end_time":599.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":599.07,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"If you see a large number of people unsubscribing like from all communication, then that''s also a reason to make it.","index":153,"end_time":606.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":599.51,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":154,"end_time":606.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":606.67,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Because that is a caution flag to HubSpot if, if they see a lot of unsubscribes.","index":155,"end_time":610.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":156,"end_time":612.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.03,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":157,"end_time":613.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.47,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Just think of like anything you sign up for.","index":158,"end_time":615.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure more often than not you''re saying don''t, don''t send me anything.","index":159,"end_time":619.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also keep in mind that a lot of people like don''t go to search for an unsubscribe button.","index":160,"end_time":625.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":619.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"They just reported that spam because they don''t want to deal with it.","index":161,"end_time":629.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":625.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then that also creates an alarm on HubSpot where they mark your domain as spam.","index":162,"end_time":635.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":629.2,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":163,"end_time":638,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":637.36,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Should I create a segment list for people like this and that way I can make sure that the numbers aren''t getting too high with people who are I guess checking off or saying stop on text messages and, and unsubscribing from our emails.","index":164,"end_time":658.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.56,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I know emails have.","index":165,"end_time":659.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.08,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Once I do like email blast, they''ll tell me how many have unsubscribed.","index":166,"end_time":665,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.92,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"But I should keep like a running list as well of this, right?","index":167,"end_time":667.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I think that''s a good idea.","index":168,"end_time":669.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":668.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, it''ll also automatically be tracked by HubSpot.","index":169,"end_time":672.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can just build a list based on those parameters.","index":170,"end_time":673.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":672.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s what I''ll do.","index":171,"end_time":677.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":675.21,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I''ll write a note here.","index":172,"end_time":678.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.61,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":173,"end_time":695.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":694.58,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So for now let''s just make it mandatory and then we''ll see how it goes.","index":174,"end_time":700.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.06,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Let me put these because I''m annoying my.","index":175,"end_time":703.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.66,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"The office here.","index":176,"end_time":705.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.5,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Can you hear me?","index":177,"end_time":712.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.14,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":178,"end_time":713.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":712.66,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay, it worked.","index":179,"end_time":718.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":716.74,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And also hubspoot has a way of tracking like email health which is also something like for each email campaign it usually shows you like what are the.","index":180,"end_time":727.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":718.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And it''s not just you know, in regards to like are people replying, but also for you to know, like is HubSpot going to, you know, flag you for anything?","index":181,"end_time":736.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":728.24,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, what are, what are the.","index":182,"end_time":740.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"At what Point.","index":183,"end_time":742.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.76,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Should we start to be worried if.","index":184,"end_time":744.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":742.52,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"You''Re like, in the yellow, don''t cross to the red.","index":185,"end_time":747.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":744.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Close to the red.","index":186,"end_time":752,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.36,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Is that what you said?","index":187,"end_time":752.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":188,"end_time":754.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s like a green, yellow, red.","index":189,"end_time":755.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":754.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we''re in the yellow, I think that''s where we start to say.","index":190,"end_time":758.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, let''s take some caution here.","index":191,"end_time":759.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":192,"end_time":762,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.36,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And also they change their benchmarks for whether they''re going to mark somebody as green, yellow, or red like, every couple of months.","index":193,"end_time":776.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":765.52,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So that''s something that you should be also aware of.","index":194,"end_time":778.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":776.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like.","index":195,"end_time":779.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":778.72,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":196,"end_time":779.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.11,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"For example, if you have a lower reply rate, like, it can.","index":197,"end_time":782.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":779.5,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like, they can change the benchmark for when it''s okay for them for you to have a low reply rate.","index":198,"end_time":787.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":782.9,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":199,"end_time":789.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.18,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So for example, our last.","index":200,"end_time":791.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.66,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So first, when I send the emails, I''m.","index":201,"end_time":794.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.58,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I''m unchecking the, like, unengaged.","index":202,"end_time":796.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.18,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":203,"end_time":797.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":797.18,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So in that way, like, we''re not reaching out to those people consistently and we''re not getting flagged.","index":204,"end_time":803.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":798.7,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"But then, like, for example, this is my last email that I sent out 6,500 people.","index":205,"end_time":808.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.58,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So 64 unsubscribed.","index":206,"end_time":809.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.3,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So 0.99%.","index":207,"end_time":811.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.98,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"That''s fine, right?","index":208,"end_time":813.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":811.82,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":209,"end_time":813.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":813.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just make sure you always exclude those 64, like, because I''m like, you can''t technically send them.","index":210,"end_time":822.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":814.14,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":211,"end_time":824.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.42,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":212,"end_time":824.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.42,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay.","index":213,"end_time":825.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824.94,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":214,"end_time":826.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":825.38,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":215,"end_time":827.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":827.02,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Now we''re all on the same page here.","index":216,"end_time":829.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":827.58,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":217,"end_time":829.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.26,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":218,"end_time":831.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.26,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":219,"end_time":834.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.94,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"What else was there?","index":220,"end_time":837.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.79,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"What was.","index":221,"end_time":839.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.11,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Give me a second.","index":222,"end_time":841.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":840.63,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Let me just recap.","index":223,"end_time":843.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":841.59,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I''m doing a lot of, like, my own lists at the moment, so if I have.","index":224,"end_time":848.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.67,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"How''s that been going on that stuff?","index":225,"end_time":850.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.55,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"It''s been fine.","index":226,"end_time":851.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.229,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yes.","index":227,"end_time":853.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.55,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Not a problem at all with.","index":228,"end_time":854.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":853.03,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"With Julia''s, like, reports.","index":229,"end_time":855.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.27,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I thought they were reports and reports I don''t believe I''m able to do.","index":230,"end_time":860.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":855.67,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Right.","index":231,"end_time":860.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.03,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"It''s just lists.","index":232,"end_time":861.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.85,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":233,"end_time":863.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":862.45,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Lists are part of, like, the sales segment, so they can be easily copied, but the reports are, I think, depend on how many, like, open spaces you have for additional reports and dashboards.","index":234,"end_time":874.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":863.05,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"You know, what we discussed.","index":235,"end_time":876.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":875.33,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I remember.","index"