INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Branding and Visual Identity**

The team decided to update the **KTC Search logo** to incorporate **Richie May''s green and blue colors** to align with the parent company''s branding and ease future integration (05:13).

- **Michael Kersten** emphasized blending Richie May’s blue and green tones into the logo and website to create visual consistency with Richie May’s existing brands.
- This change aims to support brand recognition as KTC Search builds its identity throughout **2026**, starting with no existing color recognition.
- The updated colors will help position KTC Search as a standalone brand now but ready for smooth transition into Richie May’s ecosystem later.
- The marketing team agreed to implement this immediately to leverage the current rebranding phase.

## **Video Content and Marketing Strategy**

KTC Search set up a **Riverside studio account** to start producing video content for the **Executive Advantage series**, aiming to launch initial videos by **January** and full client-featured videos by **May** (09:03).

- **Michael Kersten** proposed using **Kristen Baller** as a surrogate spokesperson for video interviews until his availability after **May**, leveraging her prior experience with Dish to speed content creation.
- This surrogate approach allows the company to start building video content early, maintaining momentum despite Michael’s limited camera availability.
- The Riverside platform will support remote interviews and video testimonials, providing flexibility and professional quality.
- Coordination meetings will be scheduled with Kristen to finalize scripting and interview prep, ensuring smooth content flow and alignment with marketing goals.

## **Website Development and SEO**

The website redesign is progressing with rewritten SEO-optimized content and new designs incorporating the updated **green color scheme**, targeting a complete launch after development in **HubSpot** (12:27).

- The team is rewriting content based on **search volume data** to improve organic discovery and lead generation.
- The homepage and testimonial pages have been mocked up, with plans to add both text and video testimonials sourced from past clients.
- Michael granted full creative autonomy to the marketing team to overhaul the site aggressively to compete effectively.
- The website will be built and hosted in HubSpot, with a planned transition that includes domain forwarding from the current site after launch to avoid downtime.

## **Client and Candidate Experience Pages**

KTC Search will create specialized landing pages to highlight **sales organization building** and **utility manufacturer expertise**, reflecting Michael’s growing work in these sectors, as well as separate pages for **candidate experience** and **resume submissions** (15:53).

- Michael is providing client and company details to tailor these pages around his core business strengths and client verticals, particularly in the utility space.
- The candidate-focused pages will support resume intake and showcase testimonials to improve candidate engagement without posting open job roles.
- The marketing team will integrate legal disclaimers and equal opportunity employer language only if needed, as no open job postings will be listed.
- This differentiated approach ensures the site serves both clients and candidates effectively while maintaining compliance and brand clarity.

## **Testimonial Acquisition and Client Engagement**

Michael is leveraging strong relationships with key past clients, including an SVP at **Sunbudsalam** and a former RevOps SVP from **ID Me**, to secure video and written testimonials for the website and marketing materials (14:39).

- These testimonials will be scripted and edited to focus on Michael’s value and services without revealing proprietary information or sensitive details.
- The testimonial content will feed into the new testimonial page designs, helping build social proof and credibility with prospects.
- The marketing team plans to provide Michael with guidelines and a content calendar to manage testimonial outreach efficiently.
- These efforts aim to increase client trust and support lead generation through authentic endorsements.

## **Operational Planning and Next Steps**

The team plans to maintain the current website live during development and then switch domain forwarding upon launch, ensuring a smooth transition with no loss of traffic or SEO ranking (27:01).

- Hosting access and credentials have been requested to facilitate the migration and deployment process.
- The next meeting is scheduled for **December 23rd**, with the team available to accommodate early morning meetings as needed to fit different time zones.
- Kristen will be fully integrated into the marketing workflow as a key operational lead for video content and client coordination.
- The marketing firm is positioned as a full **“soup to nuts”** marketing partner handling website, content, video, and HubSpot management to streamline KTC Search’s go-to-market efforts.',
  '2025-12-16 18:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Update logo colors to integrate Richie May greens and blues per Michael’s guidance (05:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Share Riverside platform credentials and usage instructions with Michael and Kristen (09:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Schedule meeting with Kristen for interview/video process coordination (11:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Send guidelines document and content calendar for testimonial interviews to Michael for client coordination (20:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Develop new website pages and candidate experience page in HubSpot including resume submission function (23:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Incorporate legal disclaimers and privacy policy from existing site or create new page if needed (26:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate transition plan for new website launch and domain forwarding with Ryan (27:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide calendar link to Kristen for easy scheduling of future meetings (29:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide Richie May branding color references to Colin for logo revision (05:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Introduce Kristen Baller on call and share her email with Colin for coordination (17:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up with clients (e.g., ID.me and Sunbursalam) to secure testimonials and submit details to Colin (14:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Ryan to ensure access and credentials provided to marketing team for website hosting and content updates (27:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Collaborate with Colin and Michael on content preps and interview scripting to serve as surrogate spokesperson (10:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Review redesigned homepage and testimonial pages and provide feedback regarding staffing legal requirements and client/candidate experience sections (21:30)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
