-- Meeting: Data Assessment Solutions // MiD: German Market Kickoff (2025-12-16 14:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'e50afe94-037e-49d6-8f2e-8c05ac7e3294',
    '2025-12-16 14:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KC9RJFYZRTREGANSE77G0GHF',
    'Data Assessment Solutions // MiD: German Market Kickoff',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Axel Völker","Eli Bebinger","Axel Völker","Maximilian Rabeler"}'::text[],
    3233,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85198351976?pwd=An5IJMrn4xPkTXebaQ27SXIxbZoEeq.1',
    '{"id":"01KC9RJFYZRTREGANSE77G0GHF","title":"Data Assessment Solutions // MiD: German Market Kickoff","summary":{"notes":"## **German Market Targeting and Messaging**\n\nThe German market shares core customers and pain points with the US but requires tailored messaging and local language adaptations.\n\n- **The core target remains mid to large IT consulting companies, focusing on skills and resource management, with the same pain points as the US market** according to **Axel Völker** (03:50)\n    - German clients prefer the term \"CV\" instead of \"resume,\" and value **data privacy and compliance** more due to local legislation.\n    - Local language support and German-based communication are advantages, as companies prefer dealing with someone familiar with their legal and cultural context.\n    - The selling approach should be less aggressive than in the US, avoiding fear-based tactics and overselling, as Germans tend to be skeptical of hard sell.\n    - Messaging should resonate with pain points like cost reduction, utilization, and bench management but remain straightforward and respectful.\n\n- **Buying decisions often involve a committee rather than a single person, typically including operations or internal sales leads, while resource managers act as primary users but rarely decision-makers** (06:59)\n    - Economic uncertainty, especially in industries like automotive, makes bench utilization and cost-saving critical messages.\n    - Time zone differences with the US and Japan create operational challenges, emphasizing the need for localized support.\n    - The campaign will focus on Germany and the wider DACH region, with Switzerland showing strong engagement due to less regulation and more spending power.\n\n- **Outreach should come from a German personality, such as Bettina, to improve response rates and local relevance** (13:43)\n    - Email and LinkedIn profiles will be adapted to German language and context.\n    - References and social proof from the German market will be leveraged to build credibility.\n    - Personalized messaging will avoid phrases like \"bench\" internally, opting for more positive terms such as \"active placement\" to respect labor council sensitivities.\n\n## **Sales Cycle and Deal Acceleration**\n\nSales velocity depends heavily on prospect readiness, with demos preferred over self-service signups.\n\n- **Sales cycles in Germany range from three months to two years, mirroring US experience; deals progress faster when prospects have an internal project and budget for the tool** (17:24)\n    - Active searchers for skill and CV management tools move faster, while casual investigators stall without internal alignment.\n    - Demo requests convert better than free registrations, as buying committees benefit from guided group presentations.\n    - Early messaging leads with sales skills and CV management, followed by resource utilization and skill building phases to align with customer priorities.\n\n- **AI is a double-edged sword: companies claim AI interest but legal and compliance teams raise concerns about data usage and bias, creating a barrier to sales** (19:33)\n    - AI messaging should be positioned carefully, focusing on practical problem-solving rather than AI for its own sake.\n    - The uncertain future of AI in consulting, especially with EU regulations, creates reluctance but also opportunity for positioning Desi Dollo as a tool for hybrid teams and reskilling.\n    - Labor market regulations in Germany make layoffs expensive, increasing demand for skills gap analysis and reskilling tools, which Desi Dollo can address.\n\n- **Key product features that spur interest include automated CV customization and skill matching, which speed up the resource allocation process and reduce administrative effort** (18:43)\n    - These features highlight the platform’s industry-specific design, which prospects recognize as a major advantage over generic HR tools.\n\n## **Campaign Setup and Asset Development**\n\nA localized campaign with German language assets and personalized outreach is planned, with clear next steps for execution.\n\n- **The campaign will build new pages and assets on the main Desi Dollo website tailored to the DACH region, avoiding US-specific micro-sites** (44:49)\n    - German and English versions of explainer videos and sales materials will be created, reflecting the multilingual nature of European markets.\n    - Translations will be coordinated with local team members to ensure cultural and linguistic accuracy.\n\n- **Multiple call-to-actions will be tested, prioritizing demo signups over free registrations to engage buying committees more effectively** (33:44)\n    - Tools like Storylane will be used to create guided demo walkthroughs, augmenting live demos and improving understanding.\n    - Data privacy concerns limit willingness to share CV data upfront, so proof of concept agreements with data processing clauses will be necessary for demos involving client data.\n\n- **Automation of lead nurturing remains minimal due to low current registration volumes (~2-3 weekly), but increased campaign activity aims to justify future automation** (48:10)\n    - Current manual processes are sufficient but scalable automation will be developed if lead volume grows.\n\n## **Metrics, Goals, and Success Criteria**\n\nDemo calls are the primary early success metric, with modest volume expectations reflecting market size and campaign stage.\n\n- **Current demo call volume in the DACH region averages around one per week, serving as the main indicator of campaign health** (40:22)\n    - Increasing demo volume will signal market traction and justify investment in automation and expanded outreach.\n    - The connected nature of the market, especially in Switzerland, presents opportunities for referral growth though no formal program yet exists.\n\n- **Close lost and referral data will be leveraged to personalize outreach and identify warm leads, including targeting contacts who have moved companies within the sector** (42:03)\n    - Enrichment of contact data to track employment changes is planned to maintain engagement with prospects who switch firms.\n    - LinkedIn’s company and past company data may support targeting but requires further research.\n\n## **Process Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nCross-team collaboration and clear communication channels will support rapid campaign development and execution.\n\n- **Maximilian Rabeler will bridge customer success insights and marketing needs, providing usage dashboards and customer feedback to optimize messaging** (36:30)\n    - He will also coordinate with US marketing to adapt successful tactics for the German market.\n    - Translation support will be facilitated by sharing source files (e.g., Figma), enabling efficient adaptation of creative assets.\n\n- **A detailed roadmap and plan document outlining goals, messaging, list parameters, and offers will be delivered ahead of the next meeting on Friday, with a schedule adjustment agreed** (49:15)\n    - Bettina’s contact details will be shared to warm up email domains and LinkedIn profiles for outreach.\n    - The team agreed to pause US ads only after current campaigns run through the holiday season, maintaining momentum while building the German campaign.\n\n- **GDPR compliance changes, particularly around cookie consent, will impact tracking and require adaptation in marketing approaches, with browser-level consent expected to simplify future compliance** (45:20)\n    - The team will monitor these regulatory shifts to stay ahead in privacy-sensitive markets.\n\n## **Strategic Positioning and Market Outlook**\n\nDesi Dollo aims to leverage its industry specialization and local presence to differentiate in a competitive and evolving market.\n\n- **The company’s niche focus on mid-sized B2B SaaS companies and deep knowledge of consulting industry pain points is a competitive advantage in Germany** (38:13)\n    - US marketing expertise will inform German campaigns but must be adapted for local market size and cultural nuances.\n    - Positioning as a mid-sized German company offering local support appeals to prospects wary of large US vendors and difficult time zones.\n\n- **The uncertain impact of AI on consulting labor dynamics drives customer hesitancy but also presents an opening for Desi Dollo to help companies prepare through skills management and reskilling tools** (25:49)\n    - Messaging will balance AI opportunity with compliance concerns, focusing on practical productivity gains and future readiness.\n    - The company recognizes the need to evolve its story around AI’s role in hybrid teams and workforce transformation.\n\n- **Cultural sensitivities around labor terms and sales approaches necessitate a respectful, consultative selling style rather than aggressive tactics** (34:00)\n    - Internal labor councils and regulations shape acceptable language and influence buying behaviors.\n    - The team plans to leverage positive framing and local terminology to build trust and reduce resistance.","outline":null,"keywords":["German market","Resource management","AI adoption","DACH region","Sales demos","Compliance/GDPR"],"overview":"- **German Market Focus:** Target mid to large IT consulting firms; adapt messaging to local language and compliance needs.  \n- **Committee Buying Decisions:** Focus on group dynamics; highlight cost-saving messages during economic uncertainty in key industries.  \n- **Localized Outreach:** Use a German persona for outreach to improve engagement; personalize messages avoiding sensitive terms.  \n- **Sales Cycle Insights:** Expect three-month to two-year sales cycles; demos are preferred for unified committee presentations.  \n- **Demo Success Metric:** Average one demo per week; increasing volume signals market traction and justifies automation investment.  \n- **Collaboration and Planning:** Maximize cross-team communication; deliver detailed roadmap ahead of Friday’s meeting for execution clarity.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDevelop and share updated Germany/DACH campaign roadmap document with German team for feedback and translation review (46:30)\nWarm up email domains and LinkedIn outreach profiles using Bettina’s account for German market outreach (14:15)\nResearch LinkedIn targeting possibilities based on past company/current company transitions to leverage referrals from personnel movements (43:20)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nProvide Bettina’s and Meiss’s contact info to Colin; add Max to New Norse chat to include him in ongoing communications (49:30)\n\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nPrepare and share relevant usage data, pain points, dashboards to support marketing asset tailoring once the exact needs are clarified (36:30)\nFacilitate ongoing communication with US marketing team to exchange insights on target markets and optimize campaign approach collaboratively (37:15)\n\n**Marketing team**\nPrepare bilingual (English/German) explainer videos and web pages to support German and broader DACH marketing efforts (46:40)\nTemporarily continue US ad campaigns for 10 more days, then pause post holiday season to focus on German campaigns (52:00)\nConsider testing campaign messaging that emphasizes utilization, active placement, sales skills to resonate with current German pain points and compliance needs (00:00)\n\n**Colin and Axel**\nCollaborate to create personalized re-engagement campaigns targeting previous lost deals with tailored messaging referencing past interactions (42:00)\n\n**Colin Costigan/Axel Völker**\nCoordinate next meeting 30 minutes earlier on Friday to review roadmap and next steps (50:40)\n"},"duration":53.880001068115234,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":2,"name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"id":3,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":4,"name":"Maximilian Rabeler"}],"sentences":[{"text":"How''s it going?","index":0,"end_time":37.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s happening?","index":1,"end_time":39.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Nice to see you, Tristan.","index":2,"end_time":41.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":40.33,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"How''s everybody doing?","index":3,"end_time":42.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.69,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Hey, how you doing this morning?","index":4,"end_time":44.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Pretty good.","index":5,"end_time":46.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hi.","index":6,"end_time":56.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hey, Axel, how''s it going?","index":7,"end_time":58.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Good, good.","index":8,"end_time":59.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":9,"end_time":60.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":10,"end_time":61.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any signs of slowed down pace or are people being back in the office or is that just kind of playing?","index":11,"end_time":69.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, it''s just the last week, so.","index":12,"end_time":71.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":69.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s the last week.","index":13,"end_time":73.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Basically next week most people will be off.","index":14,"end_time":75.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":73.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":15,"end_time":78.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, I know you''re spread pretty thin right now, so I appreciate making the time for this call.","index":16,"end_time":84.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":17,"end_time":85.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":85.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Based on everything that you mentioned last week of just bandwidth limitations and basically the low hanging fruit that''s available in Germany, we wanted to have this call which will just give us the space to ask some questions about the German market so that we can get assets produced and plan documents in place and start marketing to the German audience, switching away from the US audience.","index":18,"end_time":107.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":85.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":19,"end_time":109.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, everyone see my screen?","index":20,"end_time":114.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":21,"end_time":118.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":117.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So getting started here.","index":22,"end_time":122.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll focus on a few things today, the target market being one of them, and then we''ll go into some buying signals, things that we lead with in this campaign and then what does success look like?","index":23,"end_time":132.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So as far as understanding the German market, I want to just confirm a few things.","index":24,"end_time":140.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So hold on, there''s.","index":25,"end_time":142.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":140.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Why is our German team not in here?","index":26,"end_time":146.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":144.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re not invited or.","index":27,"end_time":147.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":146.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So hold on.","index":28,"end_time":150.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Preliminary staff Ue lion and Joachim were who we invited.","index":29,"end_time":159.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Before that, there''s.","index":30,"end_time":162.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Who.","index":31,"end_time":165.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":165.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Who are you thinking?","index":32,"end_time":166.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.71,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Max.","index":33,"end_time":167.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Betty and Max.","index":34,"end_time":170.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":168.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":35,"end_time":170.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":170.35,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Buddy and Max.","index":36,"end_time":171.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":170.71,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":175.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":175.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure, it''s maybe a bit short notice to.","index":38,"end_time":178.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":175.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I just forwarded it to them.","index":39,"end_time":180.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":40,"end_time":186.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":185.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, let''s start anyway.","index":41,"end_time":187.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":186.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":42,"end_time":188.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":43,"end_time":190.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I didn''t have any other email address.","index":44,"end_time":191.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, I thought I. I forgot to.","index":45,"end_time":193.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":191.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Forward it somehow.","index":46,"end_time":195.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So wanted to take the time just to go through some assumptions and make sure that those assumptions are accurate and then also ask some questions about the German audience.","index":47,"end_time":207.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in conversations with you and obviously with where Desi Dollo started, it''s, it''s, you know, pretty straightforward that this has become desi$,''s strongest market by experience and revenue.","index":48,"end_time":220.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Want to confirm though that the core customers are still in the mid to large IT consultant and using like skills and resource management as aspects of their business.","index":49,"end_time":229.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":50,"end_time":230.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":230.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s the same target.","index":51,"end_time":233.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":232.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The target group is pretty much the same.","index":52,"end_time":236.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":233.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we just took the German one and used the same in the US Assuming that.","index":53,"end_time":240.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And with that target market, Axle, is it the same exact pain points that you''ve found or, you know, we''ll even get into some nitty gritty of like language barrier or phrases that people want to avoid or want to see.","index":54,"end_time":255.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, so here they would say CV instead of resume.","index":55,"end_time":260.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":257.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But there''s I think the only.","index":56,"end_time":261.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":260.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean it''s all German.","index":57,"end_time":263.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No, I think it is some.","index":58,"end_time":266.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":265.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So the pain points are the same that we use.","index":59,"end_time":271.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":266.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The story is the same that we.","index":60,"end_time":272.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":271.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Use in the us There''s a few.","index":61,"end_time":274.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Things that are more important here but that are not core features that are just general for the European market.","index":62,"end_time":282.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":276.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we need.","index":63,"end_time":282.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Translations, different languages, which.","index":64,"end_time":287.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":285.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We don''t need in the US because over here everyone has mostly in English.","index":65,"end_time":292.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And the German cv.","index":66,"end_time":293.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":292.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But that is not really core differentiating feature.","index":67,"end_time":299,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":294.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I would say it is the a.","index":68,"end_time":306.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Few things for larger companies when you sell to them, probably more important like data privacy and these kind of things.","index":69,"end_time":313.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":306.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But that''s also not a sales pitch, that''s more what they''re asking for afterwards then in the conversations.","index":70,"end_time":320.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, but likely a core aspect of their research that they''re conducting.","index":71,"end_time":324.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":72,"end_time":325.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I think in general it is.","index":73,"end_time":328.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":325.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Somehow an advantage if you sell to.","index":74,"end_time":331.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"A German company at your German company.","index":75,"end_time":333.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":331.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because then they can talk to you.","index":76,"end_time":334.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":333.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"In German as well.","index":77,"end_time":335.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":334.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"German, it''s the same legislation and everything.","index":78,"end_time":338.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":335.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s just easier for companies to do business with.","index":79,"end_time":341.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":338.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But in terms of the product and.","index":80,"end_time":344.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":342.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The pain points it is I would say the same.","index":81,"end_time":346.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":82,"end_time":347.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":347.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I know a big focus here also is the time zone differences that we''ve been experiencing with the US and then your largest company also in Japan.","index":83,"end_time":355.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that became quite a stretch.","index":84,"end_time":358.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":356.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"14 hour days will add up to you.","index":85,"end_time":362.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And do we find, and I know David is an example, but he''s more in the UK based.","index":86,"end_time":368.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we find that resource managers are still like the power users of the platform, but they.","index":87,"end_time":375.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We kind of need to establish pain points with them and then give them some assets or information that they can take to leadership to make the investment.","index":88,"end_time":382.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I would say resource managers are the power users and then the ones that come to us or buy really depends.","index":89,"end_time":394.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":383.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sometimes it''s like some internal operations people, sometimes it''s resource manager, sometimes sales presets.","index":90,"end_time":402.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":395,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But the resource manager I think is.","index":91,"end_time":404.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":402.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"A good target group to start with.","index":92,"end_time":407.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or like operational leads or something like.","index":93,"end_time":411.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":408.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That, whatever the name.","index":94,"end_time":412.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And with Germany, do you find that it''s more often a buying committee that is making the decision rather than a single person?","index":95,"end_time":418.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, typically it is.","index":96,"end_time":420.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":419.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It depends on the size of the.","index":97,"end_time":421.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":420.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Company, but it''s mostly multiple people involved.","index":98,"end_time":425.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":99,"end_time":426.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":100,"end_time":427.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then so for the pain points and everything that they''re dealing with still going on, reducing costs or things that they can lean in on.","index":101,"end_time":440.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So headcount overhead, things like that.","index":102,"end_time":441.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think so here.","index":103,"end_time":443.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":442.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So actually we have quite a bit of economic problem in some industries.","index":104,"end_time":452.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":443.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So for example in automotive it''s really bad and there''s more and more consulting and IT services companies that having a bench or that at least fear of getting a bench, there''s a lot of uncertainty.","index":105,"end_time":468.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":452.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So the bench and the utilization story is probably becoming more important.","index":106,"end_time":472.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":468.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like how do I utilize, how do I my people, how do I get rid of my bench?","index":107,"end_time":476.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":472.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sales support and automation, of course, potentially.","index":108,"end_time":484.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":477.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They can save costs.","index":109,"end_time":485.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":484.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So they''re all looking to save costs right now at the moment.","index":110,"end_time":489.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":485.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And one stark difference that we found between the US target audience and almost anywhere in Europe is US responds a little bit stronger to fear.","index":111,"end_time":498.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As in if you don''t do this, this is what you will lose or experience.","index":112,"end_time":503.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Whereas other markets, that''s sort of a more aggressive tactic.","index":113,"end_time":507,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you find that the German market is more like we just need to say that we resonate with the pain points that they''re experiencing and here''s how our tool solves them rather than saying if they don''t work with Desi Dahllo they will experience more pain.","index":114,"end_time":519.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":115,"end_time":522.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s more like a messaging thing or maybe a cultural thing.","index":116,"end_time":533.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":523.229,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So people over here are not that used to like how are you?","index":117,"end_time":541.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":533.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s like, like brute force selling.","index":118,"end_time":544.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":542.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They don''t really like to be sold to.","index":119,"end_time":545.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":544.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So they''re more.","index":120,"end_time":546.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":545.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think this may be a bit different.","index":121,"end_time":550.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":547.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So they, they''re more.","index":122,"end_time":552.109,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":550.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So they''re always skeptical that that about overselling stuff.","index":123,"end_time":557.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":553.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think so that is probably trying to oversell is probably not the best approach.","index":124,"end_time":565.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":557.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I think in general, I mean.","index":125,"end_time":569.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":568.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The fear.","index":126,"end_time":570.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s really hard to say because we have not really done any scientific research on this.","index":127,"end_time":581.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":574.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What works and what doesn''t work.","index":128,"end_time":582.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think the messaging is a bit different.","index":129,"end_time":585.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":583.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s not too.","index":130,"end_time":587.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":585.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Overselling or to over emphasize.","index":131,"end_time":591.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":589.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Then people are becoming a bit skeptical.","index":132,"end_time":595.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":592.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":133,"end_time":597.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that''s, that''s certainly a difference that I would agree with.","index":134,"end_time":599.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":135,"end_time":601.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so yeah, we can test that in the message variations to make sure that our understanding is accurate.","index":136,"end_time":606.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":601.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what it sounds like is if you know, going with the free registration offer of the campaign, really letting them experience the power of the tool before saying here''s a million features and here''s the next conversation you need to have.","index":137,"end_time":617.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":606.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s a bit of a question on how you want to Again, position yourself.","index":138,"end_time":622.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":619.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s, I mean most of the software tools that we are using over here like all over the world are probably US based, the big ones, it''s Microsoft.","index":139,"end_time":632.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":622.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or Jira or whatever, Zoom or whatever.","index":140,"end_time":635.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":632.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And people are somewhat used to their kind of sales approach and that, that and some people prefer to buy like from a hip news startup that has a lot of venture capital and so forth but some don''t.","index":141,"end_time":655.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":636.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Some feel more comfortable with like a mid sized German company where they can call it someone in Germany.","index":142,"end_time":660.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":655.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it really depends.","index":143,"end_time":662.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":661.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s a bit, I think we have.","index":144,"end_time":663.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":662.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"To see how we want to position.","index":145,"end_time":666.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What you''re competing with.","index":146,"end_time":667.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":666.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right?","index":147,"end_time":668.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":667.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":148,"end_time":669.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that''s, that''s, that''s what we want to establish today as well.","index":149,"end_time":672.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also touched on tapping into, I would say close Lost.","index":150,"end_time":678.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know you had mentioned like they kind of just deals that have fallen off over the last few years and within that do we have any information of, you know, where those deals die most often?","index":151,"end_time":690.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it a lack of urgency?","index":152,"end_time":692.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it struggling to get internal alignment on signing with a tool like Desi Dollo?","index":153,"end_time":697.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do they have a fear of upgrading their systems and like time down, things like that?","index":154,"end_time":702.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is probably lack of urgency in most cases and having something that somehow.","index":155,"end_time":709.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":704.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Works like some spreadsheets or whatever.","index":156,"end_time":712.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then often it''s a problem with finding the right person in the organization that makes the decision so we are most successful or most of our sales actually work that way.","index":157,"end_time":729.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":713.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That some company has already decided to introduce a new skill resource management tool, then they start looking, then they find us and then they have everything set up internally like they have a buying committee and they have a team evaluating.","index":158,"end_time":743.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":729.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It and that works well for us.","index":159,"end_time":747.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If, if it''s more a single person just investigating a tool because he thinks oh there must be a better solution.","index":160,"end_time":755.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":747.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But the organization itself has not decided to actually start looking for it.","index":161,"end_time":759.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":755.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Then it really often stalls because then he does not get ahead internally or they don''t have a budget for it or whatever.","index":162,"end_time":768.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":760.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So.","index":163,"end_time":769.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":164,"end_time":770.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":770.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":165,"end_time":771.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":771.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And for this targeting we''re focusing solely on the country of Germany and not the Dachsh region, right?","index":166,"end_time":778.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, that we can do the Dach region.","index":167,"end_time":779.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":778.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Actually Switzerland is pretty strong.","index":168,"end_time":781.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":779.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have a lot of customers in Switzerland.","index":169,"end_time":783.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":781.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Austria, not that much.","index":170,"end_time":785.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":783.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But Switzerland is working very well for us with a lot of references there also.","index":171,"end_time":790.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":172,"end_time":791.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And are you finding any discrepancies in the process between those countries inside of the dock region?","index":173,"end_time":796.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Switzerland is actually easier because they''re not that over regulated and have more Money.","index":174,"end_time":802.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":796.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So.","index":175,"end_time":803.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":803.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":176,"end_time":807.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":177,"end_time":807.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And not to get ahead of our ourselves here but you know obviously we set up emails and everything and LinkedIn connection profiles from.","index":178,"end_time":817.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From Eli with targeting the US market.","index":179,"end_time":820.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we want to utilize another personality?","index":180,"end_time":823.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we would change that to.","index":181,"end_time":824.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":823.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"To our German colleague Athena because I.","index":182,"end_time":827.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":824.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Think that makes more sense if it''s.","index":183,"end_time":828.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":827.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s a German message and then people.","index":184,"end_time":831.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":828.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Replying in German to Eli is probably giving Eli a bit of a challenge then.","index":185,"end_time":835.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":831.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe not the best business model.","index":186,"end_time":839.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":836.17,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we should do it.","index":187,"end_time":842.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":840.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like a German outreach from.","index":188,"end_time":844.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":842.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"From Bettina''s account.","index":189,"end_time":845.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I would say so for Bettina.","index":190,"end_time":847.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, I just forwarded to her.","index":191,"end_time":849.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":847.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I think she''s.","index":192,"end_time":850.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"She was offline.","index":193,"end_time":852.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":850.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure if she''s.","index":194,"end_time":853.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":195,"end_time":858.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":857.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Just because I want to start warming up some email domains so that we can.","index":196,"end_time":863.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can send you the email address.","index":197,"end_time":865.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":863.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that would be Great.","index":198,"end_time":866.499,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":865.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And to LinkedIn.","index":199,"end_time":867.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":866.499,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":200,"end_time":870.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I know you mentioned with the buying committees and things stalling as well.","index":201,"end_time":873.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you found a most common title that has moved the deal across the finish line from the prospect side?","index":202,"end_time":880.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, but I haven''t really done any comparison.","index":203,"end_time":886.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":882.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think it''s mostly.","index":204,"end_time":887.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":886.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"People in some internal operations functions I would say.","index":205,"end_time":894.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":206,"end_time":895.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":894.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So often they are like vice president or something.","index":207,"end_time":898.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":895.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":208,"end_time":900.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":899.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":209,"end_time":902.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":210,"end_time":902.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":902.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some will likely have resource in their title, others will be more operations based, I think.","index":211,"end_time":906.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":902.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":212,"end_time":907.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Resources.","index":213,"end_time":907.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":907.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The ones that use it that the resource managers are typically not the ones making the decisions.","index":214,"end_time":914.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":907.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":215,"end_time":916.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":915.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":216,"end_time":919.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":217,"end_time":920.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":919.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All good to understand then.","index":218,"end_time":922.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have also so just making sure that our parameters are here.","index":219,"end_time":925.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So location will update to the docs reason but for industry still locked in on IT services and IT consultant wanted to check the revenue and employee levels with you though here.","index":220,"end_time":935.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we want to expand this.","index":221,"end_time":937.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is this a good range to start with?","index":222,"end_time":939.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What did you have in mind?","index":223,"end_time":940.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s a good range to start with.","index":224,"end_time":945.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":943.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":225,"end_time":948.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a lot of.","index":226,"end_time":948.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":948.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So where we''re really strong there is.","index":227,"end_time":950.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":948.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s a ton of SAP consulting companies here.","index":228,"end_time":953.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":950.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But you have SAP in there and.","index":229,"end_time":955.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":953.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''S like tons of them and pretty big ones and.","index":230,"end_time":957.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":955.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And we have actually we are very.","index":231,"end_time":959.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":957.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have a lot of them and we very familiar with their business model.","index":232,"end_time":964.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":960.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that is something we can target.","index":233,"end_time":968.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":964.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Just SAP consultancy but they''re basically in.","index":234,"end_time":971.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":968.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There from your list.","index":235,"end_time":973.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":971.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":236,"end_time":974.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And one question that just popped into mind.","index":237,"end_time":976.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we.","index":238,"end_time":976.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":976.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we feel that or in your experience of any German companies been interested in an in person meeting as part of this Process.","index":239,"end_time":984.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not since COVID anymore.","index":240,"end_time":988.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":987.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Before.","index":241,"end_time":989.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":988.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes, the large ones, sometimes we start doing it again, but mostly after they closed the design.","index":242,"end_time":999.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":989.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Then we do a kickoff workshop.","index":243,"end_time":1001.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":999.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s what we''re doing.","index":244,"end_time":1001.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1001.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But in sales, mostly not.","index":245,"end_time":1005.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1001.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean, if they''re like very nearby.","index":246,"end_time":1007.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1005.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Then you can do that.","index":247,"end_time":1008.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":248,"end_time":1009.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just wanted to see if it would be an attractive thing to mention in the emails for the companies that are pretty close located.","index":249,"end_time":1015.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":250,"end_time":1016.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1016.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"For the ones that are closed, like the Hanover area, we could do that.","index":251,"end_time":1019.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1016.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But then we have to somewhat distinguish.","index":252,"end_time":1021.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But in general or not.","index":253,"end_time":1022.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1021.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":254,"end_time":1026.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1024.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I want to tap into the buying signals now too.","index":255,"end_time":1028.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know, you know, when we first went through our kickoff phase and we were targeting the US and we were focused there and digging through, you know, information from Microsoft Dynamics, we saw sales cycles that can range from three months to upwards of two years.","index":256,"end_time":1042.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1028.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s pretty much the same.","index":257,"end_time":1045.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1044.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We''re trying to get it down, of course.","index":258,"end_time":1047.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1045.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":259,"end_time":1048.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1047.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":260,"end_time":1049.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1048.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"A little bit more velocity.","index":261,"end_time":1050.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1049.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And has there been a spark that you found that that really increases that velocity that the prospect is willing to go for the deal?","index":262,"end_time":1057.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1051.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it a discount with a time frame?","index":263,"end_time":1060.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1057.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it.","index":264,"end_time":1061.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1060.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s really how far they are in their process.","index":265,"end_time":1063.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1061.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If they have this, if they are basically actively looking for a solution and they have already internally set this up as a project to find a new.","index":266,"end_time":1073,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1063.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Tool, then it is much faster.","index":267,"end_time":1076.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1073.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If they''re starting from zero, then it can take the two years.","index":268,"end_time":1081.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1076.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":269,"end_time":1083.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1082.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":270,"end_time":1085.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1084.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I know that a lot of the deals were also word of mouth and inbound.","index":271,"end_time":1089.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1086.359,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re trying to open up the outbound arm there.","index":272,"end_time":1091.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1089.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And definitely referring to things by the CV term opening doors, you know, with managing CVs but also true resource management and how that can drive business revenue as a bottom line.","index":273,"end_time":1103.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":274,"end_time":1103.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":275,"end_time":1105.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then so really kind of back to that deal velocity.","index":276,"end_time":1109.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1106.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Has there been any phrases or specific features of the tool or anything that you''ve been able to show on a sales call that has moved someone from like I''m interested to we need to use the SE dollar right now.","index":277,"end_time":1123.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":278,"end_time":1123.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1123.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So mostly they come.","index":279,"end_time":1124.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1123.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They come to us for really the CV management skills.","index":280,"end_time":1131.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1126.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Management, like the sales support stuff.","index":281,"end_time":1134.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1131.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s where they mostly start with which.","index":282,"end_time":1136.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1134.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is the most obvious.","index":283,"end_time":1137.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1136.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then either that''s kind of enough for them to get started or they also look at the resource management.","index":284,"end_time":1145.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1138.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then I think with solutions we especially this like automatically customizing CVS and.","index":285,"end_time":1150.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1145.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Automatically finding the right people and bringing all that, all that down, all the, all the effort down and speeding up the process.","index":286,"end_time":1158.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":287,"end_time":1160.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And Our research has shown that AI is very popular as well in the docs region.","index":288,"end_time":1165.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1160.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you found anything different?","index":289,"end_time":1166.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1165.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would that be a no go for any companies or anything that we should not include in messaging?","index":290,"end_time":1173.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is.","index":291,"end_time":1174.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1173.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So they all, everyone, all these consulting companies, all the, and all companies here.","index":292,"end_time":1180.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1176.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They have an AI first strategy.","index":293,"end_time":1183.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1180.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But then when you talk to them about introducing an AI tool, the first thing is then, oh, how about the EU AI Act?","index":294,"end_time":1191.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1183.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that, oh, what is it?","index":295,"end_time":1192.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1191.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is it using my data or is.","index":296,"end_time":1194.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1192.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It, is it, is it fair?","index":297,"end_time":1195.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1194.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is it biased to anything?","index":298,"end_time":1197.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1195.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And they come up with a ton of like compliance questions where you think, sounds like they don''t want AI.","index":299,"end_time":1204.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1197.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s a bit, it''s a bit strange, but I think that those are two different.","index":300,"end_time":1211.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1206.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So that typically happens if they involve like their compliance people, which at some point larger companies have to do.","index":301,"end_time":1218.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1212.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But from the sales perspective, they all.","index":302,"end_time":1223.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1220.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Claim they want AI.","index":303,"end_time":1226.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1224.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":304,"end_time":1227.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1227.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Until it gets to legal or compliance.","index":305,"end_time":1229.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1227.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":306,"end_time":1229.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1229.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, then, yeah, exactly.","index":307,"end_time":1232.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1229.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And in your conversations, has it ever been, we''re looking to grow from X to Y.","index":308,"end_time":1238.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1233.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s why we realize we have a need for a tool like this.","index":309,"end_time":1240.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1238.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like a few years, like two years back, it was like that.","index":310,"end_time":1248.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1242.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We had a lot of companies that were growing pretty aggressively and pretty fast.","index":311,"end_time":1253.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1248.32,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Not so much at the moment, probably.","index":312,"end_time":1258.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1256.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Due to the economy.","index":313,"end_time":1260.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1258.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s more, I would say, how can.","index":314,"end_time":1263.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1260.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We get everyone utilized now?","index":315,"end_time":1267.729,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1263.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There are still companies that are growing.","index":316,"end_time":1269.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1267.729,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But not everyone is growing anymore or growing fast.","index":317,"end_time":1274.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1269.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":318,"end_time":1275.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1274.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it seems like more of the focus.","index":319,"end_time":1276.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1275.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The focus is less on pure growth in this economy, but more on making sure that a bench is not really a big aspect of their business and that they''re utilizing all employees as much as possible.","index":320,"end_time":1287.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1276.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":321,"end_time":1288.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1287.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And something that we may be able.","index":322,"end_time":1290.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1288.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"To take advantage of.","index":323,"end_time":1291.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1290.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s a lot of uncertainty.","index":324,"end_time":1292.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1291.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No one.","index":325,"end_time":1293.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So all the customers I talk to.","index":326,"end_time":1294.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They say they have no idea where they will be in two years, if every consultant will be replaced by some AI agent or if they have much more consultants because AI is creating so many consulting opportunities, they don''t know.","index":327,"end_time":1310.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1295.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But there''s a concern obviously that the whole industry is changing dramatically due to AI and AI agents.","index":328,"end_time":1317.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1310.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I think at the moment they cannot really tell where it''s going.","index":329,"end_time":1321.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1318.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So there''s some reluctance to invest.","index":330,"end_time":1325.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1321.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s fear that they''ll have people on the bench, especially union consultants.","index":331,"end_time":1330.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1326.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And so the story of we can.","index":332,"end_time":1335.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1333.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Use AI or AI agents, I think.","index":333,"end_time":1338.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1335.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What will be, it''s a bit early for us, is hybrid teams.","index":334,"end_time":1342.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1338.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We can use AI to boost the.","index":335,"end_time":1345.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1342.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Productivity of your teams by including them.","index":336,"end_time":1347.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1345.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And if we can give them that.","index":337,"end_time":1351.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1347.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Idea that this is coming, that may be interesting because I think everyone is.","index":338,"end_time":1355.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1351.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Thinking about how will this impact my business, how can I prepare for whatever''s coming?","index":339,"end_time":1361.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1355.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And larger firms probably have like multi year AI plans.","index":340,"end_time":1366.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1362.9,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right, Sorry, say it again.","index":341,"end_time":1369.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1366.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Larger firms probably have like multi year AI plans.","index":342,"end_time":1373.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1370.5,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I would imagine they would say, oh, we want to do this this year because in three years our goal is that our projections are this or something.","index":343,"end_time":1380.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1373.58,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"They have an AI first strategy, whatever that means.","index":344,"end_time":1385.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1382.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That is often not so clear.","index":345,"end_time":1389.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So there are some that are very innovative that are actually building a lot of AI agents themselves and using that and selling that.","index":346,"end_time":1396.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1389.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But then they have no view on which AI agents have you already built.","index":347,"end_time":1400.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1397.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And how can we reuse that.","index":348,"end_time":1401.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1400.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The other ones that like the SAP consultancies that are more traditional, they''re depending on whatever SAP is doing.","index":349,"end_time":1410.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1402.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think there is a lot of uncertainty what, how will it impact SAP.","index":350,"end_time":1416.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1412.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How will it impact business with SAP and so forth.","index":351,"end_time":1420.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1416.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":352,"end_time":1423.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1422.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So AI governance might be still growing as an aspect in these companies.","index":353,"end_time":1427.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1423.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s somehow like how.","index":354,"end_time":1430.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1428.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can we prepare for the future, for the AI future or whatever.","index":355,"end_time":1436.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1430.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So how can we position ourselves and.","index":356,"end_time":1439.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How can we get our team ready?","index":357,"end_time":1440.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1439.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think a lot of people are already talking or thinking about how does it.","index":358,"end_time":1444.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1440.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So do I need to do some reskilling?","index":359,"end_time":1447.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1445.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So something that is different here is the labor market is very different because.","index":360,"end_time":1453.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1447.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''S very hard to lay off people.","index":361,"end_time":1455.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1453.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Especially in large companies.","index":362,"end_time":1457.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1455.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s a lot of regulations and it''s essentially expensive to lay off people.","index":363,"end_time":1463.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1457.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what they probably try much more than in the US is to reskill people.","index":364,"end_time":1469.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1463.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And they, that is, I think a lot of people are thinking about that.","index":365,"end_time":1475.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1471.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What, what does that mean?","index":366,"end_time":1476.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1475.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Do I have to reskill my people that are in, that are doing stuff that potentially will be done by an.","index":367,"end_time":1483.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1476.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"AI agent in, in the future.","index":368,"end_time":1485.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1483.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And what will they do then?","index":369,"end_time":1486.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1485.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"My.","index":370,"end_time":1487.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1486.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That is maybe something that we can address.","index":371,"end_time":1491.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1488.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like, and I imagine they need a.","index":372,"end_time":1493.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1492.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Skills matrix to help the skill gap analysis.","index":373,"end_time":1497.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1493.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That that is what they do.","index":374,"end_time":1499.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1497.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what''s the gap?","index":375,"end_time":1500.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1499.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Which skills do I need in the future?","index":376,"end_time":1502.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1500.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Which do I have?","index":377,"end_time":1503.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1502.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How do I get there?","index":378,"end_time":1503.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1503.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s more skill management.","index":379,"end_time":1506.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1503.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But mostly they come because that is often done in hr.","index":380,"end_time":1509.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1506.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So mostly they come to us from, from the sales from Skill and cv.","index":381,"end_time":1515.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1510.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But we can tell them, okay, we know what you have to know what.","index":382,"end_time":1518.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1515.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The demand is, capture that to see where it''s going.","index":383,"end_time":1520.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1518.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I would probably still lead with the.","index":384,"end_time":1523.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1521.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sales related, like utilize, sell your skills.","index":385,"end_time":1528.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1525.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because that''s what essentially they''re trying to do.","index":386,"end_time":1532.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1528.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And kind of an open ended question here, but talking about, you know, companies either fear or excitement or uncertainty with AI.","index":387,"end_time":1539.869,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is Desi Dollo''s stance?","index":388,"end_time":1541.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1539.869,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where do you feel that the market is trending, especially in the docs region with AI and, and skills and labor.","index":389,"end_time":1548.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everyone is trying to do something there.","index":390,"end_time":1552,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1549.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Basically because everyone knows it''s changing and.","index":391,"end_time":1556.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1552.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''S again, there''s people that see it as a risk and people that see it as an opportunity.","index":392,"end_time":1561.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1556.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So people that see it as a risk, like the, I would say the whole EU in general, they''re trying to.","index":393,"end_time":1568.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1561.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Regulate it and trying to somehow keep.","index":394,"end_time":1571.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1568.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It out, which is not going to work.","index":395,"end_time":1574.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1571.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I think there''s a lot, there''s enough.","index":396,"end_time":1578.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1577.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Especially we''re talking about consulting companies so.","index":397,"end_time":1580.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1578.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''Re more innovative and they have tech companies.","index":398,"end_time":1584.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1580.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So they have to somehow embrace that.","index":399,"end_time":1586.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1584.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s what they''re trying to do.","index":400,"end_time":1587.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1586.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They just haven''t really figured out what.","index":401,"end_time":1589.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1587.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It means for their, for their business.","index":402,"end_time":1592.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1589.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I was thinking of the, the content series with the utilization effect.","index":403,"end_time":1597.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1593.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like that could be a strong series of episodes.","index":404,"end_time":1599.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1597.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just talking about the future of AI in the industry.","index":405,"end_time":1601.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is the future of AI in consulting.","index":406,"end_time":1604.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1601.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s, that''s, that''s big.","index":407,"end_time":1605.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1604.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s.","index":408,"end_time":1606.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1605.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What is it?","index":409,"end_time":1606.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1606.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is it that we need half the consultants because the other half is AI.","index":410,"end_time":1611.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1607.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Agents or twice as many because everyone.","index":411,"end_time":1615.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Needs to integrate its AI agents or.","index":412,"end_time":1618.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1615.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So and no one really knows.","index":413,"end_time":1619.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1618.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So.","index":414,"end_time":1620.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1619.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":415,"end_time":1620.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1620.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, that''s great.","index":416,"end_time":1622.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1621.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we definitely need to tap into those for some of these upcoming episodes.","index":417,"end_time":1625.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1622.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":418,"end_time":1626.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1626.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so great on the buying signals.","index":419,"end_time":1628.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1626.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the AI workforce management, you know, still going to be an important factor in this, but not always a top of funnel message.","index":420,"end_time":1636.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1629.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be introduced a little bit later where we talk about probably in those early messages getting more utilization out of their employees, reducing their bench, things like that.","index":421,"end_time":1646.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also maybe some reskilling in those opening messages.","index":422,"end_time":1649.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1646.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think selling.","index":423,"end_time":1650.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1649.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what we, so we have these three like pillars.","index":424,"end_time":1654.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1651.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have.","index":425,"end_time":1654.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1654.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sales skills, utilize skills and build and build skills.","index":426,"end_time":1660.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1656.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So and typically we lead with the.","index":427,"end_time":1663.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1660.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sell skills because that''s where it starts.","index":428,"end_time":1666.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1663.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If you cannot sell your skills, you.","index":429,"end_time":1667.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Cannot utilize your people and you don''t.","index":430,"end_time":1670.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1667.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You don''t actually need to build skills.","index":431,"end_time":1671.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1670.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that is maybe something we can lead with and it may be a good time, especially if companies have people on the bench because then sales becomes.","index":432,"end_time":1683.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1672.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"More important for them.","index":433,"end_time":1684.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1683.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":434,"end_time":1686.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1686.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll definitely have much more social proof and credibility to show with logos that resonate obviously in the German area.","index":435,"end_time":1694.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1687.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so that''s great.","index":436,"end_time":1696.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1695.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With first conversations that you''ve had historically with German prospects, have you found a message that sparked them to sign up for a demo call or something that changed their excitement level on that call?","index":437,"end_time":1710.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1698.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That, that very first call that you have with them?","index":438,"end_time":1713.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1710.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The very first call is mostly about the like the skill and CV part and then it''s mostly around the.","index":439,"end_time":1720.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1715.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we auto customize the cvs.","index":440,"end_time":1724.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1721.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Actually I think the excitement is when they realize that this solution is really custom built for the industry.","index":441,"end_time":1732.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1725.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re not looking at some HR tool, some workforce management tool.","index":442,"end_time":1739.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1733.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They looking.","index":443,"end_time":1741.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1741.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re talking to someone who really deeply understands the industry and has a solution that''s exactly designed for their business and their industries.","index":444,"end_time":1751.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1741.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that''s I think when they, where we somehow get them, when they understand, oh wow, these, these guys, they really know my problems.","index":445,"end_time":1759.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1751.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s actually one of the advantages we have in Germany because it''s much easier to transport debts here.","index":446,"end_time":1764.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1759.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right?","index":447,"end_time":1764.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1764.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":448,"end_time":1767.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1767.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":449,"end_time":1767.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1767.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It sounds like the story is going to be a much bigger piece of this, of why Desi Dolla was created.","index":450,"end_time":1772.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1767.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we, we saw this going on in the industry so we developed a solution for it.","index":451,"end_time":1777.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1773.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s really like purpose built.","index":452,"end_time":1781.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1779.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":453,"end_time":1783.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1782.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":454,"end_time":1784.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1783.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I think we''ve already covered where AI strengthens the story and where, where it could slow it down.","index":455,"end_time":1788.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1784.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Definitely an exciting piece for the sales or HR or, or skills and resource management teams.","index":456,"end_time":1795.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1788.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But definitely can, can be a factor for compliance teams to get over it sounds like.","index":457,"end_time":1800,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1795.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":458,"end_time":1803.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1802.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And you have to be because now everyone is AI, everything is AI and.","index":459,"end_time":1807.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1803.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Everyone puts AI on the front page.","index":460,"end_time":1810,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1807.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we say we''re not, we''re not.","index":461,"end_time":1813.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1810.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Applying AI for AI sake.","index":462,"end_time":1815,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1813.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have, we, we''re just applying it.","index":463,"end_time":1816.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1815,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Where it makes sense.","index":464,"end_time":1817.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1816.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":465,"end_time":1817.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1817.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"To, to we come from a problem.","index":466,"end_time":1820.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1817.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And if AI helps us to solve a problem, we do it.","index":467,"end_time":1823.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1820.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If there''s easier ways to do it, we''ll do that.","index":468,"end_time":1827.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1823.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If you don''t need it.","index":469,"end_time":1828.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1827.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":470,"end_time":1829.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1829.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, I gotcha.","index":471,"end_time":1830.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1829.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then thinking about different ways that they want to interact with the tool.","index":472,"end_time":1834.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1831.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have obviously the option for registering for free for the tool.","index":473,"end_time":1838.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1835.099,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There are other things we can do such as a guided demo using a tool like Story Lane or something like that where they''re not actually interacting in the platform, but they can click around to what you''ve said.","index":474,"end_time":1849.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1838.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like this is the next thing you should click on.","index":475,"end_time":1850.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1849.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And here''s where we explain and here''s a call to action.","index":476,"end_time":1853.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1850.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My recommendation would be to start with both of these and do a variation test.","index":477,"end_time":1859.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1854.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But have you found that the docked region likes to hop right into the tool and not have anything controlling them or have it more guidance?","index":478,"end_time":1868.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1859.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, mostly.","index":479,"end_time":1869.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1868.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Some of the most successful beers they.","index":480,"end_time":1875.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1869.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Start with a demo request, not with the self sign up.","index":481,"end_time":1878.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1875.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then we tell them you can sign up but often they don''t even do that until quite late in the process.","index":482,"end_time":1884.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1878.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Some sign up but the.","index":483,"end_time":1886.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1885.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think the conversion is actually higher when they come for a demo than.","index":484,"end_time":1890.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1886.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"When they sign up.","index":485,"end_time":1891.529,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1890.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":486,"end_time":1892.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1892.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that makes sense because they''re not.","index":487,"end_time":1895.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1892.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re likely not getting all the benefits or understanding all the features of the tool when they just sign up themselves.","index":488,"end_time":1900.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1895.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":489,"end_time":1902.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1902.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And there''s not like it''s a buying committee.","index":490,"end_time":1904.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1902.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s not like in a demo you have typically two or three people.","index":491,"end_time":1909.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1904.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And you can explain that.","index":492,"end_time":1911.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1909.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s just easier.","index":493,"end_time":1914.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1913.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":494,"end_time":1916.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1914.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then for these, do you ever consider taking some information from their team?","index":495,"end_time":1921.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1917.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know like for example the offer that we created for the skill gap analysis in resume creation or profile package was going to take their resumes and build out resources for them.","index":496,"end_time":1933.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1921.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So having all of their CVs placed into a standard format and develop that skills matrices.","index":497,"end_time":1937.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1933.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we feel that that would still be a strong offer where a German or Doc based company could send over here''s our data and some problems we''re dealing with.","index":498,"end_time":1945.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1938.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like what could you spit out to us?","index":499,"end_time":1946.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1945.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I probably not that much because I think people are much more concerned about giving their data out here.","index":500,"end_time":1953.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1948.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So all this data privacy GDPR stuff going on.","index":501,"end_time":1957.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1953.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So.","index":502,"end_time":1959.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1959.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And often they''re not even allowed to do that.","index":503,"end_time":1961.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1959.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They have to get some approval from.","index":504,"end_time":1962.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1961.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Someone to send us data and so.","index":505,"end_time":1965.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1962.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We can.","index":506,"end_time":1969.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1968.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What we do then is we offer them a poc like we''ll import your data but we have first some data processing agreement in place so that everything is covered.","index":507,"end_time":1981.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1969.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I kind of think we should maybe try to get like into a demo first.","index":508,"end_time":1989.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1985.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, but we have to try what works best.","index":509,"end_time":1995.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1992.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I agree with that.","index":510,"end_time":1996.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1995.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think, I think we''ll have a few different call to actions in this all pushing towards them using the platform.","index":511,"end_time":2001.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1996.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think one of which is the simple, you know, register.","index":512,"end_time":2004.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2001.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think that''s later on in the sequence.","index":513,"end_time":2006.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2004.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we push for them to sign up for a demo call.","index":514,"end_time":2009.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2006.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But also I think that it would be beneficial to develop with a tool like Storylane or something similar, just a personalized walkthrough demo where they can get a feel of the tool and then it pushes them to actually go to that Call.","index":515,"end_time":2021.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2010.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":516,"end_time":2023.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2022.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or maybe some video or something.","index":517,"end_time":2024.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2023.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes, in the explainer video that we''re working on as well.","index":518,"end_time":2027.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2024.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then are there any, like, phrases or anything that we need to avoid with the DAC audience?","index":519,"end_time":2034.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2029.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That depends a bit on whom you''re talking to.","index":520,"end_time":2042.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2039.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So since we have very strong labor laws, we have something called labor council or workers council or something.","index":521,"end_time":2049.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2042.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re a bit like an internal union in the company.","index":522,"end_time":2053.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2051.159,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And they don''t like words like benchmark.","index":523,"end_time":2058.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2053.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And stuff, because that sounds like people.","index":524,"end_time":2061.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2058.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"May be laid off.","index":525,"end_time":2062.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2061.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If you talk to the business, they.","index":526,"end_time":2064.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2062.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They all talk about bench management.","index":527,"end_time":2066.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2064.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They know what it is, but often they are not using that word internally.","index":528,"end_time":2070.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2066.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Due to, like, concerns.","index":529,"end_time":2072.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2071.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I think there is nothing.","index":530,"end_time":2075.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2073.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Nothing really.","index":531,"end_time":2078.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2078.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think you could even talk about bench.","index":532,"end_time":2080.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2078.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Then what would be the other term besides bench to use?","index":533,"end_time":2083.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2080.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what they call it internally, they call it, like, active placement.","index":534,"end_time":2088.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2085.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We''re actively trying to place people somewhere, which implies they don''t have anything to.","index":535,"end_time":2094.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2088.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Do at the moment.","index":536,"end_time":2095.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2094.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":537,"end_time":2096.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2095.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, so a little bit more positive.","index":538,"end_time":2098,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2096.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Spit on it.","index":539,"end_time":2098.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2098,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s positive.","index":540,"end_time":2099.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2098.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, you have to be okay.","index":541,"end_time":2101.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2099.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, well, that''s good to know.","index":542,"end_time":2102.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2101.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else similar to that?","index":543,"end_time":2104.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2102.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No problem.","index":544,"end_time":2108.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2107.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"When we do, like, the German translations, we can sort that out if there''s anything that may be problematic.","index":545,"end_time":2117.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2108.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":546,"end_time":2118.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2118.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, that makes sense.","index":547,"end_time":2119.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2118.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hi, Max.","index":548,"end_time":2121.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2120.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hey.","index":549,"end_time":2123.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2122.71,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, so, yeah, I forwarded the meeting.","index":550,"end_time":2125.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2123.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I got invited to this meeting during.","index":551,"end_time":2128.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2125.67,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I forwarded it kind of too late.","index":552,"end_time":2130.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2128.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I. I''m not sure if you met Max already.","index":553,"end_time":2132.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2130.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He''s basically working.","index":554,"end_time":2134.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2132.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":555,"end_time":2136.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2136.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So Max is working with a lot of our customers.","index":556,"end_time":2142.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2136.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He''s leading what we call the customer success team team.","index":557,"end_time":2145.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2142.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So he''s getting all the feedback from the customers and consolidating it.","index":558,"end_time":2150.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2145.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And now we want to move him more into the marketing side because he has a very good understanding of our customers and a technical background.","index":559,"end_time":2159.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2150.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So he''s building some dashboards for usage.","index":560,"end_time":2162.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2159.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Statistics and things like that.","index":561,"end_time":2163.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2162.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I would like Max to work.","index":562,"end_time":2166.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2163.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"With you guys also to understand what you''re doing and how we can provide the information that you need and adopt.","index":563,"end_time":2173.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2166.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"This to the German markets.","index":564,"end_time":2174.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2173.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So.","index":565,"end_time":2175.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2174.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":566,"end_time":2175.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2175.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And this is, you know, Eli, and.","index":567,"end_time":2177.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2175.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"This is Tristan Coin from actually New.","index":568,"end_time":2180.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2177.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Norse or market is on demand.","index":569,"end_time":2182.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2180.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I haven''t figured it out.","index":570,"end_time":2183.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2182.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So.","index":571,"end_time":2185.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2184.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"From all over the place.","index":572,"end_time":2186.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2185.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All over.","index":573,"end_time":2187.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2186.889,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":574,"end_time":2188.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2187.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How you doing, Max?","index":575,"end_time":2188.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2188.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":576,"end_time":2189.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2188.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":577,"end_time":2191.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2190.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''ll be great to.","index":578,"end_time":2192.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2191.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To get some knowledge share there, Max.","index":579,"end_time":2194.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2193.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you have any documents or anything that you can send over, that would be great.","index":580,"end_time":2198.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2194.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Whether it''s dashboards of utilization that Axel''s referring to or even the favorite aspects of the tool that you''re compiling or any pain points that people are experiencing as well.","index":581,"end_time":2207.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2198.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":582,"end_time":2210.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2209.32,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I think, I mean I have a lot of data.","index":583,"end_time":2212.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2210.52,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I think it makes sense to.","index":584,"end_time":2215.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2213.64,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Know better about what exactly you need and what could help you and what is just, I don''t know, additional information which just takes time and it''s not helpful.","index":585,"end_time":2231.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2220.28,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":586,"end_time":2232.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2231.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what I will say is I''ll never turn down information or data to utilize what we''re trying to do here.","index":587,"end_time":2238.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2232.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure if Axel and Eli have caught you up.","index":588,"end_time":2240.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2238.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had marketing going on in the U.S. axel mentioned that there was just kind of some, some pain points of stretching across different time zones and handling things coming in through that flow.","index":589,"end_time":2251.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2241.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also there''s some low hanging fruit in Germany that we can tap into.","index":590,"end_time":2254.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2251.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re looking at different aspects of our US campaigns that we can extract that are still relevant to the German market and what we need to build net new.","index":591,"end_time":2262.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2255.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so any data or extra information or understanding of the German market or the dock region is going to be super beneficial here.","index":592,"end_time":2270.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2262.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean the other way around is the same by the way.","index":593,"end_time":2276.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2272.9,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So for me, understanding what you''re doing on the US market usually is extremely helpful to understand and yeah, then I mean, I think from that point on things get clearer and easier anyways.","index":594,"end_time":2293.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2276.02,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I think so.","index":595,"end_time":2294.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2293.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"My, my kind of reasoning is why I think it makes sense to, to still hire a US company for the German market, which may sound a bit strange in the first place, is that you are very specialized on our kind of niche like SaaS mid small SaaS companies B2B that don''t have their own marketing.","index":596,"end_time":2321.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2294.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I think the German market is just too small for any marketing agency to have that kind of narrow focus because there''s not a lot of SRS companies B2B our size doing that kind of stuff.","index":597,"end_time":2336.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2324.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I think this experience will probably.","index":598,"end_time":2339.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2336.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Be kind of hard to find here.","index":599,"end_time":2341.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2339.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And most of the all the marketing.","index":600,"end_time":2344.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2342.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Tech and all that stuff is coming.","index":601,"end_time":2345.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2344.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"From the US anyway.","index":602,"end_time":2346.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2345.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So for us it''s really interesting to learn that and see how can we apply that here and use it for our market.","index":603,"end_time":2354.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2346.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":604,"end_time":2356.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2355.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Max, I can share any plan, documents and everything with you as well from what we did for the US campaigns.","index":605,"end_time":2362.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2357.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":606,"end_time":2364.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2363.28,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"All right.","index":607,"end_time":2366.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2366,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then I want to just also have a conversation around establishing success.","index":608,"end_time":2369.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2366.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, when we''re thinking hey, this, this campaign in Germany or this campaign in the docs region is working, what does that Exactly.","index":609,"end_time":2377.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2370.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mean in the first 90 days, how many, you know, are we looking at demo calls?","index":610,"end_time":2383.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2377.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we looking at close sales?","index":611,"end_time":2385.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2383.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, what are we looking at here?","index":612,"end_time":2386.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2385.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s actually probably easier for us to say because we.","index":613,"end_time":2389.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2386.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have some statistics on how many demos we get, like, per month or so now, and we can see how it goes up with the US we had absolutely no experience.","index":614,"end_time":2397.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2389.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We couldn''t even say campaign doesn''t work or the product doesn''t work for the market or whatever.","index":615,"end_time":2403.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2397.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So here I would really look at.","index":616,"end_time":2407.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2404.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The demos probably as the indicator because that''s.","index":617,"end_time":2411.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2407.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s mostly the indicator we use.","index":618,"end_time":2413.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2411.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":619,"end_time":2414.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2414.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll have to check back into our notes.","index":620,"end_time":2417.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2414.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I believe you were at two demos a week.","index":621,"end_time":2420.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2417.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not.","index":622,"end_time":2422.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2422.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No, probably.","index":623,"end_time":2423.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2423.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Actually, that''s why we would need Bettina.","index":624,"end_time":2426.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2424.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because she''s doing the demos.","index":625,"end_time":2427.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2426.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I would say it''s less probably Mark.","index":626,"end_time":2430.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2427.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So she could join definitely.","index":627,"end_time":2432.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2430.27,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"But at least from what I know, it''s.","index":628,"end_time":2435.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2432.67,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I mean, I would say one a week makes sense.","index":629,"end_time":2438.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2435.43,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":630,"end_time":2438.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2438.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That is probably more.","index":631,"end_time":2439.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2438.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"On average, but.","index":632,"end_time":2442.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2441.63,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":633,"end_time":2444.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2443.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":634,"end_time":2444.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2444.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That sounds about right.","index":635,"end_time":2445.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2444.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":636,"end_time":2446.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2445.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":637,"end_time":2447.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2447.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":638,"end_time":2448.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2447.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There should be some lowering fruits because I think the market is not that small.","index":639,"end_time":2452.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2448.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It is smaller in the US for sure.","index":640,"end_time":2457.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2454.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that thing, the market is very connected to each other.","index":641,"end_time":2466.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2460.61,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Most of our clients are.","index":642,"end_time":2467.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2466.53,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"At least they have some sort of relation.","index":643,"end_time":2471.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2468.69,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And there are way more, I think, which are connected.","index":644,"end_time":2474.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2471.73,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Mm.","index":645,"end_time":2475.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2475.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s actually why Switzerland.","index":646,"end_time":2477.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2475.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sometimes I feel easier for us because that is so much smaller.","index":647,"end_time":2480.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2477.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They all know each other.","index":648,"end_time":2482.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2480.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Every.","index":649,"end_time":2482.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2482.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Every Swiss company we''re talking to knows at least two or three or four clients.","index":650,"end_time":2486.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2482.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And have you tried any, like, referral benefit?","index":651,"end_time":2491.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2488.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if it''s not.","index":652,"end_time":2492.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2492.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No, we get referrals, but they just.","index":653,"end_time":2494.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2492.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Do that, like, just to be a good person.","index":654,"end_time":2497.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2494.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but we have not really tried.","index":655,"end_time":2499.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2497.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"To establish a program for that.","index":656,"end_time":2503.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2499.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Not really sure that would work in.","index":657,"end_time":2506.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2503.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"A B2B context with a buying committee.","index":658,"end_time":2509.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2506.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But it''s something we could definitely try.","index":659,"end_time":2511.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2509.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because we have a lot of happy customers here.","index":660,"end_time":2513.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2511.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":661,"end_time":2514.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2514.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":662,"end_time":2516.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2516.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So anything you have on that, any.","index":663,"end_time":2518.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2516.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Ideas, we''re happy to just try, I would say.","index":664,"end_time":2522.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2518.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think that''s something that we can definitely tap into.","index":665,"end_time":2525.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2523.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then like I mentioned earlier, we''ll need to work with you guys in Microsoft Dynamics to establish and pull out the list.","index":666,"end_time":2532.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2526.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"List of clothes lost that we can reach out to as well.","index":667,"end_time":2535.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2532.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And any information we have to personalize some data to them.","index":668,"end_time":2537.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2535.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we had a conversation, you know, X months ago, X years ago, you were dealing with this.","index":669,"end_time":2543.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2537.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wanted to check back in, you know, want to make sure that it''s personalized to their experience with Desi Dalo.","index":670,"end_time":2549.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2544.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we also, where we get a lot of referrals is from people that moved to one of our customers to another company because there''s some fluctuation and a lot of our.","index":671,"end_time":2562.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2550.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Since we have a very narrow target group, there''s people going to another company and then they refer us and say, hey, that''s what I worked with in the last company.","index":672,"end_time":2572.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2562.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And you should just look at it and.","index":673,"end_time":2574.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2572.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I''m not sure how, how we can.","index":674,"end_time":2577.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2574.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If there''s a way to directly target these people.","index":675,"end_time":2580.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2577.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, what we could do is if you have a list of those names, we could enrich them to find their current place of employment.","index":676,"end_time":2587.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2580.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if that''s still a fit in the industry, then we could develop a personalized campaign for them as well.","index":677,"end_time":2593.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2587.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s probably not by name because we don''t know really who that is often, but by company.","index":678,"end_time":2598.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2594.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we could probably go if someone from like in LinkedIn, you have like the past company and the current company.","index":679,"end_time":2605.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2599.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure if you can use.","index":680,"end_time":2606.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2605.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That for targeting, but yeah, I''ll need.","index":681,"end_time":2610.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2606.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"To do some research into that.","index":682,"end_time":2611.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2610.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I mean, Axel, it''s mainly about our contact people.","index":683,"end_time":2614.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2612.1,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":684,"end_time":2615.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2614.81,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Because I think the usual employee is the usual.","index":685,"end_time":2620.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2615.37,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Usual employee, really, that.","index":686,"end_time":2622.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2620.65,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Does he or she benefit from us?","index":687,"end_time":2626.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2623.37,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, this guy, the guy that Eli is talking to currently in, in Mexico even, he''s from Diddycon.","index":688,"end_time":2632.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2626.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We never heard of him at Diddycon.","index":689,"end_time":2634.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2632.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He knows Susan Zondhag and those guys and he, he, he, he knew us and he moved to actually a company in Mexico and he''s trying to bring us in there.","index":690,"end_time":2646.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2634.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And there''s, there''s several.","index":691,"end_time":2648.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2646.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like we had a demo with special.","index":692,"end_time":2649.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2648.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s a big company.","index":693,"end_time":2650.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2649.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They had someone from Computer center who came and I don''t know who that is.","index":694,"end_time":2653.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2650.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I have no idea.","index":695,"end_time":2654.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2653.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":696,"end_time":2655.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2654.58,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Didn''t think that would be a thing, to be honest.","index":697,"end_time":2658.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2655.7,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I have to imagine it''s just happening more and more across industries now of people moving jobs and quicker timelines.","index":698,"end_time":2668.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2662.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":699,"end_time":2670.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2669.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, so, you know, while we have the US.desidalo mini website that we had built for the US campaign, obviously that''s not relevant for the docked region.","index":700,"end_time":2680.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2670.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I''m planning and just wanted to run this across, you know, you guys is just building new pages and assets on the main Desi dollar website for these campaigns.","index":701,"end_time":2689.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2680.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess that''s, that''s makes sense.","index":702,"end_time":2691.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2689.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And we can just link them there or have them as a Standalone page.","index":703,"end_time":2695.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2691.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":704,"end_time":2696.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2695.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s no timeline on this, but we''ve been talking about it internally.","index":705,"end_time":2700.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2696.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There are some changes coming to GDPR compliance, one of which is a large decision happening on browser cookie data.","index":706,"end_time":2708.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2700.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what they''re leaning towards is removing consent banners from websites entirely and just having it all based in your browser so that you make that decision before you go to any website.","index":707,"end_time":2719.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2708.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess a lot of people have plugins for that already stuff.","index":708,"end_time":2724.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2720.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re just finding it''s been a pain point.","index":709,"end_time":2728.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2725.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think they''re trying to alleviate that with just making one decision in your browser.","index":710,"end_time":2732.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2728.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think the tracking in the.","index":711,"end_time":2734.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2733.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Browser will become increasingly hard because of all this GDPR stuff.","index":712,"end_time":2739.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2734.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":713,"end_time":2740.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2740.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And honestly, we feel that the US is moving in that direction as well.","index":714,"end_time":2743.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2740.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve had the year 2028 in my head as far as the research I''ve done for, you know, I mean, states like California are already moving towards a lot of privacy, but I think the rest of the US will catch up in the next few years.","index":715,"end_time":2755.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2744.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, great.","index":716,"end_time":2758.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2756.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":717,"end_time":2759.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2759.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to establish also what next steps look like.","index":718,"end_time":2762.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2759.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so from here, first of all, thank you for the conversation, but we''re going to go through and develop a new roadmap and plan document that will outline all of our goals.","index":719,"end_time":2773.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2762.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The offer, the messaging that we''re going to tap into, the parameters for the list that we''re going to build.","index":720,"end_time":2778.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2773.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll be sharing all those assets with you guys.","index":721,"end_time":2781.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2778.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One, to check our translations, of course, but two, also to just make sure that we''re speak, we''re getting in front of the right people and that we''re building new assets for these things.","index":722,"end_time":2792.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2781.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that we''re working on the explainer video, so it sounds like maybe we should change that script to German.","index":723,"end_time":2797.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2793.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What do you think about that, Axel?","index":724,"end_time":2799.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2798.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think I would have an English and German version for that.","index":725,"end_time":2802.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2799.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"For like the main assets, I would.","index":726,"end_time":2804.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2802.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Still want to have them in English.","index":727,"end_time":2805.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2804.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And German because that is one of the like disadvantages in Europe is that many different languages and typically companies do.","index":728,"end_time":2814.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2805.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"English and their native language.","index":729,"end_time":2816.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2814.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":730,"end_time":2816.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2816.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like we have, we have customer in Denmark, hopefully soon Netherlands.","index":731,"end_time":2822.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2816.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They.","index":732,"end_time":2822.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2822.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You would not build a Danish or another Dutch page.","index":733,"end_time":2825.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2822.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You just.","index":734,"end_time":2825.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2825.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They will just look at the English one.","index":735,"end_time":2827.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2825.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So.","index":736,"end_time":2828.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2828.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I know Eli had mentioned also maybe getting some new sales materials or slide decks or anything like that.","index":737,"end_time":2834.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2828.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Has there been anything raised from teams working with German prospects or prospects in the docks region for any assets that they need there?","index":738,"end_time":2841.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2834.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not.","index":739,"end_time":2844.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2844.099,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean, I think we could use that to send out follow up.","index":740,"end_time":2847.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2844.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But we don''t have it really at the moment.","index":741,"end_time":2850.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2847.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s all very manual or whole process is very manual.","index":742,"end_time":2853.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2850.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I would.","index":743,"end_time":2854.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2853.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So yeah, it could make sense to.","index":744,"end_time":2856.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2854.47,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Well, I don''t know because we were.","index":745,"end_time":2859.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2857.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Making them in English and translating to German.","index":746,"end_time":2861.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2859.59,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"But the success stories are all coming from Germany.","index":747,"end_time":2866.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2861.91,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right.","index":748,"end_time":2866.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2866.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So, yeah.","index":749,"end_time":2867.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2866.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or Switzerland.","index":750,"end_time":2868.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2867.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Germany or Switzerland, yeah.","index":751,"end_time":2869.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2868.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So.","index":752,"end_time":2871.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2871.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think so Max is probably the one who knows best.","index":753,"end_time":2876.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2874.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think there is some kind of automation around the sign up.","index":754,"end_time":2879.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2876.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"When they sign up, they you create a lead or something in the CRM and they are added to the mailing list or there''s some automation.","index":755,"end_time":2886.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2879.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I think it''s kind of basic what we''re doing there.","index":756,"end_time":2888.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2886.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":757,"end_time":2890.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2890.36,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know whether we already send out an email automatically or whether that''s manual still.","index":758,"end_time":2896.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2890.8,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"But I mean, I don''t know whether you talked about it before, but the amount of new registrations is not that big.","index":759,"end_time":2903.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2896.2,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So it''s not really.","index":760,"end_time":2904.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2903.64,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Right now it''s more time consuming to build some automation process here than just doing it manually because it''s like, I''d say we have like two to three new registrations a week.","index":761,"end_time":2917.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2905.08,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"But these are not all just new clients, so.","index":762,"end_time":2922.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2918.09,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"And also there are some clients like some really small companies, like five people or something and we cannot get any money from that.","index":763,"end_time":2929.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2922.01,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So.","index":764,"end_time":2931.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2931.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, at least from my last point of what I know is that there was no sense to fully automate that.","index":765,"end_time":2943.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2932.41,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":766,"end_time":2946.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2945.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, well we''ll see if we can increase those numbers and therefore give reason for automation to be created.","index":767,"end_time":2951.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2946.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s the goal, I would say.","index":768,"end_time":2953.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2951.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":769,"end_time":2954.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2953.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":770,"end_time":2954.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2954.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":771,"end_time":2956.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2955.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So with our Friday meeting, what we''ll have prepared for then is the updated roadmap document to go through and that''ll outline the, the approach that we''re taking with the docked region and then we can build all the assets from there if we''re all aligned and then get this campaign live.","index":772,"end_time":2972.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2956.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you could share Bettina''s contact information and we can warm up some emails.","index":773,"end_time":2977.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2972.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think she''s in the chat.","index":774,"end_time":2978.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2977.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think she''s in the New Norse chat.","index":775,"end_time":2980.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2978.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think she is as well.","index":776,"end_time":2981.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2980.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think I''ve communicated with her.","index":777,"end_time":2983.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2981.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not by the way.","index":778,"end_time":2984.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2983.07,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I can add you to that.","index":779,"end_time":2986.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2984.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, so that would be my next point.","index":780,"end_time":2989.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2986.31,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"So like I have about a million questions.","index":781,"end_time":2992.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2990.15,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know whether that makes sense to have another talk until Friday.","index":782,"end_time":2996.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2992.59,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, we can have a talk or you can chat.","index":783,"end_time":2999.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2997.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean to you as well, actually.","index":784,"end_time":3002.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2999.55,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"But I meant, I meant the colleagues.","index":785,"end_time":3004.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3002.31,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"From America, so includes all chat History.","index":786,"end_time":3009.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3004.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So now you''re in that chat.","index":787,"end_time":3011.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3010.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":788,"end_time":3012.669,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3012.189,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Worked.","index":789,"end_time":3013.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3012.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":790,"end_time":3015.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3015.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And if I''m not sure what sources you''re using for like the ads, if it''s Figma or something.","index":791,"end_time":3020.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3015.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But you can also send us the sources and we can do the translations.","index":792,"end_time":3023.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3020.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s maybe easier.","index":793,"end_time":3025.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3023.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can talk through that as well.","index":794,"end_time":3027.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3025.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I wanted to see with our Friday meeting, I do have a conflict.","index":795,"end_time":3030.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3028.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to see if you''re available either 30 minutes or earlier or an hour later than this, get current schedule.","index":796,"end_time":3038.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3030.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"30 minutes earlier, it''s fine.","index":797,"end_time":3043.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3041.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":798,"end_time":3044.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3044.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''ll make that adjustment.","index":799,"end_time":3045.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3044.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also don''t have that Friday meeting.","index":800,"end_time":3047.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3045.87,"speaker_name":"Maximilian Rabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I can forward that to you also.","index":801,"end_time":3049.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3048.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or can you just add a max?","index":802,"end_time":3051.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3049.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think you send it, right?","index":803,"end_time":3053.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3051.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":804,"end_time":3053.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3053.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I just added Marks to the chat, so you should see his email there.","index":805,"end_time":3058.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3053.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is it R A B E L E R Data assessment?","index":806,"end_time":3069.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3066.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":807,"end_time":3070.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3070.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":808,"end_time":3072.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3072.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I will add you now.","index":809,"end_time":3073.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3072.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And is there anyone else that we want included on that call?","index":810,"end_time":3075.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3073.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, bet you know, mice.","index":811,"end_time":3077.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3075.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s M eiss A data assessment should also be there in the.","index":812,"end_time":3083.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3077.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I can send you that.","index":813,"end_time":3086.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3084.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You found her?","index":814,"end_time":3090.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3089.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":815,"end_time":3091.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3091.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":816,"end_time":3096.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3096.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"M e I s s@dataassessment.com.","index":817,"end_time":3099.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3096.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":818,"end_time":3100.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3100.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":819,"end_time":3101.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3101.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":820,"end_time":3106.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3106.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well, we will work on that updated roadmap document and have that ready to go through on Friday.","index":821,"end_time":3110.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3106.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then from there we''ll have.","index":822,"end_time":3111.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3110.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll begin crafting assets and sending those over for translation.","index":823,"end_time":3116.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3112.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":824,"end_time":3117.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3117.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":825,"end_time":3118.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3118.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then wanted to touch on just one question.","index":826,"end_time":3121.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3119.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You had mentioned that you thought we had paused ads.","index":827,"end_time":3123.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3121.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We talked about pausing them from the 24th through the 1st and keeping the US campaign going while we were building this German campaign.","index":828,"end_time":3131.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3123.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would you like us to pause the US Ads?","index":829,"end_time":3133.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3131.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think.","index":830,"end_time":3134.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3133.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":831,"end_time":3134.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3134.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s like.","index":832,"end_time":3136.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3134.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Eli, did you ever get any feedback from any of the people that.","index":833,"end_time":3139.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3136.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No, I haven''t yet.","index":834,"end_time":3141.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3140.04,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"But again, it''s been like a week or two weeks.","index":835,"end_time":3144.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3141.32,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right.","index":836,"end_time":3144.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3144.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also, the new sign up, the last two look really not in the target group, like some web developer from Google Apps or something.","index":837,"end_time":3152.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3144.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not really sure how they.","index":838,"end_time":3155,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3152.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Why don''t we give it the rest of the week if any good leads come in?","index":839,"end_time":3159.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3155.48,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I don''t know how much the budget.","index":840,"end_time":3160.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3159.82,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Is on it, but what''s the cost for that?","index":841,"end_time":3163.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3160.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":842,"end_time":3163.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3163.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Our monthly budget is set at $3,500.","index":843,"end_time":3166.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3164.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, 3,000 on LinkedIn and 500 on AdRoll.","index":844,"end_time":3169.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3167.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s give it like 10 more days.","index":845,"end_time":3171.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3169.98,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"No, I don''t.","index":846,"end_time":3173.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3171.42,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I don''t think honestly that we''re going to get any good leads from that if we haven''t got any so far.","index":847,"end_time":3179.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3173.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But the new ad has only been up for like a week.","index":848,"end_time":3184.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3180.3,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Colin.","index":849,"end_time":3184.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3184.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":850,"end_time":3185.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3184.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No, no.","index":851,"end_time":3185.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3185.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is it like three weeks now or how long is it the new one?","index":852,"end_time":3188.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3185.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"This new sequence will create a new variations that launched last week, but the, the new registration was launched a week or two before that.","index":853,"end_time":3196.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3189.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s pretty recent, I think.","index":854,"end_time":3199.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3197.98,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I mean, I''m on, I''m in favor of giving it till we can leave.","index":855,"end_time":3204.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3201.02,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"It running to Friday.","index":856,"end_time":3205.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3204.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We''ll probably switch it up that, because then it''s holiday season anyway and then.","index":857,"end_time":3209.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3205.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, and that kind of lines up with our initial plan anyway.","index":858,"end_time":3211.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3209.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":859,"end_time":3213.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3211.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, like the 20th, whatever, 21st.","index":860,"end_time":3215.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3213.14,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Okay.","index":861,"end_time":3215.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3215.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":862,"end_time":3217.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3216.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, well, thank you guys very much.","index":863,"end_time":3219.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3217.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Appreciate your time and look forward to talking on Friday.","index":864,"end_time":3222.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3219.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":865,"end_time":3223.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3223.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, see you later.","index":866,"end_time":3225.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3223.85,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"}],"dateString":"2025-12-16T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85198351976?pwd=An5IJMrn4xPkTXebaQ27SXIxbZoEeq.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de,voelker@data-assessment.com,bebinger@decidalo.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de","voelker@data-assessment.com","bebinger@decidalo.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC9RJFYZRTREGANSE77G0GHF","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Aligned on expanding German outreach; Bettina will serve as local face for email campaigns.","Confirmed mid to large IT consultancies remain the main German target; SAP consultancies identified as key.","Decided to emphasize problem-solving messaging and avoid aggressive US-style fear tactics.","Identified AI-supported CV customization and reskilling features as strong purchase motivators.","Agreed demo requests outperform self-serve signups; guided walkthroughs and explainer videos planned."],"highlights":[{"quote":"So I think in general it is somehow an advantage if you sell to a German company as a German company.","speaker":"Axel Völker"},{"quote":"Mostly they come to us for really the CV management, skills management, like the sales support stuff.","speaker":"Axel Völker"},{"quote":"We’re looking at different aspects of our US campaigns that we can extract that are still relevant to the German market.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["launch","messaging","AI","delivery","targeting"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-16T20:10:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **German Market Targeting and Messaging**\n\nThe German market shares core customers and pain points with the US but requires tailored messaging and local language adaptations.\n\n- **The core target remains mid to large IT consulting companies, focusing on skills and resource management, with the same pain points as the US market** according to **Axel Völker** (03:50)\n    - German clients prefer the term \"CV\" instead of \"resume,\" and value **data privacy and compliance** more due to local legislation.\n    - Local language support and German-based communication are advantages, as companies prefer dealing with someone familiar with their legal and cultural context.\n    - The selling approach should be less aggressive than in the US, avoiding fear-based tactics and overselling, as Germans tend to be skeptical of hard sell.\n    - Messaging should resonate with pain points like cost reduction, utilization, and bench management but remain straightforward and respectful.\n\n- **Buying decisions often involve a committee rather than a single person, typically including operations or internal sales leads, while resource managers act as primary users but rarely decision-makers** (06:59)\n    - Economic uncertainty, especially in industries like automotive, makes bench utilization and cost-saving critical messages.\n    - Time zone differences with the US and Japan create operational challenges, emphasizing the need for localized support.\n    - The campaign will focus on Germany and the wider DACH region, with Switzerland showing strong engagement due to less regulation and more spending power.\n\n- **Outreach should come from a German personality, such as Bettina, to improve response rates and local relevance** (13:43)\n    - Email and LinkedIn profiles will be adapted to German language and context.\n    - References and social proof from the German market will be leveraged to build credibility.\n    - Personalized messaging will avoid phrases like \"bench\" internally, opting for more positive terms such as \"active placement\" to respect labor council sensitivities.\n\n## **Sales Cycle and Deal Acceleration**\n\nSales velocity depends heavily on prospect readiness, with demos preferred over self-service signups.\n\n- **Sales cycles in Germany range from three months to two years, mirroring US experience; deals progress faster when prospects have an internal project and budget for the tool** (17:24)\n    - Active searchers for skill and CV management tools move faster, while casual investigators stall without internal alignment.\n    - Demo requests convert better than free registrations, as buying committees benefit from guided group presentations.\n    - Early messaging leads with sales skills and CV management, followed by resource utilization and skill building phases to align with customer priorities.\n\n- **AI is a double-edged sword: companies claim AI interest but legal and compliance teams raise concerns about data usage and bias, creating a barrier to sales** (19:33)\n    - AI messaging should be positioned carefully, focusing on practical problem-solving rather than AI for its own sake.\n    - The uncertain future of AI in consulting, especially with EU regulations, creates reluctance but also opportunity for positioning Desi Dollo as a tool for hybrid teams and reskilling.\n    - Labor market regulations in Germany make layoffs expensive, increasing demand for skills gap analysis and reskilling tools, which Desi Dollo can address.\n\n- **Key product features that spur interest include automated CV customization and skill matching, which speed up the resource allocation process and reduce administrative effort** (18:43)\n    - These features highlight the platform’s industry-specific design, which prospects recognize as a major advantage over generic HR tools.\n\n## **Campaign Setup and Asset Development**\n\nA localized campaign with German language assets and personalized outreach is planned, with clear next steps for execution.\n\n- **The campaign will build new pages and assets on the main Desi Dollo website tailored to the DACH region, avoiding US-specific micro-sites** (44:49)\n    - German and English versions of explainer videos and sales materials will be created, reflecting the multilingual nature of European markets.\n    - Translations will be coordinated with local team members to ensure cultural and linguistic accuracy.\n\n- **Multiple call-to-actions will be tested, prioritizing demo signups over free registrations to engage buying committees more effectively** (33:44)\n    - Tools like Storylane will be used to create guided demo walkthroughs, augmenting live demos and improving understanding.\n    - Data privacy concerns limit willingness to share CV data upfront, so proof of concept agreements with data processing clauses will be necessary for demos involving client data.\n\n- **Automation of lead nurturing remains minimal due to low current registration volumes (~2-3 weekly), but increased campaign activity aims to justify future automation** (48:10)\n    - Current manual processes are sufficient but scalable automation will be developed if lead volume grows.\n\n## **Metrics, Goals, and Success Criteria**\n\nDemo calls are the primary early success metric, with modest volume expectations reflecting market size and campaign stage.\n\n- **Current demo call volume in the DACH region averages around one per week, serving as the main indicator of campaign health** (40:22)\n    - Increasing demo volume will signal market traction and justify investment in automation and expanded outreach.\n    - The connected nature of the market, especially in Switzerland, presents opportunities for referral growth though no formal program yet exists.\n\n- **Close lost and referral data will be leveraged to personalize outreach and identify warm leads, including targeting contacts who have moved companies within the sector** (42:03)\n    - Enrichment of contact data to track employment changes is planned to maintain engagement with prospects who switch firms.\n    - LinkedIn’s company and past company data may support targeting but requires further research.\n\n## **Process Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nCross-team collaboration and clear communication channels will support rapid campaign development and execution.\n\n- **Maximilian Rabeler will bridge customer success insights and marketing needs, providing usage dashboards and customer feedback to optimize messaging** (36:30)\n    - He will also coordinate with US marketing to adapt successful tactics for the German market.\n    - Translation support will be facilitated by sharing source files (e.g., Figma), enabling efficient adaptation of creative assets.\n\n- **A detailed roadmap and plan document outlining goals, messaging, list parameters, and offers will be delivered ahead of the next meeting on Friday, with a schedule adjustment agreed** (49:15)\n    - Bettina’s contact details will be shared to warm up email domains and LinkedIn profiles for outreach.\n    - The team agreed to pause US ads only after current campaigns run through the holiday season, maintaining momentum while building the German campaign.\n\n- **GDPR compliance changes, particularly around cookie consent, will impact tracking and require adaptation in marketing approaches, with browser-level consent expected to simplify future compliance** (45:20)\n    - The team will monitor these regulatory shifts to stay ahead in privacy-sensitive markets.\n\n## **Strategic Positioning and Market Outlook**\n\nDesi Dollo aims to leverage its industry specialization and local presence to differentiate in a competitive and evolving market.\n\n- **The company’s niche focus on mid-sized B2B SaaS companies and deep knowledge of consulting industry pain points is a competitive advantage in Germany** (38:13)\n    - US marketing expertise will inform German campaigns but must be adapted for local market size and cultural nuances.\n    - Positioning as a mid-sized German company offering local support appeals to prospects wary of large US vendors and difficult time zones.\n\n- **The uncertain impact of AI on consulting labor dynamics drives customer hesitancy but also presents an opening for Desi Dollo to help companies prepare through skills management and reskilling tools** (25:49)\n    - Messaging will balance AI opportunity with compliance concerns, focusing on practical productivity gains and future readiness.\n    - The company recognizes the need to evolve its story around AI’s role in hybrid teams and workforce transformation.\n\n- **Cultural sensitivities around labor terms and sales approaches necessitate a respectful, consultative selling style rather than aggressive tactics** (34:00)\n    - Internal labor councils and regulations shape acceptable language and influence buying behaviors.\n    - The team plans to leverage positive framing and local terminology to build trust and reduce resistance.","outline":null,"keywords":["German market","Resource management","AI adoption","DACH region","Sales demos","Compliance/GDPR"],"overview":"- **German Market Focus:** Target mid to large IT consulting firms; adapt messaging to local language and compliance needs.  \n- **Committee Buying Decisions:** Focus on group dynamics; highlight cost-saving messages during economic uncertainty in key industries.  \n- **Localized Outreach:** Use a German persona for outreach to improve engagement; personalize messages avoiding sensitive terms.  \n- **Sales Cycle Insights:** Expect three-month to two-year sales cycles; demos are preferred for unified committee presentations.  \n- **Demo Success Metric:** Average one demo per week; increasing volume signals market traction and justifies automation investment.  \n- **Collaboration and Planning:** Maximize cross-team communication; deliver detailed roadmap ahead of Friday’s meeting for execution clarity.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDevelop and share updated Germany/DACH campaign roadmap document with German team for feedback and translation review (46:30)\nWarm up email domains and LinkedIn outreach profiles using Bettina’s account for German market outreach (14:15)\nResearch LinkedIn targeting possibilities based on past company/current company transitions to leverage referrals from personnel movements (43:20)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nProvide Bettina’s and Meiss’s contact info to Colin; add Max to New Norse chat to include him in ongoing communications (49:30)\n\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nPrepare and share relevant usage data, pain points, dashboards to support marketing asset tailoring once the exact needs are clarified (36:30)\nFacilitate ongoing communication with US marketing team to exchange insights on target markets and optimize campaign approach collaboratively (37:15)\n\n**Marketing team**\nPrepare bilingual (English/German) explainer videos and web pages to support German and broader DACH marketing efforts (46:40)\nTemporarily continue US ad campaigns for 10 more days, then pause post holiday season to focus on German campaigns (52:00)\nConsider testing campaign messaging that emphasizes utilization, active placement, sales skills to resonate with current German pain points and compliance needs (00:00)\n\n**Colin and Axel**\nCollaborate to create personalized re-engagement campaigns targeting previous lost deals with tailored messaging referencing past interactions (42:00)\n\n**Colin Costigan/Axel Völker**\nCoordinate next meeting 30 minutes earlier on Friday to review roadmap and next steps (50:40)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"47a428d3-af7f-4155-a73c-bde939377b35","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
