INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: PTO Exchange Weekly',
  '## **Client Onboarding Video Strategy**

The team agreed to produce short, standardized demo videos for each new client to improve onboarding clarity and customization.

- **Josh Reinhard proposed creating 30 to 45-second demo videos with a consistent 10-second intro for each client, targeting 30 to 40 new clients next year** to showcase their specific PTO Exchange setup (11:55)  
    - Colin Costigan confirmed the team can turn these videos around within the same week of recording  
    - The intro will feature a fixed message with client branding, while the demo will reflect the client’s actual platform interface  
    - Captions will be added to support hearing-impaired users, maintaining accessibility standards  
    - This approach balances personalized demos without the complexity of full interactive tutorials, per Colin’s suggestion referencing tools like Storylane  

- **Branding consistency will follow past demo video styles, featuring PTO Exchange branding with client-specific logos embedded in the demo section** (15:04)  
    - Josh clarified the client logo will appear as it does on their actual dashboard interface, enhancing relatability for employees  
    - Colin emphasized reusing the existing video structure and branding assets to streamline production  
    - This approach ensures clear brand identity while tailoring demos to client environments  

## **Marketing Content and Homepage Development**

Progress continues on marketing collateral and website updates, with a focus on content readiness and homepage launch dependencies.

- **Colin updated that new ad creative is in development for the benchmark report, along with copywriting for HR Leaders, Employee Persona, and Industry pages, with Sam Lieberman assigned review responsibilities** (17:19)  
    - This content pipeline supports upcoming marketing campaigns and targeted messaging segments  
    - The homepage development is on hold pending FAQ approval to avoid premature exposure of incomplete sections  
    - Once FAQs are finalized, the team will hide or reveal sections dynamically based on content readiness, maintaining UX quality  
    - Sam confirmed this phased approach aligns with current development priorities  

## **Automation Stability and Scheduling Coordination**

Current automation systems are stable, and scheduling tools are being optimized to improve client engagement workflows.

- **Automation processes are running smoothly with no reported issues from the team, confirming operational stability** (17:57)  
    - This reliability reduces risk of service disruption and supports scaling plans  
    - Scheduling integration is being refined with plans to switch from individual Calendly links to a shared booking calendar for better client experience  
    - Sam will create the shared calendar within the next few days, and Josh will update links accordingly to streamline appointment setting  
    - This change aims to improve booking efficiency and resource management  

## **Deliverables and Timeline Expectations**

The team reinforced delivery timelines for key documents and videos to maintain project momentum.

- **Colin committed to delivering the updated FAQ document and marketing deck within the current week to support content and homepage progress** (23:42)  
    - Josh acknowledged the timeline and will prioritize reviewing the FAQs promptly to avoid bottlenecks  
    - Josh will record the client demo video today to enable the marketing team’s quick turnaround  
    - This tight schedule reflects the team’s goal to accelerate onboarding and marketing readiness for Q1  
    - Clear communication of deadlines ensures alignment across teams and reduces delays  

## **Market Positioning and Strategic Thought**

While casual in tone, the discussion revealed strategic intent to balance brand consistency with client-specific customization to improve client experience.

- **Colin emphasized a “happy medium” approach that personalizes client demos without adding complexity, showing a pragmatic balancing of customization and scalability** (14:05)  
    - The use of existing branding frameworks demonstrates a focus on maintaining a coherent brand image  
    - Consideration of emerging tools like Storylane indicates openness to future enhancement without immediate commitment  
    - The team’s approach reflects a strategic mindset prioritizing efficiency and client clarity to support growth targets  
    - This philosophy supports differentiation by delivering tailored yet consistent client engagement materials',
  '2025-12-15 20:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Record onboarding demo video (1.5 minutes) for Salmon Health by end of the week (13:37)","completed":false},{"text":"Review FAQs document sent by Colin (16:58)","completed":false},{"text":"Edit and brand Josh''s recorded demo videos with consistent PTO Exchange branding and add captions (16:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue development of ad creative and copy for HR Leader, Employee Persona, and industry pages; send copy to Sam for review (17:19)","completed":false},{"text":"Deliver the planned deck by the end of the week (23:42)","completed":false},{"text":"Create shared Calendly booking calendar and provide link to Colin for update (17:11)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
