-- Meeting: Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync (2025-12-15 16:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '059db008-bde9-43e2-b5ea-2d8080194a92',
    '2025-12-15 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBZJBTHM6A6558804QHRP3S3',
    'Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync',
    '{"victor garcia","Colin Costigan","Tristan Pelligrino","Colin Costigan","christinazanca","Jane"}'::text[],
    2771,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1',
    '{"id":"01KBZJBTHM6A6558804QHRP3S3","title":"Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Brand Asset Development and Design Strategy**\n\nThe team finalized the delivery of comprehensive brand assets including editable templates for presentations, emails, business cards, letterheads, and social media, with plans to refine print ad variations for different audiences (05:20).  \n- **Colin Costigan** confirmed all assets are packaged in editable formats like PowerPoint and Canva templates, facilitating easy reuse and edits.  \n- **Christina Zanca** emphasized the need for boilerplate-style completed print ads targeting both business and consumer product awareness for flexible print use.  \n- Jane raised concerns over the new headline font’s readability and print reproduction, requesting side-by-side comparisons with the existing font to assess benefits and risks (05:33).  \n- The team agreed to review these font options quickly to decide whether to revert, balancing brand consistency with practical print and digital clarity.  \n- Logo usage was also discussed, with **Christina** noting the white treatment requires background color adjustments for better visibility, and suggesting alternative accent icons in videos instead of the helmet logo to avoid clutter (08:45).  \n\nThe team plans to refine line drawing styles and their opacity to avoid visual overload, aiming for subtle background use that complements primary photography in ads (14:52).  \n- Jane suggested building a stock library of local and community-relevant line drawings to support diversified creative use.  \n- The group discussed developing accent icons and lower banner lockups for social posts and ads to enhance engagement without overwhelming imagery (19:56).  \n- The team agreed this brand asset work is a living project to be refined continuously, with feedback cycles planned over the next two weeks (21:44).  \n\n## **Social Media Account Integration and Management**\n\nThe discussion confirmed the need for **HubSpot integration** with LinkedIn and other social accounts, contingent on admin access and business manager setup (22:20).  \n- **Victor Garcia** committed to resolving Meta (Facebook) access permissions immediately to enable connection to HubSpot.  \n- Jane confirmed receipt of the partner request link and gained visibility into the access process (26:56).  \n- The absence of a LinkedIn business manager was noted; creating one was recommended to streamline campaign management and ad account access (44:22).  \n- The team decided to include Twitter in social strategy despite low activity, aiming to use it primarily for community engagement and customer service monitoring (26:13).  \n- There was consensus to create standardized social media post elements such as branded lower banners and accent icons to enable quick, consistent content creation in Canva, supporting daily social media needs (17:56).  \n\nA user access strategy for HubSpot was established to optimize license use and maintain operational efficiency (39:00).  \n- Victor and Christina will retain individual admin accounts for daily work and reporting, while a shared marketing@poncebank.net account will be set up for social media and email campaign management (41:41).  \n- Multiple simultaneous logins on the same account are discouraged to avoid session conflicts (42:53).  \n- Jane and her team will need access soon for social media and campaign management training early next year (41:41).  \n\n## **Data Security and Compliance Coordination**\n\nThe team is progressing on **SoC2 compliance and vendor risk management**, targeting an update post-holidays in January, with no immediate changes expected before then (27:20).  \n- Christina clarified that HubSpot will house masked data only, with sensitive personally identifiable information (PII) obscured for risk mitigation, aligning with vendor risk committee expectations (28:54).  \n- MID’s admin access to HubSpot will be limited and monitored, emphasizing data security protocols already in place.  \n- The team secured a high vendor risk rating approval but must provide a formal **attestation document** confirming data integrity and security practices, as requested by compliance (30:44).  \n- Tristan Pelligrino agreed to prepare a concise one-page attestation referencing existing security policies and business continuity plans to satisfy regulatory needs (36:03).  \n- The approach aims to substitute formal SOC2 reports with attestation letters for audit ease, helping maintain regulatory compliance without added delays (37:45).  \n\n## **Platform and Technical Setup for CRM and Marketing**\n\nThe team is coordinating to establish a **HubSpot sandbox environment** for GPS and marketing teams to explore and test configurations before full rollout (34:21).  \n- Tristan and Victor will handle user profile creation and access management in the sandbox, ensuring proper permissions and security practices (38:16).  \n- License management was discussed, with three out of five core seats remaining, and options to assign view-only users to preserve licenses (40:15).  \n- The marketing team will manage email domain transfers and integration from Constant Contact to HubSpot, with timelines and training to be scheduled (41:41).  \n- Colin offered support for training on HubSpot’s social media scheduling and campaign management tools during a slower period to avoid disrupting ongoing work (25:04).  \n- The team agreed to reschedule a follow-up meeting with GPS stakeholders to early January, allowing adequate preparation and to include Ashley and Gabe (33:42).  \n- Tristan and Victor will send key documentation ahead of the meeting to facilitate productive discussions on Salesforce and Mulesoft data syncing with HubSpot (33:12).  \n\n## **Meeting and Collaboration Management**\n\nThe team confirmed short-term communication and meeting plans to maintain momentum while accommodating holiday schedules and personnel availability (34:52).  \n- The GPS follow-up meeting will be postponed to the first week of January to ensure full attendance and readiness (33:50).  \n- Christina will review the collaboration plan document with Betty once she returns from leave, to gather feedback before the next steps (32:48).  \n- Victor will coordinate with Ashley and Gabe on meeting schedules and user access logistics, ensuring clarity on account email assignments and license allocations (39:14).  \n- The team acknowledged the need for quick iterative feedback cycles on brand assets and social media templates, with a goal to finalize core materials before broader deployment (21:44).","outline":null,"keywords":["Brand Assets","Font Debate","HubSpot Integration","Social Media Management","Compliance Documentation","Sandbox Environment"],"overview":"- **Brand Asset Delivery:** Finalized editable templates for presentations, emails, and social media; refining print ads for varied audiences.  \n- **Social Media Integration:** Need HubSpot integration with LinkedIn and Meta; standardized post elements planned for quick content creation.  \n- **Data Security Progress:** Targeting SoC2 compliance update in January; HubSpot to store only masked data for PII protection.  \n- **HubSpot Sandbox Setup:** Environment for testing configurations; ongoing license management and user access scrutiny to ensure security.  \n- **Meeting Coordination:** GPS follow-up meeting moved to January; emphasis on quick feedback cycles for brand assets and templates.  \n- **Training Plans:** Marketing team to manage email integration and schedule training; documentation will be sent before key meetings.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend brand assets, social media templates, and video lower thirds for team review and feedback (02:40)\nProvide side-by-side font comparison samples to Jane and Christina for review (07:42)\nSend samples of line drawings and icons to the team to build out brand asset library (16:33)\nDeliver all current assets for feedback; continue development of variations as needed (21:36)\nSet up marketing@poncebank.net login user in HubSpot for marketing team access (43:00)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nGrant super admin access on Meta (Facebook) side for HubSpot LinkedIn connection (22:44)\nPing Jane regarding LinkedIn Business Manager setup confirmation (25:25)\nHandle Twitter profile access and invite Marketers in Demand team (26:13)\nCoordinate with Ashley and Gabe regarding meeting rescheduling and HubSpot sandbox user setup (34:51)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nProvide attestation document templates or help with documents to support compliance requirements (37:47)\n"},"duration":46.18000030517578,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"victor garcia"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":5,"name":"Jane"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, what''s going on, Kyler?","index":0,"end_time":14.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.76,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Hey, how''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":16.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":2,"end_time":17.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":16.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Doing well.","index":3,"end_time":18.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you?","index":4,"end_time":19.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.88,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good, sir.","index":5,"end_time":20,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.36,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":6,"end_time":21.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":20.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There.","index":7,"end_time":65.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":65.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How''s it going, Guiller?","index":8,"end_time":69.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going well.","index":9,"end_time":71.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":70.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Happy Monday.","index":10,"end_time":71.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":71.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Happy Monday.","index":11,"end_time":72.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":12,"end_time":90.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":90.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hi, Christina.","index":13,"end_time":92.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":14,"end_time":94.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":93.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I will spare you in advance of my terrible voice.","index":15,"end_time":98.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":94.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Not going to do much talking this morning.","index":16,"end_time":101.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":99.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I have a sinus issues, so.","index":17,"end_time":104.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":102.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sorry to hear that.","index":18,"end_time":105.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":105.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Certainly that time of the year.","index":19,"end_time":107.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":105.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m used to it by now.","index":20,"end_time":109.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":107.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It happens literally every year at the same time.","index":21,"end_time":111.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":109.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I can''t get a break, especially with kids.","index":22,"end_time":113.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, it''s not so much sickness.","index":23,"end_time":115.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":114.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s just the sinuses make me cough a lot and then I get a raspy voice.","index":24,"end_time":120.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":115.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":25,"end_time":121.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":120.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":26,"end_time":121.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":121.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":27,"end_time":122.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":122.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anyways, well, we''ll jump in.","index":28,"end_time":125.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":123.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know.","index":29,"end_time":125.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":125.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or I''m not sure if Jane is planning on joining as well.","index":30,"end_time":127.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":125.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we talked about some social media questions, so.","index":31,"end_time":130.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t see Jane on yet.","index":32,"end_time":133.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":131.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"She''s gonna have to help.","index":33,"end_time":136.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":135.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Walk us through some of that.","index":34,"end_time":137.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":136.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hold on, let me just ping her.","index":35,"end_time":139.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":137.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''ll give it a minute.","index":36,"end_time":151.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":150.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have some other things we can go through in the meantime.","index":37,"end_time":154.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":152.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that''s.","index":38,"end_time":155.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":154.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":39,"end_time":156.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":156.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, so we''ve produced a lot of brand assets, so I wanted to share those with you guys for review.","index":40,"end_time":164.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":160.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we''ll go through some of the social media stuff and then just pending questions for the HubSpot projects.","index":41,"end_time":168.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":164.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ve packaged up all of the brand assets into a zip folder.","index":42,"end_time":174.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":170.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everything you guys asked for.","index":43,"end_time":174.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":174.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve also created a templated slide deck, email designs, business cards, letterheads, created social media templates inside of Canva, so we can easily put those over to your account as well as add templates.","index":44,"end_time":187.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":174.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can go through a few of these, or if you prefer to just kind of digest them on your own, we have markup links for everything as well.","index":45,"end_time":194.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":187.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you could just preview, you know, a few of them.","index":46,"end_time":198.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":194.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"My only question is, are they in editable formats?","index":47,"end_time":202.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":198.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m assuming.","index":48,"end_time":202.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":202.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":49,"end_time":203.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":202.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yes.","index":50,"end_time":203.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":203.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":51,"end_time":204.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":203.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, templates.","index":52,"end_time":206.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":205.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Nevermind, it''s my brain.","index":53,"end_time":207.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":206.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I got you.","index":54,"end_time":209.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":208.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, for example, this is a markup link, but It''ll be a PowerPoint.","index":55,"end_time":213.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":209.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"File that you''ll have that you can easily edit.","index":56,"end_time":216.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so the request was for a few different title slides and then a description slide.","index":57,"end_time":224.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":217.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just another version of that, another version of that, and then some options for end slides as well.","index":58,"end_time":231.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":59,"end_time":233.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":232.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so you know what we''ll do the team, maybe we''ll set up a few minutes just to review it.","index":60,"end_time":241.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":233.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, Jean, since you''re Kind of, you know, the brand owner, so to speak.","index":61,"end_time":249.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":242.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll look to you for maybe just some, some feedback, all the team members, but, but Gene and you most specifically.","index":62,"end_time":256.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":249.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then what we can do is make some direct tweaks and then figure out a plan to send these out if they need to be sent out, incorporate them into the SharePoint redesign for our Internet and then figure out how we''re going to start to utilize some of the print, you know, the print ad ones.","index":63,"end_time":276.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":256.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The only thing for the print ad, Colin, is that we might need some additional variations depending on the, the type.","index":64,"end_time":287.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":278.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then once we get into the, the products and stuff, what I might want to do is say, like, how do we have one general kind of this is who pon is like completely finished, designed, printed, and then one for business and one for, you know, kind of consumer product awareness that we can just use for, you know, the random print insertions that, you know, that we need.","index":65,"end_time":314.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":287.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s not necessarily like a template per se, but it''s more or less like a completed ad.","index":66,"end_time":320.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":314.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":67,"end_time":321.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":320.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A little bit more like boilerplate.","index":68,"end_time":322.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":321.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":69,"end_time":324.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we did create some ads in Canva as well.","index":70,"end_time":327.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":325.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these are available.","index":71,"end_time":329.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can port these over to your account.","index":72,"end_time":330.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":329.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have one thing to bump and you know, it may be like a broken record, but I, I really do feel strongly about this font, the headline font not working.","index":73,"end_time":344.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":333.67,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And I, I bumped this a few times in an email and asked if there was a reason, like if you could convince me.","index":74,"end_time":350.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":345.19,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"It feels like a, like a harder to read, more anticipated version of what we have now and I''m not sure there''s any benefit.","index":75,"end_time":360.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":350.67,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like some of the lines are really, really thin and I''m just very confident they''re not going to reproduce.","index":76,"end_time":365.64,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":360.24,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And you know, some of the publications that we run, print ads are actually like old school newspapers with not, you know, with like lines and not great resolution.","index":77,"end_time":374.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":365.64,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Our monitors can be a bit, you know, finicky and even so I''m, I prefer our current font for the headline.","index":78,"end_time":383.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":374.56,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So I had asked if we could see a couple like a month ago, if we can see a version of something that you''ve created, but keeping our main font.","index":79,"end_time":391.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":383.11,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean we could switch all the fonts back, the fonts from the brand guidelines that were approved by Christina and Betty.","index":80,"end_time":398.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":392.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why we were rolling with that style.","index":81,"end_time":400.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":398.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, if we want to revert back to, I think it''s Mackinaw, we can do that for headlines.","index":82,"end_time":406.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":400.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll just need to update all the brand Guidelines and everything.","index":83,"end_time":408.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":406.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I would just appreciate seeing at least one or two things.","index":84,"end_time":412.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":409.11,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"You know, it should be a quick switch just so we could, you know, put them next to each other.","index":85,"end_time":415.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":412.19,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And is there, is there merit or is there a benefit of switching it?","index":86,"end_time":419.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":415.97,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I remember when we initially spoke with you, it was, you know, there''s something perhaps a little more contemporary and I have to say this feels much less contemporary.","index":87,"end_time":428.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":420.05,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And there''s a softness to our current font and aroundness which is a little more joyful and reads better.","index":88,"end_time":433.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":428.53,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So anyway.","index":89,"end_time":435.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":433.97,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I guess we can see like a one side by side comparison on just like a, a plain word word document.","index":90,"end_time":444.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":437.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Doesn''t have to be design things.","index":91,"end_time":445.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":444.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I, I, I will say, like, for me, I''m a different.","index":92,"end_time":449.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":445.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I look at this and it doesn''t even look any different than our font today.","index":93,"end_time":453.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":449.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s why I probably didn''t even notice it when I approved the, the brand guidelines.","index":94,"end_time":459.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":453.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So J May, give me, hold on one second.","index":95,"end_time":462.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":460.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":96,"end_time":463.21,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":462.97,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I had noticed when you were away the, like on PTO like a couple months ago that like some of the lines like in the, if you look at the E and the H, you know, they''re so thin that when there''s a graphic or photo behind it, it''s just not reading.","index":97,"end_time":478.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":463.21,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":98,"end_time":481.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":480.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe we could.","index":99,"end_time":482.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":481.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What was.","index":100,"end_time":483.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":482.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''d like to revert, but yes, let''s.","index":101,"end_time":485.16,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":483.2,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Look at one and then, and then we''ll make, you know, make a decision.","index":102,"end_time":488.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":485.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, I see what you''re saying on the H a little bit, but I think it''s, I think it''s all right, but I guess I need to see it side by side, so, so.","index":103,"end_time":498.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":490.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m pretty sad and send that over.","index":104,"end_time":500.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":105,"end_time":501.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":501.06,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":106,"end_time":502.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re also, we''re reviewing these, but we''ll send these over.","index":107,"end_time":506.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":503.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have like some video templates as well for some lower thirds and some nice clean things like that.","index":108,"end_time":512.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":506.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You could actually see it and you just not to beat on this.","index":109,"end_time":519.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":516.1,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"But if you scroll back like the H, you know, like you don''t even see the line and in the end it gets lost.","index":110,"end_time":525.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":519.5,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"But.","index":111,"end_time":525.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":525.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":112,"end_time":526.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":525.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The one thing I was going to suggest is can we our logo, like putting the, the white treatment, it, it''s not really the way our brand is, so we''re going to have to figure out a way to, I guess have color behind the logo so the logo is viewable.","index":113,"end_time":555.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":528.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t know how we, we attack that.","index":114,"end_time":558.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":556.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We actually have an approved, like, fully approved knockout version.","index":115,"end_time":565.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":560.46,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that''s what I was gonna.","index":116,"end_time":567.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":566.62,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Say, yeah, this is this.","index":117,"end_time":569.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":567.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And.","index":118,"end_time":570.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":569.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And what I was going to say too, is, is that I don''t think there''s going to be any.","index":119,"end_time":573.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":570.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Any time where we''re going to want to use just the.","index":120,"end_time":575.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":573.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just the helmet alone, unless it''s, you know, something like a social media thing that we just can''t use the, the name or like a promotional item or what have you.","index":121,"end_time":590.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":576.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But what I would say is, how do we come up with another icon that works for this area?","index":122,"end_time":598.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":590.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And do we even.","index":123,"end_time":600.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":599.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Do we even need.","index":124,"end_time":600.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":600.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Need the helmet on the lower third?","index":125,"end_time":603.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":601.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe that is, like, overkill.","index":126,"end_time":607.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":605.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We could just have the guest name and guest title, but maybe like another kind of not.","index":127,"end_time":612.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":607.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Not icon, but like an accent icon or some type of accent imagery, you know, I think would be.","index":128,"end_time":622.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":612.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Would be fine.","index":129,"end_time":623.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":622.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And what I would suggest is maybe.","index":130,"end_time":628.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":623.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe we use like a standard color.","index":131,"end_time":632.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":629.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But, But, Victor, like, when you''re creating video, like, if there''s ever a white background, you know, we can edit that to make.","index":132,"end_time":640.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":632.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To make it darker.","index":133,"end_time":641.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":640.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But maybe the blue color on the bottom isn''t the best color because most of the backgrounds, you know, that in videos are going to have darker colors, so we''ll probably need to make that all white.","index":134,"end_time":652.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":641.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":135,"end_time":653.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":652.559,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":136,"end_time":656.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":655.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":137,"end_time":659.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":659.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just some other examples of things here as well, included in that.","index":138,"end_time":662.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":659.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":139,"end_time":665.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":664.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Take a look at that and then give you some.","index":140,"end_time":668.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":665.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Some feedback.","index":141,"end_time":670.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":669.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The, the thing that I. I guess I''m.","index":142,"end_time":675.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":670.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m wondering is, do we always use the blue color in the.","index":143,"end_time":681.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":676.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In the line drawings?","index":144,"end_time":683.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":682.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I. I think that it may be beneficial to see what a very, like, nice gray would look in the line drawings.","index":145,"end_time":692.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":683.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it kind of offers some variation on.","index":146,"end_time":696.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":693.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"On the color.","index":147,"end_time":697.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":696.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Another thing I wanted to mention is how do we make sure that it doesn''t become too much on the page?","index":148,"end_time":707.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":698.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I kind of.","index":149,"end_time":708.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":707.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I kind of like the, the one with the woman there.","index":150,"end_time":713.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":708.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I like that one because the background is a little more on the opaque side.","index":151,"end_time":721.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":714.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The, the one on the right with that.","index":152,"end_time":723.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":721.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s very.","index":153,"end_time":724.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":723.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s very dark blue.","index":154,"end_time":727.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":724.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I, I mean, I like the line drawings, but I''m wondering, is there.","index":155,"end_time":731.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":728.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is there a way we could balance the intensity of the.","index":156,"end_time":735.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":732.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The line drawings with, like, everything else that''s going on in, like, a designed piece?","index":157,"end_time":740.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":735.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe we use it in more of, like, an opaque, you know, background.","index":158,"end_time":747.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":740.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":159,"end_time":748.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":747.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, totally.","index":160,"end_time":750.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":748.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here, we''ll send everyone.","index":161,"end_time":751.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, go ahead.","index":162,"end_time":752.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I have one request to see something or.","index":163,"end_time":756.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":753.13,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Or your thoughts, Christina?","index":164,"end_time":757.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":756.25,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"You know, we do a lot of ads with just.","index":165,"end_time":759.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":757.69,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Or a lot of things, right.","index":166,"end_time":762.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":760.25,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"With.","index":167,"end_time":762.49,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":762.25,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"With color photography.","index":168,"end_time":764.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":762.49,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"That''s Not a person that.","index":169,"end_time":769.21,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":764.57,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I know we''re leaning, you know, not leaning.","index":170,"end_time":771.41,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":769.29,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I know this is about line drawing when we don''t have the time or it''s not appropriate.","index":171,"end_time":777.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":771.41,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like, think about our, the holiday ad we just released today.","index":172,"end_time":780.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":777.07,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like, could we see how we could best treat something like that?","index":173,"end_time":785.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":781.35,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I could.","index":174,"end_time":789.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":788.63,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":175,"end_time":791.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":790.31,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, I think they, I think they have a couple of different.","index":176,"end_time":795.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":793.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, that, that, that helps.","index":177,"end_time":797.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":796.07,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"But I, but I get what you''re saying.","index":178,"end_time":799.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":798.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s like how do we, how do we even just take like a, A, a random.","index":179,"end_time":804.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":799.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, like not, not necessarily like a building or architecture or whatever, but maybe even we line draw a person.","index":180,"end_time":813.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":806.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right?","index":181,"end_time":814.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":814.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or you know, a holiday tree.","index":182,"end_time":818.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":815.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let''s just say like if we were doing like a Christmas ad or something, I mean, I guess those are going to be things that maybe are more specific requests because you have to do them for us.","index":183,"end_time":827.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":818.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But in the brand assets, if you could send us files of just like stuff specific, just like one, just like the line drawings that we can kind of like place into other, you know, ads and then icons and stick, that would be helpful.","index":184,"end_time":843.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":828.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I like that you guys have just the people.","index":185,"end_time":847.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":844.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Uhhuh.","index":186,"end_time":848.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":847.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"As one variation because, like, I do think that although the line drawings are nice, I don''t want them to become overkill where like every piece of our, you know, creative is a, is a line drawing.","index":187,"end_time":861.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":848.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I foresee, like, to be honest, the, the stock and like the people photography being like that kind of the primary component of it and the line drawings being like the, the almost the background, very subtle, very like, you know, kind of just like that added touch to the, to the branding.","index":188,"end_time":885.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":861.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I really do like the line drawings, but in some of these it just, for some reason it looks like a lot.","index":189,"end_time":892.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":885.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I think it''s because when you mix the text that is like a very dark and other treatments, you, you then just have a lot for the eye to focus on.","index":190,"end_time":902.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":892.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think like, in this one, if we were to have like this be a little bit more opaque, I think it would be really, really cool.","index":191,"end_time":913.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":903.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then it''s like, is there standards for like not having text or you know, any like, kind of logo treatments on top of the opaque drawing?","index":192,"end_time":925.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":915.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I don''t, I don''t like how the logo kind of, you know, recreates on top of it or is it that where we need kind of that like color block behind it to kind of make it pop?","index":193,"end_time":935.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":925.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s just some of the things that maybe we can play around with like, and tweak over time.","index":194,"end_time":940.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":936.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I do kind of really like how the line drawing shows, you know, that that background.","index":195,"end_time":948.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":940.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I will say though that this one, it''s kind of, it''s kind of funny because I know that we''re doing that kind of the, the historical representation of what a, a bank used to look like.","index":196,"end_time":960.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":949.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I, I think it''s, I think it''s interesting when you start to see how the community is going to react to, to this because it, it doesn''t necessarily resonate with like kind of the reality of the banks today.","index":197,"end_time":974.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":960.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like usually the banks don''t have like a lot of people in there.","index":198,"end_time":978.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":974.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So how do we balance like the visual representation?","index":199,"end_time":981.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":978.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I do love like the architecture, like the, the digital screen.","index":200,"end_time":985.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":981.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think it''s really, I think it looks really cool and I think when we kind of just make some small tweaks, these are going to look really nice.","index":201,"end_time":993.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":985.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":202,"end_time":993.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":993.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if you guys have any pictures we can recreate them as line drawings as well.","index":203,"end_time":997.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":993.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the actual bank branch.","index":204,"end_time":999.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":997.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":205,"end_time":1000.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1000.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe Jane, maybe that''s what something, you know, you could have Rebecca work on, you know, going in and identifying a few like either local, local things that would resonate any type of images on, you know, stock images that maybe we could just have a library of just a few line drawings that we can use.","index":206,"end_time":1023.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1000.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":207,"end_time":1024.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1024.43,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Randomly.","index":208,"end_time":1025.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1024.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":209,"end_time":1027.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1027.15,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"The one other thing and I, and I''m sorry to be kind of calling out the most boring.","index":210,"end_time":1032.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1027.87,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Right.","index":211,"end_time":1033.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1032.99,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Of the instances.","index":212,"end_time":1034.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1033.35,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''m just actually thinking through like what we knock out on the daily Colin, like plentiful amounts.","index":213,"end_time":1040.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1034.59,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''m thinking a lot about our social and our EA photos that we get of like events and stuff.","index":214,"end_time":1046.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1040.43,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"In other words, when the photography isn''t as curated and it''s not going to be as, you know, on brand as what you''re showing.","index":215,"end_time":1054.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1046.35,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"What are the stylistic elements and how do we apply color on top of them?","index":216,"end_time":1059.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1054.71,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like I''m, you know, I''m actually, I''m thinking through our daily application.","index":217,"end_time":1065.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1062.31,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So like if you were to look on Instagram, you know, any of our real everyday in the community photos, I would love to see.","index":218,"end_time":1074.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1065.91,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"One thing actually that you made me think.","index":219,"end_time":1077.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1076.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"A lot of our ads have like a, almost like a lower banner where it''s like a background color and it has our social channels, our email or I mean our website and it has our logo and maybe we can come up with something somewhat like, like that that would have like a lockup, it''s called.","index":220,"end_time":1097.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1078.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, that, like something that we can use as like a bottom of a social post or a bottom of a.","index":221,"end_time":1105.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1098.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You Know, an ad that would, it wouldn''t make sense to use any of those brand treatments because it''s like a photo.","index":222,"end_time":1113.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1106.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like you see how Jean has on the top right photo there''s that little like call out icon with like the little like yellow bursts.","index":223,"end_time":1124.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1114.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, there, there''s just sometimes where we will take a random photo and kind of put something on there just so it''s not as boring.","index":224,"end_time":1133.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1125.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if you take the kind of that teal color that we are looking at right now and maybe some inspiration from some of the just blocks at the bottom, can we make a standard subset of those even just giving us some of those like just bright and fun accent icons.","index":225,"end_time":1154.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1134.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They''re not necessarily the icons that you created, but if you could come up with a few accent type of, of things, I think that would be an interesting thing to add to the print kit.","index":226,"end_time":1164.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1154.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That would be really helpful.","index":227,"end_time":1166.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1164.77,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And you know, I''m certainly trying not to sound negative.","index":228,"end_time":1171.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1167.49,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''m just again thinking through, you know, when I first joined we had a, a blue color that was similar to, you know, this new color that you''re showing.","index":229,"end_time":1179.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1171.01,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And we found it hard to reproduce which is why we ended up kind of lightning our blue to what''s used.","index":230,"end_time":1188.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1180.05,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So I would just love to see some social applications small and how the type works on top of it and if there''s a secondary type color, how that works.","index":231,"end_time":1198.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1188.13,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Like does the teal read on the blue you''re showing or then do we, you know, like I just want to be ready to knock stuff out in Canva with Rebecca.","index":232,"end_time":1208.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1198.33,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"But don''t forget that''s why I kind of asked for some of the things like not necessarily like in, in template form.","index":233,"end_time":1216.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1210.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like I just asked for like okay, here''s a J of like this icon that you can use.","index":234,"end_time":1220.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1216.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so, so Dean, some of the, some of the setup will, will come over time and develop over time by us.","index":235,"end_time":1228.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1220.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But, but we do need to have a library of some of the things that we can use to put that, to put that together.","index":236,"end_time":1234.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1228.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I would say like, if you look at like, like the top right photo, things like those three little like lines, like, you know, there''s some brand elements from our current brand that are, are not, you know, something that we would maybe not not be interested in using again.","index":237,"end_time":1255.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1235.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I think those little Starburst, you know, things are kind of interesting.","index":238,"end_time":1260.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1255.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe we, maybe we don''t necessarily use the them in yellow, but we can still, you know, morph them over.","index":239,"end_time":1266.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1261.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe take a look at our social feed and just see what Kind of content we put out there.","index":240,"end_time":1273.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1267.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":241,"end_time":1274.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1274.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then, you know, we can.","index":242,"end_time":1277.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1275.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We can go from there.","index":243,"end_time":1278.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1277.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I''m even thinking, like, a really cool, opaque kind of image that speaks to our community is, like, behind.","index":244,"end_time":1289.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1278.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Behind a color.","index":245,"end_time":1291.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1290.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re coming down with you, Bella would be.","index":246,"end_time":1293.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1291.7,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"You know, no problem.","index":247,"end_time":1295.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1293.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I totally hear you.","index":248,"end_time":1297.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1296.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I''ll do is I''ll send over what we have in the meantime, you guys can leave any feedback there, and then we''ll.","index":249,"end_time":1302.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1297.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll start working on those other variations.","index":250,"end_time":1303.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1302.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that''s great.","index":251,"end_time":1305.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1304.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And this will be like, kind of a.","index":252,"end_time":1306.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1305.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like I said, a work in.","index":253,"end_time":1307.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1306.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Work in progress as, like, we refine.","index":254,"end_time":1309.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1307.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":255,"end_time":1310.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1310.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so that''s all represented in Pulse as well.","index":256,"end_time":1313.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1311.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have all the things in our list from ad templates, social media templates, business cards, letterhead, so all marked to be delivered today.","index":257,"end_time":1322.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1315.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ll work on the variations after we send that over.","index":258,"end_time":1325.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1322.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":259,"end_time":1326.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1325.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":260,"end_time":1326.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1326.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And it''s going to be kind of quiet over the next, you know, two weeks, so what I probably will do is I''ll probably get in and review a lot of these and give you some feedback over, you know, over the break.","index":261,"end_time":1339.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1326.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":262,"end_time":1341.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1340.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":263,"end_time":1343.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1342.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":264,"end_time":1344,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1343.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also.","index":265,"end_time":1344.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1344.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we only have eight minutes left, so I want to make sure that we knock some things out.","index":266,"end_time":1348.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1344.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we have another meeting after this, but, Jane, I know you had a question on the LinkedIn side.","index":267,"end_time":1353.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1348.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can''t connect the LinkedIn social to HubSpot unless we''re a super admin on the account.","index":268,"end_time":1360.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1354.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it would have to be either one of you three or upgrading our user.","index":269,"end_time":1363.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1360.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll take care of that right now for you.","index":270,"end_time":1366.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1364.95,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It''s the meta side of things that Jane needs to take care of because I don''t have that permission.","index":271,"end_time":1372.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.87,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":272,"end_time":1373.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1372.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unfortunately, I can''t share my screen on the meta because it shows other accounts.","index":273,"end_time":1376.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1373.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I can say is I have in here.","index":274,"end_time":1380.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1377.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The partner request was sent to Jane''s email with the ID that she sent over, and that was requested from our.","index":275,"end_time":1387.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1380.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"New north account, Jane.","index":276,"end_time":1390.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1387.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It has to come from them.","index":277,"end_time":1391.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1390.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You can''t just open meta and.","index":278,"end_time":1393.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1391.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And send them.","index":279,"end_time":1394.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1393.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I followed the directions that mid sent, which is to supply them.","index":280,"end_time":1399.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1395.28,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":281,"end_time":1399.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1399.2,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"With our id, they submit requests and then I get a notification, which I followed.","index":282,"end_time":1405.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1399.56,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And I didn''t get the notification, but now I''m realizing it might be my personal email because that''s how Facebook works.","index":283,"end_time":1410.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1405.2,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Here''s a link.","index":284,"end_time":1412.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1411.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It says that you can click also.","index":285,"end_time":1414.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1412.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To view the request.","index":286,"end_time":1414.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1414.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, perfect.","index":287,"end_time":1416.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1414.96,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":288,"end_time":1417.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1416.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So let me know if that works for you.","index":289,"end_time":1418.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1417.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":290,"end_time":1419.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1419.24,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Because we did do this with Not Enlighten Uberall.","index":291,"end_time":1425.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1419.68,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So I am familiar.","index":292,"end_time":1426.52,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1425.32,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I hate that meta require.","index":293,"end_time":1428.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1427.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, Facebook sucks, guys, through your personal.","index":294,"end_time":1431.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1428.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, it should allow you to, like, almost, like, log.","index":295,"end_time":1439.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1432.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, you log in as your person, but then, like, you can, like, access the business page.","index":296,"end_time":1444.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1439.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, Facebook''s great, but it sucks.","index":297,"end_time":1447.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1444.98,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":298,"end_time":1448.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1447.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, We used to create in my old company, like, dummy accounts, like, under my name, like, just so we can log in.","index":299,"end_time":1461.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1448.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because the only way to get it approved back in, like, the day when, you know, Facebook was kind of new, so we can actually log in because they didn''t want us logging in with our personal accounts.","index":300,"end_time":1473.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1461.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It was horrific.","index":301,"end_time":1474.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1473.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":302,"end_time":1474.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1474.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But all right, well, at least hopefully that''ll get taken care of.","index":303,"end_time":1478.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1475.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So what is the.","index":304,"end_time":1480.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1480.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What is the next steps once you get, I guess, that.","index":305,"end_time":1485.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1480.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Get that access?","index":306,"end_time":1486.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1485.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, so we''ll connect it all into HubSpot and so that can start tracking through analytics, and posts can even be managed through there.","index":307,"end_time":1493.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1486.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys are currently using or it sounds like you guys were using.","index":308,"end_time":1496.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1493.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was it Sprout Social or another tool?","index":309,"end_time":1498.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1496.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, using Sprout.","index":310,"end_time":1500.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1498.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''ll have to just figure out, you know, what we''re gonna do there because.","index":311,"end_time":1504.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1500.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m happy to hop on a call and run through how to use HubSpot''s scheduling tools as well.","index":312,"end_time":1508.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1504.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe we''ll do that during, like, a break when it''s, like, slow.","index":313,"end_time":1511.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1508.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I know you said you guys are still kind of working through the.","index":314,"end_time":1514.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1511.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":315,"end_time":1514.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1514.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the only other things on Social.","index":316,"end_time":1517.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1515.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to confirm.","index":317,"end_time":1519.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1517.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you guys have a LinkedIn business manager set up or is that something.","index":318,"end_time":1522.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1519.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That hasn''t been set up?","index":319,"end_time":1523.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1522.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":320,"end_time":1527.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1525.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Jane just had to step away real quick.","index":321,"end_time":1529.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1527.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":322,"end_time":1529.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1529.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, if.","index":323,"end_time":1531.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1529.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Victor, can you just ping Jane quickly that.","index":324,"end_time":1534.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1531.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That question and she''ll confirm.","index":325,"end_time":1536.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1534.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just because when we do start running campaigns and everything, it''s a much cleaner process for us to get access to the ad account instead of you guys just adding us one by one.","index":326,"end_time":1544.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1537.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m assuming we do, because we do do the.","index":327,"end_time":1548.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1545.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The paid ads and some of the recruitment stuff.","index":328,"end_time":1552.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1549.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just.","index":329,"end_time":1553.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1552.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I haven''t gotten access to everything yet.","index":330,"end_time":1555.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1553.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Believe it or not, it''s just been insane, and I had so many priorities, so I kind of just let the team run with.","index":331,"end_time":1561.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1556.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, totally hear you.","index":332,"end_time":1563.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1561.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also, Victor, you said that X or Twitter is not very active, but we did find that profile.","index":333,"end_time":1568.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1563.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it worth inviting us or are we just crossing that off?","index":334,"end_time":1571.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1568.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, actually just invite them anyway, because I would say we''re not going to Necessarily post per se, but I think that there''s some good like listening or some, some merit to kind of us using that as a way to kind of be more of a, of an engaged community member than kind of info sharing.","index":335,"end_time":1596.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1573.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we do get a lot of customer kind of service inquiries help related stuff.","index":336,"end_time":1601.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1596.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think it''s just more or less we have to figure out what our Twitter strategy is versus, you know, so if you, if you do have access to that, Victor, just send it over to them.","index":337,"end_time":1611.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1601.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If not.","index":338,"end_time":1612.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1611.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Jean, work on that.","index":339,"end_time":1614.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1612.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yes.","index":340,"end_time":1616.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1616.38,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Also Colin, thank you.","index":341,"end_time":1618.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1616.82,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"That link helped.","index":342,"end_time":1619.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1618.18,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":343,"end_time":1620.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1620.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m able to see the request now.","index":344,"end_time":1622.78,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1620.7,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":345,"end_time":1623.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1623.18,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And I know we have another meeting right after this to dive more into some things, but just waiting on anything from compliance for the 207 postcard offer and then the big conversation around SoC2 compliance.","index":346,"end_time":1635.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1624.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we have any updates there?","index":347,"end_time":1636.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1635.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Victor, I think you mentioned Thursday you were meeting.","index":348,"end_time":1638.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1636.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Last Thursday you were meeting with the team.","index":349,"end_time":1640.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1638.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":350,"end_time":1641.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1640.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So nothing concrete yet on compliance, but I think we have a meeting on the 18th or tomorrow.","index":351,"end_time":1647.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1641.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll look at the calendar.","index":352,"end_time":1648.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1647.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''ll just be kind of a slow thing that''ll come through.","index":353,"end_time":1651.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1648.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just, you know, keep it on your radar until we get back to you.","index":354,"end_time":1655.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1651.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s not coming out until sometime in January, so I''m just thinking with the holidays and everything like that, it''s probably something we''re going to end up just picking up when we come back.","index":355,"end_time":1665.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1657.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then we had a, I guess a vendor risk management meeting with the IT steering committee and it was submitted.","index":356,"end_time":1677.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1667.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so essentially I, I sent, I sent an overview of sort of the use case and made some kind of glaring clarifications that I think needed to be made because I think that there was a misunderstanding about what you guys were going to necessarily house versus what you guys were going to have access to.","index":357,"end_time":1699.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1678.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so I kind of reminded them that, you know, HubSpot was the vendor that we were going to use to kind of house data.","index":358,"end_time":1707.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1700.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And they have those security, you know, protocols and things already set in place, software reviews are viewed and all that kind of stuff.","index":359,"end_time":1713.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1707.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I said, you know, Mulesoft and Salesforce is going to be our system of record.","index":360,"end_time":1717.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1713.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And essentially what MID is going to be doing is getting into the HubSpot platform as a kind of admin, admin user that''ll give them access to kind of building the, the systems and viewing kind of what we give them access to.","index":361,"end_time":1734.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1717.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And there are several restrictions and you know, things like mask data and all that kind of stuff.","index":362,"end_time":1741.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1734.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So essentially what I, I told them is that this is, you know, a business decision that we''re going to have to make and that I recommend not necessarily putting any PII without data masking on it.","index":363,"end_time":1754.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1741.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So when we build the data flow, we''re probably going to do data masking.","index":364,"end_time":1760.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1754.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like for social we''ll just put like the, you know, masked and just like the last four.","index":365,"end_time":1765.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1760.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I think what we can achieve from a marketing perspective is still have the data in there to kind of do the data mining, but we don''t necessarily need to view it.","index":366,"end_time":1774.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1765.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that''ll take kind of the risk that, you know, the perceived risk that, that they had.","index":367,"end_time":1779.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1774.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so you guys were approved at the higher rating, which is great.","index":368,"end_time":1784.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1780.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The only thing that they still do want is, is that attestation that I have requested.","index":369,"end_time":1788.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1784.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if there''s just a quick document that you guys could come up with, you know, and if you need, we can have a separate call on that.","index":370,"end_time":1797.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1788.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But it''s just a document that we have on, on file that kind of just, you know, confirms, you know, that you attest to, you know, maintaining the highest quality of like, you know, data integrity, yada, yada yada.","index":371,"end_time":1810.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1797.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":372,"end_time":1810.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1810.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like all of the things that you guys already do as an agency.","index":373,"end_time":1813.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1810.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":374,"end_time":1813.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1813.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that''s another thing I said.","index":375,"end_time":1814.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1813.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, they work with a bunch of other clients.","index":376,"end_time":1817.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1814.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I doubt that they''re going to do, you know, anything funny.","index":377,"end_time":1821.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1817.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But you know, again it''s, it''s one of those things that they just have to be really mindful of, you know.","index":378,"end_time":1827.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1821.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then when they mentioned things like screenshots and all that, I said, well, if we mask the data, it''s no more than, you know, us hiring an employee and trusting them to like not screenshot things.","index":379,"end_time":1837.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1827.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we have to just kind of move on.","index":380,"end_time":1839.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1837.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think that we''re in a, a good place there.","index":381,"end_time":1843.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1839.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So any.","index":382,"end_time":1843.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1843.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Christina, one question.","index":383,"end_time":1845.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1844.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Victor.","index":384,"end_time":1846.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1845.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is that what our meeting is after this?","index":385,"end_time":1848.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1846.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know you scheduled a meeting for an hour after this with me.","index":386,"end_time":1851.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1848.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, that was for the continued conversation with the GPS team.","index":387,"end_time":1856.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1851.81,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s on the data side I think.","index":388,"end_time":1859.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1858.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But it doesn''t, on the, on the, on the meeting it doesn''t say like.","index":389,"end_time":1863.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1859.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, when we discussed, after that initial meeting we said that we were going to have a follow up meeting based on the, the, the salesforce and HubSpot fields and meal souls kind of sinking together.","index":390,"end_time":1875.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1864.11,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":391,"end_time":1877.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1877.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Unless we, unless we need to cancel that meeting and that''s perfect.","index":392,"end_time":1880.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1877.95,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We just didn''t know what it was.","index":393,"end_time":1881.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1880.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I just saw it come in I think over the weekend or, or Friday.","index":394,"end_time":1885.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1881.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We just don''t have an agenda prepared for it.","index":395,"end_time":1888.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1886.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I didn''t know what it was for.","index":396,"end_time":1890.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1888.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I thought that was for the security and some of the.","index":397,"end_time":1895.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1891.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because I was confused too, because it just says Tristan and Victor.","index":398,"end_time":1899.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1896.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I was like, okay, maybe they''re having a side conversation.","index":399,"end_time":1902.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1899.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But you had set it up, Tristan, so I wasn''t sure, you know, maybe you guys were following up.","index":400,"end_time":1908.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1904.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, no, this is just.","index":401,"end_time":1910.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1908.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s booked off my calendar, but, like, I can''t tell.","index":402,"end_time":1913,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1910.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh.","index":403,"end_time":1913.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1913.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh.","index":404,"end_time":1913.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1913.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, yeah.","index":405,"end_time":1915.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1913.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, so why don''t we do this?","index":406,"end_time":1916.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1915.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Since it seems like, you know, we might not be necessarily 100% prepared for that.","index":407,"end_time":1921.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1916.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":408,"end_time":1922.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1921.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let''s go ahead and just reschedule that, Victor, if we can see what.","index":409,"end_time":1927.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1922.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, Ashley and Gabe''s availabilities are.","index":410,"end_time":1930.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1927.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The one thing, Tristan, I think that might be really super helpful is that document that you guys put together, the PowerPoint, the PDF.","index":411,"end_time":1940.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1931.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I thought it was really great.","index":412,"end_time":1943.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1942.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The one for the website and the HubSpot kind of collaboration plan.","index":413,"end_time":1948.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1943.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe we extract the certain pages that are very specific to.","index":414,"end_time":1954.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1949.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To the GPS team and send that to.","index":415,"end_time":1957.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1954.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To.","index":416,"end_time":1958.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1957.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To them prior to the next call.","index":417,"end_time":1960.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1958.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe we could use that as sort of, you know, an.","index":418,"end_time":1964.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1960.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"An area of discussion.","index":419,"end_time":1965.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1964.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I think that that was super helpful for laying out, you know, what we''re looking to achieve and.","index":420,"end_time":1970.669,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1965.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And all that.","index":421,"end_time":1971.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1970.669,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I had planned to send it to Betty and review it with her, but unfortunately she has grandmother passed away, so she''s in.","index":422,"end_time":1977.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1971.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In right now.","index":423,"end_time":1978.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1977.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''ll hold.","index":424,"end_time":1980.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1979.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hopefully I''ll get to her by the end of the week and I''ll let you know if she has any feedback on it.","index":425,"end_time":1985.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1980.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, it''s really robust.","index":426,"end_time":1986.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1985.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I didn''t review the whole thing, but I think that that''s a nice document to just have to kind of give an overview.","index":427,"end_time":1992.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1986.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But yeah, for sure.","index":428,"end_time":1993.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1992.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And Victor.","index":429,"end_time":1994.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1994.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that would be good.","index":430,"end_time":1996.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1994.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We could send that stuff as kind of a precursor to that, our next meeting and just say, hey, here''s what we''re thinking on how we''re getting information from Mulesoft, how, you know, we need the unique IDs, for example, from Core and Salesforce, and then that way they have some of that prep beforehand and the GPS team isn''t on the spot in that call.","index":431,"end_time":2016.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1996.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":432,"end_time":2017.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2016.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then we can kind of work through, like, how it''ll actually work in practice, so we can do that.","index":433,"end_time":2021.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2017.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So do we want to push this meeting maybe until the first week of January, being that people are off, or what do we want to do with.","index":434,"end_time":2030.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2022.17,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That Christina, see what Gabe and Ashley could do, you know, for.","index":435,"end_time":2034.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2030.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For the, in the next two.","index":436,"end_time":2035.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2034.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Two weeks, you know, obviously skip, maybe stick to Monday, Tuesday of each week because the less the rest of the week is more, you know, related to the holidays.","index":437,"end_time":2047.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2035.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But Tristan, when you can, if you could just send me your availability again and.","index":438,"end_time":2053.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2047.68,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, it should be the same link.","index":439,"end_time":2054.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2053.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, you can use that whenever you like it.","index":440,"end_time":2058.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2055.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''ll always have the updated calendar.","index":441,"end_time":2060.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2058.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Perfection.","index":442,"end_time":2061.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2060.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the last thing I would say, Tristan, is if we could just get the sandbox set up and have that all ready for them so they can get into it and kind of explore before the next meeting.","index":443,"end_time":2076.689,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2061.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Victor, I''m not sure if setting up the.","index":444,"end_time":2078.609,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2076.689,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Soon the sandbox will require us to set up user profiles for them.","index":445,"end_time":2084.289,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2078.609,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just let us know.","index":446,"end_time":2085.249,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2084.289,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then Victor, just ping Ashley and Gabe and just say we had to cancel because they''re.","index":447,"end_time":2089.569,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2085.809,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They''re checking in on the meeting.","index":448,"end_time":2091.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2090.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, and we were slated to do that last week, but we, we wanted to hold off until like the SoC2 and everything was squared away.","index":449,"end_time":2100.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2092.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":450,"end_time":2100.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2100.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, we have no problem building up custom fields in the sandbox environment.","index":451,"end_time":2103.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2100.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":452,"end_time":2104.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2103.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And your access in HubSpot should be like the admin.","index":453,"end_time":2107.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2104.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we''re a partner admin, so.","index":454,"end_time":2109.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2107.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you need any other, you know, access or anything like that, just let us know.","index":455,"end_time":2114.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2109.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But you know, good news is you guys were, you know, were approved.","index":456,"end_time":2117.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2114.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like I said.","index":457,"end_time":2118.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2118.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just get me the attestation document.","index":458,"end_time":2120.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2118.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, if you.","index":459,"end_time":2121.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2120.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, can we chat about that real quick?","index":460,"end_time":2124.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2122.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Christina?","index":461,"end_time":2125.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2124.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We, we have provided the, our data security policy and then there was another document.","index":462,"end_time":2129.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2125.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is there, is there an example of what you''re looking for from our side, above and beyond that?","index":463,"end_time":2137.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2129.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because the only thing is we, if we go down that path, I do want to like, check with insurance and cover.","index":464,"end_time":2143.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2137.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, do you have requirements like for cyber insurance and things that we, we need to like, look at all that information?","index":465,"end_time":2148.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2143.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, I think, I think all they requested is what, like I copied and pasted exactly what they, what they asked for.","index":466,"end_time":2155.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2148.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, it was only like two lines.","index":467,"end_time":2159.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2158.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It was like, I don''t know, just.","index":468,"end_time":2163.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2159.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Wanting something like in, in writing, you know, saying that you guys maybe.","index":469,"end_time":2172.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2163.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe you can put like in.","index":470,"end_time":2174.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2172.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In that document.","index":471,"end_time":2175.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2174.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, you know, this is what we have from a security standpoint and this is what we provided and you know, just sign it and send it over.","index":472,"end_time":2184.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2175.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It doesn''t have to be anything kind of, you know, formal, but again, like, you might have your own legal and IT teams that you have to try to discuss that with.","index":473,"end_time":2192.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2184.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if we needed to have another call, that''s fine.","index":474,"end_time":2194.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2192.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And like I said, it was approved.","index":475,"end_time":2198.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2196.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think it''s just like one last little thing that they want to just have on file as part of it.","index":476,"end_time":2204.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2198.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe you kind of caveat with like in lieu of providing like a sock to, you know, report, you know, we attest to having the following, you know, security protocols in place and you could list them out and that would, that would be enough, I think.","index":477,"end_time":2221.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2206.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":478,"end_time":2223.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2222.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I could put like a one pager together just.","index":479,"end_time":2225.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2223.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then link out to the security policy and the business continuity plan that we shared and then that should be, should cover it.","index":480,"end_time":2231.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2225.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I think that that would be fine.","index":481,"end_time":2233.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2231.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s more of like to formalize like a doc, like to have a formal, formal document on file.","index":482,"end_time":2240.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2233.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Liz was explaining that because we''re regulated by, you know, different entities.","index":483,"end_time":2245.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2240.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like each entity when they come in and do an audit, looks for, looks for certain things.","index":484,"end_time":2249.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2245.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And what she wants to be able to do is say, hey, you know, in lieu of, you know, a sock on file, we have this attestation that clearly explains, you know, this is what was provided via email versus them having to like forward an email, you know, with an attachment.","index":485,"end_time":2265.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2249.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right, okay, got that.","index":486,"end_time":2267.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2265.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":487,"end_time":2268.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2267.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":488,"end_time":2268.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2268.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Colin Gaye.","index":489,"end_time":2269.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2268.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll get that to them today.","index":490,"end_time":2270.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2269.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We already have the other two documents so it sounds like pretty straightforward.","index":491,"end_time":2273.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2270.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Really, really quick.","index":492,"end_time":2275.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2274.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Tristan, Ashley is asking if, if you''re going to be sending, on sending over any API slash multi factor credentials for HubSpot.","index":493,"end_time":2286.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2276.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, that''ll, you''ll, you''ll actually get access.","index":494,"end_time":2290.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2288.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Once they''re set up as users, they would create their own key.","index":495,"end_time":2293.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2290.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s not something we would typically share.","index":496,"end_time":2296.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2294.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, Victor, that is so, so that''s what I was asking before.","index":497,"end_time":2300.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2296.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So once they set them the sandbox up with that environment, what will probably happen is we''ll probably have to create or mid.","index":498,"end_time":2308.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2300.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You guys could create users for, for each of them.","index":499,"end_time":2311.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2308.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The only thing I would caveat is ask Ashley what email she wants to put the account under because I don''t think that we can.","index":500,"end_time":2321.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2313.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How many licenses do we have?","index":501,"end_time":2322.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2321.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like how many?","index":502,"end_time":2323.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2322.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, that is one of the things I do want to talk because right now we have like our, our like vendor like overarching email that we''re added as a license which is production and markers in demand.","index":503,"end_time":2335.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2323.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I also want to make it clear we do have several team members that have access to that.","index":504,"end_time":2339.509,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2335.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it''s not a one off.","index":505,"end_time":2340.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2339.509,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that is one security thing that we may want to check Just even across the board, if everyone does need individual users.","index":506,"end_time":2349.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2341.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because we''ll.","index":507,"end_time":2349.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2349.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If that''s the case, we''ll probably need about five or six users, I would.","index":508,"end_time":2353.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2350.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Think, on our side.","index":509,"end_time":2354.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2353.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think for you.","index":510,"end_time":2355.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2354.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think for you guys, it''s fine because, you know, as long as.","index":511,"end_time":2359.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2355.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"As you''re comfortable with, you know what?","index":512,"end_time":2363.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2359.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, let me take a step back.","index":513,"end_time":2364.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2363.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"As long as you don''t want to have a specific person tied to tracking what work was done, you know, in case there''s any issues or concerns, you know, let me know.","index":514,"end_time":2374.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2364.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I think it''s fine for you guys to just have one login, and then at the end of the day, whatever is done, you know, under that login, you would have to track who does it to hold them accountable for anything that you need to hold them for.","index":515,"end_time":2387.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2374.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For.","index":516,"end_time":2388.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2388.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For our team, you know, Victor, I would just say, like, who.","index":517,"end_time":2392.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2388.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Ask Ashley, like, who needs the, you know, access and what email should we put it under?","index":518,"end_time":2397.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2392.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I don''t think that we have unlimited seats.","index":519,"end_time":2400.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2397.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe you guys could clarify.","index":520,"end_time":2402.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2401.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, so right now, two of the five core seats are taken, and that''s Christina and Victor, and we do not count against that because we have a partner seat.","index":521,"end_time":2410.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2403.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s three core seats left.","index":522,"end_time":2412.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2410.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you could also, like, view only.","index":523,"end_time":2413.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2412.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Users if you needed at any point.","index":524,"end_time":2415.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2413.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":525,"end_time":2416.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2415.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":526,"end_time":2416.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2416.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":527,"end_time":2416.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2416.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, Victor, let''s keep that to a minimum.","index":528,"end_time":2418.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2416.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe ask Ashley if.","index":529,"end_time":2420.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2418.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If you know, her and Gabe want to share a login.","index":530,"end_time":2423.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2420.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, we could figure out how they want to do that.","index":531,"end_time":2425.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2423.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And.","index":532,"end_time":2425.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2425.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And she''ll understand because it''s the same thing with Salesforce seats, because as we get in, Jane''s going to need a seat as well now.","index":533,"end_time":2435.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2426.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''m trying to think, are we allowed to, like, if we.","index":534,"end_time":2442.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2438.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If we use like, a marketing@poncebank.net like, maybe change Victor''s account to marketing@ponsonbank.net so then it''s one account that the marketing team uses because Rebecca will also need, you know, to log in.","index":535,"end_time":2461.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2442.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Victor will need to log in.","index":536,"end_time":2463.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2461.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And originally we weren''t going to give Jane access yet because it was gonna.","index":537,"end_time":2469.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2463.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It was more of the technical stuff.","index":538,"end_time":2470.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2469.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I wanted her to stay concentrated on all the things she had to work.","index":539,"end_time":2473.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2470.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But if we''re.","index":540,"end_time":2474.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2473.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If we''re starting with, like, the social media and all that, she''s gonna definitely need to, you know, get in there, and we might need.","index":541,"end_time":2479.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2474.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I have a call probably in the new year for.","index":542,"end_time":2481.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2479.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For her because she''s going to be out after this Friday to talk through, like, the whole process and.","index":543,"end_time":2489.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2481.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Then the ads kind of campaign manager, all of that stuff will need some overview.","index":544,"end_time":2495.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2489.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I don''t know if there''s a specific like training course that they have or if it''s something that you guys could just walk us through.","index":545,"end_time":2501.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2496.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But there''s definitely going to be some things that we''re going to maybe run.","index":546,"end_time":2504.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2501.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then Victor and the team will also need sort of an email tutorial and we''ll have to figure out the process and what are the requirements to transfer our email domain and kind of counts from constant contact to HubSpot.","index":547,"end_time":2521.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2505.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So let us know when that is ready for discussion.","index":548,"end_time":2524.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2521.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":549,"end_time":2526.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2524.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":550,"end_time":2527.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2527.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And for the marketing, user marketing at Ponce, you could definitely do that.","index":551,"end_time":2530.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2527.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again, it''s the same point that Tristan was raising with ours.","index":552,"end_time":2532.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2530.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if your security team is fine with that, then yeah, that you can certainly make that swap or we can for you.","index":553,"end_time":2537.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2532.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":554,"end_time":2538.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2537.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if we could make that swap and then have it go to marketingonesbank.net so I guess it would require you to delete Victor and then, you know, create a new one and then we can just set up team a standard password for the account because it''s.","index":555,"end_time":2560.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2539.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s going to be, you know, hard.","index":556,"end_time":2562.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2560.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The one thing I, I wasn''t sure is can multiple people log in at the same time under the same profile?","index":557,"end_time":2569.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2563.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No.","index":558,"end_time":2569.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2569.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":559,"end_time":2569.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2569.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because it''ll override what you''re doing.","index":560,"end_time":2571.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2569.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s to be honest, kind of hit or miss.","index":561,"end_time":2575.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2573.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would err on the side that.","index":562,"end_time":2576.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2575.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''S less users logging at the same time.","index":563,"end_time":2579.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2576.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so then for the marketing, you know what then, then do me a favor then leave Victor then as his own account because for reporting and website and all of that stuff, I think it''s going to be.","index":564,"end_time":2597.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2580.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"He''s going to log in probably almost daily.","index":565,"end_time":2601.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2599.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then if we can create one marketing at for just more of the social media and like email stuff, then, you know, Jane, once you get Rebecca up and running, Rebecca would be the one that''s mostly logging in.","index":566,"end_time":2619.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2602,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, you could log in if you need to do, you know, do things off.","index":567,"end_time":2624.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2621.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Offline.","index":568,"end_time":2625.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2624.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I think that that''s good.","index":569,"end_time":2626.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2625.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then if there''s ever a license that we need to kind of free up, we can.","index":570,"end_time":2630.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2626.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Victor, we can figure out how maybe you and I then would share a license if we needed to give up another.","index":571,"end_time":2637.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2630.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Another license.","index":572,"end_time":2638.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2637.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":573,"end_time":2640.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2638.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":574,"end_time":2641.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2641.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, we just sent an invite toMarketing Ponce Bank.net Awesome.","index":575,"end_time":2645.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2641.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, let us know if you have any questions there.","index":576,"end_time":2647.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2645.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But other than that, we''ll send over a bunch of things for review and Attestation and all the good things like that.","index":577,"end_time":2653.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2647.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":578,"end_time":2654.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2654.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, let me know if there''s anything outstanding on the social media side and setting up all the accounts.","index":579,"end_time":2660.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2654.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think Jane got us access updates.","index":580,"end_time":2662.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2660.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I.","index":581,"end_time":2662.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2662.16,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"You access, but let me know if you have any issues.","index":582,"end_time":2666.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2662.66,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"But it says confirmed for LinkedIn, we do not have a business manager.","index":583,"end_time":2672.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2666.9,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"When the page was created, that wasn''t.","index":584,"end_time":2674.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2672.3,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"You know how everything''s always changing.","index":585,"end_time":2676.54,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2674.86,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"That wasn''t even a thing.","index":586,"end_time":2677.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2676.54,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And I. Yeah.","index":587,"end_time":2680.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2678.74,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So let''s touch base if that''s something that we need to create on our side or.","index":588,"end_time":2686.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2681.54,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, it would be on your side.","index":589,"end_time":2687.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2686.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I do recommend doing it just because, you know, it helps with access transfer and things like that.","index":590,"end_time":2693.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2687.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we.","index":591,"end_time":2694.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2693.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can control our visibility and all.","index":592,"end_time":2696.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2694.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorts of things like that.","index":593,"end_time":2697.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2696.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s do.","index":594,"end_time":2698.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2697.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let''s do that too.","index":595,"end_time":2699.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2698.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then, Gene, you have to figure out how you want to handle Carlos and Madeline''s.","index":596,"end_time":2706.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2700.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I would keep Carlos and Madeline separate from this.","index":597,"end_time":2709.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2706.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, they''re.","index":598,"end_time":2710.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2710.18,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"They''re.","index":599,"end_time":2711.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2710.82,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"It''s their own personal logins.","index":600,"end_time":2712.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2711.26,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I don''t share that.","index":601,"end_time":2713.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2712.62,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''m not.","index":602,"end_time":2713.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2713.38,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, no, no, that goes completely separate.","index":603,"end_time":2715.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2713.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":604,"end_time":2716.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2716.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":605,"end_time":2717.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2716.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then just the last thing is Ponzi Bank Direct make sure that they have access, because Ponzi Bank Direct is most likely going to stay.","index":606,"end_time":2727.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2718.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, so, Victor, you''ll handle that, right?","index":607,"end_time":2730.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2728.61,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''m sorry, repeat that one more time.","index":608,"end_time":2733.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2732.05,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Ponce Bank Direct social pages.","index":609,"end_time":2737.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2733.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have to figure out that.","index":610,"end_time":2738.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2737.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I have to figure out from Betty if we want to.","index":611,"end_time":2741.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2739.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We were having issues with those pages.","index":612,"end_time":2744.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2742.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We could discuss that offline, but we''ve had conversations internally about that.","index":613,"end_time":2748.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2744.53,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":614,"end_time":2749.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2749,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, well, let me let you guys run because we''re over, but I appreciate the time.","index":615,"end_time":2755.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2749.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":616,"end_time":2756.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2755.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I hope you feel better.","index":617,"end_time":2758.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2756.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll be in touch.","index":618,"end_time":2759.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2758.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Jane, enjoy your time out as well.","index":619,"end_time":2762.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2759.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":620,"end_time":2763.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2762.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":621,"end_time":2763.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2763.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, see you guys.","index":622,"end_time":2764.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2763.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":623,"end_time":2765,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2764.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-12-15T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,jane.trachet@poncebank.net,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,victor.garcia@poncebank.net,rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,christina.zanca@poncebank.net","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","jane.trachet@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net","rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","christina.zanca@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBZJBTHM6A6558804QHRP3S3","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Delivered full suite of brand assets including templates and print ad variations for client review.","Jane raised readability issues with headline font; team agreed to review alternate side-by-side options.","Christina confirmed vendor approval contingent on attestation document; data masking strategy in place.","Colin flagged HubSpot integration pending super admin access on LinkedIn and Meta Business tools.","Team decided to defer next GPS sync meeting; key documentation to be shared in advance."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I really do feel strongly about this font, the headline font not working.","speaker":"Jane"},{"quote":"MID is going to be doing is getting into the HubSpot platform as a kind of admin user.","speaker":"christinazanca"},{"quote":"So we have all the things in our list from ad templates, social media templates, business cards, letterhead, so all marked to be delivered today.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["branding","delivery","compliance","integration","social"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-15T21:38:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Brand Asset Development and Design Strategy**\n\nThe team finalized the delivery of comprehensive brand assets including editable templates for presentations, emails, business cards, letterheads, and social media, with plans to refine print ad variations for different audiences (05:20).  \n- **Colin Costigan** confirmed all assets are packaged in editable formats like PowerPoint and Canva templates, facilitating easy reuse and edits.  \n- **Christina Zanca** emphasized the need for boilerplate-style completed print ads targeting both business and consumer product awareness for flexible print use.  \n- Jane raised concerns over the new headline font’s readability and print reproduction, requesting side-by-side comparisons with the existing font to assess benefits and risks (05:33).  \n- The team agreed to review these font options quickly to decide whether to revert, balancing brand consistency with practical print and digital clarity.  \n- Logo usage was also discussed, with **Christina** noting the white treatment requires background color adjustments for better visibility, and suggesting alternative accent icons in videos instead of the helmet logo to avoid clutter (08:45).  \n\nThe team plans to refine line drawing styles and their opacity to avoid visual overload, aiming for subtle background use that complements primary photography in ads (14:52).  \n- Jane suggested building a stock library of local and community-relevant line drawings to support diversified creative use.  \n- The group discussed developing accent icons and lower banner lockups for social posts and ads to enhance engagement without overwhelming imagery (19:56).  \n- The team agreed this brand asset work is a living project to be refined continuously, with feedback cycles planned over the next two weeks (21:44).  \n\n## **Social Media Account Integration and Management**\n\nThe discussion confirmed the need for **HubSpot integration** with LinkedIn and other social accounts, contingent on admin access and business manager setup (22:20).  \n- **Victor Garcia** committed to resolving Meta (Facebook) access permissions immediately to enable connection to HubSpot.  \n- Jane confirmed receipt of the partner request link and gained visibility into the access process (26:56).  \n- The absence of a LinkedIn business manager was noted; creating one was recommended to streamline campaign management and ad account access (44:22).  \n- The team decided to include Twitter in social strategy despite low activity, aiming to use it primarily for community engagement and customer service monitoring (26:13).  \n- There was consensus to create standardized social media post elements such as branded lower banners and accent icons to enable quick, consistent content creation in Canva, supporting daily social media needs (17:56).  \n\nA user access strategy for HubSpot was established to optimize license use and maintain operational efficiency (39:00).  \n- Victor and Christina will retain individual admin accounts for daily work and reporting, while a shared marketing@poncebank.net account will be set up for social media and email campaign management (41:41).  \n- Multiple simultaneous logins on the same account are discouraged to avoid session conflicts (42:53).  \n- Jane and her team will need access soon for social media and campaign management training early next year (41:41).  \n\n## **Data Security and Compliance Coordination**\n\nThe team is progressing on **SoC2 compliance and vendor risk management**, targeting an update post-holidays in January, with no immediate changes expected before then (27:20).  \n- Christina clarified that HubSpot will house masked data only, with sensitive personally identifiable information (PII) obscured for risk mitigation, aligning with vendor risk committee expectations (28:54).  \n- MID’s admin access to HubSpot will be limited and monitored, emphasizing data security protocols already in place.  \n- The team secured a high vendor risk rating approval but must provide a formal **attestation document** confirming data integrity and security practices, as requested by compliance (30:44).  \n- Tristan Pelligrino agreed to prepare a concise one-page attestation referencing existing security policies and business continuity plans to satisfy regulatory needs (36:03).  \n- The approach aims to substitute formal SOC2 reports with attestation letters for audit ease, helping maintain regulatory compliance without added delays (37:45).  \n\n## **Platform and Technical Setup for CRM and Marketing**\n\nThe team is coordinating to establish a **HubSpot sandbox environment** for GPS and marketing teams to explore and test configurations before full rollout (34:21).  \n- Tristan and Victor will handle user profile creation and access management in the sandbox, ensuring proper permissions and security practices (38:16).  \n- License management was discussed, with three out of five core seats remaining, and options to assign view-only users to preserve licenses (40:15).  \n- The marketing team will manage email domain transfers and integration from Constant Contact to HubSpot, with timelines and training to be scheduled (41:41).  \n- Colin offered support for training on HubSpot’s social media scheduling and campaign management tools during a slower period to avoid disrupting ongoing work (25:04).  \n- The team agreed to reschedule a follow-up meeting with GPS stakeholders to early January, allowing adequate preparation and to include Ashley and Gabe (33:42).  \n- Tristan and Victor will send key documentation ahead of the meeting to facilitate productive discussions on Salesforce and Mulesoft data syncing with HubSpot (33:12).  \n\n## **Meeting and Collaboration Management**\n\nThe team confirmed short-term communication and meeting plans to maintain momentum while accommodating holiday schedules and personnel availability (34:52).  \n- The GPS follow-up meeting will be postponed to the first week of January to ensure full attendance and readiness (33:50).  \n- Christina will review the collaboration plan document with Betty once she returns from leave, to gather feedback before the next steps (32:48).  \n- Victor will coordinate with Ashley and Gabe on meeting schedules and user access logistics, ensuring clarity on account email assignments and license allocations (39:14).  \n- The team acknowledged the need for quick iterative feedback cycles on brand assets and social media templates, with a goal to finalize core materials before broader deployment (21:44).","outline":null,"keywords":["Brand Assets","Font Debate","HubSpot Integration","Social Media Management","Compliance Documentation","Sandbox Environment"],"overview":"- **Brand Asset Delivery:** Finalized editable templates for presentations, emails, and social media; refining print ads for varied audiences.  \n- **Social Media Integration:** Need HubSpot integration with LinkedIn and Meta; standardized post elements planned for quick content creation.  \n- **Data Security Progress:** Targeting SoC2 compliance update in January; HubSpot to store only masked data for PII protection.  \n- **HubSpot Sandbox Setup:** Environment for testing configurations; ongoing license management and user access scrutiny to ensure security.  \n- **Meeting Coordination:** GPS follow-up meeting moved to January; emphasis on quick feedback cycles for brand assets and templates.  \n- **Training Plans:** Marketing team to manage email integration and schedule training; documentation will be sent before key meetings.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend brand assets, social media templates, and video lower thirds for team review and feedback (02:40)\nProvide side-by-side font comparison samples to Jane and Christina for review (07:42)\nSend samples of line drawings and icons to the team to build out brand asset library (16:33)\nDeliver all current assets for feedback; continue development of variations as needed (21:36)\nSet up marketing@poncebank.net login user in HubSpot for marketing team access (43:00)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nGrant super admin access on Meta (Facebook) side for HubSpot LinkedIn connection (22:44)\nPing Jane regarding LinkedIn Business Manager setup confirmation (25:25)\nHandle Twitter profile access and invite Marketers in Demand team (26:13)\nCoordinate with Ashley and Gabe regarding meeting rescheduling and HubSpot sandbox user setup (34:51)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nProvide attestation document templates or help with documents to support compliance requirements (37:47)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"1c84b917-563e-4c09-a7cb-05bfb5e3b8ab","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
