INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync',
  '## **Brand Asset Development and Design Strategy**

The team finalized the delivery of comprehensive brand assets including editable templates for presentations, emails, business cards, letterheads, and social media, with plans to refine print ad variations for different audiences (05:20).  
- **Colin Costigan** confirmed all assets are packaged in editable formats like PowerPoint and Canva templates, facilitating easy reuse and edits.  
- **Christina Zanca** emphasized the need for boilerplate-style completed print ads targeting both business and consumer product awareness for flexible print use.  
- Jane raised concerns over the new headline font’s readability and print reproduction, requesting side-by-side comparisons with the existing font to assess benefits and risks (05:33).  
- The team agreed to review these font options quickly to decide whether to revert, balancing brand consistency with practical print and digital clarity.  
- Logo usage was also discussed, with **Christina** noting the white treatment requires background color adjustments for better visibility, and suggesting alternative accent icons in videos instead of the helmet logo to avoid clutter (08:45).  

The team plans to refine line drawing styles and their opacity to avoid visual overload, aiming for subtle background use that complements primary photography in ads (14:52).  
- Jane suggested building a stock library of local and community-relevant line drawings to support diversified creative use.  
- The group discussed developing accent icons and lower banner lockups for social posts and ads to enhance engagement without overwhelming imagery (19:56).  
- The team agreed this brand asset work is a living project to be refined continuously, with feedback cycles planned over the next two weeks (21:44).  

## **Social Media Account Integration and Management**

The discussion confirmed the need for **HubSpot integration** with LinkedIn and other social accounts, contingent on admin access and business manager setup (22:20).  
- **Victor Garcia** committed to resolving Meta (Facebook) access permissions immediately to enable connection to HubSpot.  
- Jane confirmed receipt of the partner request link and gained visibility into the access process (26:56).  
- The absence of a LinkedIn business manager was noted; creating one was recommended to streamline campaign management and ad account access (44:22).  
- The team decided to include Twitter in social strategy despite low activity, aiming to use it primarily for community engagement and customer service monitoring (26:13).  
- There was consensus to create standardized social media post elements such as branded lower banners and accent icons to enable quick, consistent content creation in Canva, supporting daily social media needs (17:56).  

A user access strategy for HubSpot was established to optimize license use and maintain operational efficiency (39:00).  
- Victor and Christina will retain individual admin accounts for daily work and reporting, while a shared marketing@poncebank.net account will be set up for social media and email campaign management (41:41).  
- Multiple simultaneous logins on the same account are discouraged to avoid session conflicts (42:53).  
- Jane and her team will need access soon for social media and campaign management training early next year (41:41).  

## **Data Security and Compliance Coordination**

The team is progressing on **SoC2 compliance and vendor risk management**, targeting an update post-holidays in January, with no immediate changes expected before then (27:20).  
- Christina clarified that HubSpot will house masked data only, with sensitive personally identifiable information (PII) obscured for risk mitigation, aligning with vendor risk committee expectations (28:54).  
- MID’s admin access to HubSpot will be limited and monitored, emphasizing data security protocols already in place.  
- The team secured a high vendor risk rating approval but must provide a formal **attestation document** confirming data integrity and security practices, as requested by compliance (30:44).  
- Tristan Pelligrino agreed to prepare a concise one-page attestation referencing existing security policies and business continuity plans to satisfy regulatory needs (36:03).  
- The approach aims to substitute formal SOC2 reports with attestation letters for audit ease, helping maintain regulatory compliance without added delays (37:45).  

## **Platform and Technical Setup for CRM and Marketing**

The team is coordinating to establish a **HubSpot sandbox environment** for GPS and marketing teams to explore and test configurations before full rollout (34:21).  
- Tristan and Victor will handle user profile creation and access management in the sandbox, ensuring proper permissions and security practices (38:16).  
- License management was discussed, with three out of five core seats remaining, and options to assign view-only users to preserve licenses (40:15).  
- The marketing team will manage email domain transfers and integration from Constant Contact to HubSpot, with timelines and training to be scheduled (41:41).  
- Colin offered support for training on HubSpot’s social media scheduling and campaign management tools during a slower period to avoid disrupting ongoing work (25:04).  
- The team agreed to reschedule a follow-up meeting with GPS stakeholders to early January, allowing adequate preparation and to include Ashley and Gabe (33:42).  
- Tristan and Victor will send key documentation ahead of the meeting to facilitate productive discussions on Salesforce and Mulesoft data syncing with HubSpot (33:12).  

## **Meeting and Collaboration Management**

The team confirmed short-term communication and meeting plans to maintain momentum while accommodating holiday schedules and personnel availability (34:52).  
- The GPS follow-up meeting will be postponed to the first week of January to ensure full attendance and readiness (33:50).  
- Christina will review the collaboration plan document with Betty once she returns from leave, to gather feedback before the next steps (32:48).  
- Victor will coordinate with Ashley and Gabe on meeting schedules and user access logistics, ensuring clarity on account email assignments and license allocations (39:14).  
- The team acknowledged the need for quick iterative feedback cycles on brand assets and social media templates, with a goal to finalize core materials before broader deployment (21:44).',
  '2025-12-15 16:00:00+00',
