-- Meeting: Tristan Pelligrino and Kyley Crews (2025-12-08 16:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '4cf099a8-6df8-4d70-a3eb-053cb48f9f1f',
    '2025-12-08 16:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBTPF387VG3BZAJ49EE8A7G5',
    'Tristan Pelligrino and Kyley Crews',
    '{"Tristan Pelligrino","Jenny Beightol","Kyley Crews (sheher)","Nina Belina"}'::text[],
    1928,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87531108963?pwd=t4CkWgRdKncDTZ28SEpTv5MQqj1PAk.1',
    '{"id":"01KBTPF387VG3BZAJ49EE8A7G5","title":"Tristan Pelligrino and Kyley Crews","summary":{"notes":"## **Brand Deliverables and Guidelines**\n\nThe team agreed to update and consolidate all brand deliverables to fix errors and improve consistency quickly.\n\n- **Kylie identified errors in the latest brand guidelines and sent an annotated PDF dated November 25th for corrections** (05:21)  \n    - Tristan acknowledged confusion between versions and assigned Nina to merge Kylie''s comments into one master file.  \n    - This consolidated file will speed up revisions and ensure the latest feedback is incorporated.  \n    - Final brand guidelines update is prioritized to align all teams before further design work.  \n    - This was driven by the need to prevent version conflicts and maintain brand consistency across assets.\n\n- **Kylie requested comprehensive source design files including logos, mockups, iconography sets, and templates for presentations and social media** (06:47)  \n    - Jenny highlighted the need for updated PowerPoint templates and one-pagers to support consistent external communications.  \n    - Delivering these files will empower Kylie’s team to manage assets independently, reducing bottlenecks.  \n    - Photography guidance will be revised to focus less on camping and more on trail and map imagery to better fit brand positioning.  \n    - This shift aims to avoid the brand being mistaken for a camping company and better reflect its trail-focused identity.\n\n## **Homepage and Visual Design Updates**\n\nThe homepage will undergo specific design refinements to improve readability, visual hierarchy, and brand alignment.\n\n- **Kylie requested increasing text size to at least match the current website’s 13px minimum and improving header spacing to avoid letter crowding** (11:58)  \n    - Tristan confirmed these changes are straightforward and will be implemented promptly.  \n    - Improved typography is essential to enhance user readability and maintain professional appearance.  \n    - Small text and tight letter spacing were negatively impacting user experience.  \n    - These updates will be part of global style fixes to maintain consistency across pages.\n\n- **The orange accent line on the homepage will be changed to a dashed style and possibly desaturated or changed to gray to avoid negative associations** (13:02)  \n    - Kylie explained that the solid orange line resembled blood vessels, which conflicted with the brand’s trail theme.  \n    - Animated orange elements will be lightened to better match button colors despite technical rendering limits.  \n    - This visual tweak supports the brand’s repositioning towards trail and map imagery.  \n    - Adjustments to animation and color will be tested for effectiveness before final rollout.\n\n- **Alignment improvements will be made by middle-aligning image and text blocks rather than top-aligning** (13:39)  \n    - This will create a more balanced and visually appealing layout on the homepage.  \n    - Consistency across content blocks will help create a coherent user journey.  \n    - The homepage hero image will be replaced with one featuring people guiding on an advanced trail, preferably silhouettes without visible faces** (14:19)  \n    - This change aims to better represent the brand’s outdoor leadership and community focus.  \n    - Kylie emphasized the need for more impactful imagery that tells a story rather than generic nature shots.\n\n## **Ebook Design and Content Structure**\n\nThe ebook redesign requires clearer visual hierarchy and engagement improvements to better support user scanning and comprehension.\n\n- **Kylie noted the loss of visual hierarchy in the redesign, with headers and subheaders not clearly differentiated and many sections appearing as bold text** (17:41)  \n    - She requested revisiting font sizes, colors, and weights to restore easy scanning and content flow.  \n    - Breadcrumb-style navigation should be added for better user orientation within the long asset.  \n    - Callouts and helpful tips must be visually distinct and not just placed in orange boxes to maintain emphasis.  \n    - Iconography should be incorporated to add visual interest and break up text-heavy sections.\n\n- **Vertical spacing inconsistencies and topography design elements need alignment and uniformity throughout the ebook** (19:15)  \n    - Kylie wants dashed lines used instead of solid lines for topography to match homepage changes and maintain brand consistency.  \n    - The quiz section on page three should be made more engaging beyond a simple question list.  \n    - Quote blocks require designated headshot spaces; Kylie will provide 15 headshots starting with Luke’s and Megan’s.  \n    - Consistent treatment of dark blue section pages is needed to avoid heavy visual weight at the top of pages.\n\n- **The imagery focus should shift away from camping toward trail-related visuals like maps and trailheads** (20:50)  \n    - This reinforces the strategic shift in brand positioning away from camping toward trail guidance and exploration.  \n    - Jenny and Kylie agreed on limiting camping images to one use, emphasizing trail companion themes elsewhere.  \n    - Image blending effects like cut-out mountain edges and natural fades will be used to create smoother visual transitions.  \n    - These changes aim to enhance the brand’s trail-focused narrative and visual cohesion.\n\n## **Waste Page and Feature Presentation**\n\nThe waste page design will prioritize simplicity and clarity with a preferred layout and support for multiple product images.\n\n- **Kylie preferred the simpler left-side layout for the \"How This Shapes Your Day to Day\" section, valuing brevity and clarity over the more complex right-side design** (25:21)  \n    - She requested desaturation of topography backgrounds and dashed orange lines consistent with other pages.  \n    - Jenny noted the need to support showing multiple images per feature to reflect product capabilities rather than standalone features.  \n    - Tristan confirmed the ability to implement a mini carousel for scrolling through two product screenshots in these sections.  \n    - This approach aligns with the product strategy of selling problem-solving capabilities, requiring richer visual representation.\n\n- **All waste page images are finalized and linked in a shared drive, ready for integration** (29:49)  \n    - Chemicals images are expected to be finalized by Wednesday or Thursday following a design review.  \n    - Copy for chemical-related content is expected by tomorrow to keep the timeline on track.  \n    - Nina will replicate homepage global changes like dashed animations and font size improvements on the waste page.  \n    - This alignment ensures consistent user experience and brand presentation across pages.\n\n## **Process Coordination and Communication**\n\nThe team plans to improve communication and reduce bottlenecks by decentralizing feedback and review processes.\n\n- **Tristan emphasized avoiding bottlenecks by involving Nina more directly to manage feedback and updates quickly** (31:25)  \n    - Kylie offered to be highly responsive via email to support rapid clarification and iteration.  \n    - Jenny suggested scheduling a follow-up 30-minute huddle later this week to discuss feedback and speed edits.  \n    - Increasing direct communication channels aims to accelerate the revision cycle and reduce delays.  \n    - This approach supports the fast-moving timeline and multiple overlapping deliverables.\n\n- **The team will send Kylie a detailed recap email summarizing all feedback, outstanding deliverables, and next steps** (30:13)  \n    - This will include brand guideline updates, template availability, and design file handoffs.  \n    - Clear documentation intends to prevent any feedback or tasks from being overlooked.  \n    - The recap will serve as a single source of truth for the design and brand update work.  \n    - This organizational step reflects the complexity and volume of changes underway.","outline":null,"keywords":["Brand Guidelines","Home Page Design","Ebook Redesign","Visual Hierarchy","Waste Page","Photography Guidance"],"overview":"- **Brand Guideline Updates:** Team agreed to consolidate brand guidelines, correcting errors and aligning feedback for consistency across all assets.  \n- **Design File Requests:** Comprehensive source files needed for logos and templates to enhance team autonomy and reduce bottlenecks in design.  \n- **Homepage Refinements:** Text size and spacing improvements will enhance readability; visual elements will reflect the brand''s trail-focused identity.  \n- **Ebook Visual Hierarchy:** Redesign will emphasize hierarchy with better header differentiation and engaging visuals to support user comprehension.  \n- **Waste Page Layout:** Simpler layout preferred for clarity, allowing multiple images per feature to effectively showcase product capabilities.  \n- **Improved Communication:** Team aims to decentralize feedback, enhance responsiveness, and send recap emails to ensure clarity and prevent oversights.","action_items":"\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nOrganize and consolidate all feedback including brand guidelines and send updated version to Kylie for review (05:50)\nIncrease homepage text sizes and adjust header letter spacing per Kylie’s notes (11:50)\nAdjust homepage topography background desaturation and update orange accent line animation to lighter or dashed alternative (08:30)\nCoordinate with Jenny and Nina to align deliverable templates (PowerPoints, social media, PDF layouts) and assess gaps (05:00)\nProvide email recap summarizing all discussed feedback and next steps to Kylie (30:45)\nPlan potential follow-up huddle by week’s end to review feedback progress (31:10)\n\n**Kylie Crews**\nResend annotated brand guideline PDF if needed and provide headshots for quotes (03:00)\nShare Google Doc and email detailed Tier 2 guide edits and ebook design notes with team (09:50)\nProvide final copy for chemical product page for review by Wednesday or Thursday (30:10)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nLoad latest annotated brand guidelines with Kylie’s comments into a single markup file for team review (05:50)\nIntegrate homepage and waste page design changes including carousel for dual product images and updated animations (26:50)\n\n**Jenny Beightol**\nProvide support on finalizing chemical product images and copy collaboration with designer (28:50)\nAssist with clarifying product capabilities messaging and image requirements for features sections (29:00)\n"},"duration":32.130001068115234,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"id":1,"name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"id":2,"name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"id":3,"name":"Nina Belina"}],"sentences":[{"text":"All right, looks like we have Kylie here.","index":0,"end_time":7.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll let her in and we''ll get started.","index":1,"end_time":9.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ve got ebook, we''ve got homepage that was developed and then we have the waiting on the ways page.","index":2,"end_time":19.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yep.","index":3,"end_time":19.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So look, those are the three things that I have, so.","index":4,"end_time":23.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Hey, Kylie, how you doing today?","index":5,"end_time":38.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We can''t hear you.","index":6,"end_time":43.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Hey, Jenny, how you doing?","index":7,"end_time":57.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Hi, I''m great.","index":8,"end_time":59.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.34,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Good to see you, Tristan.","index":9,"end_time":60.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.86,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"It''s been a while.","index":10,"end_time":61.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.9,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Definitely, definitely nice to.","index":11,"end_time":63.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Nice to see you again.","index":12,"end_time":64.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Hope you had a good Thanksgiving and.","index":13,"end_time":66.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And retreat and all that good stuff.","index":14,"end_time":69.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know that''s so fun and busy the last couple weeks.","index":15,"end_time":74.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.86,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Months.","index":16,"end_time":74.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.5,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"It''s been great.","index":17,"end_time":75.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":75.14,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Definitely, definitely.","index":18,"end_time":77.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And Kylie, can we hear you now?","index":19,"end_time":78.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":79.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":78.94,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Can you?","index":21,"end_time":80.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":79.58,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We can.","index":22,"end_time":80.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we are all good.","index":23,"end_time":81.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Somehow it selected a different.","index":24,"end_time":83.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":81.74,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Mic.","index":25,"end_time":85.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":85.1,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"That''s all right.","index":26,"end_time":86.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":85.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s all right.","index":27,"end_time":88.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":87.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, good.","index":28,"end_time":88.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, thanks for, for joining, Jenny.","index":29,"end_time":90.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Good to have you here today as well.","index":30,"end_time":92.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know Kylie and I have caught up on a, you know, a few times, but good to bring you in the fold and then also have Nina on our team guiding some things for us on the back end as well.","index":31,"end_time":101.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I know we gotta move fast, so wanted to have a couple more hands on deck here.","index":32,"end_time":106.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":101.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, Kylie, where.","index":33,"end_time":109.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Where would you like to start?","index":34,"end_time":111.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We have three big things that.","index":35,"end_time":112.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":111.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That we wanted to talk through.","index":36,"end_time":114.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I could probably go through one, the ebook redesign.","index":37,"end_time":119.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We have that scheduled for updating today, so we''ll probably have that revised version for you in markup for review tomorrow.","index":38,"end_time":128.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then number two, are my notes on that clear?","index":39,"end_time":132.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":128.7,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I think so.","index":40,"end_time":134.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":135.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":135.38,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So we.","index":42,"end_time":135.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''re going through that quite a bit today, so I think we''re in pretty good shape.","index":43,"end_time":141.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then with the home page, we.","index":44,"end_time":145.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We have that in markup.","index":45,"end_time":146.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s a live version that.","index":46,"end_time":148.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That you''re able to view.","index":47,"end_time":149.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":148.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I believe you have some comments in there, but we wanted to check to see, you know, the status of those comments.","index":48,"end_time":154.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then number two, we have the waste designs that we sent.","index":49,"end_time":158.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There were two versions.","index":50,"end_time":159.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We wanted to show some different representations of different components and wanted to get your feedback there.","index":51,"end_time":165.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then lastly, just, you know, next steps for the next pages in the queue and go from there.","index":52,"end_time":173.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So how''s that sound?","index":53,"end_time":174.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, we also need to discuss brand deliverables.","index":54,"end_time":177.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":174.82,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I had sent an email with several things that we need and I think you sent back prompts, but there were multiple other things that we need, including having the brand guidelines updated.","index":55,"end_time":189.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.1,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"There are some errors in the most recent brand guidelines, so I sent an annotated version of that a few weeks ago.","index":56,"end_time":197.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":189.78,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"An annotated version of the brand guidelines.","index":57,"end_time":201.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Where, where, where was that annotated?","index":58,"end_time":203.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I marked it up in the PDF and emailed it to you.","index":59,"end_time":208,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":204.56,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I sent that on November 25th.","index":60,"end_time":213.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":211.12,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Let me see here.","index":61,"end_time":218.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, I see that.","index":62,"end_time":253.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, there were comments in this brand guidelines.","index":63,"end_time":257.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t see any.","index":64,"end_time":261.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You open the PDF.","index":65,"end_time":264.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":262.66,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Double check here.","index":66,"end_time":270.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.23,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, but I know I left them.","index":67,"end_time":275.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":270.67,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay, I do see these.","index":68,"end_time":287.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"These are from November 10th though.","index":69,"end_time":289.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Quite possibly I marked it up in stages and then we had.","index":70,"end_time":295.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":291.87,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, because we had a. I''m trying to remember, we had another version that we sent.","index":71,"end_time":300.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m just going to have to go through the.","index":72,"end_time":303.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because we had ver.","index":73,"end_time":306.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We had changes in markup as well that we implemented instead of final ver.","index":74,"end_time":311.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are these different?","index":75,"end_time":312.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because this is the most recent version that I had from Jenny Vance.","index":76,"end_time":317.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":313.48,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Those awarded markup, they were separate from.","index":77,"end_time":323.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s quite possibly what happened.","index":78,"end_time":326,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because I have the markup link.","index":79,"end_time":330.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is what we just need to make sure we know where like the final comments live.","index":80,"end_time":335.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So you''re saying this is the latest version, even later than the markup version that we had?","index":81,"end_time":342.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":337.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I believe so.","index":82,"end_time":344.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":343.52,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"This is.","index":83,"end_time":344.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":344.36,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":84,"end_time":345.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.05,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"What I had as the latest version that I went through and marked up because there were some issues in it.","index":85,"end_time":351.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.29,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":86,"end_time":352.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The wait.","index":87,"end_time":358.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, all right, we''ll go through this.","index":88,"end_time":369.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a.","index":89,"end_time":370.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"A mix up on my side.","index":90,"end_time":371.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So Nina, I think what we''ll do, let''s load this version and we''ll just put all these comments in market that we have everything in one place and we have that version.","index":91,"end_time":381.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we''ll just like add Kylie''s comments there.","index":92,"end_time":385.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, we can get this back to you.","index":93,"end_time":389.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This will be pretty quick, Kylie, to get this updated.","index":94,"end_time":392.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, do you want to go through the list?","index":95,"end_time":396.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because we have the Figma file that we gave you.","index":96,"end_time":399.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then.","index":97,"end_time":401.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then fonts is there.","index":98,"end_time":403.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So the source design files, any like logos, mockups, the iconography set, we don''t have any of that.","index":99,"end_time":414.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.59,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We would love the option to potentially add a couple more icons if that''s available.","index":100,"end_time":419.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.11,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The patterns, shapes, graphical elements, topography treatments, like we don''t have any of that.","index":101,"end_time":425.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.47,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And then template files, PowerPoints, one pagers, things like that.","index":102,"end_time":433.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":428.15,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Jenny Vance mentioned wanting updated.","index":103,"end_time":436.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":434.15,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Presentation templates that we could use.","index":104,"end_time":441.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":438.23,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And so I put some notes in the email about what we were looking for there.","index":105,"end_time":445.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":442.39,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The one pager and PDF layouts.","index":106,"end_time":450.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":447.51,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We''d like a small system for the one pagers.","index":107,"end_time":452.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450.39,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And then lower on the like priority is the social media templates.","index":108,"end_time":460.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":454.69,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"You have some that you''ve already mocked up.","index":109,"end_time":462.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.41,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Just those files is probably enough for me to manage in Canva to put things together.","index":110,"end_time":467.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.93,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":111,"end_time":468.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then we have updated a little on the photography guidance.","index":112,"end_time":472.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":469.49,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We still want some of that.","index":113,"end_time":473.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.53,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"But as we were working through the Tier 2 guide and the webpage, we''ve also realized we''re leaning really hard into, like, tents and camping.","index":114,"end_time":484.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.13,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And I think we''re risking looking like a camping company.","index":115,"end_time":487.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.3,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So we''d kind of like to reprioritize, like, trail.","index":116,"end_time":491.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":488.38,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Trail heads, trail guide, maybe some map imagery.","index":117,"end_time":495.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.82,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And that also leads into one of the bigger feedbacks from our.","index":118,"end_time":500.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.7,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"One of our internal designers who we want to change the orange accent line, especially when it''s moving to be a dashed line, to look more like.","index":119,"end_time":508.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":501.1,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Like a trail map and less like blood, which is what she thought it looked like was blood pumping through veins.","index":120,"end_time":517.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.21,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And I was like, okay.","index":121,"end_time":519.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.13,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"It was mostly just due to the thickness and the fact that it''s like a darker orange.","index":122,"end_time":523.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.57,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Just because it''s thicker, it, like, looks darker.","index":123,"end_time":526.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.29,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"So if we.","index":124,"end_time":530.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.53,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"I mean, Kylie, you can expand more about, like, where some of the recommendations that you had for that.","index":125,"end_time":535.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":530.45,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Yeah, I think if we do the accent lines dashed, that will help a lot.","index":126,"end_time":541.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.2,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And then.","index":127,"end_time":543.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":542.76,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Sorry, I''m jumping around, but that goes into.","index":128,"end_time":547,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":544.52,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"On the web page.","index":129,"end_time":547.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The topography background overall, we think needs to be desaturated.","index":130,"end_time":553.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":548.6,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"It''s battling the text.","index":131,"end_time":555.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.88,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"It''s hard to.","index":132,"end_time":556.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":555.8,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"It makes it harder to read.","index":133,"end_time":557.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":556.68,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And so we kind of want to address that.","index":134,"end_time":562.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.61,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And the orange that moves looks like a different orange than is used on the buttons and around the.","index":135,"end_time":571.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":563.09,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":136,"end_time":572.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s animated, so it renders in a different color.","index":137,"end_time":575.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll do the best we can to.","index":138,"end_time":576.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Match it.","index":139,"end_time":578.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We could probably lighten it up a little bit, but that does happen when you''re using video content or, like an animated piece.","index":140,"end_time":584.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":141,"end_time":585.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":584.53,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So where.","index":142,"end_time":589.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Where should we go?","index":143,"end_time":590.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I just want to make sure we don''t lose anything.","index":144,"end_time":592.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":590.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So with.","index":145,"end_time":596.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"With those comments that you have there, Kylie, are those in markup at all?","index":146,"end_time":601.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":596.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I put several in markup, but I also made a Google Doc that I sent you.","index":147,"end_time":610.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":602.14,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Double check.","index":148,"end_time":613.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.27,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And, Kylie, I just wanted to flag that some of your notes in markup explicitly said, let''s talk about this on the Monday call.","index":149,"end_time":623.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.71,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"So I want to make sure we make time for all of those notes.","index":150,"end_time":625.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":623.27,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Okay, so is the best Friday?","index":151,"end_time":628.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":626.47,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay, so is the best.","index":152,"end_time":630.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Should I just pull that up and make sure we go through one by one?","index":153,"end_time":635.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is that probably the best route?","index":154,"end_time":636.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":635.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, this is specifically for the Tier 2 guide.","index":155,"end_time":641.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":637.06,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"There were just a lot of overarching edits and it felt more efficient to talk through it and take notes that way.","index":156,"end_time":649.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.06,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Talk about the tier two guide or the.","index":157,"end_time":651.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The homepage.","index":158,"end_time":652.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":651.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":159,"end_time":653.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":652.9,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"This.","index":160,"end_time":653.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.46,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"These edits are about the Tier 2 guide.","index":161,"end_time":655.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.02,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The homepage is all in markup.","index":162,"end_time":657.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":655.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I left comments in markup.","index":163,"end_time":662.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.1,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I also noticed that you left comments for the ebook in markup.","index":164,"end_time":666.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":663.87,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But those are the same as the ones in the notes.","index":165,"end_time":669.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":666.95,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re much less written out in there.","index":166,"end_time":674.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.87,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I just wanted to kind of put visual markers so that it wasn''t just a long list of things and you had to search through the document.","index":167,"end_time":684.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":675.71,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I thought, okay, if I can mark kind of where I am thinking about this.","index":168,"end_time":688.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":684.47,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"But that might be helpful.","index":169,"end_time":690.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":688.84,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":170,"end_time":691.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":690.76,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So should I go to the homepage or the.","index":171,"end_time":696.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The ebook design?","index":172,"end_time":697.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let''s do the homepage first because it''s fewer edits.","index":173,"end_time":701.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":698.2,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"All right, so let me share that.","index":174,"end_time":704.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so.","index":175,"end_time":711.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Text is too small.","index":176,"end_time":716.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":177,"end_time":719.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":718.61,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I think we should go for at least the size that appears on our current website.","index":178,"end_time":723.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":719.61,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And when you compare these, this is still smaller.","index":179,"end_time":727.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":723.41,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":180,"end_time":731.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s 13 pics, but we can do.","index":181,"end_time":733.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We could just increase that a bit.","index":182,"end_time":737.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":736.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":183,"end_time":741.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Several of the.","index":184,"end_time":742.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":741.82,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, the headers have some strange line spacing where the letters are nearly touching.","index":185,"end_time":748.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":742.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":186,"end_time":753.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Can add.","index":187,"end_time":755.179,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":754.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Add some spacing there?","index":188,"end_time":756.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":189,"end_time":762.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":761.9,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"See how the Y and the C are basically touching?","index":190,"end_time":764.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.26,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And then this talks through what I spoke about a little with the topography in the background.","index":191,"end_time":773.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":768.22,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":192,"end_time":777.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll just lighten this up overall.","index":193,"end_time":779.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":194,"end_time":782.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I would even say if we can''t make the oranges match, we can just make it a moving, dashed, like, gray line.","index":195,"end_time":790.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":782.46,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And that is probably fine.","index":196,"end_time":793.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":791.3,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"It''s not the preference, but it would work.","index":197,"end_time":796.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":793.78,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":198,"end_time":798.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So dust and gray.","index":199,"end_time":800.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":798.66,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"If we can''t match the oranges.","index":200,"end_time":803.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":801.22,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":201,"end_time":803.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":803.3,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":202,"end_time":804.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.42,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"All right.","index":203,"end_time":807.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":204,"end_time":814.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The question here, can we middle align the image and text block?","index":205,"end_time":818.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks like they''re top aligned.","index":206,"end_time":820.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":819.05,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"If we can middle align, that would look nicer, I think.","index":207,"end_time":823.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":820.81,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":208,"end_time":824.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":209,"end_time":834.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So there''s just more variety.","index":210,"end_time":835.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s what you mentioned there.","index":211,"end_time":837.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":212,"end_time":837.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":837.37,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And then just for consistency, even in the static one, having the orange lines be dashed.","index":213,"end_time":847.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":842.81,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"All right, Got that.","index":214,"end_time":850.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":215,"end_time":851.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think these are all pretty straightforward there.","index":216,"end_time":855.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":217,"end_time":859.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, and I did.","index":218,"end_time":860.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":859.56,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The big one is.","index":219,"end_time":861.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":861,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Trying to find something a little more impactful for the hero image here.","index":220,"end_time":868.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":863.64,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The trees are nice, but I would like to see some other options.","index":221,"end_time":871.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":868.68,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Just.","index":222,"end_time":872.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":872.36,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":223,"end_time":874.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":873.88,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I love the image that''s on the middle of the page where, you know, it''s the.","index":224,"end_time":881,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.44,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"That like being led and the trees just.","index":225,"end_time":886.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":881.48,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"It doesn''t Feel like it''s saying anything, I guess.","index":226,"end_time":890.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":886.84,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"But it''s not a huge deal.","index":227,"end_time":894,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.64,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We can doodle on it.","index":228,"end_time":896.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":894,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"What can you describe what you would like to see?","index":229,"end_time":901.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":899.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know we''ve had probably, I don''t know, eight to 10 versions.","index":230,"end_time":905.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is there something else that you can think of that I would love?","index":231,"end_time":911.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Something that''s like someone guiding people on an advanced trail.","index":232,"end_time":917.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":911.25,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay, so we want to see people here in the header, because that was one of the things that we.","index":233,"end_time":923.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think if it''s people in silhouette or like just the back.","index":234,"end_time":929.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.11,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yes.","index":235,"end_time":930.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":929.79,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I don''t think we want faces.","index":236,"end_time":931.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":930.23,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay, got that.","index":237,"end_time":935.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":238,"end_time":935.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":239,"end_time":940.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":940.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Anything else on the homepage there?","index":240,"end_time":942.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":940.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I believe that''s all for the homepage.","index":241,"end_time":945.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":943.31,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"All right.","index":242,"end_time":946.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":945.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then I believe this should be the latest ebook design.","index":243,"end_time":951.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So you have comments in here, but then there''s also a Google Doc that you sent.","index":244,"end_time":957.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I actually sent it to your email.","index":245,"end_time":959.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":957.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I apologize.","index":246,"end_time":960.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":959.22,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I have a Google Doc that I can send, but I just put the notes in an email to you on Friday.","index":247,"end_time":966.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":960.02,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"All right, got it.","index":248,"end_time":978.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":249,"end_time":978.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I haven''t even seen this yet.","index":250,"end_time":980.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I was out of the office on Friday, so let me.","index":251,"end_time":982.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And these are not in markup?","index":252,"end_time":986.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Not extensively, no.","index":253,"end_time":989.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":987.79,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I put some notes.","index":254,"end_time":992.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":991.069,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I put the Google Doc in the chat too.","index":255,"end_time":994.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":992.35,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I put some notes just to try to guide back to the longer form ones.","index":256,"end_time":1000.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.67,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"But there were so many overarching edits that I wanted made, it didn''t seem time effective to me to go through and mark every instance.","index":257,"end_time":1012.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1000.43,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay, that''s what we''ll.","index":258,"end_time":1015.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll do.","index":259,"end_time":1016.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1015.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So let me see here.","index":260,"end_time":1018.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1016.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll put it there.","index":261,"end_time":1041.359,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1040.039,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then what we''ll do is we''ll use that Nina as a reference.","index":262,"end_time":1044.839,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.359,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So let''s go back through and just make sure that we go through each page and get everything that Kylie''s looking for there.","index":263,"end_time":1052.199,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.839,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so anything you want to go through in the Google Doc?","index":264,"end_time":1059.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let me just pull that up.","index":265,"end_time":1060.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1059.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So some of the big issues for me in the copy I provided, I was very.","index":266,"end_time":1068.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1061.69,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Deliberate about using different headers, and I feel like that was lost in the designed document.","index":267,"end_time":1076.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1070.09,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"When I look at the brand guidelines you sent, you had a clearer delineation between, you know, H1s, H2s, H3s.","index":268,"end_time":1083.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1077.05,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Whereas in this designed document, there''s basically the H1s, the H2s, and then everything else just looks like bold text.","index":269,"end_time":1091.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1084.33,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And so we really lose a lot of the visual hierarchy that I want us to have so that it''s easy to scan.","index":270,"end_time":1098.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1092.25,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So I''d like us to revisit that.","index":271,"end_time":1100.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1098.97,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We also left out the breadcrumb style navigation that I would like to have.","index":272,"end_time":1107.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1101.93,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Again, this is just for like, ease of going through it since it is a long asset.","index":273,"end_time":1113.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1107.21,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So I just, I asked for, you know, the multiple font sizes, colors, weights that were detailed in the original brand guidelines to be used.","index":274,"end_time":1123.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.14,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Increasing the font size for the call outs and fallouts and helpful tips.","index":275,"end_time":1128.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1125.14,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"They feel like they kind of just got pushed into orange boxes.","index":276,"end_time":1132.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1128.58,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We also didn''t leverage any of the iconography, which felt like a missed opportunity to me.","index":277,"end_time":1138.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1133.46,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We wanted this to have, you know, some more visual areas and I think the iconography could help with that.","index":278,"end_time":1145.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1139.81,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"There''s haphazard vertical spacing, which I would really like addressed.","index":279,"end_time":1152.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1146.85,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"It''s not consistent throughout.","index":280,"end_time":1154.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1152.77,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And.","index":281,"end_time":1155.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1155.41,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Trying to make sure everything.","index":282,"end_time":1159.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1157.97,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Any place where we''re using the topography here too, I think we need to switch part of it to the dashed lines instead of solid, just for consistency.","index":283,"end_time":1168.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1159.97,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The very first section there is like a quiz that I had asked to be, you know, sort of designed out.","index":284,"end_time":1179.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1172.29,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And it''s just in there as a list of questions on page three.","index":285,"end_time":1182.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1179.49,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I''d like that to be a little more engaging if possible.","index":286,"end_time":1187.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1183.41,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We have.","index":287,"end_time":1192.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1191.67,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Oh, in the quote blocks, we just need a place for headshots because we have those.","index":288,"end_time":1197.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1192.55,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I should have said that in the original and I''m sorry about that.","index":289,"end_time":1201.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1198.23,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Have you sent us the headshots or.","index":290,"end_time":1204.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1203.03,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"No, we just got them back and luckily I have.","index":291,"end_time":1209.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.67,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We have 15 of them of the company but fortunately I have Luke''s and Megan''s so I can send those.","index":292,"end_time":1215.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1209.67,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"But yeah, we got those back late last week.","index":293,"end_time":1218.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1217.02,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And then.","index":294,"end_time":1222.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1221.98,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, a color coding system would be nice.","index":295,"end_time":1233.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1231.1,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Making the section page.","index":296,"end_time":1236.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1234.38,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The section.","index":297,"end_time":1237.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1236.54,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I don''t know what to call that.","index":298,"end_time":1239.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1238.7,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The section pages.","index":299,"end_time":1243.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1242.31,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":300,"end_time":1243.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1243.15,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The home pages in the middle.","index":301,"end_time":1245.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1243.67,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Blanket that.","index":302,"end_time":1247.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1245.91,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":303,"end_time":1247.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1247.11,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":304,"end_time":1248.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1247.67,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Some of them use like topography at the top, some of them don''t.","index":305,"end_time":1252.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1248.63,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We think that the dark blue when it''s used, if we don''t do something dynamic like this, it just is really heavy on the top.","index":306,"end_time":1262.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1254.39,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So I would like some consistency with these just so they all go together.","index":307,"end_time":1268.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1262.95,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And again, with the imagery here, leaning a little less into the camping, a little more into maybe map or trail guided, that kind of thing.","index":308,"end_time":1280.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1268.96,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Do you want to.","index":309,"end_time":1284.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1283.84,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Some of the ideas that we had around showing a trail, like, do you.","index":310,"end_time":1290.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.88,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Feel this is camping or is this trail?","index":311,"end_time":1292.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, this one works.","index":312,"end_time":1293.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1292.16,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":313,"end_time":1294.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1293.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s more like the setting up the tents and different stuff like that, I think deviates which.","index":314,"end_time":1302.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1296.33,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The setting up the tent is fine.","index":315,"end_time":1304.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.37,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"It''s just like we maybe only Want to use that once.","index":316,"end_time":1307.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1304.17,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"And then we want to make sure that the rest of the imagery is more trail and like trail companion.","index":317,"end_time":1314.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1307.25,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":318,"end_time":1316.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1315.69,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Focus.","index":319,"end_time":1317.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1316.89,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Just so that it doesn''t feel like this one''s great.","index":320,"end_time":1321.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1317.45,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"We do like the topography on those section pages, right?","index":321,"end_time":1325.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1322.12,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Yeah, I prefer it.","index":322,"end_time":1327.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1325.64,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":323,"end_time":1327.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1327.16,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So this looks incredible.","index":324,"end_time":1329.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1327.72,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"I would like them all to kind of look.","index":325,"end_time":1331.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.96,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, this feels like something''s missing.","index":326,"end_time":1333.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1331.6,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"It just makes the top section heavier when we don''t have the topography lines.","index":327,"end_time":1338.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1333.4,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Can you go back to the last one?","index":328,"end_time":1340.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1339,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The.","index":329,"end_time":1343.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1342.68,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Sorry, the navy one.","index":330,"end_time":1344.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1343.16,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And you''ve done it here.","index":331,"end_time":1346.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1345.48,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I love, like, I feel we could have cut around those mountains.","index":332,"end_time":1351.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1346.6,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I love when you guys do that.","index":333,"end_time":1352.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1351.7,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"It looks so good to make it sort of blend more naturally instead of just an.","index":334,"end_time":1358.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1352.98,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"A quick fade.","index":335,"end_time":1359.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1358.98,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"It''s like what you did on the middle image for the homepage where, you know, the people stand out more.","index":336,"end_time":1367.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1361.14,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I think that''s a really great effect and I would like to use that.","index":337,"end_time":1370.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1367.22,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So I think it would be all.","index":338,"end_time":1373.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1371.3,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The COVID images for the sections.","index":339,"end_time":1375.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1373.1,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"This is the one that you want change.","index":340,"end_time":1376.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1375.3,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The other ones are there.","index":341,"end_time":1378.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1376.9,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"They fine or do you want other images?","index":342,"end_time":1380.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1378.57,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I think it like we have these two.","index":343,"end_time":1387.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Why there''s two camping images.","index":344,"end_time":1390.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1388.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Basically.","index":345,"end_time":1391.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1390.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''S this one and then this one.","index":346,"end_time":1396.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1393.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we go to just take those out altogether, do we think?","index":347,"end_time":1400.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1398.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because I. I think pretty much everything else is true.","index":348,"end_time":1404.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think the small one is okay.","index":349,"end_time":1406.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1404.78,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I would prefer to replace those appear here.","index":350,"end_time":1410.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1407.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Oh, wait.","index":351,"end_time":1410.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1410.22,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":352,"end_time":1411.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1411.06,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So that''s a third.","index":353,"end_time":1412.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1411.66,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The smaller ones are okay.","index":354,"end_time":1414.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1413.06,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So probably just take out camping is like a big, bold image.","index":355,"end_time":1420.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1416.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Doesn''t.","index":356,"end_time":1420.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1420.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":357,"end_time":1421.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1421.38,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And I really like the idea of.","index":358,"end_time":1424.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1422.34,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And I know it''s a niche thing, so it''s trickier to find, but images where it like a difficult seeming climb, like there''s a lot of.","index":359,"end_time":1433.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1424.66,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Altitude or different things like that.","index":360,"end_time":1438.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1435.63,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Just.","index":361,"end_time":1438.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1438.11,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"That''s something that I''m interested in.","index":362,"end_time":1442.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1440.35,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"All right.","index":363,"end_time":1443.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1442.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Kylie, how are you feeling about one of the, like, photography examples we talked about last week of.","index":364,"end_time":1453.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1446.59,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Like seeing the trail map, like at a trailhead.","index":365,"end_time":1459.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1455.47,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"I think that trail map, the trail, like sign posts could be really interesting.","index":366,"end_time":1465.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.51,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And that also I thought for iconography that could work for some of the helpful tips, like a signpost thing or, you know, there''s some options there to just add a little more visual interest.","index":367,"end_time":1480.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1467.79,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"But yeah, as Jenny was saying, we''ve talked about different trail related imagery.","index":368,"end_time":1486.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1481.72,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"All right, got that.","index":369,"end_time":1490.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1488.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, so we''ll get.","index":370,"end_time":1495.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1493.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll get all that in here.","index":371,"end_time":1496.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we have one place to look at everything.","index":372,"end_time":1498.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1496.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then I know with the waste page and the two examples there, we had to put that in Miro for an alternative because markup is having.","index":373,"end_time":1511.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"They had a bug like late last week and could not get these images in there.","index":374,"end_time":1516.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we wanted to get that over to you.","index":375,"end_time":1518.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1517.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Have you had a chance to look at those yet?","index":376,"end_time":1520.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1518.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yes, I looked a little bit.","index":377,"end_time":1522.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1521.12,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I think.","index":378,"end_time":1526.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1525.52,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I like the one on the right where we.","index":379,"end_time":1530.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1528,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"But again, maybe some desaturation of the topography in the background and changing, you know, the orange to a dashed line.","index":380,"end_time":1538.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1530.96,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":381,"end_time":1540.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1539.94,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I just sent it to Jenny.","index":382,"end_time":1541.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1540.58,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I go back and forth about whether I like the teal in the middle to break some of it up or if I like it just as a endless scroll.","index":383,"end_time":1550.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1542.26,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"But I definitely prefer the how this shapes your day to day section on the left.","index":384,"end_time":1555.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1550.74,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"This.","index":385,"end_time":1558.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1558.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This component here.","index":386,"end_time":1559.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1558.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":387,"end_time":1560.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1559.94,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, I like that better than all.","index":388,"end_time":1562.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1560.34,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I don''t think it needs the added length that''s on the right.","index":389,"end_time":1567.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1563.42,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, we thought that was good.","index":390,"end_time":1569.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1567.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That was our preference too.","index":391,"end_time":1570.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1569.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it''s on the left.","index":392,"end_time":1571.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1570.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we wanted an alternative treatment just to see if that drew your attention.","index":393,"end_time":1576.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1571.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But yeah, yeah, we feel like the illustration style and kind of incorporating into this component was.","index":394,"end_time":1582.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1576.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Was a little bit cleaner.","index":395,"end_time":1583.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1582.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":396,"end_time":1583.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1583.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I liked the brevity.","index":397,"end_time":1585.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1583.78,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"It was.","index":398,"end_time":1585.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1585.1,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I thought it was really good.","index":399,"end_time":1587.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1585.9,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"All right, so what we could do is build more towards the side on the left.","index":400,"end_time":1594.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1588.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then I think, Nina, what we do is obviously we need to replicate the changes that we put in for the homepage from development side as far as like the dashed animations and some of the global changes that we''re looking at so we can get that.","index":401,"end_time":1609.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1594.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think the next version of the waste page we can give to you and developed for formats.","index":402,"end_time":1613.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1609.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You''ll see it live.","index":403,"end_time":1614.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1613.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Things like font sizes and things like that will also be global changes.","index":404,"end_time":1621.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1615.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":405,"end_time":1621.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1621.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":406,"end_time":1622.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1621.89,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So I will have.","index":407,"end_time":1624.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1622.85,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Sorry, just to confirm you like the one on the right but prefer the left one.","index":408,"end_time":1629.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1624.53,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"How to.","index":409,"end_time":1629.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1629.29,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"How this shapes your day to day?","index":410,"end_time":1631.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1630.05,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"No, I looked at it again.","index":411,"end_time":1633.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1632.61,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I misspoke earlier.","index":412,"end_time":1635.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1633.93,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I do like just the white.","index":413,"end_time":1636.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1635.65,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I think if Jenny B.","index":414,"end_time":1638.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1636.93,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Has a strong feeling about the teal in the middle.","index":415,"end_time":1641.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1638.37,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Can you.","index":416,"end_time":1643.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1643.42,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"I''m just seeing this for the first time.","index":417,"end_time":1645.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1643.98,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Can you zoom in a little bit?","index":418,"end_time":1646.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1645.34,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":419,"end_time":1653.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because it''s two different features within the teal.","index":420,"end_time":1658.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1653.98,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Like when I initially thought it, Kylie, I thought that this was the treatment for how to handle two product shots for one feature block.","index":421,"end_time":1668.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1658.46,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Oh, you know.","index":422,"end_time":1669.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1668.31,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Oh, we need to talk about that.","index":423,"end_time":1671.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1669.75,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":424,"end_time":1672.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1671.63,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry.","index":425,"end_time":1673.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1672.27,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"We do have some.","index":426,"end_time":1674.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.35,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Where Jenny and our product, other product lead have identified multiple images that need to be There two images, but I think.","index":427,"end_time":1683.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1674.63,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, two.","index":428,"end_time":1684.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1683.51,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I think we can use the scroll.","index":429,"end_time":1688.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1684.39,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":430,"end_time":1689.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1688.71,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Geez, I''m struggling this morning.","index":431,"end_time":1691.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1689.43,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"The scroll like we have on the homepage with the three images that have stats, but just with two, I think that would work.","index":432,"end_time":1699.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1691.07,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Assuming we can do that.","index":433,"end_time":1702.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1699.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Oh, like a mini carousel that runs.","index":434,"end_time":1704.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1702.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":435,"end_time":1705.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1704.66,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Carousel.","index":436,"end_time":1705.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1705.1,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yes.","index":437,"end_time":1706.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1706.02,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Yeah, we could do that for sure.","index":438,"end_time":1708.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1707.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"As.","index":439,"end_time":1710.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1710.58,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"As I''ve been working with our.","index":440,"end_time":1713.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.7,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Our product manager on these copy blocks.","index":441,"end_time":1717.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1713.02,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"The way that NCAMP is built, we have less standalone features.","index":442,"end_time":1725.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1719.55,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Like, we''re building our product more so to solve problems.","index":443,"end_time":1730.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1726.91,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"And.","index":444,"end_time":1731.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1730.91,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Like, we''re selling on capabilities rather than features, if that makes sense.","index":445,"end_time":1737.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1732.99,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"So it''s challenging to just have a single snapshot within the app that represents the capability that we''re solving for.","index":446,"end_time":1747.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1737.31,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"And so that''s why for some of these feature, you know, air quotes, feature sections.","index":447,"end_time":1751.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1747.47,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"It''S better to have like, we.","index":448,"end_time":1756.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1754.19,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"We need to show two separate snapshots of the product in order to align to that.","index":449,"end_time":1762.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1756.31,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Value messaging that''s on the page.","index":450,"end_time":1766.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1764.91,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Okay.","index":451,"end_time":1767.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1767.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":452,"end_time":1768.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1768.27,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"So I think for the.","index":453,"end_time":1769.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1768.71,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"And then with those.","index":454,"end_time":1771.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1770.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because.","index":455,"end_time":1772.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1771.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because some of these do have, like, stacked elements and some do not.","index":456,"end_time":1775.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1772.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Do you.","index":457,"end_time":1775.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1775.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That we would get.","index":458,"end_time":1776.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1776.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because we''re using the same screenshot across the board.","index":459,"end_time":1781.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1777.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Do you know when we would get those?","index":460,"end_time":1783.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1781.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are they all going to be, like the same size or.","index":461,"end_time":1786.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1783.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The waste images are all done and ready for you.","index":462,"end_time":1788.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1786.33,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"They are in the document that we use for copy.","index":463,"end_time":1793.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1789.53,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"They''re linked out to a drive folder that I''ve shared.","index":464,"end_time":1797.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1793.13,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay, so those are all final ready to go?","index":465,"end_time":1800.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1797.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yes.","index":466,"end_time":1800.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1800.49,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"And then chemicals.","index":467,"end_time":1802.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1800.89,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"I''m meeting with our designer tomorrow.","index":468,"end_time":1804.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1802.01,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"And those should be good to go by Wednesday or Thursday and I''ll have the.","index":469,"end_time":1810.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1806.12,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Copy done for that today or tomorrow.","index":470,"end_time":1813.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1810.48,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":471,"end_time":1814.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1813.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, well, I have a hard stop at 12.","index":472,"end_time":1817.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1815.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yes, I think this, this was helpful, though.","index":473,"end_time":1820.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1817.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''re gonna get everything, you know, organized on our side and then we''ll send you an email, Kylie, just like, with a recap of everything that.","index":474,"end_time":1828.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1820.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That we had.","index":475,"end_time":1828.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1828.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Just make sure we don''t lose anything and fall, you know, have something fall through the cracks because I know even on the brand guidelines, we need to get that updated version to you based on your feedback.","index":476,"end_time":1837.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1828.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Then there''s also some other elements I need to look at what we have.","index":477,"end_time":1841.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1838.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"As part of the deliverable, like PowerPoint templates, social templates.","index":478,"end_time":1846.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1843.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll give you what we have.","index":479,"end_time":1847.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1846.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then if, you know, we need to build out some things in canva layers or something like that, I''ll just have to talk with Jenny on what we do.","index":480,"end_time":1855.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1847.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There, but yeah, I think we''re, we''re in a good spot right now, so.","index":481,"end_time":1860.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1855.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Great.","index":482,"end_time":1860.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1860.49,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And I''m very responsive on email, Nina, if you have any questions, just.","index":483,"end_time":1864.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1860.85,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"I know I threw a lot at you, so.","index":484,"end_time":1866.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1864.53,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"And Tristan, if it''s helpful to snag another 30 minute huddle, like, end of this week, I think it''s very beneficial to talk through this feedback.","index":485,"end_time":1876.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1867.09,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"I hope that this allows your team to, like, jump into some edits faster just by hearing Kylie describe what she''s looking for.","index":486,"end_time":1885.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1877.49,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"So.","index":487,"end_time":1885.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1885.26,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"It does.","index":488,"end_time":1886.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1885.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And.","index":489,"end_time":1886.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1886.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I honestly want to avoid being the bottleneck.","index":490,"end_time":1890.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1886.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s why I''m pulling in Nina.","index":491,"end_time":1891.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1890.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, I was in a conference last week and, you know, I''m passing information.","index":492,"end_time":1895.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1891.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And, you know, figures things are going through you and then getting filtered down.","index":493,"end_time":1900.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1895.74,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"So.","index":494,"end_time":1900.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1900.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, Kylie, we''ll just reach out to Nina.","index":495,"end_time":1902.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1900.78,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Let''s just.","index":496,"end_time":1903.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1902.82,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll see.","index":497,"end_time":1904.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1903.3,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"See you, Tristan.","index":498,"end_time":1905.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1904.42,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, no problem.","index":499,"end_time":1906.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1905.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we''ll get there.","index":500,"end_time":1908.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1906.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All good.","index":501,"end_time":1909.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1909.02,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"Nina''s going to do a whole, whole lot better than I am, but no.","index":502,"end_time":1913.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1909.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We totally get it.","index":503,"end_time":1914.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1913.08,"speaker_name":"Jenny Beightol"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":504,"end_time":1915.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1914.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, thank you both.","index":505,"end_time":1916.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1915.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":506,"end_time":1916.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1916.4,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":507,"end_time":1917.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1916.8,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":508,"end_time":1918.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1917.6,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"},{"text":"Bye.","index":509,"end_time":1919.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1918.64,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"}],"dateString":"2025-12-08T16:30:00.000Z","host_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87531108963?pwd=t4CkWgRdKncDTZ28SEpTv5MQqj1PAk.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,kyley.crews@encamp.com,jenny.beightol@encamp.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","kyley.crews@encamp.com","jenny.beightol@encamp.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBTPF387VG3BZAJ49EE8A7G5","organizer_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Scheduled ebook redesign update for today; revised version expected in markup by tomorrow.","Agreed to consolidate brand guideline feedback into a single markup for clarity and version control.","Kylie requested full brand asset delivery including icons, mockups, templates, and typography elements.","Design revisions underway for homepage and waste page based on detailed visual and copy hierarchy feedback.","Final screenshots for waste page delivered; chemicals page assets expected by Wednesday or Thursday."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''ll get everything, you know, organized on our side and then we''ll send you an email...","speaker":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"quote":"I hope that this allows your team to, like, jump into some edits faster...","speaker":"Jenny Beightol"},{"quote":"Yeah, this is specifically for the Tier 2 guide. There were just a lot of overarching edits...","speaker":"Kyley Crews (sheher)"}],"topics":["brand","delivery","design","assets"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-15T14:06:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Brand Deliverables and Guidelines**\n\nThe team agreed to update and consolidate all brand deliverables to fix errors and improve consistency quickly.\n\n- **Kylie identified errors in the latest brand guidelines and sent an annotated PDF dated November 25th for corrections** (05:21)  \n    - Tristan acknowledged confusion between versions and assigned Nina to merge Kylie''s comments into one master file.  \n    - This consolidated file will speed up revisions and ensure the latest feedback is incorporated.  \n    - Final brand guidelines update is prioritized to align all teams before further design work.  \n    - This was driven by the need to prevent version conflicts and maintain brand consistency across assets.\n\n- **Kylie requested comprehensive source design files including logos, mockups, iconography sets, and templates for presentations and social media** (06:47)  \n    - Jenny highlighted the need for updated PowerPoint templates and one-pagers to support consistent external communications.  \n    - Delivering these files will empower Kylie’s team to manage assets independently, reducing bottlenecks.  \n    - Photography guidance will be revised to focus less on camping and more on trail and map imagery to better fit brand positioning.  \n    - This shift aims to avoid the brand being mistaken for a camping company and better reflect its trail-focused identity.\n\n## **Homepage and Visual Design Updates**\n\nThe homepage will undergo specific design refinements to improve readability, visual hierarchy, and brand alignment.\n\n- **Kylie requested increasing text size to at least match the current website’s 13px minimum and improving header spacing to avoid letter crowding** (11:58)  \n    - Tristan confirmed these changes are straightforward and will be implemented promptly.  \n    - Improved typography is essential to enhance user readability and maintain professional appearance.  \n    - Small text and tight letter spacing were negatively impacting user experience.  \n    - These updates will be part of global style fixes to maintain consistency across pages.\n\n- **The orange accent line on the homepage will be changed to a dashed style and possibly desaturated or changed to gray to avoid negative associations** (13:02)  \n    - Kylie explained that the solid orange line resembled blood vessels, which conflicted with the brand’s trail theme.  \n    - Animated orange elements will be lightened to better match button colors despite technical rendering limits.  \n    - This visual tweak supports the brand’s repositioning towards trail and map imagery.  \n    - Adjustments to animation and color will be tested for effectiveness before final rollout.\n\n- **Alignment improvements will be made by middle-aligning image and text blocks rather than top-aligning** (13:39)  \n    - This will create a more balanced and visually appealing layout on the homepage.  \n    - Consistency across content blocks will help create a coherent user journey.  \n    - The homepage hero image will be replaced with one featuring people guiding on an advanced trail, preferably silhouettes without visible faces** (14:19)  \n    - This change aims to better represent the brand’s outdoor leadership and community focus.  \n    - Kylie emphasized the need for more impactful imagery that tells a story rather than generic nature shots.\n\n## **Ebook Design and Content Structure**\n\nThe ebook redesign requires clearer visual hierarchy and engagement improvements to better support user scanning and comprehension.\n\n- **Kylie noted the loss of visual hierarchy in the redesign, with headers and subheaders not clearly differentiated and many sections appearing as bold text** (17:41)  \n    - She requested revisiting font sizes, colors, and weights to restore easy scanning and content flow.  \n    - Breadcrumb-style navigation should be added for better user orientation within the long asset.  \n    - Callouts and helpful tips must be visually distinct and not just placed in orange boxes to maintain emphasis.  \n    - Iconography should be incorporated to add visual interest and break up text-heavy sections.\n\n- **Vertical spacing inconsistencies and topography design elements need alignment and uniformity throughout the ebook** (19:15)  \n    - Kylie wants dashed lines used instead of solid lines for topography to match homepage changes and maintain brand consistency.  \n    - The quiz section on page three should be made more engaging beyond a simple question list.  \n    - Quote blocks require designated headshot spaces; Kylie will provide 15 headshots starting with Luke’s and Megan’s.  \n    - Consistent treatment of dark blue section pages is needed to avoid heavy visual weight at the top of pages.\n\n- **The imagery focus should shift away from camping toward trail-related visuals like maps and trailheads** (20:50)  \n    - This reinforces the strategic shift in brand positioning away from camping toward trail guidance and exploration.  \n    - Jenny and Kylie agreed on limiting camping images to one use, emphasizing trail companion themes elsewhere.  \n    - Image blending effects like cut-out mountain edges and natural fades will be used to create smoother visual transitions.  \n    - These changes aim to enhance the brand’s trail-focused narrative and visual cohesion.\n\n## **Waste Page and Feature Presentation**\n\nThe waste page design will prioritize simplicity and clarity with a preferred layout and support for multiple product images.\n\n- **Kylie preferred the simpler left-side layout for the \"How This Shapes Your Day to Day\" section, valuing brevity and clarity over the more complex right-side design** (25:21)  \n    - She requested desaturation of topography backgrounds and dashed orange lines consistent with other pages.  \n    - Jenny noted the need to support showing multiple images per feature to reflect product capabilities rather than standalone features.  \n    - Tristan confirmed the ability to implement a mini carousel for scrolling through two product screenshots in these sections.  \n    - This approach aligns with the product strategy of selling problem-solving capabilities, requiring richer visual representation.\n\n- **All waste page images are finalized and linked in a shared drive, ready for integration** (29:49)  \n    - Chemicals images are expected to be finalized by Wednesday or Thursday following a design review.  \n    - Copy for chemical-related content is expected by tomorrow to keep the timeline on track.  \n    - Nina will replicate homepage global changes like dashed animations and font size improvements on the waste page.  \n    - This alignment ensures consistent user experience and brand presentation across pages.\n\n## **Process Coordination and Communication**\n\nThe team plans to improve communication and reduce bottlenecks by decentralizing feedback and review processes.\n\n- **Tristan emphasized avoiding bottlenecks by involving Nina more directly to manage feedback and updates quickly** (31:25)  \n    - Kylie offered to be highly responsive via email to support rapid clarification and iteration.  \n    - Jenny suggested scheduling a follow-up 30-minute huddle later this week to discuss feedback and speed edits.  \n    - Increasing direct communication channels aims to accelerate the revision cycle and reduce delays.  \n    - This approach supports the fast-moving timeline and multiple overlapping deliverables.\n\n- **The team will send Kylie a detailed recap email summarizing all feedback, outstanding deliverables, and next steps** (30:13)  \n    - This will include brand guideline updates, template availability, and design file handoffs.  \n    - Clear documentation intends to prevent any feedback or tasks from being overlooked.  \n    - The recap will serve as a single source of truth for the design and brand update work.  \n    - This organizational step reflects the complexity and volume of changes underway.","outline":null,"keywords":["Brand Guidelines","Home Page Design","Ebook Redesign","Visual Hierarchy","Waste Page","Photography Guidance"],"overview":"- **Brand Guideline Updates:** Team agreed to consolidate brand guidelines, correcting errors and aligning feedback for consistency across all assets.  \n- **Design File Requests:** Comprehensive source files needed for logos and templates to enhance team autonomy and reduce bottlenecks in design.  \n- **Homepage Refinements:** Text size and spacing improvements will enhance readability; visual elements will reflect the brand''s trail-focused identity.  \n- **Ebook Visual Hierarchy:** Redesign will emphasize hierarchy with better header differentiation and engaging visuals to support user comprehension.  \n- **Waste Page Layout:** Simpler layout preferred for clarity, allowing multiple images per feature to effectively showcase product capabilities.  \n- **Improved Communication:** Team aims to decentralize feedback, enhance responsiveness, and send recap emails to ensure clarity and prevent oversights.","action_items":"\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nOrganize and consolidate all feedback including brand guidelines and send updated version to Kylie for review (05:50)\nIncrease homepage text sizes and adjust header letter spacing per Kylie’s notes (11:50)\nAdjust homepage topography background desaturation and update orange accent line animation to lighter or dashed alternative (08:30)\nCoordinate with Jenny and Nina to align deliverable templates (PowerPoints, social media, PDF layouts) and assess gaps (05:00)\nProvide email recap summarizing all discussed feedback and next steps to Kylie (30:45)\nPlan potential follow-up huddle by week’s end to review feedback progress (31:10)\n\n**Kylie Crews**\nResend annotated brand guideline PDF if needed and provide headshots for quotes (03:00)\nShare Google Doc and email detailed Tier 2 guide edits and ebook design notes with team (09:50)\nProvide final copy for chemical product page for review by Wednesday or Thursday (30:10)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nLoad latest annotated brand guidelines with Kylie’s comments into a single markup file for team review (05:50)\nIntegrate homepage and waste page design changes including carousel for dual product images and updated animations (26:50)\n\n**Jenny Beightol**\nProvide support on finalizing chemical product images and copy collaboration with designer (28:50)\nAssist with clarifying product capabilities messaging and image requirements for features sections (29:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"8b37e4dd-d825-426b-bf88-7ec36c2593da","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
