    '{"id":"01KC4C964YNAAS7YB9XBM56Y6E","title":"New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Source Data Automation and Contact Management**\n\nThe team finalized the automation setup for updating **lead source** and **lead source specific fields**, focusing on **first touch attribution** to ensure accurate tracking of lead origins (14:53).\n\n- **Greg Smith confirmed** using first touch attribution for lead source fields to maintain consistency in lead tracking.\n- The automation excludes imported Salesforce contacts due to complex activity data embedded in integrations, requiring manual updates.\n- Colin Costigan reported several thousand contacts have already been updated, with fields properly mapped to Salesforce for seamless CRM integration.\n- The team plans to test and activate the workflow soon, expecting improved lead source accuracy and reporting for marketing and sales efforts.\n\n## **Content and Marketing Campaign Planning**\n\nThe team scheduled content releases and marketing materials to maintain engagement through the holiday and early new year period (08:56).\n\n- The **Peter Taylor podcast episode** was published, with the next episode planned for **January 7th**, initiating a regular publishing cadence.\n- The **year-end compilation video** will be ready this week and is slated for release on **January 5th** as a “Year in Review” post to boost engagement before the new episode.\n- Greg suggested creating two separate holiday graphics: one for general **holiday greetings** and another for **New Year**, to support social media and partner outreach.\n- The team is considering boosting the compilation video post to maximize reach and build momentum for upcoming episodes.\n\n## **Product and Website Development Priorities**\n\nThe team reprioritized web development tasks based on recent audits and upcoming projects to optimize resource use (11:06).\n\n- Web audit led by Kate ThreatMark identified low-effort fixes and improvements, which she will share today for rapid implementation.\n- The Behavioral Intelligence funnel pages were deprioritized pending a more comprehensive web strategy, coordinated with HubSpot’s upcoming project.\n- The **Banking Fraud Summit website** currently includes about **five pages**, with branding still evolving; further discussions planned as the project progresses.\n- The team will keep the existing WordPress site ready as a fallback while trialing HubSpot for hosting, allowing a six-month proof of concept before fully committing.\n\n## **HubSpot Integration and Cost Optimization**\n\nHubSpot’s evolving capabilities and contract timing offer potential cost savings and enhanced content management (19:29).\n\n- Greg Smith highlighted expected cost savings by consolidating content and sales outreach tools within HubSpot.\n- The team aims to coterm the HubSpot contract with broader account renewals in **June**, allowing a six-month trial period.\n- Pending successful trial results, the plan is to fully migrate from WordPress to HubSpot, simplifying management and improving integration.\n- Monitoring HubSpot analytics capabilities is critical, especially around first-party vs. third-party cookie tracking, to anticipate impacts from upcoming **EU cookie policy changes**.\n\n## **Process Adjustments and Meeting Cadence**\n\nThe team plans to reduce synchronous meeting time in favor of more asynchronous communication during the holiday period to maintain productivity (13:09).\n\n- Colin proposed reducing weekly meetings from one hour to **30–45 minutes** based on workload.\n- Greg and Kate agreed to rely more on Slack for updates the week of **December 29th** and the following week, reserving meetings only if needed.\n- A **SavvyCal link** will be shared to schedule the **2026 planning session** in the first week of January for about **90 minutes**.\n- This flexible approach balances team availability with ongoing deliverables during a high-vacation period.\n\n## **External Factors Impacting Marketing Analytics**\n\nUpcoming regulatory changes in the EU will significantly alter cookie tracking and web analytics, affecting campaign measurement (23:40).\n\n- Nina Belina warned that from next year, **third-party cookie pop-ups** will disappear across browsers, shifting control to user browser settings.\n- This change will impact data collection for **Google Ads** and other search engines, requiring adjustments in tracking strategies.\n- Greg stressed the importance of understanding if HubSpot hosting enables **first-party analytics** to mitigate tracking losses.\n- The team will monitor these developments closely to adapt marketing measurement and maintain data quality.","outline":null,"keywords":["lead source automation","holiday marketing graphic","podcast scheduling","HubSpot migration","web audit","EU cookie policy"],"overview":"- **Lead Source Automation:** Team finalized setup for lead source tracking, improving lead origin accuracy and reporting for sales.\n- **Content Schedule:** Holiday content releases planned, including a Year in Review video on January 5th and regular podcast episodes starting January 7th.\n- **Web Development Priorities:** Low-effort improvements identified; HubSpot project strategy aligned with Behavioral Intelligence pages still pending.\n- **HubSpot Integration:** Cost savings expected by consolidating tools; contract renewal in June with six-month trial to assess migration.\n- **Meeting Adjustments:** Weekly meetings reduced to 30-45 minutes; emphasis on Slack for updates during holiday period to enhance productivity.\n- **Regulatory Changes Impact:** Upcoming EU cookie policy to eliminate third-party cookies, necessitating changes in tracking and data collection strategies.","action_items":"\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nSend updated fraud lifecycle graphic and text for white paper inclusion (02:10)\nShare web audit report with recommended fixes and improvements (05:20)\nDeliver newsletter and monthly article briefs (05:25)\nRequest creation of simple holiday graphic for social media and partner distribution using inclusive themes (05:45)\nConfirm availability and coordinate January planning meeting via SavvyCal link (03:40)\n\n**Iulia Lungu**\nComplete target account list by the end of this week (02:40)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize homepage banner updates on test site and send for approval; then push live (03:05)\nSend SavvyCal scheduling link for January 2026 planning session (03:35)\nCoordinate with team to produce and schedule holiday and New Year graphics (16:50)\nOversee end-of-year compilation video and coordinate release timing (07:50)\n\n**Greg Smith**\nJoin meeting to discuss lead source and lead source-specific automation workflow and confirm first-touch attribution setup (14:00)\nMonitor HubSpot migration, evaluate Banking Fraud Summit site readiness, and decide on potential platform switch after trial (19:40)\nManage communication on HubSpot analytics and technical implications of tracking changes (26:00)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nAdvise team about EU cookie regulation changes affecting tracking and ad data, guide strategy adjustments accordingly (23:20)\n"},"duration":27.979999542236328,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Greg Smith"},{"id":2,"name":"Nina Belina"},{"id":3,"name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"id":4,"name":"Kate ThreatMark"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi everyone.","index":0,"end_time":2.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":1,"end_time":3.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.8,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Hey, how''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":4.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":3,"end_time":5.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4.88,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Good, all good.","index":4,"end_time":6.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s almost the end of the year, so I think just one week left, let''s say.","index":5,"end_time":12.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":6.88,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"And most of the people are already going on holidays and annual leaves.","index":6,"end_time":16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":12.32,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":7,"end_time":17.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is it busy?","index":8,"end_time":18.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":17.84,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":9,"end_time":22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s busy.","index":10,"end_time":22.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were just talking about how the weekend kind of flew by.","index":11,"end_time":24.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":12,"end_time":27.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":25.77,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Always the same.","index":13,"end_time":28.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":27.69,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Likewise.","index":14,"end_time":29.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":29.13,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":31.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I see that Greg said he''s going to be about 10 minutes late.","index":16,"end_time":33.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you know if Kate is planning on joining?","index":17,"end_time":35.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have no idea.","index":18,"end_time":39.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":38.41,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I think just wait.","index":19,"end_time":42.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":40.01,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Hello, Kate.","index":20,"end_time":78.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.63,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Hi.","index":21,"end_time":79.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How''s everyone doing?","index":22,"end_time":81.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":80.75,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Well, how about yourself?","index":23,"end_time":84.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":82.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, bad.","index":24,"end_time":85.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":85.15,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So that Greg said to go ahead and get started.","index":25,"end_time":90.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''ll be a few minutes late.","index":26,"end_time":91.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, well, I mean it''s not a super high amount of things to cover since we just had our last meeting like three business days ago, but we do have a few things.","index":27,"end_time":103.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So obviously Kate, you saw my message.","index":28,"end_time":105.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Peter Taylor episode is live.","index":29,"end_time":107.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You have the asset and everything for that now.","index":30,"end_time":109.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else that you need there?","index":31,"end_time":110.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":32,"end_time":111.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":111.45,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":33,"end_time":112.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":111.85,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":34,"end_time":113.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":112.45,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"No, no issues.","index":35,"end_time":114.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":113.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then wanted to just check up on a few things.","index":36,"end_time":120.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":116.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you guys mentioned that you had made some updates to the fraud life cycle image text.","index":37,"end_time":125.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you send that over so we can get that updated?","index":38,"end_time":128.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that was that with me.","index":39,"end_time":130.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":128.81,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I wasn''t sure if it was like a ready to go back to you or we needed Mikael to look over once more kind of thing.","index":40,"end_time":140.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":130.77,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But I''ll send it over to you and then we''ll get final feedback from Raquel and company.","index":41,"end_time":145.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":140.66,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, send it over today.","index":42,"end_time":147.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":145.7,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":43,"end_time":148.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":147.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I also know you guys are working on an account list.","index":44,"end_time":151.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have a timeline of when you think that would be ready?","index":45,"end_time":155.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Julia, do you want to take about.","index":46,"end_time":163.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":160.91,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The target account list?","index":47,"end_time":164.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":163.55,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I''m working on it.","index":48,"end_time":167.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":165.95,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I think let''s put a deadline until the end of this week.","index":49,"end_time":172.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":168.11,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, approximately.","index":50,"end_time":175.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":173.71,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Let''s see if I can get it done.","index":51,"end_time":177.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":175.87,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I''ll try.","index":52,"end_time":177.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":177.03,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":53,"end_time":179.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just wanted to check.","index":54,"end_time":180.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re finalizing the updates to the homepage banner on the test site today with the form Kate.","index":55,"end_time":187.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll send that over to you and then if everything looks good, we''ll get that updated on the live site.","index":56,"end_time":191.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":57,"end_time":192.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":192.33,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Also wanted to check availability for a meeting in I think last week Greg said the first week of January would be best for 2026 planning session because of vacation and everything coming up.","index":58,"end_time":208.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":59,"end_time":209.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":208.97,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"So would you guys just like a savvy Cal link to find what works for your availability or do you want to find Some time right now.","index":60,"end_time":216.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":61,"end_time":218.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":218.16,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Savvy Cal link is fine.","index":62,"end_time":221.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":219.2,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":63,"end_time":221.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can do it like that.","index":64,"end_time":223.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":222,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":65,"end_time":226.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s really only one other thing on the list and that is the lead source and lead source specific.","index":66,"end_time":236.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So obviously there''s a lot of records that were imported from HubSpot, but we did go through for anything that was not just a direct import.","index":67,"end_time":246.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lead source and lead source specific have been updated.","index":68,"end_time":249.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can continue to go through just you can see like right here an example of where lead source specific wasn''t updated because the record source is Salesforce from an import.","index":69,"end_time":258.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those just require a little bit more of a one, one at a time updating because it''s buried in their activity field from an integration that was set up with Hyperscale.","index":70,"end_time":270.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can make those updates, but by and large those are the only ones that haven''t been updated as far as lead source specific and lead source fields.","index":71,"end_time":280.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s come back to this point when Greg joins, I think.","index":72,"end_time":286,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":282.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":73,"end_time":286.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":74,"end_time":288.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, like I mentioned, that was the last thing that we had even to talk about.","index":75,"end_time":292.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there any updates on your side that you wanted to go through?","index":76,"end_time":294.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, I do have a couple of things to share.","index":77,"end_time":296.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":295.04,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Firstly, the web audit thing that I was talking about for a little while, I do actually have something to share with you.","index":78,"end_time":305.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":298.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Just a few fixes, improvements, yada yada that I think are pretty low effort that we could just get done.","index":79,"end_time":313.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":305.18,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I''ll send that to you today.","index":80,"end_time":314.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":313.34,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I also have the brief ready for you for the newsletter and like the monthly article that I spoke about.","index":81,"end_time":321.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":315.34,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I''ll get them both to you.","index":82,"end_time":323.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":322.14,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The other request we had was if you could create us a Christmas graphic for social and to send out to some of our partners that aren''t special enough for a Christmas gift.","index":83,"end_time":338.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":324.24,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yes, could do that.","index":84,"end_time":341.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you have specific platform or size dimensions in mind or just like.","index":85,"end_time":347.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, go ahead.","index":86,"end_time":349.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":348.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Something like super simple that would work for both.","index":87,"end_time":353.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":349.28,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I don''t think we need to over complicate it.","index":88,"end_time":355.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":353.57,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So it was a yes?","index":89,"end_time":357.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":355.37,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I had something in mind, but no, nothing specific.","index":90,"end_time":359.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":357.09,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":91,"end_time":360.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When you say Both, you mean LinkedIn and Facebook?","index":92,"end_time":364.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":93,"end_time":366.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":94,"end_time":368.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then do you need like a banner for the profile or anything like that?","index":95,"end_time":371.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":96,"end_time":373.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":372.93,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, easy enough.","index":97,"end_time":375.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":98,"end_time":377.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":376.84,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":99,"end_time":380.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Don''t think so, no.","index":100,"end_time":387.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":386.44,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":101,"end_time":391.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, definitely want to give Greg just a few more minutes.","index":102,"end_time":394.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Greg and I were on a call with HubSpot earlier this morning as well, so I''m catching up on all the changes happening there.","index":103,"end_time":401.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds like sales is going to be more integrated and outreach is going to be phased out, which is exciting.","index":104,"end_time":406.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":105,"end_time":407.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":406.88,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Good news.","index":106,"end_time":407.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":407.28,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I actually did notice that the portal is a little bit outdated.","index":107,"end_time":414.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":410.24,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Like, the link to the competitor research you guys did last week isn''t on there.","index":108,"end_time":419.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":414.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Would you mind sharing that with me, please?","index":109,"end_time":422.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":420.72,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":110,"end_time":423.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did we get the creative assets across onto the Q2 audience in LinkedIn, by the way?","index":111,"end_time":449.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":441.37,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The creative assets is in the new PDFs.","index":112,"end_time":454.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":113,"end_time":455.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":455.24,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Ads.","index":114,"end_time":456.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, everything except for the frog disruption, because we''re waiting on getting that live.","index":115,"end_time":460.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":116,"end_time":461.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.16,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":117,"end_time":462.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How is the complete compilation video coming up?","index":118,"end_time":473.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":468.68,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That will be ready tomorrow, as well as Kelly Paxton.","index":119,"end_time":479.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":120,"end_time":480.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you know we just move forward with a title, right?","index":121,"end_time":482.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":122,"end_time":484.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we have any title changes.","index":123,"end_time":486.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate, I know you said you were checking if there was, because she had.","index":124,"end_time":489.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A few different titles Kate sent.","index":125,"end_time":491.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.97,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Oh, that''s what you sent.","index":126,"end_time":492.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":127,"end_time":493.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":492.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":128,"end_time":494.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I will butt out of that then.","index":129,"end_time":495.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":130,"end_time":498.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":131,"end_time":506.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ll have the end of year video put together this week.","index":132,"end_time":512.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":133,"end_time":515.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":514.97,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And Kelly Paxton put together this week as well.","index":134,"end_time":518.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":135,"end_time":522.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for Kelly Paxton, do we want to go.","index":136,"end_time":524.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if Peter was just posted today, do you want to do next Wednesday or the 31st?","index":137,"end_time":535.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And let''s do the New Year.","index":138,"end_time":537.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":536.26,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, so New Year''s Eve, the 31st.","index":139,"end_time":540.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you saying later in January, like the next week?","index":140,"end_time":543.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s do the New Year, like the first week of Jan.","index":141,"end_time":547.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":544.42,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, so that would be January 7th.","index":142,"end_time":550.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":547.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then let''s try and start our cadence from then maybe.","index":143,"end_time":556.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":551.3,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":144,"end_time":557.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":145,"end_time":564.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And do you maybe have a.","index":146,"end_time":566.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.23,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"An overview of how usually, like on the timeline when the podcasts are filmed, which day of the week, or we say the month or something like that?","index":147,"end_time":577.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":566.67,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"No, they''re so irregular, which I don''t think is a huge deal because.","index":148,"end_time":585.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":578.51,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Just.","index":149,"end_time":588.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because it isn''t.","index":150,"end_time":588.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":588.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But yeah, I need to check in with Mike in terms of how.","index":151,"end_time":594.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":588.99,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How his outreach is going.","index":152,"end_time":596.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":594.59,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We do have, like a short list of people we are focusing on getting on next.","index":153,"end_time":605.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":600.03,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"They''re just giving us a bit of a run around because of the time of year, I think.","index":154,"end_time":610.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":606.51,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":155,"end_time":613.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''d like to get into a regular cadence, though.","index":156,"end_time":621.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":619.26,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, we had.","index":157,"end_time":623.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had a good one for a while.","index":158,"end_time":624.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were like.","index":159,"end_time":625.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":624.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were months booked out on.","index":160,"end_time":627.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On publishing and everything, and we were in a good flip.","index":161,"end_time":636.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Remind me, Colin, this is swapping topics where.","index":162,"end_time":651.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":647.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"With HubSpot and the landing pages we have in HubSpot.","index":163,"end_time":655.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":652.31,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Where did we land with the, like, the Behavioral intelligence pages, the other kind of funnel project pages that we had in there.","index":164,"end_time":665.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":656.47,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So it kind of got sidelined based on the web audit that you were running.","index":165,"end_time":670.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":166,"end_time":670.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":670.42,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We''re going to come up with a priority list from that because we decided that it wasn''t worth putting a bunch of effort into new web pages if we were going to think about it comprehensively pretty soon.","index":167,"end_time":680.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":168,"end_time":682.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":681.7,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Which in communication with HubSpot sounds like an upcoming project.","index":169,"end_time":686.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":170,"end_time":687.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":686.82,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"As well as the Banking Fraud Summit website.","index":171,"end_time":690.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":172,"end_time":693.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":692.67,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Which correct me if I''m wrong, but that is as far as I can see, just two pages.","index":173,"end_time":698.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s like max five, because.","index":174,"end_time":703.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":700.11,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All I see is there''s one page for past summits and then everything else is just hyperlinked on the homepage or anchor linked.","index":175,"end_time":713.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":176,"end_time":713.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think some of the actual.","index":177,"end_time":717.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":715.62,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Details pages.","index":178,"end_time":720.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":179,"end_time":721.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":180,"end_time":721.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s a little bit of a listing in here.","index":181,"end_time":723.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":182,"end_time":725.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And like color scheme and everything.","index":183,"end_time":728.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously it''s very different than the Threatmark branding.","index":184,"end_time":731.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that something we want to keep?","index":185,"end_time":732.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I assume we''ll have more conversations around this project.","index":186,"end_time":735.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s.","index":187,"end_time":736.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":736.1,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think we''ll have.","index":188,"end_time":737.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":736.98,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think it''s going to evolve.","index":189,"end_time":739.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":738.42,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"To be honest, the branding it uses at the moment, even kind of the name is pretty new for the last six months of this year, so I couldn''t tell you where it will end up.","index":190,"end_time":753.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":739.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":191,"end_time":755.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":754.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":192,"end_time":755.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":755.18,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":193,"end_time":756.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, well then I think we''re just waiting on Greg.","index":194,"end_time":767.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Kate.","index":195,"end_time":773.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also figure, you know, if we.","index":196,"end_time":775.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because last week''s meeting wasn''t super long.","index":197,"end_time":777.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we''ve got a lot of async communication going on as well.","index":198,"end_time":780.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we find that maybe we don''t need an hour for these, maybe we can jump back down to 30 or 45 as well.","index":199,"end_time":786.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":200,"end_time":790.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":789.91,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Sometimes an hour a week isn''t enough at all.","index":201,"end_time":792.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":790.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And then other times it''s like we''re.","index":202,"end_time":793.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":792.11,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":203,"end_time":794.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can always, you know, if it''s like, hey, we have a lot to go through, we can always, you know, update to have an hour.","index":204,"end_time":799.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":205,"end_time":800.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":799.96,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"There he is.","index":206,"end_time":809.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":207,"end_time":810.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":208,"end_time":811.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"No, no worries.","index":209,"end_time":812.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":811.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Long time no see, Greg.","index":210,"end_time":814.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know, right?","index":211,"end_time":815.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":814.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How was.","index":212,"end_time":818.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your last two hours?","index":213,"end_time":819.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Non stop.","index":214,"end_time":821.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s all right.","index":215,"end_time":824.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, we walked through just a few updates.","index":216,"end_time":828.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can rattle through those if you''d like.","index":217,"end_time":831.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But really the only thing that we have left is just going through the updates for the lead source and lead source specific.","index":218,"end_time":836.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s go through that instead.","index":219,"end_time":839.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":837.33,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So on this, obviously we have a lot of contacts that have been imported from Salesforce through hyperscales connections and integrations that they set up with, with Salesforce.","index":220,"end_time":851.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":841.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those are the only contact records that we didn''t update everything across the board for.","index":221,"end_time":855.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because it just takes a little bit more of like you have to go into each contact record to find the activity.","index":222,"end_time":859.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":855.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":223,"end_time":860.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":859.98,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":224,"end_time":860.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":860.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But everything else was updated.","index":225,"end_time":862.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all the.","index":226,"end_time":863.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":862.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The paid leads and everything that have come in since Salesforce Imports are updated.","index":227,"end_time":867.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":864.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":228,"end_time":869.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":868.22,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I saw what are we doing this automatically now?","index":229,"end_time":872.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":230,"end_time":873.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just have one question on the workflow that we''re setting up.","index":231,"end_time":876.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So set lead source.","index":232,"end_time":879.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":878.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing I just wanted to check is verifying that we want lead source and lead source specific to be other first attribution or most recent attribution.","index":233,"end_time":891.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think lead source should be first touch.","index":234,"end_time":898.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.61,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let''s just go first.","index":235,"end_time":901.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.05,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"First touch.","index":236,"end_time":902.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":902.01,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":237,"end_time":903.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"First on first, first touch, full send.","index":238,"end_time":906.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":903.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":239,"end_time":906.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":240,"end_time":907.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then we don''t even need a re enroll in here, which is great.","index":241,"end_time":910.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it just goes through a huge branch.","index":242,"end_time":913.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re just putting the final touches on this and then we''re going to test it and make sure that we''re all good.","index":243,"end_time":917.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":913.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":244,"end_time":918.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":245,"end_time":920.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":246,"end_time":921.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":921.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And it''s like organic social could get tricky.","index":247,"end_time":925.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For example, if someone comes from there and then downloads a website resource, they would most likely get tagged as website resource for filling out that form.","index":248,"end_time":933.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":249,"end_time":934.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":934.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":250,"end_time":935.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":934.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So there will be some.","index":251,"end_time":936.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some in betweens like that.","index":252,"end_time":937.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":253,"end_time":938.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":937.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But other than that, you can go through the contact records as well.","index":254,"end_time":940.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":938.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We updated a few thousand of them so they''re all showing in here.","index":255,"end_time":946.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":940.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the.","index":256,"end_time":949.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":949,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The fields are mapped properly to Salesforce, which is great.","index":257,"end_time":952.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":949.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I checked that I think last week to make sure they were.","index":258,"end_time":957,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":952.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, awesome.","index":259,"end_time":958.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":957.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":260,"end_time":959.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.94,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, so that was the update there.","index":261,"end_time":962.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":960.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll keep you updated when we get that automation set up in live.","index":262,"end_time":966.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And other than that, we talked through.","index":263,"end_time":969.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate''s going to send over the updated fraud lifecycle graphic so we can add that into the white paper.","index":264,"end_time":975.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Julia is working on the account list this week.","index":265,"end_time":980.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll finish the form addition to the homepage banner today and send that over to you guys.","index":266,"end_time":986.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":981.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m going to send over a savvy Cal link which is just our availability for booking an hour and a half in the first week of January for planning session.","index":267,"end_time":995.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate''s going to share a web audit that she''s done.","index":268,"end_time":998.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":996.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to produce Christmas graphic to post on socials and Christmas or holiday?","index":269,"end_time":1005.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a great question.","index":270,"end_time":1007.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1006.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Holidays is fine.","index":271,"end_time":1016.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1015.3,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":272,"end_time":1017.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1016.74,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The American in me is saying holiday, but I know you can get away with Christmas elsewhere.","index":273,"end_time":1025.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.22,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Make a holidays graphic.","index":274,"end_time":1029.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1027.859,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Make it holiday.","index":275,"end_time":1030.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1029.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, keep going.","index":276,"end_time":1032.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.46,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I think that was everything we have the latest episode will be ready this week as well from the Behind Enemy Lines podcast as well as the compilation video.","index":277,"end_time":1045.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1033.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So on the compilation, we were thinking about doing a Year in Review style post for that.","index":278,"end_time":1055.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1047.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I''m wondering if we want to do a holiday graphic and then like a Happy New Year graphic that we can then do.","index":279,"end_time":1064.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1056.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You know, behind Enemy Lines, a Year in Review type thing.","index":280,"end_time":1069.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1065.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then we should discuss if that''s something that we want to do a boosted post around.","index":281,"end_time":1077.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.7,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I think that might be part of the.","index":282,"end_time":1082.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1080.42,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The strategy too.","index":283,"end_time":1083.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1082.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''m thinking we probably want to publish that not the first week, like not January 2nd, but January, whatever that is.","index":284,"end_time":1094.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1084.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The fifth, sixth, that first full week of January.","index":285,"end_time":1097.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1094.18,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":286,"end_time":1099.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1098.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we had talked about publishing the newest episode on the 7th of January, but yeah, we can do the end of year on the 5th as well if you wanted to do that.","index":287,"end_time":1110.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1099.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":288,"end_time":1110.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1110.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is the new episode in the compilation?","index":289,"end_time":1113.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.25,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I can''t remember off the top of my head if it''s in the script.","index":290,"end_time":1118.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":291,"end_time":1118.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nina''s shaking her head as though it''s not.","index":292,"end_time":1120.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"No, it''s not.","index":293,"end_time":1122.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1120.81,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But we can.","index":294,"end_time":1123.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1122.49,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mean, we can put it.","index":295,"end_time":1124.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1123.21,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But it will just delay it for a couple.","index":296,"end_time":1126.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1124.89,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"No, don''t.","index":297,"end_time":1127.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1126.89,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Don''t put it in.","index":298,"end_time":1128.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.53,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Keep it out.","index":299,"end_time":1128.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.25,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''ll be a 20, 20, 26 episode and we''ll run the compilation first and then we''ll publish the next episode.","index":300,"end_time":1136.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.89,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And that''s good because that if we boost the compilation and we get anything off of that, then.","index":301,"end_time":1142.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1136.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Then we have those people organically for the next episode.","index":302,"end_time":1145.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1142.97,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":303,"end_time":1146.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1145.93,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And possibly some new guests.","index":304,"end_time":1148.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1147.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":305,"end_time":1149.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1149.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":306,"end_time":1150.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1150.34,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Fingers crossed.","index":307,"end_time":1151.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1150.78,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":308,"end_time":1152.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1151.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that we met with HubSpot this morning and there''s another call on Friday that I need to move something to be able to join that.","index":309,"end_time":1159.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1153.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Greg, is there anything on the HubSpot front that you wanted to talk through?","index":310,"end_time":1162.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you probably didn''t need to be on today''s call.","index":311,"end_time":1164.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1162.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think the Friday calls, the more relevant one for you.","index":312,"end_time":1166.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1164.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1167.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.98,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But just wanted to show my support.","index":314,"end_time":1168.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, appreciate it, Appreciate it.","index":315,"end_time":1171.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1169.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I think from my perspective, I think they cover off on most of the capability that we need.","index":316,"end_time":1180.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think that there''s.","index":317,"end_time":1183.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s some cost savings in there for us to switch, which, you know, is what we''re really looking for, to be completely honest.","index":318,"end_time":1189,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1183.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re.","index":319,"end_time":1189.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1189.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going through.","index":320,"end_time":1190.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1189.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''ve got our scissors out right now.","index":321,"end_time":1193.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1191.8,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I think the content one''s the one I''m more interested in from, like, how do we redefined what we''re doing?","index":322,"end_time":1205.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1195.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I think you have most of the context for that.","index":323,"end_time":1210.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right.","index":324,"end_time":1210.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1210.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":325,"end_time":1211.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.77,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We want to try out baking Fraud Summit, see how it works.","index":326,"end_time":1214.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1211.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"If it works well, we''ll go for it.","index":327,"end_time":1217.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1214.77,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I got the sense that we could coterm the contract so that way the content renewal aligns with our broader account renewal in June, which basically gives us a six month trial, if you will.","index":328,"end_time":1236.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Proof of concept.","index":329,"end_time":1237.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that''s how I''m thinking about it, is we''ll keep the WordPress site in a ready to roll back state and if we don''t like it, we''ll roll back and, and we won''t go forward.","index":330,"end_time":1250.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1237.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"If we do like it, then we''ll blow up the old WordPress site and start thinking about other exciting web challenges.","index":331,"end_time":1260.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":332,"end_time":1261.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1260.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":333,"end_time":1262.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":334,"end_time":1263,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And definitely want to talk a bit further through the Banking Fraud Summit as we get closer to that product or project.","index":335,"end_time":1267.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1263,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, like, do we want to change any branding?","index":336,"end_time":1270.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we want to go past, you know, the content on the site or rewrite anything, things like that?","index":337,"end_time":1275.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":338,"end_time":1276.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1275.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we''ll, we''ll scope that out if, if, if and when we feel like we''re gonna pull the trigger.","index":339,"end_time":1281.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1276.69,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":340,"end_time":1282.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1281.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":341,"end_time":1283.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1282.77,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":342,"end_time":1284.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else from your side?","index":343,"end_time":1285.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1284.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, do you think so, Julia?","index":344,"end_time":1295.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1292.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not from my side.","index":345,"end_time":1297.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1296.21,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":346,"end_time":1297.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I think, I think that''s, I think that''s what''s up.","index":347,"end_time":1301.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.89,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Do we need our call next week?","index":348,"end_time":1305.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1303.65,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I know you guys have a lot of.","index":349,"end_time":1309.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You mentioned a lot of vacation happening, so that is up to you.","index":350,"end_time":1312.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1309.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are in.","index":351,"end_time":1313.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we can probably go a sync via Slack.","index":352,"end_time":1323.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1315.81,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So next week and then I''ll be out the week following.","index":353,"end_time":1329.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1327.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that''s the 29th.","index":354,"end_time":1335.708,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.86,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"29th.","index":355,"end_time":1336.561,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1335.878,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"29th, yeah, the 29th.","index":356,"end_time":1338.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1336.732,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Kate, are you in on the 29th?","index":357,"end_time":1343.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1342.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''m in.","index":358,"end_time":1344.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1344.3,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"You are?","index":359,"end_time":1345.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1345.18,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Do you want to keep something on the books for then we can always.","index":360,"end_time":1349.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1346.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Keep it on and if anything pops up we can.","index":361,"end_time":1352.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1349.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we can remove it.","index":362,"end_time":1354.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If anything pops up, we can schedule something.","index":363,"end_time":1356.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1354.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s plan to do that for both next week and the week following because I have a feeling we can probably manage what we need to manage over Slack because we''re probably just working through the homepage thing, the recap video, the source automation stuff.","index":364,"end_time":1379.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1357.57,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So yeah, let''s do that.","index":365,"end_time":1382.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1380.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":366,"end_time":1382.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1382.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well I''ve just updated to have those two taken off.","index":367,"end_time":1386.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1383.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":368,"end_time":1389.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1388.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, we''ll be in touch with a few updates today and tomorrow and the next day regarding compilation videos, lead Source Automations homepage, everything like that.","index":369,"end_time":1397.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1389.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":370,"end_time":1398.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1398.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Kate, if you can just send over the web audit and the graphic for the fraud lifecycle, that would be great.","index":371,"end_time":1404.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1398.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll work on also the holiday graphic.","index":372,"end_time":1407.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so that''s going to be two graphics, right.","index":373,"end_time":1409.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One for holidays and one for New Year.","index":374,"end_time":1410.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1409.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":375,"end_time":1412.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.33,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":376,"end_time":1414.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1412.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nina, anything that I''m missing that you wanted to go through?","index":377,"end_time":1418.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1416.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not really.","index":378,"end_time":1420.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1420.33,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I just wanted to mention what I also talked with Colin that I don''t know if it''s something that concerns your ads, but the European Union is going to change its cookie policy.","index":379,"end_time":1432.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1421.29,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So next year all the pop ups for third party cookies will disappear and like all users can choose in their browser how if they want to allow third party cookies or anything.","index":380,"end_time":1444.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1432.65,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So it''s going to change the web traffic a little bit and all the information you can get from Google Ads.","index":381,"end_time":1450.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1444.67,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Oh, interesting.","index":382,"end_time":1453.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1451.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So for.","index":383,"end_time":1457.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1457.27,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is that just Google Ads?","index":384,"end_time":1460.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1459.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I mean they''re going to go broader implications.","index":385,"end_time":1466.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1463.03,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, yeah, but there''s where you''re going to see it first.","index":386,"end_time":1470.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1467.25,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So.","index":387,"end_time":1471.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1470.77,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But it''s going to go across all search engines.","index":388,"end_time":1475.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1472.69,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So Mozilla, Firefox, everything.","index":389,"end_time":1478.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1475.73,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":390,"end_time":1479.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1479.33,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So from a user perspective that feels like a better.","index":391,"end_time":1485.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1482.61,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean for user experience it''s great.","index":392,"end_time":1488.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1485.73,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So that are they.","index":393,"end_time":1492.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1491.42,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So when we do the, when we do the cookie consent we have categories of like essential analytics advertising.","index":394,"end_time":1499.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1494.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Are they categorizing the consent styles?","index":395,"end_time":1505.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1500.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know how it''s going to be, how it''s going to look exactly, but it''s going to, once they choose it, it''s going to be the same for every site.","index":396,"end_time":1513.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1506.779,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So I''m going to guess they''re going to, you know, say nothing.","index":397,"end_time":1518.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1513.98,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":398,"end_time":1520.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1519.79,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, new development.","index":399,"end_time":1522.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1521.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we got to keep our pulse on it.","index":400,"end_time":1524.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1522.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":401,"end_time":1526.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1526.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I, I almost wish we went to this cookie less world and just pulled the trigger.","index":402,"end_time":1531.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1526.75,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":403,"end_time":1533.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1532.829,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think Colin, I think ending.","index":404,"end_time":1536.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1533.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think one of the things that I''m super curious about with hosting a website on HubSpot is if the analytics that we get is becomes first party versus third party, if that makes sense.","index":405,"end_time":1555.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1536.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I haven''t been able to get a straight answer out of them on it.","index":406,"end_time":1560.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1556.86,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I kind of feel like we''re just gonna have to try it and see what happens.","index":407,"end_time":1564.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1560.46,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":408,"end_time":1565.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you gotten any read on how that works?","index":409,"end_time":1570.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1566.94,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it has a pretty similar hit rate to most browsers being like if you do have some privacy settings set that you''re not going to get tracked.","index":410,"end_time":1580.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1571.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Funny thing about that Greg is HubSpot actually reached out to me to ask about their cookie tracking capabilities and I said isn''t this what your engineering team should be able to answer right away.","index":411,"end_time":1592.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1581.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How is nobody else asking this question?","index":412,"end_time":1595.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1593.27,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":413,"end_time":1596.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1595.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was just shocked that they came to me for the question.","index":414,"end_time":1599.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1596.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was like, should I just do a bunch of research and answer them on their own product or should I push back on them answering their own question?","index":415,"end_time":1605.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So probably that one.","index":416,"end_time":1606.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, they haven''t responded since, so.","index":417,"end_time":1610.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1607.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because like, if I''m hosting.","index":418,"end_time":1615.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1612.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"If your server is hosting my website and your server is also the basis for analytics, the it should be close.","index":419,"end_time":1624.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1615.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Your server should be where you pull the analytics, not a JavaScript element that''s dependent upon a third party cookie.","index":420,"end_time":1631.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1624.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, like, to me, that feels like the simplest thing and.","index":421,"end_time":1637.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And like, yeah, you can anonymize and.","index":422,"end_time":1642.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1638.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And all that.","index":423,"end_time":1642.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1642.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":424,"end_time":1643.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1642.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But.","index":425,"end_time":1644.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1644.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, we''ll see.","index":426,"end_time":1646.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1644.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, but I wanted to fill you in on that.","index":427,"end_time":1649.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1647.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s hilarious.","index":428,"end_time":1650.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1649.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okie doke.","index":429,"end_time":1653.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1653.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":430,"end_time":1655.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1654.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, we''ll be in touch.","index":431,"end_time":1657.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1655.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If anything else pops up, please do let us know.","index":432,"end_time":1659.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1657.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":433,"end_time":1660.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1659.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And enjoy your vacations.","index":434,"end_time":1662.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1660.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I hope you both have some time, some downtime planned, so.","index":435,"end_time":1668.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1662.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, trying to figure that out.","index":436,"end_time":1670.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1668.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":437,"end_time":1671.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":438,"end_time":1671.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1671.04,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right, we''ll see you guys.","index":439,"end_time":1672.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1671.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Take care.","index":440,"end_time":1673.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1672.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Bye.","index":441,"end_time":1673.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.4,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Bye.","index":442,"end_time":1674.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1673.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-12-15T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,kate.burwood@threatmark.com,gregory.smith@threatmark.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,iulia.lungu@threatmark.com","kate.burwood@threatmark.com","gregory.smith@threatmark.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","iulia.lungu@threatmark.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC4C964YNAAS7YB9XBM56Y6E","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Confirmed homepage banner and form updates will be finalized and sent to Kate today.","Kate to share web audit findings and fraud lifecycle graphic for final integration.","Greg and Colin aligned lead source automation to track first-touch attribution in HubSpot.","Team decided to delay podcast release cadence restart until January 7, post-compilation launch.","Agreed to remove next two weekly calls and handle updates asynchronously via Slack."],"highlights":[{"quote":"First on first, first touch, full send.","speaker":"Greg Smith"},{"quote":"We''ll be in touch with a few updates today and tomorrow and the next day.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"There’s some cost savings in there for us to switch, which... is what we''re really looking for.","speaker":"Greg Smith"}],"topics":["attribution","planning","content","website","process"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-15T18:11:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Source Data Automation and Contact Management**\n\nThe team finalized the automation setup for updating **lead source** and **lead source specific fields**, focusing on **first touch attribution** to ensure accurate tracking of lead origins (14:53).\n\n- **Greg Smith confirmed** using first touch attribution for lead source fields to maintain consistency in lead tracking.\n- The automation excludes imported Salesforce contacts due to complex activity data embedded in integrations, requiring manual updates.\n- Colin Costigan reported several thousand contacts have already been updated, with fields properly mapped to Salesforce for seamless CRM integration.\n- The team plans to test and activate the workflow soon, expecting improved lead source accuracy and reporting for marketing and sales efforts.\n\n## **Content and Marketing Campaign Planning**\n\nThe team scheduled content releases and marketing materials to maintain engagement through the holiday and early new year period (08:56).\n\n- The **Peter Taylor podcast episode** was published, with the next episode planned for **January 7th**, initiating a regular publishing cadence.\n- The **year-end compilation video** will be ready this week and is slated for release on **January 5th** as a “Year in Review” post to boost engagement before the new episode.\n- Greg suggested creating two separate holiday graphics: one for general **holiday greetings** and another for **New Year**, to support social media and partner outreach.\n- The team is considering boosting the compilation video post to maximize reach and build momentum for upcoming episodes.\n\n## **Product and Website Development Priorities**\n\nThe team reprioritized web development tasks based on recent audits and upcoming projects to optimize resource use (11:06).\n\n- Web audit led by Kate ThreatMark identified low-effort fixes and improvements, which she will share today for rapid implementation.\n- The Behavioral Intelligence funnel pages were deprioritized pending a more comprehensive web strategy, coordinated with HubSpot’s upcoming project.\n- The **Banking Fraud Summit website** currently includes about **five pages**, with branding still evolving; further discussions planned as the project progresses.\n- The team will keep the existing WordPress site ready as a fallback while trialing HubSpot for hosting, allowing a six-month proof of concept before fully committing.\n\n## **HubSpot Integration and Cost Optimization**\n\nHubSpot’s evolving capabilities and contract timing offer potential cost savings and enhanced content management (19:29).\n\n- Greg Smith highlighted expected cost savings by consolidating content and sales outreach tools within HubSpot.\n- The team aims to coterm the HubSpot contract with broader account renewals in **June**, allowing a six-month trial period.\n- Pending successful trial results, the plan is to fully migrate from WordPress to HubSpot, simplifying management and improving integration.\n- Monitoring HubSpot analytics capabilities is critical, especially around first-party vs. third-party cookie tracking, to anticipate impacts from upcoming **EU cookie policy changes**.\n\n## **Process Adjustments and Meeting Cadence**\n\nThe team plans to reduce synchronous meeting time in favor of more asynchronous communication during the holiday period to maintain productivity (13:09).\n\n- Colin proposed reducing weekly meetings from one hour to **30–45 minutes** based on workload.\n- Greg and Kate agreed to rely more on Slack for updates the week of **December 29th** and the following week, reserving meetings only if needed.\n- A **SavvyCal link** will be shared to schedule the **2026 planning session** in the first week of January for about **90 minutes**.\n- This flexible approach balances team availability with ongoing deliverables during a high-vacation period.\n\n## **External Factors Impacting Marketing Analytics**\n\nUpcoming regulatory changes in the EU will significantly alter cookie tracking and web analytics, affecting campaign measurement (23:40).\n\n- Nina Belina warned that from next year, **third-party cookie pop-ups** will disappear across browsers, shifting control to user browser settings.\n- This change will impact data collection for **Google Ads** and other search engines, requiring adjustments in tracking strategies.\n- Greg stressed the importance of understanding if HubSpot hosting enables **first-party analytics** to mitigate tracking losses.\n- The team will monitor these developments closely to adapt marketing measurement and maintain data quality.","outline":null,"keywords":["lead source automation","holiday marketing graphic","podcast scheduling","HubSpot migration","web audit","EU cookie policy"],"overview":"- **Lead Source Automation:** Team finalized setup for lead source tracking, improving lead origin accuracy and reporting for sales.\n- **Content Schedule:** Holiday content releases planned, including a Year in Review video on January 5th and regular podcast episodes starting January 7th.\n- **Web Development Priorities:** Low-effort improvements identified; HubSpot project strategy aligned with Behavioral Intelligence pages still pending.\n- **HubSpot Integration:** Cost savings expected by consolidating tools; contract renewal in June with six-month trial to assess migration.\n- **Meeting Adjustments:** Weekly meetings reduced to 30-45 minutes; emphasis on Slack for updates during holiday period to enhance productivity.\n- **Regulatory Changes Impact:** Upcoming EU cookie policy to eliminate third-party cookies, necessitating changes in tracking and data collection strategies.","action_items":"\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nSend updated fraud lifecycle graphic and text for white paper inclusion (02:10)\nShare web audit report with recommended fixes and improvements (05:20)\nDeliver newsletter and monthly article briefs (05:25)\nRequest creation of simple holiday graphic for social media and partner distribution using inclusive themes (05:45)\nConfirm availability and coordinate January planning meeting via SavvyCal link (03:40)\n\n**Iulia Lungu**\nComplete target account list by the end of this week (02:40)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize homepage banner updates on test site and send for approval; then push live (03:05)\nSend SavvyCal scheduling link for January 2026 planning session (03:35)\nCoordinate with team to produce and schedule holiday and New Year graphics (16:50)\nOversee end-of-year compilation video and coordinate release timing (07:50)\n\n**Greg Smith**\nJoin meeting to discuss lead source and lead source-specific automation workflow and confirm first-touch attribution setup (14:00)\nMonitor HubSpot migration, evaluate Banking Fraud Summit site readiness, and decide on potential platform switch after trial (19:40)\nManage communication on HubSpot analytics and technical implications of tracking changes (26:00)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nAdvise team about EU cookie regulation changes affecting tracking and ad data, guide strategy adjustments accordingly (23:20)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"4d787437-755d-4c17-a109-d6e518121432","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
    '2025-12-15 15:34:59.927425+00',
    '2025-12-15 15:34:59.927425+00'
  )
  RETURNING meeting_id, contract_id
)
INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Lead Source Data Automation and Contact Management**

The team finalized the automation setup for updating **lead source** and **lead source specific fields**, focusing on **first touch attribution** to ensure accurate tracking of lead origins (14:53).

- **Greg Smith confirmed** using first touch attribution for lead source fields to maintain consistency in lead tracking.
- The automation excludes imported Salesforce contacts due to complex activity data embedded in integrations, requiring manual updates.
- Colin Costigan reported several thousand contacts have already been updated, with fields properly mapped to Salesforce for seamless CRM integration.
- The team plans to test and activate the workflow soon, expecting improved lead source accuracy and reporting for marketing and sales efforts.

## **Content and Marketing Campaign Planning**

The team scheduled content releases and marketing materials to maintain engagement through the holiday and early new year period (08:56).

- The **Peter Taylor podcast episode** was published, with the next episode planned for **January 7th**, initiating a regular publishing cadence.
- The **year-end compilation video** will be ready this week and is slated for release on **January 5th** as a “Year in Review” post to boost engagement before the new episode.
- Greg suggested creating two separate holiday graphics: one for general **holiday greetings** and another for **New Year**, to support social media and partner outreach.
- The team is considering boosting the compilation video post to maximize reach and build momentum for upcoming episodes.

## **Product and Website Development Priorities**

The team reprioritized web development tasks based on recent audits and upcoming projects to optimize resource use (11:06).

- Web audit led by Kate ThreatMark identified low-effort fixes and improvements, which she will share today for rapid implementation.
- The Behavioral Intelligence funnel pages were deprioritized pending a more comprehensive web strategy, coordinated with HubSpot’s upcoming project.
- The **Banking Fraud Summit website** currently includes about **five pages**, with branding still evolving; further discussions planned as the project progresses.
- The team will keep the existing WordPress site ready as a fallback while trialing HubSpot for hosting, allowing a six-month proof of concept before fully committing.

## **HubSpot Integration and Cost Optimization**

HubSpot’s evolving capabilities and contract timing offer potential cost savings and enhanced content management (19:29).

- Greg Smith highlighted expected cost savings by consolidating content and sales outreach tools within HubSpot.
- The team aims to coterm the HubSpot contract with broader account renewals in **June**, allowing a six-month trial period.
- Pending successful trial results, the plan is to fully migrate from WordPress to HubSpot, simplifying management and improving integration.
- Monitoring HubSpot analytics capabilities is critical, especially around first-party vs. third-party cookie tracking, to anticipate impacts from upcoming **EU cookie policy changes**.

## **Process Adjustments and Meeting Cadence**

The team plans to reduce synchronous meeting time in favor of more asynchronous communication during the holiday period to maintain productivity (13:09).

- Colin proposed reducing weekly meetings from one hour to **30–45 minutes** based on workload.
- Greg and Kate agreed to rely more on Slack for updates the week of **December 29th** and the following week, reserving meetings only if needed.
- A **SavvyCal link** will be shared to schedule the **2026 planning session** in the first week of January for about **90 minutes**.
- This flexible approach balances team availability with ongoing deliverables during a high-vacation period.

## **External Factors Impacting Marketing Analytics**

Upcoming regulatory changes in the EU will significantly alter cookie tracking and web analytics, affecting campaign measurement (23:40).

- Nina Belina warned that from next year, **third-party cookie pop-ups** will disappear across browsers, shifting control to user browser settings.
- This change will impact data collection for **Google Ads** and other search engines, requiring adjustments in tracking strategies.
- Greg stressed the importance of understanding if HubSpot hosting enables **first-party analytics** to mitigate tracking losses.
- The team will monitor these developments closely to adapt marketing measurement and maintain data quality.',
  '2025-12-15 15:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send updated fraud lifecycle graphic and text for white paper inclusion (02:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Share web audit report with recommended fixes and improvements (05:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Deliver newsletter and monthly article briefs (05:25)","completed":false},{"text":"Request creation of simple holiday graphic for social media and partner distribution using inclusive themes (05:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm availability and coordinate January planning meeting via SavvyCal link (03:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Complete target account list by the end of this week (02:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Finalize homepage banner updates on test site and send for approval; then push live (03:05)","completed":false},{"text":"Send SavvyCal scheduling link for January 2026 planning session (03:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with team to produce and schedule holiday and New Year graphics (16:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Oversee end-of-year compilation video and coordinate release timing (07:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Join meeting to discuss lead source and lead source-specific automation workflow and confirm first-touch attribution setup (14:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor HubSpot migration, evaluate Banking Fraud Summit site readiness, and decide on potential platform switch after trial (19:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Manage communication on HubSpot analytics and technical implications of tracking changes (26:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Advise team about EU cookie regulation changes affecting tracking and ad data, guide strategy adjustments accordingly (23:20)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Rugged Robotics <> MiD Bi-Weekly (2025-12-10 15:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'db0afec5-85bc-41b0-8c0f-79b368eb3b16',
    '2025-12-10 15:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBZB5MN2VZFKGEDNJDQ0XM4S',
    'Rugged Robotics <> MiD Bi-Weekly',
    '{"Rob","Tristan Pelligrino"}'::text[],
    1935,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84801960534?pwd=tq9BFJBUCprJPJ0W7NRoAlJYH7bZXD.1&jst=2',
    '{"id":"01KBZB5MN2VZFKGEDNJDQ0XM4S","title":"Rugged Robotics <> MiD Bi-Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **Data Sourcing and AI Filtering for Prospect Lists**\n\nThe team refined the prospect list by combining AI-driven filters with domain and job title data to improve targeting accuracy.\n\n- **The master company list consists of 283 rows**, split between hyperscaler and non-hyperscaler companies, with **five hyperscalers including Oracle recently added** (02:16)\n    - Hyperscaler prospects are filtered by domain, job titles, seniority, and profile keywords to focus on likely candidates\n    - Tristan explained they use OpenAI via CLAY to generate a \"prospect qualify\" score based on LinkedIn profile summaries, enabling a smarter filter than traditional keyword matching\n    - A sample AI test on 10 profiles showed about **30% of prospects meet criteria**, suggesting around **1,500 qualified prospects** when applied to the full database\n    - AI helps identify infrastructure-related roles but struggles to perfectly separate software vs. construction roles, requiring ongoing prompt refinement\n\n- **Non-hyperscaler list filtering reduced 3,000 companies to about 500 prospects without AI**, capturing more construction-specific titles but fewer varied roles (12:59)\n    - Rob suggested differentiating project manager titles by company type, allowing inclusion of \"project manager\" for general contractors but not hyperscalers\n    - Location filtering to exclude prospects outside the US was planned to improve relevance\n    - The team agreed to exclude Amazon and review key client domains like Turner to avoid duplicates or irrelevant targets\n    - Tristan will provide Rob CSV exports for validation and job title lists to refine filters (15:39)\n\n- **Rob requested exploring a reverse LinkedIn API approach** to retrieve all job titles at specific companies for better title coverage and to identify possible filtering gaps (16:01)\n    - Tristan to attempt creating a company table with job titles for a few key companies like Turner and Vanderla to give Rob a clear view (17:41)\n    - Rob plans to analyze this data to address AI’s limitations and uncover missing roles (16:19)\n\n## **Email Outreach Strategy and Content Adjustments**\n\nEmail messaging was reviewed with a focus on improving engagement and avoiding spam filters.\n\n- **The first email currently avoids hyperlinks to reduce spam risk but may include domain names in parentheses**, as suggested by Tristan (20:15)\n    - Rob proposed switching case studies from PDFs to website-based success stories, making links more relevant and clickable (20:47)\n    - A hyperlink could be introduced later in the sequence (emails 4 or 5) to nurture interest before asking for clicks (21:21)\n    - Adding a line like \"Interested in learning more?\" to the first email was agreed to increase response rates (21:50)\n\n## **Website Staging Environment and Content Management**\n\nRob is gaining control over the WordPress site but needs guidance on managing page hierarchy and template structures.\n\n- **Rob is comfortable editing text and photos but cautious about deleting parent pages that remove child pages**, which risks losing important content (23:10)\n    - Tristan recommended recording a Loom video to document specific deletion questions for the development team to assist (24:08)\n    - Demir, who built the staging environment and new pages, remains the best contact for complex WordPress questions (22:48)\n    - Tristan explained the site uses advanced custom fields (ACF) and PHP template files, making it difficult to visualize page assembly without developer support (25:40)\n    - Rob is learning the relationship between templates, layouts, and flexible content fields but finds it challenging to identify where front-end views correspond to backend templates (28:00)\n    - Tristan showed the theme file editor and explained the PHP snippets linked to layout components, highlighting the complexity for non-developers (27:56)\n    - Rob plans to mostly work within existing frameworks and carefully remove sections, knowing he can restore anything if needed (31:29)\n\n## **Next Steps and Deliverables**\n\nClear follow-up tasks and information exchange were planned to refine prospect data and support website management.\n\n- Tristan will send Rob the current prospect lists, including company and job title tables, by the end of the day for review and validation (31:58)\n- Tristan will build location filters and exclude certain domains, per Rob’s input, to improve list quality (14:44)\n- Rob will analyze job title exports and explore LinkedIn API data to identify gaps and adjust filters accordingly (16:01)\n- Rob will prepare specific questions and video walkthroughs regarding WordPress page deletions and template concerns for Demir or Tristan’s team to address (24:08)\n- Tristan offered to provide hands-on support for complex website updates beyond Rob’s scope (24:43)","outline":null,"keywords":["Clay database","AI filtering","LinkedIn profiles","WordPress architecture","email campaign","construction project management"],"overview":"- **Refined Prospect List:** Combined AI filters with job data; master list has 283 companies, including five new hyperscalers.  \n- **Qualified Prospects Estimation:** AI tested on 10 profiles predicted 1,500 likely matches from full database with 30% success rate.  \n- **Non-Hyperscaler Targets:** Filtered down from 3,000 to 500, focusing on relevant construction titles and excluding Amazon.  \n- **Email Strategy Revamp:** First email will avoid hyperlinks; later messages may include clickable content to boost engagement.  \n- **Website Control Challenges:** Rob is editing WordPress but needs guidance on hierarchy and parent/child page management.  \n- **Next Steps Defined:** Tristan will provide prospect lists; Rob to analyze job titles and prepare WordPress questions for clarification.","action_items":"\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nApply location-based filters to company and contact database, excluding non-US and specific clients (e.g., Amazon) (14:44)\nExport comprehensive job title lists from selected companies’ data for Rob''s review and refinement (19:51)\nSend CSV exports of filtered prospect lists to Rob for validation (15:39)\nCoordinate with Demir on any technical website questions forwarded from Rob (24:43)\n\n**Rob**\nValidate AI-filtered prospect CSVs and provide feedback on relevancy (15:39)\nPrepare Loom video or detailed questions on WordPress page deletion and site management for technical support (24:21)\nTest manual website edits in staging, primarily text and images, while avoiding risky deletions without guidance (23:45)\nProvide sample companies for generating comprehensive job title datasets and review discrepancies (17:41)\n"},"duration":32.25,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Rob"},{"id":1,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"}],"sentences":[{"text":"There we go.","index":0,"end_time":22.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.08,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah, I can hear you.","index":1,"end_time":25.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How you doing, Rob?","index":2,"end_time":26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":25.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":26.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.63,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Bluetooth.","index":4,"end_time":27.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.27,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"A little funky scoring, but yeah, that''s what it is.","index":5,"end_time":32.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.91,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"I still go wired just because of those situations like you bounce from Zoom to Google Meets or something and it just stops working.","index":6,"end_time":40.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I go the old fashioned way.","index":7,"end_time":43.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But better for your brain if you''re.","index":8,"end_time":47.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.27,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":9,"end_time":48.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"RFK focused.","index":10,"end_time":50.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.79,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Kylan person.","index":11,"end_time":51.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.63,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":12,"end_time":53.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, good.","index":13,"end_time":54.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ve got some things just building on Monday, got clay updated, some things I want to go through with you there.","index":14,"end_time":64.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we built those yesterday.","index":15,"end_time":66.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll also just explain like how we got to the list too.","index":16,"end_time":69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think it might be helpful.","index":17,"end_time":70.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Took a look at the emails that we could talk.","index":18,"end_time":73.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No revolutionary comments there.","index":19,"end_time":76.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I just had one comment on the first email and then I know we wanted to talk about website.","index":20,"end_time":80.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":76.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know you were taking a look at that yesterday.","index":21,"end_time":82.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So those are the big things I had this morning.","index":22,"end_time":85.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What about your side?","index":23,"end_time":87.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s perfect.","index":24,"end_time":89.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.22,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"I saw the.","index":25,"end_time":91.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.3,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"If it''s that one comment on the word thing.","index":26,"end_time":94.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.82,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"I saw that.","index":27,"end_time":95.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.22,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Okay.","index":28,"end_time":96.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, you probably got a notification.","index":29,"end_time":97.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":30,"end_time":99.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.98,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"And then website.","index":31,"end_time":100.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.22,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"I have an idea kind of going through the structure that I wanted to bounce off you.","index":32,"end_time":106.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":100.46,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"So I think we''re are relatively aligned, but.","index":33,"end_time":109.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.98,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"All right, where do you want to start?","index":34,"end_time":117.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What''s the best.","index":35,"end_time":119.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let''s start with the clay stuff and we can kind of go through your one.","index":36,"end_time":124.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.08,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"All right, let me share my screen here.","index":37,"end_time":127.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I''ll start.","index":38,"end_time":131.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So here''s the canvas.","index":39,"end_time":133.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Can you see my screen?","index":40,"end_time":134.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":133.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yep, yep.","index":41,"end_time":136.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.87,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"All right, so here, here''s the canvas and basically this maps the, the data sources and how they''re.","index":42,"end_time":142.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":136.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"They''re basically built off.","index":43,"end_time":144.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":143.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"A clay search using a variety of databases.","index":44,"end_time":150.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":146.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But effectively what we do in this situation is we get a top list of companies and so, so this master table here has 283 rows that you can see.","index":45,"end_time":161.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":150.349,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And let me see, let me increase that a little bit.","index":46,"end_time":164.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":161.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we''re just pulling in domains from those lists.","index":47,"end_time":168.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":165.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s what we did.","index":48,"end_time":169.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":168.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We just upload CSV, use that in clay, go out, pull all the elements of those companies and then we''re able to use that list building later on.","index":49,"end_time":182.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":169.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So let me just double click on that.","index":50,"end_time":184.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So here''s a couple views.","index":51,"end_time":188.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So what I did is there''s a hyperscaler view.","index":52,"end_time":191.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So these are the five.","index":53,"end_time":192.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know we wanted to add Oracle back into the hyperscaler.","index":54,"end_time":195.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that was placed here.","index":55,"end_time":198.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then the alternative view is we''re excluding hyperscalers from that list of 283.","index":56,"end_time":204.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this gives us the 278 that we''re left with.","index":57,"end_time":207.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":204.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s kind of like our universe there.","index":58,"end_time":210.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":207.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So then from there we''re able to build the actual find people list from there from that database.","index":59,"end_time":220.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And that''s where we have filters here.","index":60,"end_time":222.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then we''re left with the hyperscaler and the non hyperscaler people list based on the criteria that we set, sorry in the filter here on this side.","index":61,"end_time":235.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So for the hyperscalers we use obviously the domain because that''s pulling from the, the filter itself.","index":62,"end_time":243.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then we excluded keywords and job titles.","index":63,"end_time":248.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":243.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''re pulling in a list of job titles that, that you know, we''ve mapped out.","index":64,"end_time":256.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":250.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then there''s also.","index":65,"end_time":258.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, seniority levels that we put in there.","index":66,"end_time":263.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":260.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then also basically created a list of profile keywords that if any of these appear, it''s more likely that they could be a candidate.","index":67,"end_time":272.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So kind of like three layers there.","index":68,"end_time":274.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That leaves us with.","index":69,"end_time":277.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So let me go to the hyperscaler list.","index":70,"end_time":279.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"These are the large organizations obviously.","index":71,"end_time":282.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so you see the domains over here.","index":72,"end_time":287.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The one thing I wanted to show you is I want to just go through like how we do an AI filter on top of this and haven''t run it for the whole database because these take up credits.","index":73,"end_time":298.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I have done a sample set of 10 that I wanted to go through with you.","index":74,"end_time":300.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So what we do first off is we Pull in the LinkedIn profile summary of that specific person.","index":75,"end_time":307.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We found that that''s helpful.","index":76,"end_time":309.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"A lot of people have like some information in there about us or you know, there''s something that we can detect in their, their job role and description and their profile about what they do.","index":77,"end_time":319.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Some people have information there, some, some don''t, but it gives us a good snapshot of what exists.","index":78,"end_time":324.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s where we get this job history summary that is put together, assembled, and then we can use this field along with others in an actual prospect qualify column.","index":79,"end_time":338.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is where we''re using, it''s called a CLAY agent.","index":80,"end_time":344.569,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we''re using OpenAI to run a prompt here.","index":81,"end_time":350.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.569,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so you can see we can tune this like basically if you have some other things that you want to uses criteria.","index":82,"end_time":358.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":350.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And this is where Clay gets a little bit more powerful because we''re able to use AI to, to soften the filters or add a little bit more intelligence than just a hard filter on a field, you know what I''m saying?","index":83,"end_time":372.399,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, it can look at the context of the company, the job description, and come up with a probability that this would be a prospect for what we''re looking for.","index":84,"end_time":382.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.399,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is how we typically do it with a title and history.","index":85,"end_time":386.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But then I''m just wrapping it with some.","index":86,"end_time":388.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Some other context that.","index":87,"end_time":390.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That we can use.","index":88,"end_time":390.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s a little background how we got here.","index":89,"end_time":394.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But you know, obviously I want to get some insights from you on how we can maybe make this work, you know, a little better for you.","index":90,"end_time":401.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":394.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then obviously there''s some results here on the right that we could validate just to see if it is giving us the intended filter.","index":91,"end_time":409.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":92,"end_time":413.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":411.69,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"So I could pull up.","index":93,"end_time":416.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You want me to pull up some that met the criteria and see if it works.","index":94,"end_time":418.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Can you go over to which there are actual titles?","index":95,"end_time":423.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":419.61,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah, Technical Program Manager.","index":96,"end_time":425.849,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.37,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"For two, Cloud Operations.","index":97,"end_time":434.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.93,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Row two.","index":98,"end_time":436.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.37,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"What is it?","index":99,"end_time":436.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.5,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"What does the AI say at the end?","index":100,"end_time":438.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.98,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"No, no.","index":101,"end_time":440.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.18,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Okay.","index":102,"end_time":441.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.06,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Is there a compute.","index":103,"end_time":446.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.06,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"What''s the title for one?","index":104,"end_time":447.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.14,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":105,"end_time":447.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.38,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah, let me see.","index":106,"end_time":450.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Program Engineering Manager.","index":107,"end_time":451.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.14,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":108,"end_time":452.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.02,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Senior Engineering Manager.","index":109,"end_time":457.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.78,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Fourteen engineers and data scientists.","index":110,"end_time":459.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.7,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"That''s five.","index":111,"end_time":460.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.9,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"What does five say?","index":112,"end_time":462.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.22,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Five is nose.","index":113,"end_time":465.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well.","index":114,"end_time":465.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Four did meet.","index":115,"end_time":468.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And let me see, this was this one.","index":116,"end_time":474.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":470.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I was surprised it did meet.","index":117,"end_time":476.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Looked like mostly software to me.","index":118,"end_time":478.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There are some keywords that trigger.","index":119,"end_time":481.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But this to me, like the infrastructure piece sometimes will cloud the.","index":120,"end_time":488.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":481.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, it''s hard.","index":121,"end_time":490.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s hard because there''s like a whole software layer of infrastructure that makes.","index":122,"end_time":494.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.11,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":123,"end_time":494.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The keyword stuff tougher.","index":124,"end_time":496.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.07,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"What''s our actual.","index":125,"end_time":497.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":496.83,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Go down to our actual title and roles?","index":126,"end_time":500.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.11,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":127,"end_time":501.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":500.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Senior Principal Product and Technical Program Management.","index":128,"end_time":505.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And let me see what''s on the latest.","index":129,"end_time":506.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":505.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, Program Manager.","index":130,"end_time":509.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":508.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s what I mean.","index":131,"end_time":509.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.31,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"That''s what''s driving is the cloud infrastructure.","index":132,"end_time":512.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.95,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":133,"end_time":513.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I can.","index":134,"end_time":517.179,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":516.699,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I could do some more work to try to pull out software and you know, we''ll create maybe a bigger prompt.","index":135,"end_time":524.059,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.499,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But it looks like this one I did not feel should meet.","index":136,"end_time":528.219,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.539,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then this one actually let me pull this guy up here.","index":137,"end_time":531.979,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.539,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This one felt closer.","index":138,"end_time":535.499,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":532.619,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":139,"end_time":540.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.07,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Quality assurance, highly accomplished.","index":140,"end_time":547.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":543.51,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"And we go to background here.","index":141,"end_time":553.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":550.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then the.","index":142,"end_time":557.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.95,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah, this is the main thing.","index":143,"end_time":561.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":559.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Construction projects from inception to complete.","index":144,"end_time":566.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean.","index":145,"end_time":566.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.39,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah, if.","index":146,"end_time":569.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.11,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"And then what''s his title?","index":147,"end_time":572.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.55,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":148,"end_time":574.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":573.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Senior Construction Manager, qa.","index":149,"end_time":578.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":575.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean this would be the one, if we caught it would be great.","index":150,"end_time":586.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.91,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"I mean, it''s interesting why it''s not why it''s saying no.","index":151,"end_time":591.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.03,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Oh, no.","index":152,"end_time":592.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":592.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This one says yes.","index":153,"end_time":593.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":592.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":154,"end_time":594.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.06,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":155,"end_time":595.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":594.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That one seemed to.","index":156,"end_time":596.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":595.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"To meet like basically what we had had provided.","index":157,"end_time":600.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That one made sense to me.","index":158,"end_time":601.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":600.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then I think this one was.","index":159,"end_time":603.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Was also fine.","index":160,"end_time":604.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"John Harnish, Senior Engineering Manager.","index":161,"end_time":607.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":604.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Data Center Management.","index":162,"end_time":614.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":163,"end_time":614.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, buildings run better, so everyone.","index":164,"end_time":620.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So kind of infrastructure with the.","index":165,"end_time":623.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The physical space.","index":166,"end_time":624.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":623.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s what was detected here.","index":167,"end_time":626.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":624.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think this one''s fine.","index":168,"end_time":637.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":635.46,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"It''s an engineering manager in this space.","index":169,"end_time":639.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.38,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"It''s weird that he worked at ever, like Evernote before that.","index":170,"end_time":645.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":640.42,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Like.","index":171,"end_time":646.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.7,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":172,"end_time":646.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What was that?","index":173,"end_time":647.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let me see.","index":174,"end_time":647.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I didn''t go security.","index":175,"end_time":650.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So he ran like the internal software teams at Evernote, which is kind of a weird.","index":176,"end_time":656.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":651.19,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"He was a software developer manager and the role he came back to fit.","index":177,"end_time":662.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.75,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"So it''s just.","index":178,"end_time":663.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.15,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":179,"end_time":665.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":664.31,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"I think it''s fine.","index":180,"end_time":666.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.71,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Like we''re not gonna self correct everything.","index":181,"end_time":668.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.55,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"It''s just kind of a weird.","index":182,"end_time":669.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.19,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"It is.","index":183,"end_time":670.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The one thing I.","index":184,"end_time":671.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The one thing I did not do, Rob, is pulling their.","index":185,"end_time":673.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":671.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Their past job experience.","index":186,"end_time":675.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That might be a layer that I could fold in.","index":187,"end_time":677.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I could go back to.","index":188,"end_time":679.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":678.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":189,"end_time":680.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I don''t think we need.","index":190,"end_time":681.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.53,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Okay.","index":191,"end_time":682.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, I''d rather hit people who are not super.","index":192,"end_time":685.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.93,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Like, I''d rather go a little bit wider than.","index":193,"end_time":689.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.29,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"It''s just weird that he''s like fulfillment technologies and it''s like cloud.","index":194,"end_time":695.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":691.09,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"I think he''s an edge case that I don''t think too much about.","index":195,"end_time":701.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.85,"speaker_na