no"},{"text":"And.","index":551,"end_time":1826.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1826.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Page flexible content.","index":552,"end_time":1831.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1829.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":553,"end_time":1832.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1832.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is where we''ll have to figure out.","index":554,"end_time":1834.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1832.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is where they are.","index":555,"end_time":1837.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1836.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So these are basically the.","index":556,"end_time":1839.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1837.969,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The code snippets that match Rob to.","index":557,"end_time":1842.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1839.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"To those.","index":558,"end_time":1843.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1842.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":559,"end_time":1844.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1843.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So like this is the actual PHP snippet.","index":560,"end_time":1847.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1844.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s pretty confusing but that''s how it''s assembled.","index":561,"end_time":1852.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1848.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s really hard for someone like you on the front end to figure how this comes together.","index":562,"end_time":1857.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1852.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean in theory do they build.","index":563,"end_time":1860.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1858.77,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Mock like visuals place though to get like a name that makes sense to you though, you know?","index":564,"end_time":1866.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1860.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":565,"end_time":1867.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1866.69,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":566,"end_time":1867.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1867.05,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"I mean it doesn''t show what the front end looks like.","index":567,"end_time":1871.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1868.29,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"No.","index":568,"end_time":1872.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1871.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Anywhere in here you have to.","index":569,"end_time":1873.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1872.17,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"That''s the disadvantage because it''s just using the, the PHP template file and because all these are.","index":570,"end_time":1880.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1874.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are just short code snippets and you don''t actually see it until you assemble a full page.","index":571,"end_time":1886.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1880.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":572,"end_time":1890.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1889.82,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Okay, that''s fine.","index":573,"end_time":1891.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1890.38,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":574,"end_time":1891.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1891.42,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":575,"end_time":1892.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1891.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Mostly work within the existing framework because it''s very even within these custom ones.","index":576,"end_time":1898.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1894.14,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"It''s very easy to, like, remove stuff like the.","index":577,"end_time":1903.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1898.82,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"You can very clearly.","index":578,"end_time":1905.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1904.26,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Like.","index":579,"end_time":1905.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1905.46,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"I mean, the simplest version is, like, the employee one.","index":580,"end_time":1908.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1906.42,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"It''s, like, adding and.","index":581,"end_time":1909.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1908.9,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":582,"end_time":1912.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1911.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":583,"end_time":1914.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1914.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":584,"end_time":1916.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1915.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":585,"end_time":1917.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1916.9,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Thank you for the time.","index":586,"end_time":1918.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1917.58,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"Yep.","index":587,"end_time":1919.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1918.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Appreciate it, Rob.","index":588,"end_time":1920.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1919.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, we''ll be in touch.","index":589,"end_time":1921.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1920.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll send you, you know, some of these lists here today, and then we''ll go from there.","index":590,"end_time":1925.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1921.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":591,"end_time":1926.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1925.54,"speaker_name":"Rob"},{"text":"All right, man.","index":592,"end_time":1926.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1926.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Thanks, Rob.","index":593,"end_time":1927.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1926.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Bye.","index":594,"end_time":1928.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1927.94,"speaker_name":"Rob"}],"dateString":"2025-12-10T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84801960534?pwd=tq9BFJBUCprJPJ0W7NRoAlJYH7bZXD.1&jst=2","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,rob@rugged-robotics.com,kiyan.klocker@marketersindemand.com","rob@rugged-robotics.com","kiyan.klocker@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBZB5MN2VZFKGEDNJDQ0XM4S","organizer_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Clarified AI filtering logic in Clay to improve candidate relevance for hyperscaler targeting.","Agreed to filter project managers differently across hyperscalers and non-hyperscalers for better accuracy.","Rob requested job title exports for specific companies to refine outreach logic.","Reviewed email copy adjustments and agreed to soft call-to-action with no links in Email 1.","Confirmed Rob will revise website content directly, with Demir available for deeper WordPress questions."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think it''s fine. Like we''re not gonna self correct everything.","speaker":"Rob"},{"quote":"I''ll send you, you know, some of these lists here today, and then we''ll go from there.","speaker":"Tristan Pelligrino"}],"topics":["filters","delivery","AI","website"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-15T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Data Sourcing and AI Filtering for Prospect Lists**\n\nThe team refined the prospect list by combining AI-driven filters with domain and job title data to improve targeting accuracy.\n\n- **The master company list consists of 283 rows**, split between hyperscaler and non-hyperscaler companies, with **five hyperscalers including Oracle recently added** (02:16)\n    - Hyperscaler prospects are filtered by domain, job titles, seniority, and profile keywords to focus on likely candidates\n    - Tristan explained they use OpenAI via CLAY to generate a \"prospect qualify\" score based on LinkedIn profile summaries, enabling a smarter filter than traditional keyword matching\n    - A sample AI test on 10 profiles showed about **30% of prospects meet criteria**, suggesting around **1,500 qualified prospects** when applied to the full database\n    - AI helps identify infrastructure-related roles but struggles to perfectly separate software vs. construction roles, requiring ongoing prompt refinement\n\n- **Non-hyperscaler list filtering reduced 3,000 companies to about 500 prospects without AI**, capturing more construction-specific titles but fewer varied roles (12:59)\n    - Rob suggested differentiating project manager titles by company type, allowing inclusion of \"project manager\" for general contractors but not hyperscalers\n    - Location filtering to exclude prospects outside the US was planned to improve relevance\n    - The team agreed to exclude Amazon and review key client domains like Turner to avoid duplicates or irrelevant targets\n    - Tristan will provide Rob CSV exports for validation and job title lists to refine filters (15:39)\n\n- **Rob requested exploring a reverse LinkedIn API approach** to retrieve all job titles at specific companies for better title coverage and to identify possible filtering gaps (16:01)\n    - Tristan to attempt creating a company table with job titles for a few key companies like Turner and Vanderla to give Rob a clear view (17:41)\n    - Rob plans to analyze this data to address AI’s limitations and uncover missing roles (16:19)\n\n## **Email Outreach Strategy and Content Adjustments**\n\nEmail messaging was reviewed with a focus on improving engagement and avoiding spam filters.\n\n- **The first email currently avoids hyperlinks to reduce spam risk but may include domain names in parentheses**, as suggested by Tristan (20:15)\n    - Rob proposed switching case studies from PDFs to website-based success stories, making links more relevant and clickable (20:47)\n    - A hyperlink could be introduced later in the sequence (emails 4 or 5) to nurture interest before asking for clicks (21:21)\n    - Adding a line like \"Interested in learning more?\" to the first email was agreed to increase response rates (21:50)\n\n## **Website Staging Environment and Content Management**\n\nRob is gaining control over the WordPress site but needs guidance on managing page hierarchy and template structures.\n\n- **Rob is comfortable editing text and photos but cautious about deleting parent pages that remove child pages**, which risks losing important content (23:10)\n    - Tristan recommended recording a Loom video to document specific deletion questions for the development team to assist (24:08)\n    - Demir, who built the staging environment and new pages, remains the best contact for complex WordPress questions (22:48)\n    - Tristan explained the site uses advanced custom fields (ACF) and PHP template files, making it difficult to visualize page assembly without developer support (25:40)\n    - Rob is learning the relationship between templates, layouts, and flexible content fields but finds it challenging to identify where front-end views correspond to backend templates (28:00)\n    - Tristan showed the theme file editor and explained the PHP snippets linked to layout components, highlighting the complexity for non-developers (27:56)\n    - Rob plans to mostly work within existing frameworks and carefully remove sections, knowing he can restore anything if needed (31:29)\n\n## **Next Steps and Deliverables**\n\nClear follow-up tasks and information exchange were planned to refine prospect data and support website management.\n\n- Tristan will send Rob the current prospect lists, including company and job title tables, by the end of the day for review and validation (31:58)\n- Tristan will build location filters and exclude certain domains, per Rob’s input, to improve list quality (14:44)\n- Rob will analyze job title exports and explore LinkedIn API data to identify gaps and adjust filters accordingly (16:01)\n- Rob will prepare specific questions and video walkthroughs regarding WordPress page deletions and template concerns for Demir or Tristan’s team to address (24:08)\n- Tristan offered to provide hands-on support for complex website updates beyond Rob’s scope (24:43)","outline":null,"keywords":["Clay database","AI filtering","LinkedIn profiles","WordPress architecture","email campaign","construction project management"],"overview":"- **Refined Prospect List:** Combined AI filters with job data; master list has 283 companies, including five new hyperscalers.  \n- **Qualified Prospects Estimation:** AI tested on 10 profiles predicted 1,500 likely matches from full database with 30% success rate.  \n- **Non-Hyperscaler Targets:** Filtered down from 3,000 to 500, focusing on relevant construction titles and excluding Amazon.  \n- **Email Strategy Revamp:** First email will avoid hyperlinks; later messages may include clickable content to boost engagement.  \n- **Website Control Challenges:** Rob is editing WordPress but needs guidance on hierarchy and parent/child page management.  \n- **Next Steps Defined:** Tristan will provide prospect lists; Rob to analyze job titles and prepare WordPress questions for clarification.","action_items":"\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nApply location-based filters to company and contact database, excluding non-US and specific clients (e.g., Amazon) (14:44)\nExport comprehensive job title lists from selected companies’ data for Rob''s review and refinement (19:51)\nSend CSV exports of filtered prospect lists to Rob for validation (15:39)\nCoordinate with Demir on any technical website questions forwarded from Rob (24:43)\n\n**Rob**\nValidate AI-filtered prospect CSVs and provide feedback on relevancy (15:39)\nPrepare Loom video or detailed questions on WordPress page deletion and site management for technical support (24:21)\nTest manual website edits in staging, primarily text and images, while avoiding risky deletions without guidance (23:45)\nProvide sample companies for generating comprehensive job title datasets and review discrepancies (17:41)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"6955a9ee-d484-4921-9707-80b9de9da643","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
