    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1',
    '{"id":"01KC21DSZ9BF8MQA1X17APDWSY","title":"New North x Planon Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Performance and Optimization**\n\nThe ABM campaign has restarted and is currently ramping up with steady progress in connections and messaging sequences (01:54).\n\n- **The campaign restarted one week ago with a focus on syncing all account activities** to ensure simultaneous progress across segments (01:54)  \n    - Connections and conversations have increased, following the acceptance of LinkedIn connection requests  \n    - Developer adjustments are ongoing to align the campaign flow and messaging timing post-restart  \n    - Metrics show active sending of emails and LinkedIn messages, though no significant replies have been received yet  \n    - The phased approach allows catching up on paused segments while maintaining weekly maintenance checks  \n\n- **Taylor emphasized the need to separate European data from the dashboard to comply with GDPR and internal policies** (04:53)  \n    - Current dashboard pulls all live campaigns under the Planon account, mixing data from different markets  \n    - Developer will modify the dashboard to exclude non-ABM campaign data before the ads launch  \n    - This prevents data skew and respects strict separation requirements expressed by Merit  \n    - Maintaining a clean, compliant data view will improve tracking accuracy and reporting integrity  \n\n- **LinkedIn message replies are tracked but require manual review to filter irrelevant responses** (13:30)  \n    - Only three replies recorded so far, none with actionable interest  \n    - Taylor will compile and share all message replies with Lauren, including non-engagement replies, to maintain transparency  \n    - This tracking helps identify genuine engagement opportunities and prevents over-reporting noise  \n    - Notifications are set up for timely alerts of any meaningful replies going forward  \n\n## **Ad Campaign Launch and Asset Approval**\n\nThe ad campaign setup awaits final approval and coordination for launch, with clear next steps defined (03:46).\n\n- **Ads are ready for deployment pending Roderick’s approval, with tracking links updated and old assets set for removal** (03:46)  \n    - Taylor integrated updated tracking links into suggested documents for review before replacing previous versions  \n    - Lauren will verify link accuracy before deleting outdated sections, ensuring clean campaign materials  \n    - Once approved, the campaign manager setup will proceed with coordination to enable final team review prior to going live  \n    - This staged approval process ensures accuracy and alignment across teams before public launch  \n\n- **Paid media specialists will handle LinkedIn campaign setup, with Bailey and Taylor providing oversight and quality checks** (06:51)  \n    - After setup, campaign details will be shared with Lauren’s team for final review  \n    - This division of labor streamlines execution while maintaining control over campaign quality  \n    - Clear ownership and verification steps reduce risk of errors or misalignment in paid media efforts  \n\n## **Contract and Resource Allocation**\n\nThe current contract is structured around a points system, with recent clarification on scope and potential adjustments to fit budget and workload (08:39).\n\n- **The contract currently allocates 60 points per month at $6,000, down from an initial 80 points at $8,000 during onboarding months** (08:39)  \n    - Baylee clarified that the original 80-point engagement was limited to March-April for foundational work  \n    - Recent months have stabilized at 60 points per month aligned with ongoing ABM and ad hoc tasks  \n    - This reflects a scaling back after initial setup while maintaining core deliverables  \n\n- **A points plan totaling 54 points was proposed to cover ABM, ad hoc design, performance reporting, and tech stack management** (08:39)  \n    - This plan fits within the current monthly allocation, leaving a slight negative balance of 95 points overall  \n    - Baylee recommended maintaining the current clip to maximize value and retain flexibility for extra tasks  \n    - Reducing scope to lower monthly points would extend contract duration into late May, delaying project completion  \n    - Lauren will share this plan with her leadership team for a final decision  \n\n## **Dashboard and Reporting Enhancements**\n\nDashboard accuracy and clarity are being improved to better reflect campaign data and support decision-making (13:30).\n\n- **Developer is making changes to the ABM outreach dashboard page to correct LinkedIn reply counts and data sources** (13:30)  \n    - LinkedIn replies include some automated or irrelevant messages, so reporting filters will be added to highlight valid responses  \n    - The dashboard will exclude European campaign data to avoid GDPR conflicts and maintain clean reporting  \n    - These updates will improve usability and trust in campaign performance metrics  \n    - Weekly performance updates will continue until the dashboard enhancements are complete  \n\n- **Taylor committed to sharing detailed reply data, including names and companies, to improve tracking and engagement insight** (14:21)  \n    - This transparency will help Lauren’s team identify early signals of interest or resistance in target accounts  \n    - It supports more informed follow-up strategies and keeps the team aligned on engagement quality  \n\n## **Communication and Next Steps**\n\nClear communication protocols and timelines were established to keep the campaign on track and aligned with leadership input.\n\n- **Taylor will wait for Roderick’s final ad approval before setting up the campaign and informing Lauren’s team for review** (15:04)  \n    - This pause ensures all stakeholders have sign-off before moving to execution  \n    - Once approved, campaign setup and launch will proceed promptly  \n\n- **Baylee will send a detailed message with the points plan later today to facilitate leadership review** (13:07)  \n    - This provides decision-makers with clear options and financial implications  \n    - Lauren will coordinate internally and respond with direction on contract adjustments  \n\n- **Weekly updates on campaign performance and any new replies will continue until the campaign reaches stable momentum** (05:53)  \n    - Ongoing monitoring supports timely adjustments and maximizes campaign effectiveness  \n    - Notification systems ensure no response goes unnoticed by the team  ","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM campaign","LinkedIn outreach","dashboard adjustments","contract points","GDPR compliance","ad approval"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Status:** Restarted with increased connections; adjustments ongoing for syncing and messaging flow across all segments.  \n- **GDPR Compliance:** Upcoming dashboard modifications to separate European data; ensures compliance and improves tracking accuracy.  \n- **Ad Campaign Readiness:** Ads pending Roderick’s approval; updated tracking links integrated, with old assets set to be removed.  \n- **Contract Update:** Points system reduced from 80 to 60 points; proposed 54-point plan fits budget, awaiting leadership review.  \n- **Dashboard Enhancements:** Developer tasked with improving data accuracy; manual review needed to filter LinkedIn replies.  \n- **Communication Protocols Established:** Final ad approval pending; weekly updates will continue to ensure campaign momentum and alignment.","action_items":"\n**Lauren Poirier**\nReview and confirm tracking links in the campaign document; approve deletion of old links (03:40)\nShare points plan and contract details with leadership team for feedback and decision-making (12:50)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nContinue weekly monitoring of ABM campaign performance and provide updates (05:53)\nCompile and share a document listing all LinkedIn replies with sender names and companies (14:20)\nCoordinate with developer to adjust dashboard data filtering to exclude European campaign data and isolate ABM data (04:50)\nProceed with campaign manager setup for ads once Roderick provides final approval; notify Lauren’s team accordingly (03:57)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nSend detailed points plan document showing breakdown of current scope, points, and fees to Lauren (12:50)\n"},"duration":15.40999984741211,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"id":1,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey there.","index":0,"end_time":19.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":1,"end_time":20.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":2,"end_time":21.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":21.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":21.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":4,"end_time":22.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Good.","index":5,"end_time":23.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How''s your week been going so far?","index":6,"end_time":25.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s been good.","index":7,"end_time":26.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.77,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s been definitely busy.","index":8,"end_time":28.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.73,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think it''s finally starting to slow down now that everyone''s taking PTO before the holidays, so.","index":9,"end_time":33.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":28.97,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I was gonna say I''m surprised to hear it''s busy.","index":10,"end_time":35.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I feel like everybody''s saying it''s, like, completely slowed down, but I guess you have to get a lot of stuff into before the end of the year, so.","index":11,"end_time":41.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":35.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, all my clients, there''s people that are taking off, I think all of the next week.","index":12,"end_time":47.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''ve been working through schedules, but it''s just crazy to me that it''s the end of the year.","index":13,"end_time":52.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know.","index":14,"end_time":53.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It flew by.","index":15,"end_time":54.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It really did.","index":16,"end_time":55.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are you doing anything fun for Christmas?","index":17,"end_time":57.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The usual.","index":18,"end_time":59.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.88,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"All of my family and my husband''s family is near us, so.","index":19,"end_time":63.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.76,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Oh, that''s great.","index":20,"end_time":64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''re hosting my family, and then Christmas Day, we have something with, like, his extended family, and then the day after with his immediate family, so just, you know, small, small stuff.","index":21,"end_time":74.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.16,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"How about you?","index":22,"end_time":75.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.88,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, so my parents actually just moved down here, which is really great.","index":23,"end_time":80,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":76.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Um, so they''ll be here, and then the rest of my family from Buffalo''s driving down with their dog because they wanted to bring their dog.","index":24,"end_time":87.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''ll be a long drive.","index":25,"end_time":89.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, yeah, they''re gonna stay here and we''re gonna have a nice little family all together for Christmas.","index":26,"end_time":95.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So are they staying with you?","index":27,"end_time":97.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.91,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":28,"end_time":98.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":29,"end_time":99.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think my sister''s gonna stay with my parents, and then my brother and his fiance will stay here.","index":30,"end_time":104.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":31,"end_time":105.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Nice.","index":32,"end_time":106.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.59,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":33,"end_time":106.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.03,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That''s very exciting.","index":34,"end_time":107.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.87,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We''ll just be bouncing back and forth.","index":35,"end_time":109.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":36,"end_time":112.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.43,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Well, I just wanted to update you on the ABM campaign currently.","index":37,"end_time":117.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So right now I wanted to show you kind of what''s going on since we restarted the campaign.","index":38,"end_time":124.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":119.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I just broke it down into the different categories here.","index":39,"end_time":126.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":124.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So as you can see, these ones started taking off before we paused.","index":40,"end_time":130.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s why that you see the difference there in the conversations and connections.","index":41,"end_time":134.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So now that we restarted, this one''s kind of playing catch up, and we do a weekly maintenance each week.","index":42,"end_time":140.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I was actually talking to one of our developers this morning.","index":43,"end_time":142.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":140.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So he''s been keeping an eye on it, and since it stopped and started, he''s just adjusting a few things to make sure that they''re all going to start kind of going at the same time now that we restarted the campaign.","index":44,"end_time":153.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":142.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But as you can see, a lot of connections have been sent across all of the accounts and then we have started conversations.","index":45,"end_time":162.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just to remind you, as soon as the connection request gets accepted, then the conversation begins.","index":46,"end_time":168.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":162.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s when we send out that messaging sequence that we have already started.","index":47,"end_time":172.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":168.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''ll continue to see those come through.","index":48,"end_time":174.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Nothing to report as far as replies right now, but we are seeing those move through.","index":49,"end_time":178.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then at the top here you''ll see we have sent a good chunk of emails to from those groups and then these ones now will also start catching up now that we have restarted the campaign.","index":50,"end_time":188.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":178.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, okay, yeah, it''s moving through.","index":51,"end_time":191.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s only been live for a week now.","index":52,"end_time":193.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''ll, we''ll continue to monitor these and if anything else comes up.","index":53,"end_time":197.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, once we can get the ads live and kind of have those grouped together and I know you messaged me this morning, I put them as suggested in the document because I wanted to make sure those were correct before changing the alternate ones that were in there.","index":54,"end_time":213.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can just pull it up.","index":55,"end_time":214.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Actually, I have it here.","index":56,"end_time":215.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":214.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I added that tracking link just to the end.","index":57,"end_time":219.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So are we good to go ahead and get rid of this section then?","index":58,"end_time":223.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we are just replacing with the tracking.","index":59,"end_time":226.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll review these and just make sure the links are good.","index":60,"end_time":229.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.76,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then, yeah, we can delete the old ones.","index":61,"end_time":232.279,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.96,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes, and then I know you said we''re going to wait on Roderick for the final approval on those.","index":62,"end_time":239,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Ads and then.","index":63,"end_time":242.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Whenever that happens, we can go ahead and set it up in the campaign manager like you said.","index":64,"end_time":247.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":243.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I''ll let your team know so that they can review before we go ahead and push that live.","index":65,"end_time":252.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, and then just another part of the ABM ads is with the dashboard.","index":66,"end_time":257.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Now that we have restarted the campaign, we are going to make adjustments to that LinkedIn page on the dashboard.","index":67,"end_time":264.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So one question I did have is I know that Merit said specifically we can''t have any European data coming together with that.","index":68,"end_time":275.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I think right now it''s pulling from what campaigns it sees in there.","index":69,"end_time":279.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we need to just make sure that when we do launch, we''re going to have it just focus on our campaigns.","index":70,"end_time":285.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That way we can get rid of that specific section of any data that''s not ours.","index":71,"end_time":291.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That way it''s all in one place.","index":72,"end_time":293.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So what page is that in the dashboard?","index":73,"end_time":295.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know there''s five pages.","index":74,"end_time":297.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.95,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That''s three on paid media.","index":75,"end_time":300.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, so you''re saying right now this is pulling all of our live campaigns on the Planon account?","index":76,"end_time":306.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.15,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes, because that''s what we have access to.","index":77,"end_time":308.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I''M going to talk to our developer once we launch our own ads and see if we can just get rid of all the other data because that we don''t want it to skew with our data for the ABM ads.","index":78,"end_time":318.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":79,"end_time":318.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And also respect to what merit was saying where we don''t want to pull their data in as well.","index":80,"end_time":323.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":81,"end_time":324.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As long as this is just aggregate data and not, you know, personally identifiable information, I think is just gdpr.","index":82,"end_time":333.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.57,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I don''t know on your side, if you do have access to that personal data from this dashboard, I think that''s where it would be a problem.","index":83,"end_time":342.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.73,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, good to know.","index":84,"end_time":343.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":342.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it seemed like she wanted it very separate, so I just want to make sure that we''re staying in line with that.","index":85,"end_time":348.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we can have it completely separate, that''s, that''s the first choice that would be.","index":86,"end_time":353.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.45,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Would this be beneficial too for our tracking of the data as well?","index":87,"end_time":357.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So once we get that all set up in live, we will make those changes to the dashboard so that everything is in step with what we''re doing on our end and reflects that data.","index":88,"end_time":369.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we will make changes to that.","index":89,"end_time":371.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But in the meantime, I''ll continue to update us weekly on the performance of the different groups and how the campaign''s performing.","index":90,"end_time":377.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Then if we get any replies to.","index":91,"end_time":379.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll see those come through and yeah, take care of that.","index":92,"end_time":383.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s nice having the three different centers though too, because we''re able to get through so many emails and the sequences in LinkedIn.","index":93,"end_time":390.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s crazy because I have a couple other ones that we don''t have that many going out.","index":94,"end_time":394.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s cool to see how much it increases.","index":95,"end_time":397,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":394.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''ll be helpful too as we get through the campaign.","index":96,"end_time":399.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So a couple questions for you.","index":97,"end_time":402,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.16,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So first off, about the campaign set up in LinkedIn, did what Stella said, did that make sense to you?","index":98,"end_time":408.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.4,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The way she phrased, like setting up the.","index":99,"end_time":410.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":100,"end_time":411.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":101,"end_time":412.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.23,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And we have a separate paid media specialist that will do that.","index":102,"end_time":416.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then Bailey and I usually go in and check it and then we''ll send it over to you.","index":103,"end_time":419.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, yeah, we will make sure to send that information along.","index":104,"end_time":422.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if you go back to the slide where you broke down the data based on.","index":105,"end_time":427.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that one.","index":106,"end_time":427.909,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":427.11,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So where it says conversation started, that means that the connection was accepted and you sent a message.","index":107,"end_time":433.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.15,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"There hasn''t been like a response per se.","index":108,"end_time":435.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Not yet.","index":109,"end_time":436.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":110,"end_time":436.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Correct.","index":111,"end_time":437.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So as soon as someone accepts the connection, then you have the ability to send them a message on LinkedIn.","index":112,"end_time":441.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s what those are, is that first message in the secrets get sent and then there''s a break of a few days and then we do like a follow up and then it ends.","index":113,"end_time":449.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, so that''s how that, that plays out.","index":114,"end_time":453.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":115,"end_time":454.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.73,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"In the dashboard.","index":116,"end_time":455.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.37,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And I know you said it''s still being kind of tweaked on fourth page, ABM outreach.","index":117,"end_time":460.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I still see the LinkedIn message replies 3.","index":118,"end_time":462.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.13,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Is that not accurate?","index":119,"end_time":464.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.93,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, we need to go through now that we have restarted it and I have our developer just waiting to do a couple of the changes.","index":120,"end_time":471.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I was going to see if we could do it at once with the LinkedIn thinking we''d launch that.","index":121,"end_time":474.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":471.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This, but if we''re going to hold on that until we hear from Roderick, we can go ahead and make those changes, like apart from that, and then we''ll go back to LinkedIn.","index":122,"end_time":482.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":123,"end_time":483.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":124,"end_time":484.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":483.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, that makes sense.","index":125,"end_time":485.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.59,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, we just wanted to make sure everything was done kind of all at the same time when we relaunched.","index":126,"end_time":491.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, since we''re going to wait on Rodrick, we''ll just go ahead and make those adjustments.","index":127,"end_time":495.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":491.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":128,"end_time":496.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":496.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we will.","index":129,"end_time":497.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":496.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We will keep an eye on that Sounds good.","index":130,"end_time":500.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, we will continue to monitor these and if we do get anything through, we have like notification systems set up on our end too.","index":131,"end_time":507.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We will send that over to you.","index":132,"end_time":508.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":507.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":133,"end_time":510.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That sounds good to me.","index":134,"end_time":511.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.77,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Great.","index":135,"end_time":512.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll pass over to Bailey.","index":136,"end_time":515.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":514.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we''re going to talk through a couple of contract things, so.","index":137,"end_time":518.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you for talking to your leadership team too and getting us more information.","index":138,"end_time":523.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":519.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We definitely want to find something that, that works for everyone.","index":139,"end_time":527.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, yeah, just lots of changes have been going on and all that good stuff.","index":140,"end_time":533.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we were looking through the points and I know we''ve really been trying to over deliver on some projects which you can probably see if you look on Pulse.","index":141,"end_time":543.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think right now there''s a balance of like negative 95 points right now.","index":142,"end_time":548.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we put together a points plan too to see what it would look like if we just did ABM and some ad hoc design projects.","index":143,"end_time":556.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":549.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that comes to be around like 54 points and you''re currently at like a current clip of like 6,000.","index":144,"end_time":566.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":557.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s just like six points short of where you''re currently at.","index":145,"end_time":570.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":567.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we were at 80 points a month in the contract.","index":146,"end_time":573.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.23,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Let me double check that.","index":147,"end_time":579.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":577.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Really quick.","index":148,"end_time":582.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that might change things a little bit if it''s 80 points.","index":149,"end_time":610.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"See?","index":150,"end_time":613.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh no.","index":151,"end_time":614.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":152,"end_time":614.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It, it is 6,000.","index":153,"end_time":615.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It is.","index":154,"end_time":616.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.51,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":155,"end_time":617.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.99,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":156,"end_time":617.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":617.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So just pulled that up.","index":157,"end_time":618.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":617.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":158,"end_time":620.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"60 points for 6,000amonth.","index":159,"end_time":623.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we did we did gift some points at the very beginning.","index":160,"end_time":628.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":624.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think like the first few months might have been around 80 so that we could get some, some foundational documents all set up.","index":161,"end_time":637.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But at least the last little bit has been 60amonth.","index":162,"end_time":642.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":638.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good to know.","index":163,"end_time":644.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Where did I see that?","index":164,"end_time":645.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m just looking back at the sow, just out of curiosity.","index":165,"end_time":650.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Glitching.","index":166,"end_time":653.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.16,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The msa.","index":167,"end_time":658.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I see in the, in the MSA, under section 3, length of engagement or no section 4 points and fees, client has agreed to purchase 80 points for $8,000 for the period noted in section 3 above.","index":168,"end_time":679.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.57,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Although that was March to April, so that must be just from the initial one month engagement.","index":169,"end_time":685.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.01,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":170,"end_time":686.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.77,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that would have just been for that first engagement.","index":171,"end_time":690.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":686.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So yeah, so just recently it''s been at the 60 points.","index":172,"end_time":694.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":690.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll show you too.","index":173,"end_time":696.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":695.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like this points plan we put together so you can see like the breakdown.","index":174,"end_time":700.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":696.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So 54 points.","index":175,"end_time":701.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":700.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Ad hoc design tasks, managing performance reporting, managing ABM, your tech stack, like just all the platforms we were using comes out to 54 points.","index":176,"end_time":712.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So with that being said and considering that there''s like a negative 95 points balance, I would just recommend that we stay at the current clip.","index":177,"end_time":723.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":713.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If, if that doesn''t work though, the other option is we could reduce things.","index":178,"end_time":729.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":724.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So maybe we could like cut out these two things and bring us around like $4,000 a month.","index":179,"end_time":735.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":729.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But if we did that, we''d need to extend the contract.","index":180,"end_time":738.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":736.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So right now we''re like ending March, like last week of March, first week of April.","index":181,"end_time":745.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Ish.","index":182,"end_time":745.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":745.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So if we wanted to reduce, we''d probably end up in May, like end of May.","index":183,"end_time":750.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":746.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s really up to you what, what you want to do.","index":184,"end_time":755.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":751.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I would definitely recommend staying at the current clip because you''re going to get more bang for your buck because we can keep doing like extra ad hoc tasks and things like that.","index":185,"end_time":763.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Whereas if we reduce the scope, you''re just going to be extending the time.","index":186,"end_time":767.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":763.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Period.","index":187,"end_time":767.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.05,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And kind of get less out of it.","index":188,"end_time":771.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":769.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, thank you for breaking that down.","index":189,"end_time":775.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":772.26,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If you could share that with me.","index":190,"end_time":777.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.38,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I haven''t had the chance to talk to my leadership team yet about this, but I could share that with them and we can get back to you on decisions there.","index":191,"end_time":786.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.14,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":192,"end_time":787.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll send over a message later today.","index":193,"end_time":789.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":194,"end_time":790.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.62,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":195,"end_time":798.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":798.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any other questions on that?","index":196,"end_time":799.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":798.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I think that clears that up.","index":197,"end_time":803.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":801.31,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":198,"end_time":807.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.27,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that that sounds good.","index":199,"end_time":809.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Great.","index":200,"end_time":810.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":201,"end_time":811.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Else, quickly, Lauren, I just wanted to point out, I was just reviewing and I had our developer working on A couple things for that dashboard.","index":202,"end_time":817.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I was just checking.","index":203,"end_time":818.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We guys are talking about that.","index":204,"end_time":819.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That that page with the ABM outreach is what is currently happening right now.","index":205,"end_time":825.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They restarted it when we restarted the campaign.","index":206,"end_time":828.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we checked everything.","index":207,"end_time":829.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":828.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The LinkedIn replies that you see the three, when someone replies, it doesn''t always mean it''s a good one.","index":208,"end_time":834.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So sometimes they say, like, appreciate the connection.","index":209,"end_time":836.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s not that we like, report to you guys because there''s nothing to do with that, or somebody says, like, I no longer work here, things like that.","index":210,"end_time":843.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":837.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we had.","index":211,"end_time":844.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":843.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We technically have had three LinkedIn replies, but they, they weren''t anything noteworthy.","index":212,"end_time":848.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":213,"end_time":849.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":848.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if there is anything that comes through, we will let you know.","index":214,"end_time":852.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But it is tracking those, so that''s what you''ll see there reflected.","index":215,"end_time":856.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Even though they''re not noteworthy, I still would be really interested to see what those replies were.","index":216,"end_time":860.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":856.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I can compile a sheet.","index":217,"end_time":862.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"One of my other clients for my ABM campaign I have running, I have an ABM responses document.","index":218,"end_time":867.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":863.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so I just note responses that we''ve received.","index":219,"end_time":869.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":867.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They don''t want to see those ones, but if you want to see any of them that come through, like, appreciate the connection, I can go ahead and create a shared document and we can do that.","index":220,"end_time":878.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I''d love to see all of them in the.","index":221,"end_time":880.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":878.93,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The name of the person in the company.","index":222,"end_time":882.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":880.65,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That would be great just to keep track of, like, you know, if someone is a little more open to talking to someone who''s like, I''m not interested.","index":223,"end_time":890.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.45,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So.","index":224,"end_time":891.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes, understandable.","index":225,"end_time":892.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":891.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":226,"end_time":893.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Nothing on email yet, but I will send.","index":227,"end_time":895.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I will compile a document after this and send you those three messages on a spreadsheet.","index":228,"end_time":899.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":895.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''ll send that over to you, but just wanted to clarify what those replies were.","index":229,"end_time":903.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":899.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great, thank you.","index":230,"end_time":904.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.41,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":231,"end_time":905.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":232,"end_time":906.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":905.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":233,"end_time":907.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":907.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, we will be in touch and I''ll wait to hear back from you about the ABM ads.","index":234,"end_time":910.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":907.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then once we have those from Roderick, we''ll get that campaign set up for you.","index":235,"end_time":914.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":910.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":236,"end_time":914.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.51,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":237,"end_time":915.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.99,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":238,"end_time":916.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thanks, Lauren.","index":239,"end_time":917.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Talk to you soon.","index":240,"end_time":919.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.59,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"}],"dateString":"2025-12-11T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC21DSZ9BF8MQA1X17APDWSY","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.78,"bullets":["Restarted ABM campaign is progressing; weekly developer checks ensure alignment post-restart.","Lauren confirmed old assets can be deleted once new links are verified and tracking is added.","Team expects ad launch upon Roderick’s final approval; pre-launch setup work is complete.","Baylee confirmed current contract is 60 points/month despite earlier engagement at 80 points.","Lauren requested all LinkedIn reply data, including non-noteworthy responses, to track sentiment."],"highlights":[{"quote":"So I think right now there''s a balance of like negative 95 points right now.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"So we had. We technically have had three LinkedIn replies, but they weren''t anything noteworthy.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"topics":["ABM","campaign","reporting","contract"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-12T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Performance and Optimization**\n\nThe ABM campaign has restarted and is currently ramping up with steady progress in connections and messaging sequences (01:54).\n\n- **The campaign restarted one week ago with a focus on syncing all account activities** to ensure simultaneous progress across segments (01:54)  \n    - Connections and conversations have increased, following the acceptance of LinkedIn connection requests  \n    - Developer adjustments are ongoing to align the campaign flow and messaging timing post-restart  \n    - Metrics show active sending of emails and LinkedIn messages, though no significant replies have been received yet  \n    - The phased approach allows catching up on paused segments while maintaining weekly maintenance checks  \n\n- **Taylor emphasized the need to separate European data from the dashboard to comply with GDPR and internal policies** (04:53)  \n    - Current dashboard pulls all live campaigns under the Planon account, mixing data from different markets  \n    - Developer will modify the dashboard to exclude non-ABM campaign data before the ads launch  \n    - This prevents data skew and respects strict separation requirements expressed by Merit  \n    - Maintaining a clean, compliant data view will improve tracking accuracy and reporting integrity  \n\n- **LinkedIn message replies are tracked but require manual review to filter irrelevant responses** (13:30)  \n    - Only three replies recorded so far, none with actionable interest  \n    - Taylor will compile and share all message replies with Lauren, including non-engagement replies, to maintain transparency  \n    - This tracking helps identify genuine engagement opportunities and prevents over-reporting noise  \n    - Notifications are set up for timely alerts of any meaningful replies going forward  \n\n## **Ad Campaign Launch and Asset Approval**\n\nThe ad campaign setup awaits final approval and coordination for launch, with clear next steps defined (03:46).\n\n- **Ads are ready for deployment pending Roderick’s approval, with tracking links updated and old assets set for removal** (03:46)  \n    - Taylor integrated updated tracking links into suggested documents for review before replacing previous versions  \n    - Lauren will verify link accuracy before deleting outdated sections, ensuring clean campaign materials  \n    - Once approved, the campaign manager setup will proceed with coordination to enable final team review prior to going live  \n    - This staged approval process ensures accuracy and alignment across teams before public launch  \n\n- **Paid media specialists will handle LinkedIn campaign setup, with Bailey and Taylor providing oversight and quality checks** (06:51)  \n    - After setup, campaign details will be shared with Lauren’s team for final review  \n    - This division of labor streamlines execution while maintaining control over campaign quality  \n    - Clear ownership and verification steps reduce risk of errors or misalignment in paid media efforts  \n\n## **Contract and Resource Allocation**\n\nThe current contract is structured around a points system, with recent clarification on scope and potential adjustments to fit budget and workload (08:39).\n\n- **The contract currently allocates 60 points per month at $6,000, down from an initial 80 points at $8,000 during onboarding months** (08:39)  \n    - Baylee clarified that the original 80-point engagement was limited to March-April for foundational work  \n    - Recent months have stabilized at 60 points per month aligned with ongoing ABM and ad hoc tasks  \n    - This reflects a scaling back after initial setup while maintaining core deliverables  \n\n- **A points plan totaling 54 points was proposed to cover ABM, ad hoc design, performance reporting, and tech stack management** (08:39)  \n    - This plan fits within the current monthly allocation, leaving a slight negative balance of 95 points overall  \n    - Baylee recommended maintaining the current clip to maximize value and retain flexibility for extra tasks  \n    - Reducing scope to lower monthly points would extend contract duration into late May, delaying project completion  \n    - Lauren will share this plan with her leadership team for a final decision  \n\n## **Dashboard and Reporting Enhancements**\n\nDashboard accuracy and clarity are being improved to better reflect campaign data and support decision-making (13:30).\n\n- **Developer is making changes to the ABM outreach dashboard page to correct LinkedIn reply counts and data sources** (13:30)  \n    - LinkedIn replies include some automated or irrelevant messages, so reporting filters will be added to highlight valid responses  \n    - The dashboard will exclude European campaign data to avoid GDPR conflicts and maintain clean reporting  \n    - These updates will improve usability and trust in campaign performance metrics  \n    - Weekly performance updates will continue until the dashboard enhancements are complete  \n\n- **Taylor committed to sharing detailed reply data, including names and companies, to improve tracking and engagement insight** (14:21)  \n    - This transparency will help Lauren’s team identify early signals of interest or resistance in target accounts  \n    - It supports more informed follow-up strategies and keeps the team aligned on engagement quality  \n\n## **Communication and Next Steps**\n\nClear communication protocols and timelines were established to keep the campaign on track and aligned with leadership input.\n\n- **Taylor will wait for Roderick’s final ad approval before setting up the campaign and informing Lauren’s team for review** (15:04)  \n    - This pause ensures all stakeholders have sign-off before moving to execution  \n    - Once approved, campaign setup and launch will proceed promptly  \n\n- **Baylee will send a detailed message with the points plan later today to facilitate leadership review** (13:07)  \n    - This provides decision-makers with clear options and financial implications  \n    - Lauren will coordinate internally and respond with direction on contract adjustments  \n\n- **Weekly updates on campaign performance and any new replies will continue until the campaign reaches stable momentum** (05:53)  \n    - Ongoing monitoring supports timely adjustments and maximizes campaign effectiveness  \n    - Notification systems ensure no response goes unnoticed by the team  ","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM campaign","LinkedIn outreach","dashboard adjustments","contract points","GDPR compliance","ad approval"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Status:** Restarted with increased connections; adjustments ongoing for syncing and messaging flow across all segments.  \n- **GDPR Compliance:** Upcoming dashboard modifications to separate European data; ensures compliance and improves tracking accuracy.  \n- **Ad Campaign Readiness:** Ads pending Roderick’s approval; updated tracking links integrated, with old assets set to be removed.  \n- **Contract Update:** Points system reduced from 80 to 60 points; proposed 54-point plan fits budget, awaiting leadership review.  \n- **Dashboard Enhancements:** Developer tasked with improving data accuracy; manual review needed to filter LinkedIn replies.  \n- **Communication Protocols Established:** Final ad approval pending; weekly updates will continue to ensure campaign momentum and alignment.","action_items":"\n**Lauren Poirier**\nReview and confirm tracking links in the campaign document; approve deletion of old links (03:40)\nShare points plan and contract details with leadership team for feedback and decision-making (12:50)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nContinue weekly monitoring of ABM campaign performance and provide updates (05:53)\nCompile and share a document listing all LinkedIn replies with sender names and companies (14:20)\nCoordinate with developer to adjust dashboard data filtering to exclude European campaign data and isolate ABM data (04:50)\nProceed with campaign manager setup for ads once Roderick provides final approval; notify Lauren’s team accordingly (03:57)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nSend detailed points plan document showing breakdown of current scope, points, and fees to Lauren (12:50)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"44eed195-c821-43ba-ab74-5843017bcdba","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
