  'Meeting Notes: New North x Planon Weekly Meeting',
  '## **ABM Campaign Performance and Optimization**

The ABM campaign has restarted and is currently ramping up with steady progress in connections and messaging sequences (01:54).

- **The campaign restarted one week ago with a focus on syncing all account activities** to ensure simultaneous progress across segments (01:54)  
    - Connections and conversations have increased, following the acceptance of LinkedIn connection requests  
    - Developer adjustments are ongoing to align the campaign flow and messaging timing post-restart  
    - Metrics show active sending of emails and LinkedIn messages, though no significant replies have been received yet  
    - The phased approach allows catching up on paused segments while maintaining weekly maintenance checks  

- **Taylor emphasized the need to separate European data from the dashboard to comply with GDPR and internal policies** (04:53)  
    - Current dashboard pulls all live campaigns under the Planon account, mixing data from different markets  
    - Developer will modify the dashboard to exclude non-ABM campaign data before the ads launch  
    - This prevents data skew and respects strict separation requirements expressed by Merit  
    - Maintaining a clean, compliant data view will improve tracking accuracy and reporting integrity  

- **LinkedIn message replies are tracked but require manual review to filter irrelevant responses** (13:30)  
    - Only three replies recorded so far, none with actionable interest  
    - Taylor will compile and share all message replies with Lauren, including non-engagement replies, to maintain transparency  
    - This tracking helps identify genuine engagement opportunities and prevents over-reporting noise  
    - Notifications are set up for timely alerts of any meaningful replies going forward  

## **Ad Campaign Launch and Asset Approval**

The ad campaign setup awaits final approval and coordination for launch, with clear next steps defined (03:46).

- **Ads are ready for deployment pending Roderick’s approval, with tracking links updated and old assets set for removal** (03:46)  
    - Taylor integrated updated tracking links into suggested documents for review before replacing previous versions  
    - Lauren will verify link accuracy before deleting outdated sections, ensuring clean campaign materials  
    - Once approved, the campaign manager setup will proceed with coordination to enable final team review prior to going live  
    - This staged approval process ensures accuracy and alignment across teams before public launch  

- **Paid media specialists will handle LinkedIn campaign setup, with Bailey and Taylor providing oversight and quality checks** (06:51)  
    - After setup, campaign details will be shared with Lauren’s team for final review  
    - This division of labor streamlines execution while maintaining control over campaign quality  
    - Clear ownership and verification steps reduce risk of errors or misalignment in paid media efforts  

## **Contract and Resource Allocation**

The current contract is structured around a points system, with recent clarification on scope and potential adjustments to fit budget and workload (08:39).

- **The contract currently allocates 60 points per month at $6,000, down from an initial 80 points at $8,000 during onboarding months** (08:39)  
    - Baylee clarified that the original 80-point engagement was limited to March-April for foundational work  
    - Recent months have stabilized at 60 points per month aligned with ongoing ABM and ad hoc tasks  
    - This reflects a scaling back after initial setup while maintaining core deliverables  

- **A points plan totaling 54 points was proposed to cover ABM, ad hoc design, performance reporting, and tech stack management** (08:39)  
    - This plan fits within the current monthly allocation, leaving a slight negative balance of 95 points overall  
    - Baylee recommended maintaining the current clip to maximize value and retain flexibility for extra tasks  
    - Reducing scope to lower monthly points would extend contract duration into late May, delaying project completion  
    - Lauren will share this plan with her leadership team for a final decision  

## **Dashboard and Reporting Enhancements**

Dashboard accuracy and clarity are being improved to better reflect campaign data and support decision-making (13:30).

- **Developer is making changes to the ABM outreach dashboard page to correct LinkedIn reply counts and data sources** (13:30)  
    - LinkedIn replies include some automated or irrelevant messages, so reporting filters will be added to highlight valid responses  
    - The dashboard will exclude European campaign data to avoid GDPR conflicts and maintain clean reporting  
    - These updates will improve usability and trust in campaign performance metrics  
    - Weekly performance updates will continue until the dashboard enhancements are complete  

- **Taylor committed to sharing detailed reply data, including names and companies, to improve tracking and engagement insight** (14:21)  
    - This transparency will help Lauren’s team identify early signals of interest or resistance in target accounts  
    - It supports more informed follow-up strategies and keeps the team aligned on engagement quality  

## **Communication and Next Steps**

Clear communication protocols and timelines were established to keep the campaign on track and aligned with leadership input.

- **Taylor will wait for Roderick’s final ad approval before setting up the campaign and informing Lauren’s team for review** (15:04)  
    - This pause ensures all stakeholders have sign-off before moving to execution  
    - Once approved, campaign setup and launch will proceed promptly  

- **Baylee will send a detailed message with the points plan later today to facilitate leadership review** (13:07)  
    - This provides decision-makers with clear options and financial implications  
    - Lauren will coordinate internally and respond with direction on contract adjustments  

- **Weekly updates on campaign performance and any new replies will continue until the campaign reaches stable momentum** (05:53)  
    - Ongoing monitoring supports timely adjustments and maximizes campaign effectiveness  
    - Notification systems ensure no response goes unnoticed by the team  ',
