    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86719613161?pwd=FUtBTO6w0NHl6Zybphu2fW18etobyw.1',
    '{"id":"01KC2CCZTPKF1PCJAHTVG5S2VK","title":"Taylor Doerbaum and Daniel nelsen","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Content and Structure Updates**\n\nThe team agreed to finalize and implement key website content changes to enable a relaunch by the week of the 22nd (00:00).\n\n- **Dan Nelsen confirmed completion of about 56 initial copy comments and detailed upcoming technical content for the digester and EDS product pages, expected by Monday or Tuesday next week to unblock development work** (01:24)  \n    - He is gathering technical notes from engineers to produce 3 paragraphs per product page for precise details.  \n    - These content additions will complete the last major blockers before launch.  \n    - Taylor Doerbaum plans to allocate developer time mid-next week for implementing these edits to meet the timeline.  \n    - Launching before the holidays is preferred to allow lower traffic for smoother issue resolution.\n\n- **The website will adopt a new homepage layout featuring three images across the top representing each product line, linking directly to product pages, to improve visitor navigation and product discovery** (06:21)  \n    - Dan wants the images to occupy roughly the top third of the page with text sections, including the “Future of Wastewise Treatment,” moved below.  \n    - The current layout with a single image and text will be replaced to give users clear, immediate product options.  \n    - This approach addresses unknown visitor intent and supports better engagement with product lines.\n\n- **Several UX and content adjustments were approved, including relocating the “trusted bar” with carousel to the bottom to reduce white space and improve perceived page flow** (05:43)  \n    - Dan’s reasoning is that placing it mid-page misleads users into thinking it’s the page bottom.  \n    - Minor copy and layout tweaks on About Us and other pages will align with the overall refresh.\n\n- **A new “Technical Library” dropdown will be added to replace the “Service Tools” section, initially housing cut sheets and spec sheets, with plans to expand over time** (10:10)  \n    - An additional dropdown for “Service Validation, Commissioning, System Modernization” product page will be created using existing templates.  \n    - Dan will provide copy for these subsections in the next few days or early next week to flesh out those pages.  \n    - Stock imagery will be used initially, with the possibility of enhancements later.\n\n## **Project Timeline and Launch Planning**\n\nThe team aligned on a clear timeline targeting a website launch during the week of the 22nd, with key development milestones scheduled for the week prior (00:13).\n\n- **Dan will finalize all technical copy inputs by Monday morning, enabling development work to start by midweek (17th-18th), aiming for a draft site by the 19th for internal review** (13:29)  \n    - Taylor confirmed developer availability to prioritize these tasks immediately upon content receipt.  \n    - This schedule supports a launch window before the holidays while ensuring support coverage post-launch.\n\n- **A follow-up review call is planned for the week after initial updates to walk through the site with Dan’s leadership team and ensure all requested changes are captured** (12:14)  \n    - This will serve as the final quality check before public rollout.  \n    - Any minor copy or image tweaks identified can be handled after launch to avoid blockers.\n\n- **The regular Tuesday meeting will be rescheduled to Thursday next week to align with the anticipated new site version, enabling a live walkthrough and launch planning discussion** (20:46)  \n    - This flexibility accommodates the development and review cadence without delaying progress.\n\n## **Content Strategy and Prioritization**\n\nWebsite updates are the highest current priority, with other marketing content to be layered in after completion (00:19).\n\n- **Dan emphasized that all focus is on the website until the final copy and technical details are delivered, after which he will shift to blogs and other marketing materials** (19:51)  \n    - He highlighted the importance of rapid turnaround on website clarifications by requesting high-priority email flags to avoid blocking developers.  \n    - This prioritization reflects the critical role of the website as the primary customer touchpoint.\n\n- **The team will continue to refine and expand content post-launch, including adding new imagery and fleshing out service-related pages as copy becomes available** (10:50)  \n    - This phased approach balances a timely launch with ongoing content improvements.\n\n## **Technical and SEO Considerations**\n\nKey technical questions regarding SEO and tracking compliance are pending developer input to ensure smooth transition and regulatory adherence (00:17).\n\n- **Dan raised concerns about maintaining search engine rankings through the website switch and requested clarity on tracking options and GDPR compliance** (17:38)  \n    - Taylor will forward these queries to the developer and provide answers to mitigate risks of traffic loss.  \n    - Understanding which tracking tools require explicit user consent will help maintain compliance and user trust.\n\n- **The team agreed to monitor these technical aspects closely during the launch phase to avoid disruptions and ensure accurate analytics** (18:20)  \n    - This proactive approach guards against SEO setbacks and data gaps.\n\n## **Collaboration and Communication Protocols**\n\nClear communication channels and quick response expectations were established to keep the website project on track (00:16).\n\n- **Dan encouraged the team to reach out promptly with questions during development, promising quick clarifications to prevent developer delays** (16:06)  \n    - He has embedded relevant assets and notes within Bugherd to support self-service and reduce back-and-forth.  \n    - Taylor confirmed this documentation will aid the developer’s understanding and expedite fixes.\n\n- **Priority emails marked with a red exclamation flag will be used for urgent website clarifications to ensure timely responses** (20:23)  \n    - This system aims to avoid bottlenecks and maintain momentum.\n\n- **Regular check-ins and alignment calls are planned post-update to review progress and plan next steps, ensuring all stakeholders remain informed and engaged** (21:05)  \n    - Taylor and Dan will coordinate schedules and maintain visibility on developer workloads and content delivery.\n\n","outline":null,"keywords":["Website launch","copywriting","product pages","developer scheduling","UX design","SEO preservation"],"overview":"- **Website Relaunch Target:** Key content changes will enable a website relaunch by the week of the 22nd.\n\n- **Content Completion:** Technical content for product pages will be finished early next week to unblock development work.\n\n- **New Homepage Design:** The homepage will feature three product images for improved navigation and visitor engagement.\n\n- **Technical Library Addition:** A new dropdown will be created for technical documents, starting with existing resources.\n\n- **Launch Timeline Agreement:** A draft site review is planned for the 19th, aiming for a holiday launch.\n\n- **Communication Protocols:** Urgent questions will be flagged in emails to ensure quick developer responses and avoid delays.","action_items":"\n**Dan Nelsen**\nProvide approximate three paragraphs of copy for digester and EDS product pages by Monday or Tuesday (00:59)\nDeliver copy for the new Service Validation, Commissioning, and Modernization product page early next week (10:50)\nReview updated website with leadership immediately after first round of edits to confirm completeness and accuracy before launch (12:03)\nFollow up with engineering team Monday morning to ensure completion of technical notes and copy (13:42)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nCoordinate developer scheduling for mid-next week (Dec 17-18) to implement website changes as soon as copy and assets are received (13:43)\nSend Dan the developer’s SEO and tracking questions regarding ranking maintenance and GDPR compliance (17:47)\nFollow up with Bailey and team to confirm availability and feedback on edits and will reschedule the usual Tuesday meeting to Thursday next week for website walkthrough (20:46)\nEmail any additional comments or questions about website edits to Dan (17:30)\nMonitor progress and provide feedback or escalate urgent bugs with high priority email flag for quick resolution (20:23)\n"},"duration":22.149999618530273,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":1,"name":"Dan Nelsen"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It''s going good.","index":0,"end_time":1.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s wrapping up the year.","index":1,"end_time":3.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s crazy.","index":2,"end_time":3.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":3,"end_time":5.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.36,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Incidents.","index":4,"end_time":7.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.12,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I know we have a few things to review.","index":5,"end_time":12.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Bailey''s not able to make it today, so we can just hop into a couple of things.","index":6,"end_time":15.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know I''ve seen you''ve been sending over something, so that is great.","index":7,"end_time":21.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The cut sheets.","index":8,"end_time":22.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I saw those come in, so that was one of the things I just had on here.","index":9,"end_time":25.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I know you said, I think, some additional comments as far as the website that we can start working on edits.","index":10,"end_time":31.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is that correct?","index":11,"end_time":32.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yep.","index":12,"end_time":33.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":13,"end_time":34.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I would like to talk through just some of the.","index":14,"end_time":39.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.5,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Just kind of talk through some of the points in case it''s my copy isn''t totally clear.","index":15,"end_time":45.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then I think the only piece that''s missing is for the digester and EDS product pages.","index":16,"end_time":52.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.62,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''ll have about three paragraphs of copy to go into each of those.","index":17,"end_time":57.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.06,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":18,"end_time":58.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m just getting some technical notes from my engineers that''ll go into those.","index":19,"end_time":65.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.78,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I should have those notes back later today or tomorrow, and then I''ll get the copy turned for you tomorrow or Monday.","index":20,"end_time":72.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.82,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And that should be the last blocker piece.","index":21,"end_time":77.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"There''ll be some.","index":22,"end_time":78.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.42,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Cut sheet links to cut sheets we don''t have ready yet that we''ll want to strip off.","index":23,"end_time":83.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.88,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":24,"end_time":85.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But other than that, that should be the only pieces we need with these changes to get the launch of the website running.","index":25,"end_time":95.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So I guess I''m curious, once we''ve run through these, what your sense of timeline is for getting these implemented.","index":26,"end_time":104,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I want to do a last review with my team, which really we can do day of or the next day from whenever these are implemented, and then what the launch Runway looks like.","index":27,"end_time":114.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":28,"end_time":115.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":114.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''ll just depend on the comments.","index":29,"end_time":118.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":116.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it looks like, I think these are the ones you left today.","index":30,"end_time":120.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Does 56 sound correct?","index":31,"end_time":124.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":125.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":33,"end_time":126.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just depending on the amount of comments, I''ll send these over to our developer.","index":34,"end_time":129.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Did you say that these particular ones are ready to go ahead and get edited and you''ll send something additional for other pages?","index":35,"end_time":136.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we can start on these.","index":36,"end_time":137.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":138.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So if you take a look at, say, or I can share my screen, whatever''s easier.","index":38,"end_time":143.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Sure.","index":39,"end_time":144.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If you want to walk through, we can look at yours.","index":40,"end_time":146.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do I have the ability to share?","index":41,"end_time":150.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.7,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Maybe not.","index":42,"end_time":151.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":150.86,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"You might have to.","index":43,"end_time":152.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Might have to get.","index":44,"end_time":159.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":158.7,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Oh, here we go.","index":45,"end_time":160.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Cool.","index":46,"end_time":164.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":164.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Can you see my screen?","index":47,"end_time":165.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":164.91,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It''s loaded.","index":48,"end_time":167.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yep, there it is.","index":49,"end_time":168.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, like, on this page, what we''re going to do is tweak some of these to.","index":50,"end_time":176.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":169.51,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Be more options.","index":51,"end_time":179.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":178.63,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So rather than like BSL 3 and 4 compliant.","index":52,"end_time":182.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.67,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It''s going to be lab integrated or building integrated, continuous flow or batch, thermic or chemical.","index":53,"end_time":189.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.95,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":54,"end_time":192.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just changing out kind of the copy on those options.","index":55,"end_time":198.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So what that''s going to be is.","index":56,"end_time":199.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.52,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"These are going to be.","index":57,"end_time":200.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":199.84,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It doesn''t let me change the thing unless I have comments.","index":58,"end_time":210.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":206.76,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So these will be say continuous or batch, thermal or chemical.","index":59,"end_time":216.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.76,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Building integrated, lab integrated.","index":60,"end_time":219.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":217.55,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then here.","index":61,"end_time":221.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Sorry, not here.","index":62,"end_time":224.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Maybe here.","index":63,"end_time":224.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":224.15,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, here.","index":64,"end_time":226.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.87,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Between these two elements.","index":65,"end_time":228.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.15,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''d like to insert that copy.","index":66,"end_time":231.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":230.27,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And what that will look like is I''ve just got it kind of bulleted out now.","index":67,"end_time":236.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.91,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And this is one wing for some, but for like eds it''ll be.","index":68,"end_time":241.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":237.55,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This will be a paragraph.","index":69,"end_time":244.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This will be a paragraph.","index":70,"end_time":246.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.44,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This will be a paragraph.","index":71,"end_time":249.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.24,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This will be a paragraph.","index":72,"end_time":252.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":250.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":73,"end_time":253.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So then what I''d like to do is then clicking say continuous flow or batch to drop you down to that.","index":74,"end_time":263.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.16,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":75,"end_time":264.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then it''ll be the digester here.","index":76,"end_time":269.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.96,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Sidebar loads.","index":77,"end_time":273.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271.94,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This is going to be higher, low pressure.","index":78,"end_time":275.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":273.3,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This can be mechanically agitated, thermic or caustic.","index":79,"end_time":278.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Or caustic.","index":80,"end_time":280.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And this can be building integrated and containment or standalone.","index":81,"end_time":284.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then similarly there''s going to be those couple paragraphs for each of those.","index":82,"end_time":290.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.3,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''d like to drop that in here.","index":83,"end_time":292.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.9,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":84,"end_time":294.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then have each of those elements link down to it.","index":85,"end_time":298.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":86,"end_time":298.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you still want it below this first section, engineered for safe tissue waste.","index":87,"end_time":303.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This is still the first one.","index":88,"end_time":304.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":89,"end_time":305.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":304.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because I was thinking, okay, yeah, this.","index":90,"end_time":308.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is more, I think this.","index":91,"end_time":309.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.58,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"That''s a more high level kind of overall description.","index":92,"end_time":312.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.78,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And that gives us then the ability to use that space for things that are kind of going to be broadly applicable across the systems.","index":93,"end_time":319.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.22,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Right.","index":94,"end_time":319.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then below that we''ll start getting into the deep, more detailed options.","index":95,"end_time":323.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.86,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then we''ll drop into the how it works.","index":96,"end_time":326.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.41,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then we have some of the more, you know, generic, broader pieces.","index":97,"end_time":332.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I left comments on a couple of the pages.","index":98,"end_time":335.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":333.37,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''d like to move this trusted bar with the carousel.","index":99,"end_time":340.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.77,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"To the bottom of the page.","index":100,"end_time":342.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.61,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":101,"end_time":344.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"There are a couple reasons behind that.","index":102,"end_time":349.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.17,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I think that I''m a little bit worried if it''s in the middle.","index":103,"end_time":353.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Like when I hit there, I thought that was the bottom of the page.","index":104,"end_time":355.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.07,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":105,"end_time":356.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the way.","index":106,"end_time":358.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I think it looks nice, but the way the carousel sits with white space just means that there ends up being a lot of white space kind of around it.","index":107,"end_time":366.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.27,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So I''d like to shift that down.","index":108,"end_time":368.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.59,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then there were a couple other kind of smaller comments, but those are all fairly self explanatory.","index":109,"end_time":376.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.59,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":110,"end_time":377.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh, and then just on the homepage, what I''d like to do.","index":111,"end_time":385.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.33,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Is.","index":112,"end_time":388.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.37,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Move, rather than this layout, I''d like to move this image.","index":113,"end_time":396.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''d like to have basically three images across the top one for each of our product lines.","index":114,"end_time":403.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.29,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then have.","index":115,"end_time":405.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.3,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"If you click those, take it over to the product page and then move this future waste treatment.","index":116,"end_time":411.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then instead for hospitals and biopharma, for hospitals and life sciences, move that below the three images.","index":117,"end_time":418.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.66,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":118,"end_time":419.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then still have this graphic below it.","index":119,"end_time":422.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.06,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then we can come down and we have a little bit more blurb on each of these.","index":120,"end_time":427.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.78,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''d like to.","index":121,"end_time":428.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.58,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So for this one here, the rapidly decontaminate solid and redback waste, move that text over to here on the right, push the two images up, and then move an image of an STI over to the left where this is now.","index":122,"end_time":445.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.55,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":123,"end_time":448.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":124,"end_time":451.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"For the images at the top, did you have a particular set in mind or just.","index":125,"end_time":455.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Images for this?","index":126,"end_time":458.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I dropped to it.","index":127,"end_time":460.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.55,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":128,"end_time":460.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":129,"end_time":461.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we use 1, 2, 3 across the top, even if we kind of look at it and then decide we want to replace those images with something else, either be as a color scheme fits better or sharper, whatever it is, we''ll still have the layout kind of locked in with those.","index":130,"end_time":480.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.55,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And that doesn''t have to be a blocker for moving ahead.","index":131,"end_time":482.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":132,"end_time":483.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And do you want the images to appear first on the top?","index":133,"end_time":486.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No text.","index":134,"end_time":487.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''ll just be the images when you first land on the page and then the text below it, or do you want the future of wastewise treatment?","index":135,"end_time":494.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":487.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Then the images and then images.","index":136,"end_time":497.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Images at the top.","index":137,"end_time":498.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":497.17,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":138,"end_time":499.009,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then future waste treatment.","index":139,"end_time":501.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.57,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Kind of like drop, let''s say if it''s going to be occupying this space, if this top third is images, maybe a little bit more than a third.","index":140,"end_time":511.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":141,"end_time":512.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then move this text down to like this face down here.","index":142,"end_time":516.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":513.07,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":143,"end_time":519.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":518.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, just.","index":144,"end_time":521.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.31,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"We.","index":145,"end_time":521.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"We had.","index":146,"end_time":523.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.51,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"We had done this for a couple.","index":147,"end_time":524.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"We had made a couple tweaks to this site as we had various projects come up or as various landing pages for ABMs.","index":148,"end_time":531.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"What I want to do is we relaunch this.","index":149,"end_time":534.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":532.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This updated site.","index":150,"end_time":536.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":535.15,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Right now, have the landing page set that we don''t know what product people who are landing there are looking for and we don''t want to.","index":151,"end_time":546.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":539.05,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And we want to have those three options immediately available.","index":152,"end_time":549.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":153,"end_time":550.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"One other note I had on there was.","index":154,"end_time":555.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I want to look at how we''re having the contact us button show, I think like having these two contact us buttons immediately visible here.","index":155,"end_time":567.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.09,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I don''t Love.","index":156,"end_time":569.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":568.59,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"But I think that.","index":157,"end_time":570.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.55,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I think that at times we will have those.","index":158,"end_time":574.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.27,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"That''s just going to be how it is.","index":159,"end_time":577.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":575.79,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Maybe if as you''re scrolling down, this top bar retracts up so you don''t see it, and that is only when you mouse up, the top bar drops down.","index":160,"end_time":586.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":578.67,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then we can keep some of these.","index":161,"end_time":589.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Contact us here.","index":162,"end_time":590.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.11,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"What I do want to try to avoid, though, is it wasn''t this page.","index":163,"end_time":596.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":590.92,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Maybe it was this page.","index":164,"end_time":599.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.76,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":165,"end_time":603.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"What I want to avoid is this though, where you have three.","index":166,"end_time":606.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Right.","index":167,"end_time":608.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I understand what you''re saying.","index":168,"end_time":609.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":169,"end_time":610.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":610.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Other than that, mostly little things.","index":170,"end_time":615.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.76,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I want to take this section here that''s now Service Tools.","index":171,"end_time":619.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":615.24,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I want to call and make that our technical library.","index":172,"end_time":623,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":620.44,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":173,"end_time":624.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Add a dropdown for it on here.","index":174,"end_time":627.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So that brings you in.","index":175,"end_time":630.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":628.84,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then that''s where we''ll house the cut sheets, spec sheets, kind of pieces like that.","index":176,"end_time":635.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And right now we''ll start with cut sheets, and as we can keep going, we''ll see what else goes in there.","index":177,"end_time":640.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":636.12,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And at some point we may add another one of these buckets.","index":178,"end_time":643.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":641.08,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"But for right now, I think we can keep these elements kind of as they are.","index":179,"end_time":647.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":643.92,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Mm.","index":180,"end_time":648.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":647.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I want to add one more drop down here.","index":181,"end_time":654.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":650.45,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So one more product page.","index":182,"end_time":659.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":657.57,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And that''s going to be the.","index":183,"end_time":661.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":659.97,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"That''s going to be service validation, commissioning system modernization.","index":184,"end_time":670.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.97,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then if we can set that, we can use any of the.","index":185,"end_time":674.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":671.89,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Any template from any other page.","index":186,"end_time":676.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.13,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"To host that information.","index":187,"end_time":680.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.29,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then these are going to be the subsection headers I want there.","index":188,"end_time":684.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":681.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This is a page where we could use more stock imagery, at least initially, flesh it out.","index":189,"end_time":694.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.09,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then I will provide copy for each of these subsections in the next few days or early next week.","index":190,"end_time":702.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":695.13,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":191,"end_time":703.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it seems like a few of these edits kind of are go hand in hand with the copy we''ll get from you, so we can work on a couple of the little ones that are independent of those.","index":192,"end_time":716.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then once we get those additional documents from you, we can get the rest of the.","index":193,"end_time":721.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":716.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The site together.","index":194,"end_time":722.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I think it''d be beneficial once we send you the new versions, then we can hop on a call and walk through it again if there''s anything else before we launch it, like you said, so we can get a final walk through.","index":195,"end_time":733.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, yeah, so what I want to do from my end is take when you guys have that round of updates up, I want to sit down with my leadership team, go through it, make sure everything everyone''s asked for, talked about has been captured and that there aren''t any you know, if it''s little copy tweaks or image, you know, things like that we can change down the road.","index":196,"end_time":753.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.05,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"But if it''s going to be like adding that, you know, additional service filter changes, whatever else page that, that''s all captured before we go live with it.","index":197,"end_time":763.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":198,"end_time":764.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And in terms of follow up materials, what I''m expecting to have for you is this document with kind of two to four sentences under each of these bullet points that''ll go into each of the digester and EDS product pages and then.","index":199,"end_time":781.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":764.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"One more like this for that new service oriented page.","index":200,"end_time":787,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":783.16,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":201,"end_time":788.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds good.","index":202,"end_time":789.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as timeline, do you know when you would.","index":203,"end_time":793.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think you said the next couple days.","index":204,"end_time":794.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m going to try to see if I can book one of our developers just a time, maybe middle of next week that I can just get him on the calendar so we can get these done as quick as possible.","index":205,"end_time":805.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Would you say by Monday or Tuesday we''d have these things from you?","index":206,"end_time":809.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, and what I''ll do is I''ll set a reminder to chase down because I''m getting some of our engineering team.","index":207,"end_time":818.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Just help me flesh those out to make sure I don''t miss anything.","index":208,"end_time":822.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.5,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":209,"end_time":823.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll set a reminder for Monday morning to follow up with them on those points.","index":210,"end_time":827.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":823.34,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":211,"end_time":828.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll try to block some time out one of our developers calendars.","index":212,"end_time":833.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So as soon as we get those, we can just get them in progress.","index":213,"end_time":836.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect launch.","index":214,"end_time":838.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":836.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So you know, actually if you.","index":215,"end_time":842.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.19,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Cool, yeah, that works.","index":216,"end_time":845.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.15,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then so let''s say that is next week.","index":217,"end_time":848.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":845.71,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"What I mean, is it crazy to try to launch say the week of the 22nd?","index":218,"end_time":856.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":851.11,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Let me check our team calendar here.","index":219,"end_time":861.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because to some extent, I mean if, if you guys have the capacity for that, it might not be the worst thing to launch in advance of the holidays because I would expect there''d be lower traffic.","index":220,"end_time":874.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.47,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So if there are issues or there are things that come up, that''s probably a safer period to do it, you know, Plus I''d just kind of like to have this done for the new year.","index":221,"end_time":883.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":874.78,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"If that''s going to be too tight for y'', all, that''s fine.","index":222,"end_time":888.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":884.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"We can kind of do it.","index":223,"end_time":889.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I want to, I want to do it on a timeline where we''ll have support for it.","index":224,"end_time":893.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.94,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So if something does go wrong, it''s not like an empty house while that''s going on.","index":225,"end_time":899.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.58,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Absolutely, that makes sense.","index":226,"end_time":901.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":899.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":227,"end_time":901.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"One of our main developers has availability Wednesday.","index":228,"end_time":906.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like we were saying, if we got the things back from you either Monday or Tuesday.","index":229,"end_time":910.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I can just get a Task in place to him for that 17th and 18th hopefully.","index":230,"end_time":915.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then we can get maybe the draft to you or the new version by the 19th and we can shoot for the week of the 22nd.","index":231,"end_time":923.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me just put a note in my calendar for the 19th.","index":232,"end_time":928.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":924.58,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So it dates back.","index":233,"end_time":933.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":930.98,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Second.","index":234,"end_time":939.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":938.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":235,"end_time":939.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"But I will double check too with Bailey and the team.","index":236,"end_time":947.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But that the week of the 22nd that gives us like those three days in the next week to.","index":237,"end_time":952.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"To get those turned around to you.","index":238,"end_time":955.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":239,"end_time":956.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":956,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":240,"end_time":956.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.36,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, so yeah, we''ll look for those sheets from you then and then take it from there.","index":241,"end_time":961.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":242,"end_time":962.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.32,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Cool.","index":243,"end_time":966.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if as you''re going through, as you or the development team is kind of going through these changes, if there you want clarification on anything or have any questions, just drop me an email or give me a call.","index":244,"end_time":979.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":966.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I should be able to answer.","index":245,"end_time":982.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Resolve any of them pretty quickly.","index":246,"end_time":985.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":982.82,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I tried to include any relevant assets in areas where I''ve mentioned it or called it out.","index":247,"end_time":991.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":985.82,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So that should all be fairly self contained and ready to go.","index":248,"end_time":995.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":993.179,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":249,"end_time":996.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":996.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that''ll be helpful to have those extra notes in there too in bugherd.","index":250,"end_time":1001.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":996.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And also just you walking through this is helpful too.","index":251,"end_time":1004.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1001.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me take a quick look down here.","index":252,"end_time":1008.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Oh.","index":253,"end_time":1009.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1008.55,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, I think, I think everything else is pretty self explanatory.","index":254,"end_time":1025.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1021.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I had some.","index":255,"end_time":1026.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1025.59,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Copy pieces and some other changes for like the About Us page.","index":256,"end_time":1031.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1028.31,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":257,"end_time":1032.999,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1032.599,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Put all that copy and imagery in there so it should all be fairly one to one.","index":258,"end_time":1038.799,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.479,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, this goes here, this goes here.","index":259,"end_time":1040.519,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.799,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":260,"end_time":1041.399,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1040.919,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think we''ve talked through most of the kind of more general or broader comments.","index":261,"end_time":1049.239,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1041.959,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":262,"end_time":1050.719,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1050.039,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, if we have any comments too, I''ll send an email over to you and yeah, we can reach out with anything else.","index":263,"end_time":1057.239,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1050.719,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I have a question from my engineer.","index":264,"end_time":1060.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"How are we going to maintain.","index":265,"end_time":1062.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1061.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"How do we maintain rankings through the switch?","index":266,"end_time":1065.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1062.97,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"That will be a developer question so I can ask them and let you know.","index":267,"end_time":1071.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1067.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, if you could have two questions to send over for them, that''s one the second and this is also noted here if you could do a quick out like what tracking options we are available to load up on the site and which ones would fall under a gdpr you need to click to click and accept and which.","index":268,"end_time":1093.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1071.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And which ones wouldn''t.","index":269,"end_time":1094.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":270,"end_time":1095.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1095.14,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":271,"end_time":1099.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1099.3,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, I will send those over to him as well.","index":272,"end_time":1102.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1100.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"With these edits.","index":273,"end_time":1103.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Were you able to get the pictures that were needed for that one?","index":274,"end_time":1122.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That page?","index":275,"end_time":1122.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1122.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I know you''ve been waiting on someone.","index":276,"end_time":1126.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1124.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Everyone except this one.","index":277,"end_time":1128.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1126.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":278,"end_time":1129.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1128.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Everyone except the one headshot.","index":279,"end_time":1130.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1129.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"When I mentioned that again I got a Laugh.","index":280,"end_time":1135.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1133.71,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So.","index":281,"end_time":1136.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1135.71,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Oh.","index":282,"end_time":1136.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1136.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":283,"end_time":1146.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I will make sure to ask him these with the edits, but that sounds good.","index":284,"end_time":1150.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Cool.","index":285,"end_time":1166.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.84,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":286,"end_time":1166.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.04,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So, you know, just as you''re working through it again, if you have any questions or want any clarification on anything, don''t hesitate to reach out.","index":287,"end_time":1174.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I will have the rest of this copy for your team in the next couple of days.","index":288,"end_time":1179.919,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.88,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And I think those are all the outstanding pieces here.","index":289,"end_time":1182.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1180,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yes.","index":290,"end_time":1184,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"On a website, I believe so.","index":291,"end_time":1186.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1184,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Did you have anything else on the other things we''ve been sending or priority is now?","index":292,"end_time":1191.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Not yet.","index":293,"end_time":1192.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1191.83,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Priority is website.","index":294,"end_time":1193.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1192.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Priority has been website.","index":295,"end_time":1195.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1194.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Now that I''m kind of blocked on this until I get some of these notes back.","index":296,"end_time":1200.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1196.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''ll turn focus over to some of those blogs and other pieces until I get the notes back and then I''ll focus on getting you the copy over.","index":297,"end_time":1209.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1200.87,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"But what highest priority is website right now and then I''m going to keep layering in some of these other pieces.","index":298,"end_time":1215.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.99,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":299,"end_time":1216.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1215.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds good.","index":300,"end_time":1217.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1216.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll look for those things from you and we''ll just be in touch with email if we need any questions on any of the other comments.","index":301,"end_time":1223.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1217.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":302,"end_time":1224.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1223.93,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And.","index":303,"end_time":1226.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1226.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"If their email is about clarifications on this website piece, please go ahead and hit that big red exclamation mark.","index":304,"end_time":1236.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1228.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Send a high priority email just so I know that that''s a.","index":305,"end_time":1240.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.45,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Quick turnaround.","index":306,"end_time":1243.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.25,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Get it back to you so I''m not blocking the developer''s work on it.","index":307,"end_time":1245.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.05,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":308,"end_time":1247.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then just thinking ahead for our meeting, I know we are normally on Tuesdays now.","index":309,"end_time":1251.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we''re going to be working on the website Wednesday, would you want to meet maybe Thursday next week when the website may have a new version so you can walk through it at that time instead since we won''t have the update.","index":310,"end_time":1263.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1251.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just thinking ahead there.","index":311,"end_time":1264.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1263.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes, let''s.","index":312,"end_time":1266.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1265.02,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Let''s plan, let''s plan that we''re going to reschedule the Tuesday meeting.","index":313,"end_time":1270.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1266.06,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So send me when you have a sense of when that will be ready.","index":314,"end_time":1274.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1270.94,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"We''ll base, we''ll just schedule that meeting around when that''s going to be finished and then we''ll at that meeting we can talk through the following week.","index":315,"end_time":1283.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1275.35,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Whether what launch is going to look like and what we''ll do in terms of touch points around that.","index":316,"end_time":1289.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1285.51,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":317,"end_time":1290.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1289.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":318,"end_time":1291.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1291.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I will go let our developer know and also touch base with Bailey too and see what she thinks.","index":319,"end_time":1297.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1291.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know she''s been working on the website too for a while, so.","index":320,"end_time":1299.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1297.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":321,"end_time":1300.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1299.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":322,"end_time":1301.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then I think when we get this up and clear, there''ll probably be a little bit of cleanup work around it, but then we can have our focus on some of these other content and marketing pieces.","index":323,"end_time":1312.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.52,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":324,"end_time":1314.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that works.","index":325,"end_time":1315.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1314.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you.","index":326,"end_time":1318.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1317.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I appreciate the feedback.","index":327,"end_time":1319.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1318.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we''ll get started on this.","index":328,"end_time":1321.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1319.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":329,"end_time":1322.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1321.72,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":330,"end_time":1322.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1322.2,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":331,"end_time":1323.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1323.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Bye.","index":332,"end_time":1324.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1323.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"dateString":"2025-12-11T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86719613161?pwd=FUtBTO6w0NHl6Zybphu2fW18etobyw.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,dnelsen@biosafeeng.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","dnelsen@biosafeeng.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC2CCZTPKF1PCJAHTVG5S2VK","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed website launch targeted for week of December 22 pending final content delivery.","Dan committed to delivering final product page and service copy by Monday or Tuesday.","Taylor blocked developer time for December 17–18 to implement website updates quickly.","Team aligned on visual layout revisions: homepage images, copy sections, and page flow.","New ''Technical Library'' and service dropdown page agreed, with content to follow soon."],"highlights":[{"quote":"What I want to do is we relaunch this updated site.","speaker":"Dan Nelsen"},{"quote":"I''ll try to block some time out one of our developers'' calendars.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"Priority is website. Now that I''m kind of blocked on this...","speaker":"Dan Nelsen"}],"topics":["launch","delivery","content","timeline"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-12T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Website Content and Structure Updates**\n\nThe team agreed to finalize and implement key website content changes to enable a relaunch by the week of the 22nd (00:00).\n\n- **Dan Nelsen confirmed completion of about 56 initial copy comments and detailed upcoming technical content for the digester and EDS product pages, expected by Monday or Tuesday next week to unblock development work** (01:24)  \n    - He is gathering technical notes from engineers to produce 3 paragraphs per product page for precise details.  \n    - These content additions will complete the last major blockers before launch.  \n    - Taylor Doerbaum plans to allocate developer time mid-next week for implementing these edits to meet the timeline.  \n    - Launching before the holidays is preferred to allow lower traffic for smoother issue resolution.\n\n- **The website will adopt a new homepage layout featuring three images across the top representing each product line, linking directly to product pages, to improve visitor navigation and product discovery** (06:21)  \n    - Dan wants the images to occupy roughly the top third of the page with text sections, including the “Future of Wastewise Treatment,” moved below.  \n    - The current layout with a single image and text will be replaced to give users clear, immediate product options.  \n    - This approach addresses unknown visitor intent and supports better engagement with product lines.\n\n- **Several UX and content adjustments were approved, including relocating the “trusted bar” with carousel to the bottom to reduce white space and improve perceived page flow** (05:43)  \n    - Dan’s reasoning is that placing it mid-page misleads users into thinking it’s the page bottom.  \n    - Minor copy and layout tweaks on About Us and other pages will align with the overall refresh.\n\n- **A new “Technical Library” dropdown will be added to replace the “Service Tools” section, initially housing cut sheets and spec sheets, with plans to expand over time** (10:10)  \n    - An additional dropdown for “Service Validation, Commissioning, System Modernization” product page will be created using existing templates.  \n    - Dan will provide copy for these subsections in the next few days or early next week to flesh out those pages.  \n    - Stock imagery will be used initially, with the possibility of enhancements later.\n\n## **Project Timeline and Launch Planning**\n\nThe team aligned on a clear timeline targeting a website launch during the week of the 22nd, with key development milestones scheduled for the week prior (00:13).\n\n- **Dan will finalize all technical copy inputs by Monday morning, enabling development work to start by midweek (17th-18th), aiming for a draft site by the 19th for internal review** (13:29)  \n    - Taylor confirmed developer availability to prioritize these tasks immediately upon content receipt.  \n    - This schedule supports a launch window before the holidays while ensuring support coverage post-launch.\n\n- **A follow-up review call is planned for the week after initial updates to walk through the site with Dan’s leadership team and ensure all requested changes are captured** (12:14)  \n    - This will serve as the final quality check before public rollout.  \n    - Any minor copy or image tweaks identified can be handled after launch to avoid blockers.\n\n- **The regular Tuesday meeting will be rescheduled to Thursday next week to align with the anticipated new site version, enabling a live walkthrough and launch planning discussion** (20:46)  \n    - This flexibility accommodates the development and review cadence without delaying progress.\n\n## **Content Strategy and Prioritization**\n\nWebsite updates are the highest current priority, with other marketing content to be layered in after completion (00:19).\n\n- **Dan emphasized that all focus is on the website until the final copy and technical details are delivered, after which he will shift to blogs and other marketing materials** (19:51)  \n    - He highlighted the importance of rapid turnaround on website clarifications by requesting high-priority email flags to avoid blocking developers.  \n    - This prioritization reflects the critical role of the website as the primary customer touchpoint.\n\n- **The team will continue to refine and expand content post-launch, including adding new imagery and fleshing out service-related pages as copy becomes available** (10:50)  \n    - This phased approach balances a timely launch with ongoing content improvements.\n\n## **Technical and SEO Considerations**\n\nKey technical questions regarding SEO and tracking compliance are pending developer input to ensure smooth transition and regulatory adherence (00:17).\n\n- **Dan raised concerns about maintaining search engine rankings through the website switch and requested clarity on tracking options and GDPR compliance** (17:38)  \n    - Taylor will forward these queries to the developer and provide answers to mitigate risks of traffic loss.  \n    - Understanding which tracking tools require explicit user consent will help maintain compliance and user trust.\n\n- **The team agreed to monitor these technical aspects closely during the launch phase to avoid disruptions and ensure accurate analytics** (18:20)  \n    - This proactive approach guards against SEO setbacks and data gaps.\n\n## **Collaboration and Communication Protocols**\n\nClear communication channels and quick response expectations were established to keep the website project on track (00:16).\n\n- **Dan encouraged the team to reach out promptly with questions during development, promising quick clarifications to prevent developer delays** (16:06)  \n    - He has embedded relevant assets and notes within Bugherd to support self-service and reduce back-and-forth.  \n    - Taylor confirmed this documentation will aid the developer’s understanding and expedite fixes.\n\n- **Priority emails marked with a red exclamation flag will be used for urgent website clarifications to ensure timely responses** (20:23)  \n    - This system aims to avoid bottlenecks and maintain momentum.\n\n- **Regular check-ins and alignment calls are planned post-update to review progress and plan next steps, ensuring all stakeholders remain informed and engaged** (21:05)  \n    - Taylor and Dan will coordinate schedules and maintain visibility on developer workloads and content delivery.\n\n","outline":null,"keywords":["Website launch","copywriting","product pages","developer scheduling","UX design","SEO preservation"],"overview":"- **Website Relaunch Target:** Key content changes will enable a website relaunch by the week of the 22nd.\n\n- **Content Completion:** Technical content for product pages will be finished early next week to unblock development work.\n\n- **New Homepage Design:** The homepage will feature three product images for improved navigation and visitor engagement.\n\n- **Technical Library Addition:** A new dropdown will be created for technical documents, starting with existing resources.\n\n- **Launch Timeline Agreement:** A draft site review is planned for the 19th, aiming for a holiday launch.\n\n- **Communication Protocols:** Urgent questions will be flagged in emails to ensure quick developer responses and avoid delays.","action_items":"\n**Dan Nelsen**\nProvide approximate three paragraphs of copy for digester and EDS product pages by Monday or Tuesday (00:59)\nDeliver copy for the new Service Validation, Commissioning, and Modernization product page early next week (10:50)\nReview updated website with leadership immediately after first round of edits to confirm completeness and accuracy before launch (12:03)\nFollow up with engineering team Monday morning to ensure completion of technical notes and copy (13:42)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nCoordinate developer scheduling for mid-next week (Dec 17-18) to implement website changes as soon as copy and assets are received (13:43)\nSend Dan the developer’s SEO and tracking questions regarding ranking maintenance and GDPR compliance (17:47)\nFollow up with Bailey and team to confirm availability and feedback on edits and will reschedule the usual Tuesday meeting to Thursday next week for website walkthrough (20:46)\nEmail any additional comments or questions about website edits to Dan (17:30)\nMonitor progress and provide feedback or escalate urgent bugs with high priority email flag for quick resolution (20:23)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"893ee661-0f5a-4998-b92c-8364bb802fa2","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
