  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Taylor Doerbaum and Daniel nelsen',
  '## **Website Content and Structure Updates**

The team agreed to finalize and implement key website content changes to enable a relaunch by the week of the 22nd (00:00).

- **Dan Nelsen confirmed completion of about 56 initial copy comments and detailed upcoming technical content for the digester and EDS product pages, expected by Monday or Tuesday next week to unblock development work** (01:24)  
    - He is gathering technical notes from engineers to produce 3 paragraphs per product page for precise details.  
    - These content additions will complete the last major blockers before launch.  
    - Taylor Doerbaum plans to allocate developer time mid-next week for implementing these edits to meet the timeline.  
    - Launching before the holidays is preferred to allow lower traffic for smoother issue resolution.

- **The website will adopt a new homepage layout featuring three images across the top representing each product line, linking directly to product pages, to improve visitor navigation and product discovery** (06:21)  
    - Dan wants the images to occupy roughly the top third of the page with text sections, including the “Future of Wastewise Treatment,” moved below.  
    - The current layout with a single image and text will be replaced to give users clear, immediate product options.  
    - This approach addresses unknown visitor intent and supports better engagement with product lines.

- **Several UX and content adjustments were approved, including relocating the “trusted bar” with carousel to the bottom to reduce white space and improve perceived page flow** (05:43)  
    - Dan’s reasoning is that placing it mid-page misleads users into thinking it’s the page bottom.  
    - Minor copy and layout tweaks on About Us and other pages will align with the overall refresh.

- **A new “Technical Library” dropdown will be added to replace the “Service Tools” section, initially housing cut sheets and spec sheets, with plans to expand over time** (10:10)  
    - An additional dropdown for “Service Validation, Commissioning, System Modernization” product page will be created using existing templates.  
    - Dan will provide copy for these subsections in the next few days or early next week to flesh out those pages.  
    - Stock imagery will be used initially, with the possibility of enhancements later.

## **Project Timeline and Launch Planning**

The team aligned on a clear timeline targeting a website launch during the week of the 22nd, with key development milestones scheduled for the week prior (00:13).

- **Dan will finalize all technical copy inputs by Monday morning, enabling development work to start by midweek (17th-18th), aiming for a draft site by the 19th for internal review** (13:29)  
    - Taylor confirmed developer availability to prioritize these tasks immediately upon content receipt.  
    - This schedule supports a launch window before the holidays while ensuring support coverage post-launch.

- **A follow-up review call is planned for the week after initial updates to walk through the site with Dan’s leadership team and ensure all requested changes are captured** (12:14)  
    - This will serve as the final quality check before public rollout.  
    - Any minor copy or image tweaks identified can be handled after launch to avoid blockers.

- **The regular Tuesday meeting will be rescheduled to Thursday next week to align with the anticipated new site version, enabling a live walkthrough and launch planning discussion** (20:46)  
    - This flexibility accommodates the development and review cadence without delaying progress.

## **Content Strategy and Prioritization**

Website updates are the highest current priority, with other marketing content to be layered in after completion (00:19).

- **Dan emphasized that all focus is on the website until the final copy and technical details are delivered, after which he will shift to blogs and other marketing materials** (19:51)  
    - He highlighted the importance of rapid turnaround on website clarifications by requesting high-priority email flags to avoid blocking developers.  
    - This prioritization reflects the critical role of the website as the primary customer touchpoint.

- **The team will continue to refine and expand content post-launch, including adding new imagery and fleshing out service-related pages as copy becomes available** (10:50)  
    - This phased approach balances a timely launch with ongoing content improvements.

## **Technical and SEO Considerations**

Key technical questions regarding SEO and tracking compliance are pending developer input to ensure smooth transition and regulatory adherence (00:17).

- **Dan raised concerns about maintaining search engine rankings through the website switch and requested clarity on tracking options and GDPR compliance** (17:38)  
    - Taylor will forward these queries to the developer and provide answers to mitigate risks of traffic loss.  
    - Understanding which tracking tools require explicit user consent will help maintain compliance and user trust.

- **The team agreed to monitor these technical aspects closely during the launch phase to avoid disruptions and ensure accurate analytics** (18:20)  
    - This proactive approach guards against SEO setbacks and data gaps.

## **Collaboration and Communication Protocols**

Clear communication channels and quick response expectations were established to keep the website project on track (00:16).

- **Dan encouraged the team to reach out promptly with questions during development, promising quick clarifications to prevent developer delays** (16:06)  
    - He has embedded relevant assets and notes within Bugherd to support self-service and reduce back-and-forth.  
    - Taylor confirmed this documentation will aid the developer’s understanding and expedite fixes.

- **Priority emails marked with a red exclamation flag will be used for urgent website clarifications to ensure timely responses** (20:23)  
    - This system aims to avoid bottlenecks and maintain momentum.

- **Regular check-ins and alignment calls are planned post-update to review progress and plan next steps, ensuring all stakeholders remain informed and engaged** (21:05)  
    - Taylor and Dan will coordinate schedules and maintain visibility on developer workloads and content delivery.

',
  '2025-12-11 20:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Provide approximate three paragraphs of copy for digester and EDS product pages by Monday or Tuesday (00:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Deliver copy for the new Service Validation, Commissioning, and Modernization product page early next week (10:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Review updated website with leadership immediately after first round of edits to confirm completeness and accuracy before launch (12:03)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up with engineering team Monday morning to ensure completion of technical notes and copy (13:42)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate developer scheduling for mid-next week (Dec 17-18) to implement website changes as soon as copy and assets are received (13:43)","completed":false},{"text":"Send Dan the developer’s SEO and tracking questions regarding ranking maintenance and GDPR compliance (17:47)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up with Bailey and team to confirm availability and feedback on edits and will reschedule the usual Tuesday meeting to Thursday next week for website walkthrough (20:46)","completed":false},{"text":"Email any additional comments or questions about website edits to Dan (17:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor progress and provide feedback or escalate urgent bugs with high priority email flag for quick resolution (20:23)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: New North x Sedra Solutions: Weekly Meeting (2025-12-10 16:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '292bf658-a285-4fdd-a6e5-d352a30347c9',
    '2025-12-10 16:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBZF0DADZG11EC6BRBTEPB47',
    'New North x Sedra Solutions: Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Taylor Doerbaum","fahad al mutawa","Baylee Gunnell","Jackie Wheeler"}'::text[],
    890,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88927304763?pwd=asbbQolEtVpMuYX5uccJpOibhnlog1.1',
    '{"id":"01KBZF0DADZG11EC6BRBTEPB47","title":"New North x Sedra Solutions: Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Social Media and Content Strategy**\n\nThe team is seeing strong engagement and follower growth on social channels due to consistent posting and plans to sustain momentum into early next year.\n\n- **Organic social posts are scheduled through January 15th**, with the main page content booked until January 8th, supporting ongoing audience engagement (02:24)  \n    - The main page gained **18 new followers** and Fahad''s page added **16 new followers and 15 new connections** in the last seven days.  \n    - Taylor highlighted that consistent posting boosts reach and engagement rates, validating the current content strategy.  \n    - Jackie is developing an ebook on the fraud landscape for 2026, aiming to finish next week for a blog launch and social promotion in early January.  \n    - The team plans to pull additional blog content and fresh ideas from Fahad to maintain posting consistency beyond January.\n\n- **Taylor will prepare a year-end review comparing paid and organic social stats** to showcase gains from recent campaigns and content efforts (02:24)  \n    - This review will highlight Fahad’s ABM campaign’s role in driving significant organic connections.  \n    - The data comparison aims to inform future planning and demonstrate ROI on social initiatives.\n\n## **ABM Email Campaign and Lead Management**\n\nThe ABM campaign was streamlined for better tracking, with 175 emails sent since Monday, and improvements planned in lead notification processes.\n\n- **Two new email sequences were merged into one campaign in Lemlist, sending 175 emails since Monday** to improve tracking and consistency (03:39)  \n    - Fahad confirmed ongoing weekly list updates to add new contacts and expand outreach.  \n    - The team expects improved engagement from refined messaging and consolidated campaigns.  \n    - Taylor will continue monitoring results to adjust tactics as needed.\n\n- **Lead notifications currently go to Fahad, but adding Jeffrey to this list will improve efficiency** by removing Fahad as a bottleneck in lead distribution (05:00)  \n    - Taylor agreed to update the notification list to include Jeffrey, streamlining lead access and follow-up.  \n    - Fahad downloads lead data and shares it with Jeffrey; automating this step will save time.  \n    - Jackie clarified she does not handle leads directly; Jeffrey is the lead owner.\n\n## **Paid Advertising and Targeting Strategy**\n\nPaid ads are generating leads and impressions, and the team is refining targeting using job titles and company lists to increase brand awareness among key stakeholders.\n\n- **LinkedIn lead gen ads produced 39 leads for the ebook Free Guide and additional leads for other assets like the procurement data sheet** (03:57)  \n    - The video ad amassed **4,306 views over the last 30 days**, maintaining consistent exposure.  \n    - Taylor asked if regular lead spreadsheets would be helpful; Fahad confirmed lead notifications suffice if Jeffrey is included.  \n    - The team is preparing to add targeted company and job title data to improve ad precision.\n\n- **Targeting will combine specific job titles and company names to reach relevant decision-makers involved in a major restructuring case** (06:37)  \n    - Fahad shared a docket with creditor and law firm contacts managing over **$750 million** in loans, highlighting a focused audience interested in fraud solutions.  \n    - The team aims to reach not just the law firms, but also creditors and corporate contacts to maximize brand exposure.  \n    - Baylee confirmed LinkedIn requires either a list of at least **250 people** or targeting by company and title, so a mixed approach will be used.  \n    - Jackie emphasized targeting job titles containing keywords like “fraud,” “investigations,” or “analyst” to narrow the audience within large firms.\n\n- **Fahad will provide the finalized list of companies and job titles by tomorrow morning**, enabling quick campaign implementation (11:46)  \n    - Taylor committed to having the paid media specialist launch the updated campaign promptly once the list is received.  \n    - The urgency is driven by ongoing court decisions appointing examiners, making timing critical to gain early brand recognition.  \n    - Fahad noted the court is still reviewing over **50 proposals**, keeping the window open for outreach.\n\n## **Strategic Positioning and Market Insights**\n\nThe team is focused on positioning their platform as a trusted fraud solution to relevant stakeholders while carefully managing brand messaging.\n\n- **Fahad clarified the platform targets those uncovering fraud, not those seeking to cover it up, to protect brand integrity** (12:59)  \n    - The team acknowledged the risk of unwanted associations but reaffirmed the platform’s neutral role as a financial data tool.  \n    - Jackie and Taylor joked about a stealth campaign angle for fraudsters but agreed it would harm the brand.  \n    - This clarity guides messaging to ensure the company is seen as a solution for transparency and accountability.\n\n- **The campaign’s broader strategy includes reaching multiple parties involved in restructuring—creditors, companies, and law firms—to maximize market presence** (11:03)  \n    - Fahad emphasized flexibility in targeting to capture all potential users of the platform regardless of their role in the case.  \n    - This multi-angle approach aims to increase adoption and awareness across the ecosystem surrounding financial fraud cases.  \n    - Taylor and Jackie’s collaboration on targeting parameters reflects a balance between precision and scale.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Operational Coordination**\n\nThe team is streamlining processes for content scheduling, lead handling, and campaign management to improve efficiency and responsiveness.\n\n- **Content scheduling avoids low-engagement periods like Christmas week to maximize impact and resource use** (01:44)  \n    - Taylor paused posting during Christmas week, anticipating low audience activity.  \n    - Planning now focuses on ramping back up with fresh content starting early January.\n\n- **Lead handling will be automated by adding Jeffrey to notification lists, reducing manual steps and speeding response times** (05:00)  \n    - This change will eliminate Fahad’s current role as lead distributor, freeing him to focus on other priorities.  \n    - The adjustment reflects a commitment to improving internal workflows for campaign success.\n\n- **Paid media implementation will begin immediately once Fahad provides the finalized targeting list, reflecting tight coordination between teams** (11:54)  \n    - Taylor’s quick handoff to the paid media specialist ensures no delay in campaign updates.  \n    - This tight turnaround is critical given the ongoing court process and competitive environment.\n\n- **Year-end data review of paid vs organic performance is planned to inform next year’s strategy and budget allocation** (02:24)  \n    - This review will provide actionable insights on what channels and content types drive the best ROI.  \n    - It supports continuous improvement in marketing efficiency and goal alignment.","outline":null,"keywords":["Procurement video","Social media campaign","ABM email campaign","LinkedIn ads targeting","Fraud landscape blog","Financial fraud case"],"overview":"- **Social Media Growth:** Consistent posts led to **18 new followers** on the main page and **16 on Fahad''s page** over the last week.\n\n- **Ebook Development:** Jackie is finishing an ebook on the fraud landscape to launch with a blog in early January.\n\n- **ABM Campaign Updates:** Combined email sequences sent **175 emails**, enhancing tracking; lead notification process improved by adding Jeffrey.\n\n- **Paid Ads Performance:** LinkedIn ads generated **39 leads** for the ebook, video ad received **4,306 views** in the last month.\n\n- **Targeting Strategy:** Focus on creditors and law firms involved with **$750 million** in loans; aim for precision by job titles.\n\n- **Process Streamlining:** Automating lead notifications and minimizing engagement drops during low activity periods like Christmas week.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend final procurement video cut for client input upon completion (00:33)\nSchedule additional social media posts for January and February based on Fahad’s input and Jackie’s blog (01:44)\nPrepare year-end review comparing paid and organic campaign data for next week (02:40)\nAdd Jeffrey to lead notification emails for direct lead download to streamline process (05:00)\nImplement paid media campaign targeting using Fahad’s company and job title lists immediately after receipt (11:54)\nProvide ongoing video ad updates to team (14:29)\n\n**Fahad Al Mutawa**\nFinalize and send the detailed company and job title lists for ad targeting by next morning (11:46)\nAdd Jeffrey to lead notification system for direct lead access (05:00)\n\n**Jackie Wheeler**\nContinue ideation and produce “fraud landscape in 2026” ebook and blog targeted for early January launch (02:03)\n"},"duration":14.829999923706055,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":1,"name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":3,"name":"Jackie Wheeler"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Good morning.","index":0,"end_time":3.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":1,"end_time":4.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh, hi, F. How are you guys?","index":2,"end_time":8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.04,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":8.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How''s everyone doing this week?","index":4,"end_time":10.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Excellent, thank you.","index":5,"end_time":12.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.72,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Good.","index":6,"end_time":13.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me get our agenda pulled up.","index":7,"end_time":19.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Past couple weeks, every time I go to share my screen with the agenda, Google logs me out of everything.","index":8,"end_time":26.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":9,"end_time":27.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":27.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''S a feature.","index":10,"end_time":30.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":29.46,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I know.","index":11,"end_time":32.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I swear.","index":12,"end_time":33.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":32.58,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"It''s like every time I''m on a call, I''m like.","index":13,"end_time":34.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Logs me out.","index":14,"end_time":37.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So annoying.","index":15,"end_time":38.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":16,"end_time":41.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Looks like it''s going to be okay today.","index":17,"end_time":44.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All right, so just a couple of updates for you with the procurement video.","index":18,"end_time":50.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thanks for getting back to us with that approval.","index":19,"end_time":52.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that is in progress.","index":20,"end_time":53.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right now we''re doing the with and without captions version.","index":21,"end_time":55.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":53.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''m excited to see that final cut and we''ll send that over to you once it is done so you get your final input on that.","index":22,"end_time":63.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s looking good.","index":23,"end_time":65.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then organic social, we got all of Fahad''s posts that we had created and were approved by you.","index":24,"end_time":69.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":65.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s scheduled through January 15th now.","index":25,"end_time":72.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we should be good with posts there for a little bit.","index":26,"end_time":74.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m thinking like the beginning of January.","index":27,"end_time":76.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll try to get some more ideas from ifahad and then we can get those scheduled out through February and keep that consistency up because as you''ll see in the next slide on Publer, we''re seeing some good stats come through with those that just the consistency of your posts.","index":28,"end_time":89.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s really good.","index":29,"end_time":91.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then as far as the main page, we have those through the eighth.","index":30,"end_time":95.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so I took a break during Christmas week too, because not a lot of people are going to be paying attention.","index":31,"end_time":98.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we didn''t schedule anything during that week.","index":32,"end_time":101.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":98.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But for the main page we have till the 8th.","index":33,"end_time":104.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":101.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''m thinking maybe towards the end of this month or even if you have a couple of things now, I can just pull from blogs as well, but sometimes some additional posts that we can get ready to go for January, so that way we can keep that consistency too.","index":34,"end_time":117.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":104.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know if you have anything in the works, Jackie, as far as new blogs or pull from what we have.","index":35,"end_time":123.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":117.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Nothing at the moment.","index":36,"end_time":124.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":123.9,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m still kind of ideating on some ideas of like, what, you know, the fraud landscape in 2026, you know, kind of an ebook maybe sort of thing.","index":37,"end_time":133.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":125.1,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"You know, I''m trying to think if I can pull that off and I think I can.","index":38,"end_time":136.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":133.74,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I think maybe I can do that next week and then we can write a blog about that and launch it.","index":39,"end_time":140.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":136.7,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"But yeah, I''d love to have that go out like beginning of the.","index":40,"end_time":143.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":140.62,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah, so yeah, that''d be perfect timing then.","index":41,"end_time":147.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then we could promote that on social.","index":42,"end_time":149.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":147.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So great.","index":43,"end_time":150.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, so just for the last seven days, sort of the social stats I was talking about, we have the main page got 18 new followers, which is really great.","index":44,"end_time":160.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":153.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The reach is really high and engagement rate too.","index":45,"end_time":163.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s been more consistent now that we have had those posts going out.","index":46,"end_time":167.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then Fahad''s page as well.","index":47,"end_time":168.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"16 new followers and 15 new connections with a high reach too.","index":48,"end_time":173.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I was looking at some year over year year data this past year and so I figure next week before Christmas happens, we can kind of do like a year review of some stats between paid and also organic because the organic stats are so great just from the connections that Fahad''s gotten from the ABM campaign, but also just the posts we''ve had on the page.","index":49,"end_time":192.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I think it''ll be really cool to compare the data that we''ve seen since we''ve launched these initiatives.","index":50,"end_time":197.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''ll do that next week.","index":51,"end_time":198.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, even though the week data looks really good, so excited to see that come through.","index":52,"end_time":203.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the ABM campaign.","index":53,"end_time":206.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":205.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we implemented the two new emails into lemlist.","index":54,"end_time":209.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":206.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We combined them into one campaign now so we can keep that more consistent as far as tracking in the one section.","index":55,"end_time":216.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so 175 emails have been sent out so far since Monday.","index":56,"end_time":219.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":216.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I know we keep having those new lists come through, so we''ll add those in each week.","index":57,"end_time":223.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As well.","index":58,"end_time":223.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":59,"end_time":224.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So hopefully with those new email messaging sequences we can see some more traction come through and engagement on those.","index":60,"end_time":230.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But those have been launched, just want to let you know there.","index":61,"end_time":233.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we''ll keep an eye on those as well.","index":62,"end_time":234.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":63,"end_time":236.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.89,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"And then paid ad updates.","index":64,"end_time":239.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So for the LinkedIn ads, I just wanted to give you a recap of where we''re at now for the lead gen ads.","index":65,"end_time":244.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So these usually perform very well for your company.","index":66,"end_time":247.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so we have the 39 leads on that ebook Free guide.","index":67,"end_time":250.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The procurement data sheet has seven.","index":68,"end_time":252.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the Buyer''s Guide and White Collar Crime also have a couple of leads.","index":69,"end_time":256.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Jackie, I think you do check in on these, but is it helpful if I send them in Slack, the spreadsheets or I know sometimes you go in there.","index":70,"end_time":265.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I can do either.","index":71,"end_time":266.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I have all the links here, like of all the leads that we have.","index":72,"end_time":270.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if it''s helpful.","index":73,"end_time":271.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I just wanted to see if you wanted me to send this like consistently each week.","index":74,"end_time":274.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I mean, that''s up to Fahad.","index":75,"end_time":277.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":276.09,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I''m not doing anything with the leads.","index":76,"end_time":278.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":277.29,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":77,"end_time":279.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think Jeffrey is taking care of that, right, Fahad?","index":78,"end_time":282.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":279.68,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah, but it will be helpful.","index":79,"end_time":284.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.56,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"I mean, whenever we get a lead, it''s.","index":80,"end_time":287.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.56,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"I''m getting a notification, I download it and I just share it with them.","index":81,"end_time":290.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.08,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Okay.","index":82,"end_time":291.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I, I knew that there were notifications being given, so I wasn''t sure if it was necessary to send the spreadsheets, but we have them all compiled.","index":83,"end_time":297.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If it is easier for your team.","index":84,"end_time":299.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It would be great if we could add Jeffrey to the list of notifications so he could start downloading them instead of me doing it and sending it to him.","index":85,"end_time":306.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.24,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Yeah, remove a step there.","index":86,"end_time":309.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":87,"end_time":309.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think I have his email through Slack on there, so we can do that for sure.","index":88,"end_time":316.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then our video ad has been performing really well.","index":89,"end_time":319.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just in the last 30 days.","index":90,"end_time":320.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We have 4,306 views and a lot of impressions on there.","index":91,"end_time":324,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that one''s been consistent.","index":92,"end_time":325.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then just wanted to touch base for you on those new ads.","index":93,"end_time":328.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''re working on adding in the companies that you were talking about, Jackie and I know you gave those two titles, but Fahad, did you have any additional titles that you want to implement?","index":94,"end_time":339.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me share my screen and share with you what we''re compiling.","index":95,"end_time":343.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.24,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Let me see if I could share here.","index":96,"end_time":347.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.52,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Okay, here we go.","index":97,"end_time":348.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.28,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"So this is a docket that we''ve been working on with.","index":98,"end_time":353.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.36,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"A lot of information.","index":99,"end_time":356.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.08,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"I don''t think all of it''s going to be relevant to you guys.","index":100,"end_time":359.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.2,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"But for example, these are the different people titles.","index":101,"end_time":363.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.52,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"We''re still looking at, you know, any information that we could get from the multiple companies involved.","index":102,"end_time":370.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":364.48,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"So here we do have some emails with while in different companies.","index":103,"end_time":376.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.45,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Involved in this specific case.","index":104,"end_time":381.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":379.97,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"So is that going to be sufficient for you guys?","index":105,"end_time":384.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.37,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"We''re just trying to figure out what it is that you need.","index":106,"end_time":387.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.17,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"But we still need probably another couple of days to finalize this so we could share it with you so we don''t keep on sharing a new one.","index":107,"end_time":394.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.89,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"I''m happy to share it as it is, but I don''t think it''s ready yet.","index":108,"end_time":396.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":394.53,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"You have to do it by job title, right, Taylor?","index":109,"end_time":399.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":397.41,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Is it by job title?","index":110,"end_time":401.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":399.89,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"We can do job titles within the LinkedIn ads and I believe the Google ones as well.","index":111,"end_time":405.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But definitely we can add in some titles to those.","index":112,"end_time":407.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The LinkedIn campaigns.","index":113,"end_time":408.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or can you just target.","index":114,"end_time":409.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":408.81,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I mean, you can''t target specific people with LinkedIn ads.","index":115,"end_time":412.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":409.81,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"It has to be like a title on a and or company.","index":116,"end_time":415.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":412.69,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Or is it.","index":117,"end_time":415.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":415.29,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"It has to be title.","index":118,"end_time":417.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":415.97,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I can''t remember what the parameters are.","index":119,"end_time":419.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":417.13,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I know that for the parameters, you can do the titles for sure.","index":120,"end_time":422.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":419.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You add those in.","index":121,"end_time":423.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Bailey, are you sure you do know about the companies?","index":122,"end_time":425.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think you can target companies.","index":123,"end_time":429.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You also can target specific people, but you need a list of at least 250.","index":124,"end_time":435.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":430.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, 250 people.","index":125,"end_time":440.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.42,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"I don''t think we have that.","index":126,"end_time":443.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":442.34,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"But we can always add two from previous lists because I know we are trying to target these specific ones.","index":127,"end_time":449.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But do you want this new campaign with this demo initiative to only be these people or more broad?","index":128,"end_time":456.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No, it can be more broad.","index":129,"end_time":459.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.47,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"But let me give you an example.","index":130,"end_time":460.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.15,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"So, for example here, these are the creditors that you know.","index":131,"end_time":464.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.27,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"For example, this company Jefferies manages these companies and they''ve lent out to first brand $750 million, right.","index":132,"end_time":473.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.43,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Another 45 over here.","index":133,"end_time":476.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.51,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Then you have another company called Rainstone that lent out $650 million.","index":134,"end_time":481.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.07,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"So these people would definitely be interested in if there''s any fraud taking place.","index":135,"end_time":485.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":481.31,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"So the idea is, how can we get as many people that have been defrauded aware of the solution that we have?","index":136,"end_time":492.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":485.16,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"So it doesn''t have to be the law firm itself.","index":137,"end_time":494.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":492.92,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"It could be the creditors.","index":138,"end_time":495.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.64,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"And we have a list of all these creditors.","index":139,"end_time":498.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":496.36,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"And for example, with Merrill Europe, we have quite a few names right from the CEO all the way down.","index":140,"end_time":504.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.36,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"And.","index":141,"end_time":507.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":506.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This one is only 6 million, but it''s still quite sizable.","index":142,"end_time":514.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":511.09,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"But you know, some companies over 200 million.","index":143,"end_time":517.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.09,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Well, for capitalism.","index":144,"end_time":521.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.97,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"So we just wanted to get brand recognition with these people.","index":145,"end_time":523.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":521.25,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So if ideally, this is a Kuwaiti company.","index":146,"end_time":527.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.81,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Huh?","index":147,"end_time":530.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This is the next client of ours.","index":148,"end_time":532.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":530.85,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"No kidding.","index":149,"end_time":533.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":533.09,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I just saw that.","index":150,"end_time":535.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.54,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Well, that''s worth a phone call.","index":151,"end_time":536.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":535.5,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"First thing tomorrow morning.","index":152,"end_time":540.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":539.1,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"I mean, honestly, if there''s any way to reach out to these people, like it not as a cold email or cold text or something, but if you have a way to get an actual call with them or a.","index":153,"end_time":552.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":540.62,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"A warm connection, that would be irreplaceable.","index":154,"end_time":556.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":552.86,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"But if nothing else, we would like to get our brand name in front of these people.","index":155,"end_time":562.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":556.78,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So we''re trying to figure out the best way to do that.","index":156,"end_time":563.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":562.11,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"And yeah, like, Fahad is worried that, you know, DMing them on LinkedIn or something is just not going to go anywhere for if it''s a cold outreach.","index":157,"end_time":573.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":564.23,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"That way.","index":158,"end_time":574.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"For the restructuring group, this is the company.","index":159,"end_time":579.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.39,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"These are the law firms involved in the restructuring.","index":160,"end_time":581.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.27,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Brown, Rudnick, most of them are, I think, out of the New York office.","index":161,"end_time":585.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.83,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"It might be out of Boston as well.","index":162,"end_time":587.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.31,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"But they have many more people involved in restructuring.","index":163,"end_time":591.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":588.6,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Doesn''t have to be on this specific case.","index":164,"end_time":593.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":591.92,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"So we could definitely come up with a list of 250 people.","index":165,"end_time":596.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":594.04,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"That we could potentially target.","index":166,"end_time":601.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":600.04,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"But, yeah, there''s, like, so many ways we could go about it, but we.","index":167,"end_time":608.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":603.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can target by companies.","index":168,"end_time":610.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":608.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So if you just got a list of a couple companies that you feel like are a good fit, and then we can do job titles with that, too, so then you don''t need to put together a whole list.","index":169,"end_time":620.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s.","index":170,"end_time":621.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":171,"end_time":622.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"In my head, that feels like the easiest step is just drop titles and company names, but a list works, too.","index":172,"end_time":628.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":622.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":173,"end_time":630.059,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.5,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"We could try to do a combination of both.","index":174,"end_time":632.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.3,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Right.","index":175,"end_time":632.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":632.58,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"If we can figure out who''s actually working on the case, that''s great.","index":176,"end_time":636.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.02,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"But maybe there''s somebody else we''re not aware of.","index":177,"end_time":638.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":636.18,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"And ideally, we''d want to turn this around immediately because they''re making the decision still, right, Fahad?","index":178,"end_time":644.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":638.94,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"About who''s going to be.","index":179,"end_time":645.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":644.93,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":180,"end_time":646.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646.45,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"The.","index":181,"end_time":647.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646.81,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"The court still hasn''t appointed the examiner, but all these people on these lists are involved already because they have nothing to do with the doj.","index":182,"end_time":656.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.05,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"You know, see, the lawyers for the creditors or lawyers for the legal team for the company or the lawyers for the perpetrator, they''re all on the list.","index":183,"end_time":663.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.29,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Mm.","index":184,"end_time":664.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":663.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So at the very least, if we could get that list of those company names from Ufahad, and we can add that as a targeted.","index":185,"end_time":671.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":665.01,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"As a targeted firms that we want to.","index":186,"end_time":673.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":671.65,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Making sure our ads are displaying to.","index":187,"end_time":676.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":675.15,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"And then if there''s any overlap in the job titles, like, I think on LinkedIn, it doesn''t have to be a specific title, but it could say something like, it has the word fraud in it, for example, or investigations or analyst or something along those lines.","index":188,"end_time":692.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":678.43,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Like, if we could somehow target that a little bit more, rather than if it''s one of these giant firms, then we don''t want our ad necessarily going out to, you know, 150,000 people at that company.","index":189,"end_time":704.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":692.79,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"We want to make sure we''re targeting it.","index":190,"end_time":706.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":704.19,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So.","index":191,"end_time":706.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":706.03,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":192,"end_time":707.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.23,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Ab.","index":193,"end_time":708.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.91,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":194,"end_time":709.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":708.59,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"I''ll be able to give you a list by tomorrow morning.","index":195,"end_time":710.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.03,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Okay, Perfect.","index":196,"end_time":712.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":197,"end_time":713.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":712.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":198,"end_time":714.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":714.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"As soon as we have that list from you, I''ll have our paid media specialist get that implemented into the.","index":199,"end_time":719.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The campaign so we can get that rolling quickly.","index":200,"end_time":721.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":201,"end_time":722.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":721.95,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"That''s amazing.","index":202,"end_time":723.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":722.47,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":203,"end_time":724.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":204,"end_time":724.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":724.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can''t believe they''re still waiting on that.","index":205,"end_time":726.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":724.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I remember.","index":206,"end_time":726.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":726.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I guess it''s a big case.","index":207,"end_time":730.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s.","index":208,"end_time":731.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":731,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"It''s.","index":209,"end_time":731.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":731.4,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"It''s.","index":210,"end_time":732.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":731.76,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"The court has to decide, and they left you with the DOJ, and I think 50 firms have submitted proposals, and they have to review them all to make sure.","index":211,"end_time":740.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.08,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"They have the right.","index":212,"end_time":741.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.72,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"But that.","index":213,"end_time":743.119,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.6,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"That''s one angle.","index":214,"end_time":743.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.119,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"I don''t want that to be our only angle.","index":215,"end_time":745.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.84,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"You know, we could be working for the creditors.","index":216,"end_time":747.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.4,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"We could be working for the company.","index":217,"end_time":748.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":747.2,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Unfortunately, we could also, you know, the perpetrator might want to utilize the services.","index":218,"end_time":753.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":749.56,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"We provide the platform.","index":219,"end_time":758.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":757.14,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Whoever wants to utilize it can utilize it.","index":220,"end_time":760.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.3,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Right, but that''s funny.","index":221,"end_time":761.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.3,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"What.","index":222,"end_time":761.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.46,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"What we''re pushing for is the people that want to uncover the fraud.","index":223,"end_time":765.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.86,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Not to cover the fraud, but.","index":224,"end_time":766.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.38,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"But, you know, maybe he''s been wrongfully accused.","index":225,"end_time":771.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":768.5,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":226,"end_time":772.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.54,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Not my problem to deal with.","index":227,"end_time":775.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":774.58,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Right.","index":228,"end_time":776.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.86,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"We''re just giving a solution for financial data.","index":229,"end_time":778.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.1,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"That''s funny.","index":230,"end_time":780.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That would be a twist in the story.","index":231,"end_time":781.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It sure would.","index":232,"end_time":783.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":782.19,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":233,"end_time":784.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":783.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Innocent until proven guilty, so it''s not.","index":234,"end_time":787.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":784.35,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Something we''re involved in.","index":235,"end_time":788.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":787.47,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"It''s like everybody tells me it''s like, you know, somebody''s gonna utilize Word or Excel to, you know.","index":236,"end_time":793.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.67,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"To use Excel to, you know, put in wrong numbers and wrong.","index":237,"end_time":798.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":795.79,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Excel has nothing to do with that.","index":238,"end_time":800.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":799.23,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"It''s the individual itself.","index":239,"end_time":802.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.71,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"All we do is provide a platform.","index":240,"end_time":804.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.99,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"How people utilize it, that''s on them.","index":241,"end_time":807.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":805.47,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Obviously, we don''t market to fraudsters, but you never know.","index":242,"end_time":810.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":807.64,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Defend yourself in court.","index":243,"end_time":813.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":812.28,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"A new campaign angle.","index":244,"end_time":818.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":816.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Jackie, to be honest, it is a campaign angle, but not something that we want to be openly associated with.","index":245,"end_time":826.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.04,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"No.","index":246,"end_time":827.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"For branding purposes, but.","index":247,"end_time":829.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":827.8,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"No, that''s a brand killer right there.","index":248,"end_time":831.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":829.36,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I''ve been accused of embezzlement.","index":249,"end_time":834.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":833.3,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Utilize Citro solutions to make sure you don''t get caught.","index":250,"end_time":836.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.62,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"I mean, honestly, like, we could do a stealth campaign on the dark web.","index":251,"end_time":840.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":836.98,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Anonymous.","index":252,"end_time":843.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":842.42,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Someone says, like, yeah, I''m using this platform to cover my tracks, to make it look like I''m, you know, legit.","index":253,"end_time":849.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":843.18,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"And, yeah, this is the.","index":254,"end_time":850.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":849.3,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"This is the best platform for proving your case.","index":255,"end_time":853.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":850.82,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"As long as you feed in falsified data that it''ll spit out a story that looks great.","index":256,"end_time":859.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":853.26,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Like.","index":257,"end_time":860.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That is too funny.","index":258,"end_time":862.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t want to go down this road.","index":259,"end_time":864.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":862.96,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"My brain will go there.","index":260,"end_time":865.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":864.4,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Oh, that''s good.","index":261,"end_time":870.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":869.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, we''ll wait to hear from you for that list then.","index":262,"end_time":872.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then as soon as we have that, we''ll get that rolling.","index":263,"end_time":874.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, yeah, and then I''ll send any other updates on the video as they come through.","index":264,"end_time":878.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":265,"end_time":880.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":879.76,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":266,"end_time":881.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":880.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, have a good rest of the week, everyone.","index":267,"end_time":882.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thanks, everyone.","index":268,"end_time":883.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":882.92,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":269,"end_time":884.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":883.68,"speaker_name":"fahad al mutawa"}],"dateString":"2025-12-10T16:30:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88927304763?pwd=asbbQolEtVpMuYX5uccJpOibhnlog1.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,j.wheeler@sedrasolutions.com,i.hamshari@sedrasolutions.com,f.almutawa@sedrasolutions.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","j.wheeler@sedrasolutions.com","i.hamshari@sedrasolutions.com","f.almutawa@sedrasolutions.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBZF0DADZG11EC6BRBTEPB47","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Confirmed procurement video edit is underway and includes captioned and non-captioned versions.","Extended organic social posts through Jan 15; seeing improved engagement consistency from Fahad’s content.","Generated 175 ABM campaign emails this week; new sequences deployed and monitored for traction.","Discussed refining LinkedIn targeting with company and job title lists; Fahad to send data by tomorrow.","Video ad surpassed 4,300 views in 30 days; lead gen ads yielded 39 ebook and 7 datasheet conversions."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Even though the week data looks really good, so excited to see that come through.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"As soon as we have that list from you, I''ll have our paid media specialist get that implemented.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"We''re just giving a solution for financial data. How people utilize it, that''s on them.","speaker":"fahad al mutawa"}],"topics":["ads","engagement","campaign","targeting","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-12T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Social Media and Content Strategy**\n\nThe team is seeing strong engagement and follower growth on social channels due to consistent posting and plans to sustain momentum into early next year.\n\n- **Organic social posts are scheduled through January 15th**, with the main page content booked until January 8th, supporting ongoing audience engagement (02:24)  \n    - The main page gained **18 new followers** and Fahad''s page added **16 new followers and 15 new connections** in the last seven days.  \n    - Taylor highlighted that consistent posting boosts reach and engagement rates, validating the current content strategy.  \n    - Jackie is developing an ebook on the fraud landscape for 2026, aiming to finish next week for a blog launch and social promotion in early January.  \n    - The team plans to pull additional blog content and fresh ideas from Fahad to maintain posting consistency beyond January.\n\n- **Taylor will prepare a year-end review comparing paid and organic social stats** to showcase gains from recent campaigns and content efforts (02:24)  \n    - This review will highlight Fahad’s ABM campaign’s role in driving significant organic connections.  \n    - The data comparison aims to inform future planning and demonstrate ROI on social initiatives.\n\n## **ABM Email Campaign and Lead Management**\n\nThe ABM campaign was streamlined for better tracking, with 175 emails sent since Monday, and improvements planned in lead notification processes.\n\n- **Two new email sequences were merged into one campaign in Lemlist, sending 175 emails since Monday** to improve tracking and consistency (03:39)  \n    - Fahad confirmed ongoing weekly list updates to add new contacts and expand outreach.  \n    - The team expects improved engagement from refined messaging and consolidated campaigns.  \n    - Taylor will continue monitoring results to adjust tactics as needed.\n\n- **Lead notifications currently go to Fahad, but adding Jeffrey to this list will improve efficiency** by removing Fahad as a bottleneck in lead distribution (05:00)  \n    - Taylor agreed to update the notification list to include Jeffrey, streamlining lead access and follow-up.  \n    - Fahad downloads lead data and shares it with Jeffrey; automating this step will save time.  \n    - Jackie clarified she does not handle leads directly; Jeffrey is the lead owner.\n\n## **Paid Advertising and Targeting Strategy**\n\nPaid ads are generating leads and impressions, and the team is refining targeting using job titles and company lists to increase brand awareness among key stakeholders.\n\n- **LinkedIn lead gen ads produced 39 leads for the ebook Free Guide and additional leads for other assets like the procurement data sheet** (03:57)  \n    - The video ad amassed **4,306 views over the last 30 days**, maintaining consistent exposure.  \n    - Taylor asked if regular lead spreadsheets would be helpful; Fahad confirmed lead notifications suffice if Jeffrey is included.  \n    - The team is preparing to add targeted company and job title data to improve ad precision.\n\n- **Targeting will combine specific job titles and company names to reach relevant decision-makers involved in a major restructuring case** (06:37)  \n    - Fahad shared a docket with creditor and law firm contacts managing over **$750 million** in loans, highlighting a focused audience interested in fraud solutions.  \n    - The team aims to reach not just the law firms, but also creditors and corporate contacts to maximize brand exposure.  \n    - Baylee confirmed LinkedIn requires either a list of at least **250 people** or targeting by company and title, so a mixed approach will be used.  \n    - Jackie emphasized targeting job titles containing keywords like “fraud,” “investigations,” or “analyst” to narrow the audience within large firms.\n\n- **Fahad will provide the finalized list of companies and job titles by tomorrow morning**, enabling quick campaign implementation (11:46)  \n    - Taylor committed to having the paid media specialist launch the updated campaign promptly once the list is received.  \n    - The urgency is driven by ongoing court decisions appointing examiners, making timing critical to gain early brand recognition.  \n    - Fahad noted the court is still reviewing over **50 proposals**, keeping the window open for outreach.\n\n## **Strategic Positioning and Market Insights**\n\nThe team is focused on positioning their platform as a trusted fraud solution to relevant stakeholders while carefully managing brand messaging.\n\n- **Fahad clarified the platform targets those uncovering fraud, not those seeking to cover it up, to protect brand integrity** (12:59)  \n    - The team acknowledged the risk of unwanted associations but reaffirmed the platform’s neutral role as a financial data tool.  \n    - Jackie and Taylor joked about a stealth campaign angle for fraudsters but agreed it would harm the brand.  \n    - This clarity guides messaging to ensure the company is seen as a solution for transparency and accountability.\n\n- **The campaign’s broader strategy includes reaching multiple parties involved in restructuring—creditors, companies, and law firms—to maximize market presence** (11:03)  \n    - Fahad emphasized flexibility in targeting to capture all potential users of the platform regardless of their role in the case.  \n    - This multi-angle approach aims to increase adoption and awareness across the ecosystem surrounding financial fraud cases.  \n    - Taylor and Jackie’s collaboration on targeting parameters reflects a balance between precision and scale.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Operational Coordination**\n\nThe team is streamlining processes for content scheduling, lead handling, and campaign management to improve efficiency and responsiveness.\n\n- **Content scheduling avoids low-engagement periods like Christmas week to maximize impact and resource use** (01:44)  \n    - Taylor paused posting during Christmas week, anticipating low audience activity.  \n    - Planning now focuses on ramping back up with fresh content starting early January.\n\n- **Lead handling will be automated by adding Jeffrey to notification lists, reducing manual steps and speeding response times** (05:00)  \n    - This change will eliminate Fahad’s current role as lead distributor, freeing him to focus on other priorities.  \n    - The adjustment reflects a commitment to improving internal workflows for campaign success.\n\n- **Paid media implementation will begin immediately once Fahad provides the finalized targeting list, reflecting tight coordination between teams** (11:54)  \n    - Taylor’s quick handoff to the paid media specialist ensures no delay in campaign updates.  \n    - This tight turnaround is critical given the ongoing court process and competitive environment.\n\n- **Year-end data review of paid vs organic performance is planned to inform next year’s strategy and budget allocation** (02:24)  \n    - This review will provide actionable insights on what channels and content types drive the best ROI.  \n    - It supports continuous improvement in marketing efficiency and goal alignment.","outline":null,"keywords":["Procurement video","Social media campaign","ABM email campaign","LinkedIn ads targeting","Fraud landscape blog","Financial fraud case"],"overview":"- **Social Media Growth:** Consistent posts led to **18 new followers** on the main page and **16 on Fahad''s page** over the last week.\n\n- **Ebook Development:** Jackie is finishing an ebook on the fraud landscape to launch with a blog in early January.\n\n- **ABM Campaign Updates:** Combined email sequences sent **175 emails**, enhancing tracking; lead notification process improved by adding Jeffrey.\n\n- **Paid Ads Performance:** LinkedIn ads generated **39 leads** for the ebook, video ad received **4,306 views** in the last month.\n\n- **Targeting Strategy:** Focus on creditors and law firms involved with **$750 million** in loans; aim for precision by job titles.\n\n- **Process Streamlining:** Automating lead notifications and minimizing engagement drops during low activity periods like Christmas week.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend final procurement video cut for client input upon completion (00:33)\nSchedule additional social media posts for January and February based on Fahad’s input and Jackie’s blog (01:44)\nPrepare year-end review comparing paid and organic campaign data for next week (02:40)\nAdd Jeffrey to lead notification emails for direct lead download to streamline process (05:00)\nImplement paid media campaign targeting using Fahad’s company and job title lists immediately after receipt (11:54)\nProvide ongoing video ad updates to team (14:29)\n\n**Fahad Al Mutawa**\nFinalize and send the detailed company and job title lists for ad targeting by next morning (11:46)\nAdd Jeffrey to lead notification system for direct lead access (05:00)\n\n**Jackie Wheeler**\nContinue ideation and produce “fraud landscape in 2026” ebook and blog targeted for early January launch (02:03)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"1671dfc1-8b1d-4b20-964e-3adcc22adeaa","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
