    357,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81972288348?pwd=dlFCmDE617TIYs0IxaFQZUuNMTsSxP.1',
    '{"id":"01KC03KA4RQS2W3B0GCS0R8BK2","title":"Taylor Doerbaum and Nigel Sapp","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Performance and Engagement**\n\nThe podcast has reached a natural pause after completing **10 episodes**, marking the end of its first season and showing steady listener growth each week (05:18).\n\n- **Nigel Sapp highlighted that the podcast is still gaining traction, with more listens than ever recorded recently** (02:59).\n    - Taylor Doerbaum confirmed weekly listener increases across episodes, including both newer and early content.\n    - This steady growth supports maintaining the podcast as a viable engagement channel despite current production slowdowns.\n    - Positioning this pause as a seasonal break sets clear expectations for a fresh start in the new year.\n\n- **The team agreed to pause new episode releases after December, resuming in the new year as “season two”** (04:55).\n    - This break aligns with typical year-end slowdowns and client schedules, avoiding audience drop-off risks.\n    - Taylor will cancel meetings on December 23rd and 30th to reflect this pause but maintain communication via Slack for updates.\n    - Nigel framed this as a strategic reset, allowing the team to focus on other priorities and return with renewed energy.\n\n## **Content Development and Production**\n\nProgress on enhancing promotional materials aims to showcase the podcast’s evolution and increase audience connection (04:15).\n\n- **Taylor is completing the first rough cut of a compilation video that blends clips from early and recent episodes** (03:50).\n    - The video will highlight changes in branding and feature host introductions to emphasize the podcast’s growth.\n    - This compilation will serve as a marketing tool to re-engage listeners ahead of season two.\n    - Taylor offered flexibility to adjust clips based on Nigel’s feedback before finalizing the video.\n\n- **The video production timeline targets completion before the end-of-year break** (04:15).\n    - This timing ensures promotional materials are ready for use when new episodes relaunch.\n    - The project requires minimal additional resources, leveraging existing episode content.\n    - The video is expected to boost listener interest and highlight the podcast’s evolving identity.\n\n## **Meeting and Operational Scheduling**\n\nThe team is streamlining meeting schedules during the holiday season to optimize focus and reduce overhead (05:00).\n\n- **Regular meetings scheduled for December 23rd and 30th will be canceled, with updates shifted to Slack** (04:54).\n    - This decision reflects varying client availability and a lack of urgent topics in late December.\n    - Taylor will communicate the cancellations and manage asynchronous updates as needed.\n    - This approach prevents unnecessary meetings while maintaining team alignment.\n\n- **Meetings will resume in early January, aligning with the podcast’s planned season two launch** (05:02).\n    - This restart supports renewed planning and production efforts without disruption.\n    - The schedule adjustment helps balance workload and holiday downtime.\n    - Nigel emphasized the importance of this break for team morale and strategic focus.\n\n## **Strategic Positioning and Future Planning**\n\nThe team views the podcast as a growing asset that requires careful pacing and strategic content refreshment (05:18).\n\n- **Nigel framed the completion of 10 episodes as a milestone that naturally concludes season one** (05:18).\n    - This milestone supports a narrative of progress and readiness for a relaunch.\n    - It provides a clear point to assess performance and adjust strategy before scaling further.\n    - The seasonal break will allow reflection on audience data and content direction.\n\n- **Resuming production in the new year positions the podcast for stronger impact with refreshed branding and content** (05:46).\n    - This timing aligns with typical marketing cycles and audience engagement rhythms.\n    - The team plans to leverage insights from season one to improve content relevance and reach.\n    - Nigel’s outlook emphasizes quality and consistency over rushing new episodes.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast analytics","compilation video","meeting schedule","season wrap-up","content review","December break"],"overview":"- **Podcast Growth:** Podcast reached 10 episodes; steady increase in listeners confirmed across both new and older content.\n\n- **Seasonal Pause:** Team agreed to pause new episodes after December, relaunching “season two” in the new year.\n\n- **Promo Video:** Taylor is finalizing a compilation video to showcase podcast growth, targeting completion before year-end.\n\n- **Meeting Schedule:** Regular meetings canceled for December 23rd and 30th; updates to be communicated via Slack.\n\n- **Strategic Focus:** Break allows team to reflect on performance and enhance content strategy for a stronger relaunch.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nFinalize and send the rough cut of the podcast compilation video for review and feedback (04:28)\nCancel scheduled meetings for December 23rd and 30th and communicate the change accordingly (05:04)\nMaintain Slack communications to provide updates during the meeting hiatus (05:10)\n\n**Nigel Sapp**\nReview the compilation video rough cut upon receipt and suggest any clip changes or edits as needed (04:28)\n"},"duration":5.949999809265137,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":1,"name":"Nigel Sapp"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello.","index":0,"end_time":95.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Hey, Taylor.","index":1,"end_time":96.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.27,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":97.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.99,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":98.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":4,"end_time":98.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":98.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m okay.","index":5,"end_time":100.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.39,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":101.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.31,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":7,"end_time":102.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.95,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Looking forward to Christmas time, honestly.","index":8,"end_time":104.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.07,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Plowing through till the end of the month, I guess.","index":9,"end_time":107.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You''re.","index":10,"end_time":107.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, both.","index":11,"end_time":108.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.31,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Both.","index":12,"end_time":109.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.03,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"All the.","index":13,"end_time":109.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.43,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"All the above.","index":14,"end_time":110.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.87,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":15,"end_time":111.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":110.55,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":112.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are you getting some Christmas weather out there?","index":17,"end_time":114.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s so cold.","index":18,"end_time":116.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.55,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"It''s like.","index":19,"end_time":116.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":116.03,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"It''s brutal.","index":20,"end_time":117.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":117.03,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":21,"end_time":119.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I feel like I always have an idea that California is always sunny in 75, but I do know it.","index":22,"end_time":124.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It does get weather.","index":23,"end_time":125.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I mean, for the most part.","index":24,"end_time":127.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":126.47,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Well, Northern California is a little bit more.","index":25,"end_time":130.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.91,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"A little stranger, honestly, than SoCal is, like, always pretty warm up here.","index":26,"end_time":137.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.38,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"It.","index":27,"end_time":137.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":137.34,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"It''s always a little breezy.","index":28,"end_time":140.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.14,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Like, it''s always 60 with a breeze, which is nice, but you kind of have to always wear, like, a little bit of a jacket, so.","index":29,"end_time":149.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":140.86,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But now it''s like 50 in a breeze, and that''s on.","index":30,"end_time":153.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":150.14,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"That''s, like, unbearable for us, really.","index":31,"end_time":156.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.54,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, we can''t do it.","index":32,"end_time":158.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.94,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"We can''t do it versus, like.","index":33,"end_time":160.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":158.14,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Growing up.","index":34,"end_time":163.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":162.61,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I mean, in Atlanta, like, it would get to 30 all the time, you know.","index":35,"end_time":166.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.05,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":36,"end_time":166.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166.57,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Think twice about it.","index":37,"end_time":167.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166.93,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But it also got to 100 in the summer, so.","index":38,"end_time":170.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.73,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, you get all.","index":39,"end_time":172.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All the ranges.","index":40,"end_time":173.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Tough stuff.","index":41,"end_time":175.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.61,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"It''s tough stuff.","index":42,"end_time":176.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":175.29,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Looks funny.","index":43,"end_time":178.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, you know.","index":44,"end_time":180.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.09,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But anyway, I don''t.","index":45,"end_time":183.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":180.21,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I don''t think.","index":46,"end_time":183.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.37,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I personally don''t think I have too much to talk about.","index":47,"end_time":185.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.81,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I don''t really have many updates on the podcast front because.","index":48,"end_time":188.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.69,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, we just have been, like, so busy working on other things and it''s not really our.","index":49,"end_time":192.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.37,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Whoa.","index":50,"end_time":193.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.4,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"That''s cool, though, that we still getting.","index":51,"end_time":195.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":194.2,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Still getting ton of listens.","index":52,"end_time":197.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":195.72,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"People are.","index":53,"end_time":197.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.08,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Wow.","index":54,"end_time":198.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.72,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"More listens than ever, in fact.","index":55,"end_time":199.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.16,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Okay, interesting.","index":56,"end_time":200.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":199.6,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I did want to show you this because I was looking at it this morning and I was going to see if there''s anything.","index":57,"end_time":203.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Obviously this one''s newer, but it''s still jumping each week.","index":58,"end_time":207.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then, yeah, this first one always will have some.","index":59,"end_time":211.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, yeah, increase on all of them, which was cool to see.","index":60,"end_time":214.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, yeah, just some fun stats to show you that it is continuing to get traction each.","index":61,"end_time":221.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Each week that we look at it.","index":62,"end_time":222.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, I agree with you.","index":63,"end_time":225.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Not.","index":64,"end_time":225.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Not too much going on to.","index":65,"end_time":226.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"On our end.","index":66,"end_time":227.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The only other update I had for you was just that we are.","index":67,"end_time":229.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The first cut of that compilation video is getting wrapped up right now, actually.","index":68,"end_time":233.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I went ahead and just pulled clips from episodes I know you had mentioned for some of your favorites.","index":69,"end_time":240.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I tried doing some early ones with, like, the old branding and.","index":70,"end_time":244.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And it''s going to transition into, like, the Newer ones with the new branding to kind of show that, like, change throughout the season.","index":71,"end_time":251.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then those intros that you were saying, like, hi, I''m Anthony.","index":72,"end_time":254.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Hi, I''m Eli and Isaac.","index":73,"end_time":256.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''re working on that now.","index":74,"end_time":258.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''ll be a rough cut, so we''ll send it over to you.","index":75,"end_time":260.649,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if you want to switch out any clips or anything, we can.","index":76,"end_time":262.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.649,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can do that.","index":77,"end_time":263.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''ll be like the.","index":78,"end_time":264.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I guess, like the basic format of it, and then we can switch anything out according to what you''d prefer.","index":79,"end_time":270.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right on.","index":80,"end_time":272.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.14,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yes.","index":81,"end_time":273.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So excited to see how that looks.","index":82,"end_time":275.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''ll be a.","index":83,"end_time":276.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''ll be a cool one.","index":84,"end_time":277.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes, indeed.","index":85,"end_time":279.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":278.7,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":86,"end_time":281.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.86,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Okay, well, good to know.","index":87,"end_time":282.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.34,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":88,"end_time":283.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.82,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":89,"end_time":284.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.66,"speaker_name":"Ta