    '{"id":"01KBJHCM384WMQ98RW2KM9BFHK","title":"GSS // MID Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Strategy and Production**\n\nThe team prioritized producing targeted content to address current market challenges and maintain engagement.\n\n- **Three blog topics were prioritized for production**, focusing on the talent crisis, risk analysis, and cash flow control, with the first two slated for immediate work and the third deferred to January (02:18)\n    - The first topic targets the talent crisis, which is highly relevant given current industry conditions, ensuring timely engagement.\n    - Will Fleming emphasized the importance of these topics to capture attention in the present environment.\n    - The team agreed to proceed without additional interviews, relying on previous conversations for insights to speed up production.\n    - This focus aligns with a strategy to produce **two blog posts this month**, maximizing content output without overextending resources.\n\n- **The Restaurant Finance Function blog is now live**, providing fresh content to support marketing efforts and drive traffic (01:35)\n    - A new blog titled \"Rowing in the Same Direction, How Alignment Cuts Audit Costs\" is ready for review and will launch post-approval.\n    - The team plans to integrate this content into upcoming newsletters to leverage audience interest in audit-related topics.\n\n- **Newsletter subject lines were discussed to improve open rates**, with the final choice favoring a straightforward audit-related angle to avoid deterring readers (05:06)\n    - Will Fleming noted the challenge of making audit topics appealing and advised against deep technical details.\n    - The team considered alternative content sources for newsletters but kept podcast-inspired themes for now.\n\n## **Email and LinkedIn Sequence Launch**\n\nThe team prepared to launch updated outreach sequences with a planned pause over the holidays to optimize engagement.\n\n- **The updated email and LinkedIn sequences are scheduled to launch immediately**, integrating Nick’s recent input to improve response rates (06:24)\n    - Nick advised starting the sequence this week with a cadence of about **four days between sends** to maintain momentum without overwhelming recipients.\n    - The team plans to pause the campaigns around **December 19th** to avoid low engagement during holiday absences, resuming around **January 2nd**.\n    - This timing aims to maximize contact during active periods while respecting seasonal audience availability.\n\n- **No new campaign data is available yet**, as the sequences have not been launched before this meeting (06:56)\n    - The team will monitor initial responses post-launch to assess effectiveness and adjust timing or messaging if needed.\n\n## **Website Migration and Platform Transition**\n\nThe migration to a new website platform was successfully completed, improving operational efficiency and reducing costs.\n\n- **The new website was launched on WordPress with no reported bugs, enabling cancellation of the previous Duda subscription** (08:14)\n    - Baylee Gunnell highlighted the smooth and rapid transition compared to other client projects.\n    - Will Fleming confirmed satisfaction with the site’s look and functioning as of the morning review.\n    - Moving to WordPress streamlines future updates and maintenance, reducing ongoing vendor costs and complexity.\n\n## **Content Management and Podcast Planning**\n\nThe client portal provides transparency on content progress, with plans to maintain a steady podcast release schedule despite booking challenges.\n\n- **Current portal data shows monthly management tasks underway and a placeholder for a podcast episode, reflecting ongoing content delivery** (09:12)\n    - Nick is actively pursuing podcast guests, aiming for at least one December recording despite booking difficulties.\n    - A December episode is planned, with the next scheduled for January to maintain consistent audience engagement.\n    - Available blog post points will be used to cover prioritized content topics, ensuring resource allocation matches strategy.\n\n## **Meeting Scheduling and Year-End Review**\n\nThe team planned around the holiday season to maintain momentum while respecting availability.\n\n- **An end-of-year content performance review is scheduled for next week, providing strategic insights on annual progress** (10:09)\n    - This meeting will help assess what worked and guide plans for 2024 content priorities.\n    - The Christmas Eve meeting was canceled due to holiday plans, but the New Year’s Eve meeting remains on schedule as all participants are available.\n    - A brief update will be sent during the Christmas week, recognizing limited team availability while keeping stakeholders informed.","outline":null,"keywords":["content updates","email sequence","blog production","podcast scheduling","website launch","holiday campaign pause"],"overview":"- **Content Focused on Current Challenges:** Prioritized three blog topics: talent crisis, risk analysis, cash flow control; first two produced immediately.  \n- **New Blog Live:** \"Rowing in the Same Direction\" blog launched, integrating content into newsletters to drive traffic.  \n- **Optimized Email Sequences:** Updated email and LinkedIn outreach to launch this week with four-day intervals; campaigns pause December 19.  \n- **Successful Website Migration:** New WordPress site launched with no bugs, allowing cancellation of old subscription and reducing costs.  \n- **Ongoing Podcast Planning:** Aiming for one podcast episode in December; posts aligned with strategy for consistent engagement.  \n- **Year-End Review Scheduled:** Content performance review next week to assess annual progress; New Year’s Eve meeting remains on schedule.","action_items":"\n**Will Fleming**\nReview and approve the blog \"Rowing in the Same Direction, How Alignment Cuts Audit Costs\" for launch after the meeting (02:08)\nProvide quick reviews for upcoming blog drafts on talent crisis and risk analysis topics (03:56)\nDecide on maintaining the New Year’s Eve meeting on 31st December (10:51)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nSend the blog draft from Kerry Maue’s episode for review post-meeting (02:08)\nProceed with content creation on prioritized blogs: talent crisis first, risk analysis second, and regaining cash flow control in January (03:28)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nLaunch updated email and LinkedIn sequences on the meeting day (06:24)\nSchedule a pause for the email campaigns starting December 19 and resume January 2 (07:03)\nConfirm newsletter subject line inspired by Kerry Maue episode focusing on audits (06:24)\nReview the client portal setup with current tasks and podcast placeholders (09:11)\nPrepare and present the end-of-year content performance review for next week (10:07)\n\n**Nick S**\nContinue outreach to secure guests for podcast recordings aiming for one episode this month and more in January (09:27)\nSet cadence and timing for email and LinkedIn sequence sends pre- and post-holiday (07:32)\n"},"duration":11.600000381469727,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Will Fleming"},{"id":1,"name":"Guille Santana"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":3,"name":"Nick S (GSS)"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Thanks.","index":0,"end_time":0.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Hi.","index":1,"end_time":1.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.56,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Hi.","index":2,"end_time":2.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.76,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yay.","index":3,"end_time":3.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":4,"end_time":5.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well.","index":5,"end_time":5.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":5.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Great.","index":6,"end_time":7.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":7.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I, I, I''m gonna have to leave at about 11:15 if, but I know Nick was working on.","index":7,"end_time":22.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.16,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It may be a little earlier than that, but I know Nick was working on the, the marketing sequence, so I think that''s an important discussion.","index":8,"end_time":35.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.32,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I''m sure you have other things to talk about, but.","index":9,"end_time":39.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.11,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Continue with that with you.","index":10,"end_time":43.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.07,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s definitely on the agenda.","index":11,"end_time":47.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":44.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Looks like Nick is joining right now.","index":12,"end_time":49.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":47.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":13,"end_time":51.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.75,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Hey.","index":14,"end_time":63.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":63.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Great.","index":15,"end_time":65.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":65.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, Will was just telling us he asked to leave at like the 15 mark, so we''ll just jump right into things so we can make sure we get to everything.","index":16,"end_time":74.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":65.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":17,"end_time":76.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.96,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we''re going to go over some content updates, the email sequence and some ABM updates and then we''ll go ahead and take a look at your client portal as well.","index":18,"end_time":89.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":79.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll kick it to Guille to go over some of these content updates first.","index":19,"end_time":94.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":91.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right, well, quick update on content first.","index":20,"end_time":100.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":95.65,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The Restaurant Finance Function blog is now live and the link is right there if you want to check it out.","index":21,"end_time":107.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And, and then I have a new blog for you guys to review.","index":22,"end_time":112.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.21,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We pulled that from the episode you recorded with Kerry Maue and it''s titled Rowing in the Same Direction, How Alignment Cuts Audit Costs.","index":23,"end_time":123.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":113.68,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Once you have a chance to review it, we will launch it.","index":24,"end_time":126.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":124,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So I will send out today in the email that we always send out after this meeting.","index":25,"end_time":132,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":126.92,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":26,"end_time":133.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then we mentioned that we also have capacity to produce like two more pieces this month.","index":27,"end_time":144.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.73,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And based on this strategy we shortlisted five topics and we would love to you to give us your input on which, like, which to prioritize.","index":28,"end_time":155.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":144.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"You can pick two and just let us know and we can start moving on those.","index":29,"end_time":162.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.29,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"These are very good, I would say in the order of.","index":30,"end_time":170.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.56,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like.","index":31,"end_time":172.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.88,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"What I''m attracted to is the first one.","index":32,"end_time":178.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":174.84,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think that''s very important.","index":33,"end_time":181,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.52,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The fourth one, risk analysis.","index":34,"end_time":185.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.84,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then if there was a third one.","index":35,"end_time":187.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I know you said two, but we.","index":36,"end_time":190.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Could do the third next month though.","index":37,"end_time":191.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":190.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, the third one.","index":38,"end_time":193.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.5,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"How Restaurant Operations can Regain control of Cash flow.","index":39,"end_time":197.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.62,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think that those three would, especially in the environment we''re in, will be, will get a lot of attention.","index":40,"end_time":206.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.46,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Got it.","index":41,"end_time":208.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":207.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll start with the talent crisis and then we''ll do the risk analysis and we''ll let the.","index":42,"end_time":214.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":208.66,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Regaining control for January.","index":43,"end_time":219.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.83,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":44,"end_time":224.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":45,"end_time":225.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":224.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I think we will get started on these.","index":46,"end_time":228.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we can do these probably without an interview with you, Will, unless you have some specific insights, but I think we''ll probably have enough from the conversations we''ve had previously to put these together.","index":47,"end_time":240.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":228.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, if you, if you, you know, feel free to go ahead and I, I''m usually pretty quick on the review, so.","index":48,"end_time":248.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.87,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You are.","index":49,"end_time":249.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We appreciate that a lot.","index":50,"end_time":251.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":249.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":51,"end_time":252.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.42,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay.","index":52,"end_time":254.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":254.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And our newsletter.","index":53,"end_time":255.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":254.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, for the newsletter.","index":54,"end_time":259.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"These are the proposed titles for the episode inspired by Gary Maoes on, like, audits.","index":55,"end_time":268.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":260.02,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We''d like to confirm.","index":56,"end_time":273.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.18,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Which one would you like or which one do you think is the strongest fit for the subject line?","index":57,"end_time":278.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":273.18,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I guess the last one.","index":58,"end_time":308.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.11,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, people don''t.","index":59,"end_time":309.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.71,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s not a topic that people are drawn to in general.","index":60,"end_time":313.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.79,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So.","index":61,"end_time":316.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.35,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We could do a different angle.","index":62,"end_time":320.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":318.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If none of these are really resonating with you, like, we could also.","index":63,"end_time":324.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":320.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we''ve been doing most of the newsletters inspired by a podcast episode, but we have a ton of blog content that we could use as the basis instead.","index":64,"end_time":333.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think the last one is fine.","index":65,"end_time":342.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.18,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, that it goes usually hand in hand with.","index":66,"end_time":346.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":342.78,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"If they have problems with this at the CFO level.","index":67,"end_time":349.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.62,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They don''t.","index":68,"end_time":349.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.18,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They''re.","index":69,"end_time":350.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They have problems with their audit.","index":70,"end_time":352.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.64,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, there''s a cl.","index":71,"end_time":353.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.2,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"There''s a.","index":72,"end_time":354.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.16,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"A.","index":73,"end_time":355.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.96,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Class of company that does an audit, and then there''s a.","index":74,"end_time":360.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.36,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"A smaller one that doesn''t.","index":75,"end_time":362.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.64,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So this is obviously focused to.","index":76,"end_time":364.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.56,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"To one group, which is fine.","index":77,"end_time":366.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.44,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I don''t know how many owners think about it as something that they.","index":78,"end_time":373.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Oh, they just know it needs to be better.","index":79,"end_time":375.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.36,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I think the last one could be interesting as long as we don''t get into the weeds on audits, because I think people are just naturally sort of drawn away from that.","index":80,"end_time":384.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.12,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":81,"end_time":385.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, we can do that then.","index":82,"end_time":389.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":387.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So next exciting update is we were able to update the email sequence and the LinkedIn sequence.","index":83,"end_time":398.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":391.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Based on those inputs that Nick provided us, we''ve been able to just get it all set up in smartly and hayrage.","index":84,"end_time":408.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":398.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''re planning on getting that launched today.","index":85,"end_time":410.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":408.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":86,"end_time":413.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":412.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any other questions or thoughts on this?","index":87,"end_time":415.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Glad you didn''t send it out already because I was like, I haven''t gotten any responses.","index":88,"end_time":421.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":416.93,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"No, yeah, we haven''t launched it yet.","index":89,"end_time":423.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":421.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":90,"end_time":424.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.97,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re good.","index":91,"end_time":425.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":424.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''ll go out today and then I think we''d probably recommend pausing it on, like, December 19th.","index":92,"end_time":433.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":425.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So just a couple days before.","index":93,"end_time":434.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":433.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Before a lot of people are.","index":94,"end_time":435.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":434.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Are going to be out.","index":95,"end_time":436.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":435.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then probably get it set back up.","index":96,"end_time":442.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":439.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Maybe like January 2nd.","index":97,"end_time":443.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":442.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you have any preferences on when it''s paused?","index":98,"end_time":449.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean.","index":99,"end_time":452.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":452.27,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Over the holidays it''s going to be.","index":100,"end_time":456.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":454.75,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean.","index":101,"end_time":456.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":456.35,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t know.","index":102,"end_time":461.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":459.96,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I think maybe Sending something out this week would be good to start it.","index":103,"end_time":467.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":464.36,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then I think I have the cadence set at like, what, how many days did I say change it to?","index":104,"end_time":473.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":467.84,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I can''t remember off the top of my head.","index":105,"end_time":475.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":474.04,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I think it was like four days or something like that.","index":106,"end_time":477.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":475.52,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":478.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.8,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So if we send it Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, and then be like, send again Tuesday of next week.","index":108,"end_time":485.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":479.16,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":109,"end_time":486.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.63,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, I guess we can run it and see how it works before the holidays.","index":110,"end_time":493.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":489.19,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":111,"end_time":495.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":494.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it definitely.","index":112,"end_time":498.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":497.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It does.","index":113,"end_time":498.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Doesn''t hurt to get it launched beforehand.","index":114,"end_time":500.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":115,"end_time":504.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":116,"end_time":504.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":504.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll keep that in mind then.","index":117,"end_time":506.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":504.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then no crazy updates here because nothing new has been running.","index":118,"end_time":512.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then our super exciting update is we got your new website launched through WordPress.","index":119,"end_time":518.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":514.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think it looks awesome.","index":120,"end_time":520.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s been working great.","index":121,"end_time":521.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We haven''t noticed any bugs, so I think we''re doing really great.","index":122,"end_time":526.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":521.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And you can go ahead and cancel your Duda subscription now.","index":123,"end_time":529.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, well, that''s a great update.","index":124,"end_time":533.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.41,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Thanks a lot.","index":125,"end_time":533.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":533.17,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I took a look at it this morning.","index":126,"end_time":535.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":534.29,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It looks great.","index":127,"end_time":536.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.53,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you.","index":128,"end_time":537.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re super happy with how it turned out.","index":129,"end_time":540.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":538.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It went really fast too.","index":130,"end_time":542.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, what?","index":131,"end_time":543.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":542.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve done this for several clients and this one just went, I feel like, really smoothly.","index":132,"end_time":547.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we were really happy about that.","index":133,"end_time":548.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good.","index":134,"end_time":551.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.1,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay, so then last, we''ll just take a look here at your portal so you can see everything that we''re currently working on.","index":135,"end_time":558.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":552.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you can see our monthly management tasks currently.","index":136,"end_time":561.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And working.","index":137,"end_time":561.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Does a placeholder for a podcast episode?","index":138,"end_time":565.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":139,"end_time":565.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nick, do you have any recordings coming.","index":140,"end_time":567.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Up soon of anything scheduled?","index":141,"end_time":570.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":567.78,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Got a couple feelers out there.","index":142,"end_time":571.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":570.38,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Just nothing in, nothing booked.","index":143,"end_time":576.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":574.38,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"This is a hard time to get people booked.","index":144,"end_time":579.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":577.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I.","index":145,"end_time":581.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":580.14,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Maybe I''m thinking I should be able to get one done this month.","index":146,"end_time":584.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":581.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"That''s the goal.","index":147,"end_time":586.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":585.66,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then, you know, we''ll have something ready for January, so we released one in December and then we''ll have something for January, so.","index":148,"end_time":592.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":586.86,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":149,"end_time":594.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":593.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then you can see where we''re at with points.","index":150,"end_time":598.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":595.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We do have some available, but we''ll use those blog post ideas that we talked about earlier to use those extra points.","index":151,"end_time":604.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But any other questions?","index":152,"end_time":606.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":605.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":153,"end_time":608.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.91,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":154,"end_time":610.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then next week we''re going to have like an end of year review for you.","index":155,"end_time":615.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll be looking at how contents performed for the whole year so far.","index":156,"end_time":619.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":615.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve.","index":157,"end_time":620.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve put some good stuff together.","index":158,"end_time":621.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re excited to show that to you, but just so you can look forward to that next week.","index":159,"end_time":625.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I think, yeah, we''ve already canceled I think the meeting for the week after that, which is on Christmas Eve, and we''re.","index":160,"end_time":635.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":626.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we still have the meeting scheduled for the 31st, so New Year''s Eve.","index":161,"end_time":639.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you still want to keep that one?","index":162,"end_time":641.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_